page1.title: Halkaa
page1.description: Halkaa (Relief) is a unique take on a slum child's heroism, aspirations and dreams. The child protagonist, Pichku fights for the basic problem that he faces everyday; defecating in the open among others.

page1.title: Yamla Pagla Deewana: Phir Se
page1.description: An upright Ayurveda practitioner is hounded by big pharmacy giants for his age-old formula that cures everything.

page1.title: Teesri Aankh: The Hidden Camera
page1.description: 'Teesri Aankh'' is the story of the plight of women who are trapped, used and abused by the use of the hidden camera. A psychological-techno thriller!!

page1.title: Mr. Medhavi
page1.description: A young Vishwak meets Sweta and falls in love with her. Their relationship begins to dwindle when Vishwak becomes increasingly manipulative and selfish to succeed in life.(Hindi Dubbed)

page1.title: Trip to Bhangarh
page1.description: Five friends plan a trip to Bhangarh, an apparently haunted fort in rural Rajasthan, a place where even staying overnight is forbidden by law.

page1.title: The Violin Player
page1.description: The Violin Player is the story of one day in the life of a Bollywood session violinist who finds expression in an unlikely place.

page2.title: Paltan
page2.description: Indian and Chinese forces clash over a border dispute.

page2.title: Genius
page2.description: An overbearing father pushes his brilliant son toward a psychological breakdown.

page2.title: Laila Majnu
page2.description: Laila and Kais refuse to give up on their love despite severe obstacles.

page2.title: Sui Dhaaga: Made In India
page2.description: An unemployed small-town man defies all odds and naysayers and starts his own garment business.

page2.title: Mitron
page2.description: A father searches for a suitable wife for his son.

page2.title: Gold
page2.description: After gaining independence, India wins its first Olympic gold medal in 1948.

page3.title: Nanu Ki Jaanu
page3.description: Nanu Ki Jaanu is a dark comedy, the story of which revolves around a Delhi land mafia agent (Abhay Deol) who tries to deal with the arrival of a ghost in his apartment.

page3.title: Satyameva Jayate
page3.description: Veer takes on the mission of killing corrupt cops in the Mumbai police force. Haunted by ghastly incidents from his past, he turns into a vigilante and Veer has his own mysterious plan of action.

page3.title: Sanju
page3.description: Coming from a family of cinematic legends, East Indian actor Sanjay Dutt reaches dizzying heights of success -- but also battles numerous addictions and other personal demons.

page3.title: Fanney Khan
page3.description: Anil Kapoor plays father to a teenage daughter who has musical inspirations, while Aishwarya Rai plays the role of a gorgeous singer with Rajkummar Rao as her love interest.

page3.title: Shaadi Teri Bajayenge Hum Band
page3.description: Nunu, against his father's consent, ends up marrying a girl. However, a hilarious situation arises when he, along with his friends, tries to hide the same from his father.

page3.title: Soorma
page3.description: East Indian field hockey player Sandeep Singh tries to make a comeback after a gunshot wound leaves him in a wheelchair.

page4.title: Chakarghinni
page4.description: Chakarghinni is a story about a life in a Village where basic amenities still lacks even after 65 years of independence.

page4.title: Veerappan
page4.description: A remake of Ram Gopal Varma's critically appreciated Kannada hit Killing Veerappan. The film is based on the real-life Indian bandit Veerappan and the events leading to Operation Cocoon, a mission to capture and kill him.

page4.title: Dhadak
page4.description: Madhu and Parthavi's love rises above social status, but their families oppose.

page4.title: Karwaan
page4.description: Two friends and a chirpy teenager take a road trip from Bangalore to Kochi.

page4.title: Mulk
page4.description: Based on a real-life story, Mulk revolves around the struggles of a Muslim joint family from a small town in India, who fight to reclaim their honour after a member of their family takes to terrorism.

page4.title: Nawabzaade
page4.description: Three best friends fall in love with the same girl and fight among themselves to win her affections. But, they soon realize that their beloved is much more than her exterior of a simple girl.

page5.title: Saheb, Biwi Aur Gangster 3
page5.description: The royal saga of deceit, conspiracy, greed and lust continues in the third installment of the film series, as the Saheb and Biwi are pitted against a foe who is dreaded by one and all. With everyone involved scheming ruthlessly for their own personal gain.

page5.title: Saawariya
page5.description: Based on Fyodor Dostoevsky's short story "White Nights", Saawariya is a timeless story of two young, star-crossed lovers whose passions almost consume their will to the brink of self-destruction.

page5.title: Ribbon
page5.description: Ribbon is the story of Sahana and Karan, a married couple, and the challenges they face when they have to deal with unplanned parenthood.

page5.title: Angrezi Mein Kehte Hain
page5.description: A romantic drama film about three couples and their distinct viewpoints on the concept of love.

page5.title: Zero
page5.description: A couple is entangled in a mystery as the lines between the living and dead blur around them. (Hindi Dubbed Version)

page5.title: Race 3
page5.description: Race 3 is an internationally mounted saga of a family that deals in borderline crime but is ruthless and vindictive to the core.

page6.title: Bhavesh Joshi Superhero
page6.description: A young man's desire to do well sets him on a journey from ordinary citizen to superhero vigilante.

page6.title: Beyond The Clouds
page6.description: After a hedonistic teenager in Mumbai gets busted for dealing drugs, he moves in with his estranged sister.

page6.title: Veere Di Wedding
page6.description: Four girls on their way to find true love discover that friendship this strong has its consequences. An adult entertainer!!

page6.title: Daddy
page6.description: From the rough streets and back alleys of Central Mumbai comes the sensational true story of Arun Gawli, a man who scripted his own destiny, eventually going on to become one of India’s most feared gangsters.

page6.title: Bombay Summer
page6.description: Bombay Summer explores the fleeting and delicate friendship between three young people in Mumbai, India and its eventual disintegration in the face of betrayal and personal loss. An international art-house cinema!!

page6.title: Parmanu: The Story Of Pokhran
page6.description: The Story of Pokhran is based on the nuclear bomb test explosions conducted by the Indian Army at Pokhran in 1998, under the leadership of India's future President Dr. APJ Abdul Kalam, during the time of PM Atal Bihari Vajpayee's tenure.

page7.title: Bioscopewala
page7.description: The story of Rehmat Khan, a man from Kabul, Afghanistan who used to show films to children through his Bioscope. Rehmat befriends a little girl named Minnie who is of the same age as his own daughter and one day disappear from her life.

page7.title: The Indian Post Graduate
page7.description: Sudheer, a young M.A degree holder drops his future studies due to economic crisis and moves to Mumbai. Things take a turn when he meets an M.B.A. pass out guy who is also unemployed.

page7.title: Billa 2
page7.description: An ordinary man from the slums enters an underworld gang and becomes the most feared underworld don. It is a prequel to Billa (2007) and focuses on how David, an ordinary man becomes Billa, a dreaded underworld don. (Hindi Dubbed Version)

page7.title: Raazi
page7.description: An Indian spy marries a Pakistani man during the Indo-Pakistan War of 1971.

page7.title: 102 Not Out
page7.description: Dattatraya Vakharia is a 102-year-old man who wants to break the record of oldest living male. There's just one problem -- he must find a way to change the sad and grumpy demeanor of his 75-year-old son.

page7.title: Zinda
page7.description: A man taken and locked up for 14 years without any sane reason is suddenly released, and has 4 days to figure out why this was done to him. Inspired by the South Korean film Oldboy.

page8.title: Welcome
page8.description: People always say that love is blind, but what happens when an ordinary guy falls deeply in love with a beautiful woman, only thing is he has no idea that her brothers are actually gangsters.

page8.title: Victory
page8.description: Vijay achieves his lifelong dream of playing cricket on India's national team, but loses his place when the fame goes to his head. He vows to be a better person, makes amends for his mistakes, and works hard to make it back on the team.

page8.title: Soch
page8.description: Raj Matthews has been selected the best actor in the Bollywood Cine Awards. He dedicates this award to his pretty co-star, Preeti Sardesai, making his wife extremely jealous in the process. A remake of Alfred Hitchcock's 1951 film Strangers on a Train.

page8.title: Tahalka
page8.description: A man and his daughter are kidnapped whilst on a yachting holiday by an evil army Major who has also captured dozens of schoolgirls in order to build an army of lady suicide bombers.

page8.title: Showbiz
page8.description: The movie revolves around the journey of a budding artist Rohan Arya (Tushar Jalota) trying to make a mark in the Hindi music industry and his brushes with the ups and downs of fame and media which is after him and his personal life.

page8.title: Love Express
page8.description: Love Express tells the story of two Punjabi families who have known each other for 30 years and are trying to have wedding during a train journey.

page9.title: Road to Ladakh
page9.description: Road To Ladakh is a suspenseful tale of falling in love with the wrong kind of mysterious stranger near the borders of India and Pakistan. *MATURE CONTENT*

page9.title: Noorie
page9.description: Yusuf and Noorie are engaged to be married, but shortly before the wedding, both Noorie and her father are said to have died, yet Yusuf believes that there is something far more sinister going on, and he sets out to rescue them.

page9.title: MSG-2 The Messenger
page9.description: A 2015 Indian faith-based action film written by and starring religious leader Gurmeet Ram Rahim Singh.

page9.title: Mr Ya Miss
page9.description: A womanizer is accidentally killed by one of his many girlfriends. He then finds himself reincarnated as a woman. Loosely inspired by 2002 American film The Hot Chick.

page9.title: Memsahab
page9.description: Memsahab is a woman-oriented movie with a social message of non-violence.Memsahab is based on the cruel incidents post the 1984 riots that happened in Northern India.

page9.title: Jo Bole So Nihaal
page9.description: When police officer Nihaal releases a notorious criminal, Romeo, by mistake, he expects to be fired but is instead hired by the FBI to track down and identify Romeo, who is a terrorist on the Most Wanted list. An action-comedy!!

page10.title: Kashmir Ki Kali
page10.description: A wealthy young man (Shammi Kapoor) falls in love with a flower girl (Sharmila Tagore) who supports her blind father.

page10.title: Judge Mujrim
page10.description: A judge witnesses a murder and assists the police in getting the killer, a death sentence. Soon after he discovers that the suspect is not the murderer, he must now find the real killer before the death sentence is passed.

page10.title: Haal-e-Dil
page10.description: While travelling by train, Shekhar attempts to woo Sanjana Sharma, but finds out she had given her heart to a former boyfriend, Rohit, who is no more.

page10.title: Chef
page10.description: Roshan Kalra(Saif Ali Khan)’s passion has been cooking ever since young. After losing his job as a chef, he decides to start his own mobile kitchen, and learning life lessons along the way. an official remake of an American film with the same name.

page10.title: Ek Aur Ek Gyarah
page10.description: Two petty thieves get on the bad side of two wanted criminals. On the run, they end up at the home of a Major, who takes them in, but is eventually betrayed by them.

page10.title: Dhan Dhana Dhan Goal
page10.description: A contemporary fictional story of the South Asian community in the UK, told through the prism of professional football.

page11.title: Click
page11.description: Shreyas Talpade, a fashion photographer, suddenly finds a strange apparition in the photographs clicked by him.A remake of 2004 Thai horror film Shutter.

page11.title: Bhanwarey
page11.description: Set in the late 90s in Delhi, Bhanwarey revolves around three friends and their struggle for survival in a shoddy apartment. An Adult Comedy!!

page11.title: Allah Ke Banday
page11.description: Two boys commit murder at the age of 12 and after serving time in juvenile prison they return to rule the streets they grew up on. A critically acclaimed crime-drama!!

page11.title: Freaky Ali
page11.description: Ali, a petty businessman struggles to make ends meet. However, in a twisted fate of incidence, his fortune 'tee's off and he goes on to become a champion golfer. Based on the 1996 American comedy film, Happy Gilmore.

page11.title: My Birthday Song
page11.description: The film revolves around a happily-married man and the song on his 40th birthday. A dark psychological thriller film!!

page11.title: Sonu Ke Titu Ki Sweety
page11.description: A man is going to marry a perfect woman, but his best friend doubts her character and tries to break the marriage while she tries to do the opposite.

page12.title: Zoo
page12.description: Misha Mehta, a teenager who believes she is the cause of an accident that happened a few years ago, finds herself trapped in her house to escape her emotions and to find solace, she resorts to drugs.

page12.title: Maatr
page12.description: Vidya, who's left shattered after her daughter Tia's murder, seeks vengeance by fighting the broken justice and criminal system.

page12.title: Pad Man
page12.description: Lakshmi is a newly married welder who causes a stir in his East Indian village when he tries to revolutionize the manufacturing of sanitary napkins for women.

page12.title: Super Singh
page12.description: A story of Sajjan Singh, a Punjabi man who resides in Canada with his mother. Circumstances bring him back to his hometown in Punjab where he accidentally attains superpowers and sets off on a path of self-realization. (Hindi Dubbed Version)

page12.title: Vodka Diaries
page12.description: Loosely based on the 2010 movie Shutter Island, the story revolves around a club called Vodka Diaries, where few murders occur and their investigation

page12.title: Vikram Vedha
page12.description: A team lead by Vikram, a ruthless, no-nonsense encounter cop, is on the hunt to capture or kill Vedha, a dreaded gangster. A neo-noir crime thriller film!! (Hindi Dubbed)

page13.title: Rudhramadevi
page13.description: The film revolves around the story of the queen, Rudramadevi, who ruled the Kakatiya dynasty in the 13th century. (Hindi Dubbed)

page13.title: Blackmail
page13.description: A man secretly blackmails his wife and her lover when he discovers the affair.

page13.title: October
page13.description: Dan, a student of hotel management is an intern at a top hotel in Delhi along with his batch mates. An incident occurs at the hotel where one of his colleagues Shiuli, lands up at the hospital.

page13.title: Poorna
page13.description: The real story of the youngest girl in history to climb Mt Everest – a 13-year-old tribal girl and her extraordinary journey from a village in Telangana to the top of the world.

page13.title: Baaghi 2
page13.description: Neha calls for her ex-boyfriend and army man Ranveer to find her 3-year-old daughter Rhea, who's been kidnapped 2 months ago. A remake of 2016 Telugu movie Kshanam.

page13.title: Missing
page13.description: A couple search through a beach resort for their missing daughter.

page14.title: Raid
page14.description: Amay Patnaik, a fearless income tax officer, carries out a raid at the mansion of the most powerful man in Lucknow.

page14.title: Kaalakaandi
page14.description: The movie has 3 parallel tracks: a man who discovers he has terminal illness decides to let go of his principles and live a little; a woman involved in a hit-and-run seeks redemption and two goons must decide if they can trust each other. *MATURE CONTENT*

page14.title: Gurgaon
page14.description: A dark story of a family living in Gurgaon - the city - and the members struggling with their individual demons, of conscience and the past. It is a neo-noir thriller movie shot in Hindi and Haryanvi language.

page14.title: Mercury
page14.description: Five friends, all affected in some way by a mercury poisoning incident are partying when a freak accident put them on a collision course with an entity that is in no mood to forgive their misgivings. A sound film which lacks dialogues!!

page14.title: Aiyaary
page14.description: An Army officer is compelled to chase down his protege when the latter turns rogue and threatens to disrupt the country’s government and army.

page14.title: Hate Story 4
page14.description: Two brothers compete against each other to win the affection of a girl. But the girl has her own ulterior motives to manipulate the brothers. It is the fourth installment of the erotic thriller series Hate Story.

page15.title: Hichki
page15.description: After several interviews and numerous rejections, a woman who has Tourette's syndrome lands a job as a teacher at an elite school. She soon tries to do whatever she can to make her rebellious and troublemaking students realize their full potential.

page15.title: Pari: Not a Fairytale
page15.description: Although a kind-hearted man attempts to help a young woman who seems to be a victim of abuse, everything is not as it appears on the surface.

page15.title: Ajji
page15.description: Little Manda is found raped and dumped in a trash heap in her slum. Her parents are more concerned with survival than dignity and want to forget and move on. The cops are powerless to help as the rapist is a local politician's son. *MATURE CONTENT*

page15.title: Meri Nimmo
page15.description: The film revolves around an eight-year-old boy who thinks he is in love with a 24-year-old girl and what follows when the object of his affection decides to get married. This movie was released direct-to-digital platforms.

page15.title: Welcome 2 Karachi
page15.description: Two men from India find themselves trapped by the Taliban when they arrive in Pakistan without their passports. A comedy movie!!

page15.title: Mukkabaaz
page15.description: A gritty young man Shravan Singh wants to be known as a ‘boxer’. It’s his ticket to a better life, one that offers respect.Things go awry when he falls in love with a girl of a different caste. A critically acclaimed sports drama!!

page16.title: Mere Huzoor
page16.description: Mere Huzoor is about two Lucknow based Muslim men falling in love with the same woman named Saltalat. One of them is a prince while the other is a poet. A classic romantic musical film!!

page16.title: Om-Dar-B-Dar
page16.description: The adventures of a schoolboy named Om along with his family which is set in Rajasthan. It employs nonlinear narrative and an absurdist storyline to satirize mythology, arts, politics, and philosophy. A cult classic!!

page16.title: Dushmani A Violent Love Story
page16.description: In order to settle personal scores; two gang leaders, Jai Singh and Oberoi fight for many years in gang-wars. There enmity multiplies when Jai's younger brother, Suraj falls in love with Oberoi's sister, Sapna which forces Suraj and Sapna to elope.

page16.title: Hind Ka Napak Ko Jawab: MSG Lion Heart 2
page16.description: A secret agent with a huge stockpile of weapons takes on enemies of the state.

page16.title: Ek : The Power of One
page16.description: Nandu an orphan turned assassin somehow gets wrongly accused of a politician’s murder and is on the run.A remake of Telugu film Athadu.

page16.title: Dor
page16.description: The story is about two women who come from different backgrounds and how fate brings them together.An official adaptation of the Malayalam film, Perumazhakkalam (2004).

page17.title: Bumboo
page17.description: Hired gun Mangal meets suicidal Suresh - while shooting a swindler. Does fate shaft the best-laid plans? Based on an original play/film L'emmerdeur written by Francis Veber. A comedy-drama!!

page17.title: Bittoo Boss
page17.description: A wedding photographer believes in spreading happiness through the beautiful moments he captures in pictures, but things start to go wrong when he takes a shortcut to earn a fast buck.

page17.title: Bachke Rehna Re Baba
page17.description: Rukmini and her niece, Padmini, entice wealthy men, steal their money, abandon them, and then move on to their next target.Inspired by the 2001 American film Heartbreakers. An Adult comedy!!

page17.title: Baabarr
page17.description: Baabarr film throws light on the growing ambitions of the youth and how their focus shifts to organized crime with an underlying message that Crime never dies, it just changes faces. A film-noir action film!!

page17.title: Aloo Chaat
page17.description: The story focuses on a US return guy Nikhil who is in love with a Muslim girl Aamna.To convince his orthodox Hindu family Nikhil plots a drama with the help of his uncle and hires a girl Nikki to play his girlfriend from the US while Aamna plays her friend.

page17.title: Trump Card
page17.description: The plot of the film revolves around a huge transaction of property which leads to murders and sting operations and spy work. A suspense action thriller!!

page18.title: Teen Thay Bhai
page18.description: Teen Thay Bhai is the story of 3 brothers separated for many years and reunited by their grandfather's will. A comedy-drama!!

page18.title: Rokkk
page18.description: Anushka helps her sister fight a murder charge and she becomes trapped in a nightmarish world that may be inescapable. A horror-thriller!!

page18.title: Red : The Dark Side
page18.description: Neil Oberoi is a billionaire with a serious heart condition and is in need of a new heart. He finds a donor and meets his widow, Anaita and they fall in love. However, her husband dies under mysterious circumstances.

page18.title: Raghu Romeo
page18.description: Set in modern-day Mumbai, the film focuses on the life of a waiter working in a dance bar. The film won the National Film Award for Best Feature Film in Hindi. A critically acclaimed comedy-drama!!

page18.title: My Name Is Anthony Gonsalves
page18.description: A young girl meets a man who convinces her that he wants to be a Bollywood actor.The name of the movie is derived from the 1977 hit movie Amar Akbar Anthony's famous song, "My Name Is Anthony Gonsalves."

page18.title: Love Kaa Taddka
page18.description: Aditya gets married to Riya.He comes to know that her father is very wealthy, and in order to impress him, both take loans to purchase a flat.The owner of the flat, Rustam, conditionally sells it to them if they come up with the rest of the money in 3 months.

page19.title: Love U...Mr. Kalakaar!
page19.description: Rich girl Ritu loves simpleton Saahil because he is an artist. Her business tycoon dad disapproves of the relationship for the very same reason. He agrees with the alliance if the artist can prove to be a successful businessman too.

page19.title: Kushti
page19.description: A comedy movie that stars Rajpal Yadav in the lead role along with the WWE wrestler The Great Khali (Dalap Singh Rana) making his Bollywood debut.The movie is inspired by the 1985 Malayalam film Mutharamkunnu P.O.

page19.title: The Film Emotional Atyachar
page19.description: A businessman deals with corrupt police officers and gangsters when he finds a bag full of money. A black comedy!!

page19.title: Zokkomon
page19.description: Kunal, an orphaned boy, soon realizes the hero within and begins his epic journey of adventure and transformation to become Zokkomon. An action superhero movie!!

page19.title: Soch Lo
page19.description: An unidentified man, suffering a memory loss, in a bruised and battered state, is left in the desert to die. He manages to survive the brutal terrain and sets out on a journey to seek out his identity.  A thriller movie!!

page19.title: MSG : The Warrior Lion Heart
page19.description: The story is about a medieval warrior who fights for the honor of his land and the dignity of the womenfolk. The story travels centuries apart as he emerges in another role as a modern Indian equivalent of James Bond, a stylish top secret agent.

page20.title: Motu Patlu : King of Kings
page20.description: A runaway circus lion tries to protect his new jungle home from a greedy poacher.The film was inspired by the popular TV series Motu Patlu. A computer-animated adventure comedy film!!

page20.title: Milta Hai Chance by Chance
page20.description: Rahul and Mehul come to Mumbai to become stars and fall in love with Megha and Reva respectively.They decide to enter a reality contest to make money but it is for married couples only. A comedy movie!!

page20.title: Joggers' Park
page20.description: An aging celebrity becomes attracted to the vibrant young woman he befriended in a popular park. A critically acclaimed rom-com!!

page20.title: Aparachit (Anniyan)
page20.description: A man suffers from multiple personality disorder, he shifts from being a lawyer to a suave supermodel and finally a vigilante who wreaks havoc on people who cheat, loots or con the first one.(Hindi Dubbed Version)

page20.title: Chingari
page20.description: The film is a commentary on the abuse of power and in particular discusses the injustices of the priests in India. The film is based on the novel, The Prostitute and the Postman by Bhupen Hazarika.

page20.title: Kuchhe Dhaage
page20.description: After a man is sentenced to be hanged, his wife swears she will raise their child to hunt down and kill the man who betrayed him.

page21.title: Akhiyon Ke Jharokon Se
page21.description: Arun and Lily are elated when their parents agree to get them married. Things take a turn when Lily is diagnosed with blood cancer.

page21.title: Secret Superstar
page21.description: The film tells the coming-of-age story of a teenage girl who aspires to be a singer and her relationship with her mother.The film deals with social issues including feminism, gender equality, and domestic violence.

page21.title: Rukh
page21.description: A son’s search for closure posts his father’s death in a road mishap leads to some dark realizations. A mystery thriller!!

page21.title: Padmaavat
page21.description: Padmaavat is a 2018 Indian epic period drama film directed by Sanjay Leela Bhansali. Loosely based on the epic poem Padmavat by Malik Muhammad Jayasi, it is one of the most expensive Indian films ever made.

page21.title: Fukrey Returns
page21.description: Fukrey Returns picks up a year later from where it ended. Having enjoyed the spoils of war they had so audaciously waged, the Fukras are now at crossroads with their past, which is about to decide their future. A sequel to 2013 film Fukrey.

page21.title: Shaadi Mein Zaroor Aana
page21.description: Aarti, a bright, ambitious woman, is on the cusp of making a great career for herself. She agrees to marry Satyendar, but flees the arrangement when she learns she will not be allowed to work once they are wed.

page22.title: Qarib Qarib Singlle
page22.description: Jaya and Yogi set out on a short journey to retrace past relationships and end up in the most eventful, strange, crazy trip of their lives.

Ayush, a pianist, moves to London from India to learn music. The mansion he stays in has a haunted past and soon enough strange events start happening around him, threatening to engulf his entire life.It is the fourth film in the 1920 franchise.

page22.title: Haseena Parkar
page22.description: Haseena Parkar is an Indian biographical crime film based on the life of Haseena Parkar. Haseena was the sister of terrorist Dawood Ibrahim.

page22.title: Raj Hath
page22.description: The story revolves around two neighboring empires with long-term mutual enmity, whose children turn their rivalry into love.

page22.title: Tiger Zinda Hai
page22.description: Inspired by real events, Tiger Zinda Hai is a sequel to the blockbuster Ek Tha Tiger, and an espionage action thriller that follows an adventurous rescue mission in Iraq.

page22.title: Jagga Jasoos
page22.description: Jagga, a gifted teenage detective, embarks on a quest to find her missing father with help from a female companion.

page23.title: Hum Tere Ashiq Hain
page23.description: An NRI doctor travels to India to work for six months but he falls for a princess and never returns back. His father along with his fiancée travels to India to check on him and are shocked to know that he is getting married to the princess.

page23.title: Azaad
page23.description: The story revolves around the activities of a young man, Ashok, who strives to help those in distress and are oppressed. An action-drama movie!!

page23.title: Hulchul
page23.description: A war emerges between two families when two young people (Akshaye Khanna, Kareena Kapoor) fall in love.The story is adapted from the Malayalam film Godfather.

page23.title: Judwaa 2
page23.description: Twin brothers Raja and Prem are separated at birth after their father exposes a kingpin and his racket. They eventually come together to battle a smuggling ring and save their family from certain doom.

page23.title: Sons of Ram
page23.description: Luv and Kush, the twin sons of Lord of Ram and Sita, who are raised by her mother alone whilst she in exile at the sage Valmiki's ashram, embark on a journey from the enchanted forests to the revered land of Ayodhya.

page23.title: Bal Ganesh 2
page23.description: The Elephant God is loved, adored and worshipped by millions worldwide. He, who is considered as the God of Gods, was once a cute little child. Bal Ganesha 2 explores new adventures of Bal Ganesh.

page24.title: Krishna Aur Kans
page24.description: Life is a curse for the inhabitants of this kingdom that is ruled and threatened by evil Kans. Can someone put an end to all this mess? Yes, the eighth son of Devaki.. provided he escapes the wrath and injustice of his maternal uncle, Kans.

page24.title: Chhota Bheem and the Throne of Bali
page24.description: On an invitation from the King of Bali, Bheem & team head out to Bali to attend the crowning ceremony of their Prince Arjun. But before they reach Bali, the Kingdom is captured by evil witch Rangda who arrests the king & queen of Bali.

page24.title: Chhota Bheem and the Curse of Damyaan
page24.description: Bheem and his friend have to destroy Damyaan to free themselves from a prison.An Indian animation film based on the characters Chhota Bheem and his friends!!

page24.title: Dhoom Dadakka
page24.description: A don who needs an heir faces a dilemma when four people claim to be his relatives. A crime-comedy-drama!!

page24.title: The House Next Door
page24.description: Two families have a tough time dealing with a revenge-seeking spirit, which is strangely connected with one of its members.

page24.title: A Flying Jatt
page24.description: Aman, a meek youngster who is scared of heights, discovers his superpowers when he engages in a fight with Raka, a greedy industrialist's ally who becomes a beast and plans to destroy the world.

page25.title: Not a Love Story
page25.description: Not a Love Story is a crime/thriller movie based on the gruesome murder of Neeraj Grover in 2008 that led to the arrest of Emile Jerome and Maria Susairaj.

page25.title: Moksha
page25.description: An idealistic lawyer wants to help the poor get justice, but lacks finance, so plans to rob a bank, alongside his love interest. His black n white emotional nature, leads to an unforgivable deed, which he severely repents.

page25.title: My Friend Pinto
page25.description: Following his mother's death, a young man from a small village travels to Mumbai to track down a childhood friend.

page25.title: Love Shagun
page25.description: Love Shagun is a romantic comedy about seven different definitions of love where the definitions are the characters themselves.

page25.title: Love in Bombay
page25.description: Baadal is in love with Preeti and the two want to get married. But Preeti's father and her fiance try every possible means to break their union.Due to lack of funds, this movie was released later in 2013.

page25.title: Kismat Konnection
page25.description: Sparks fly when Raj (Shahid Kapoor), a newly graduated architect, meets Priya (Vidya Balan), an activist who is trying to save a local community center. They have feelings for each other, and Raj secretly believes Priya to be his lucky charm.

page26.title: Khiladi 420
page26.description: A con artist loses his life in a scuffle; his widow then meets his twin brother, who must pay the price for his misconduct with the police and the gangsters.

page26.title: Karam
page26.description: John is an assassin working for a mobster named Captain. After killing an entire family, he is hit by the consequences of his actions and decides to quit his job.

page26.title: Kala Bazar
page26.description: Fired from his job as a conductor, an impoverished man sells movie tickets on the black market but starts to have a change of heart after he falls in love.

page26.title: Jashnn : The Music Within
page26.description: A young singer (Adhyayan Suman) falls in love with the sister (Anjana Sukhani) of a production mogul (Humayun Saeed), who tries to stop the romance.

page26.title: Jaani Dushman : Ek Anokhi Kahani
page26.description: The spirit of a murdered student (Manisha Koirala) joins forces with a shape-shifting snake (Munish Kohli) to avenge her death.

page26.title: Island City
page26.description: Three stories unfold in Mumbai. A middle-aged man wins the office Fun Committee Award, a man's family buys a TV to watch a soap while he is unconscious, and a woman's repetitive existence is changed by a letter.

page27.title: Hostel
page27.description: An engineering student stays in a hostel and he is molested, beaten and humiliated by its residents.

page27.title: Koi Mere Dil Se Poochhe
page27.description: A student (Aftab Shivdasani) falls in love with a beautiful woman (Esha Deol) who shares a terrifying secret with her father.

page27.title: Ek Se Badhkar Ek
page27.description: Advocate Anand Mathur draws up a will for his client, while reading the novel "Godfather", and erroneously makes out the will with a provision that the beneficiary must be a criminal don in order to inherit the billions of rupees.

page27.title: Ek Rishtaa : The Bond of Love
page27.description: The film is a family drama where a big family encounters a crisis when disputes take place between the father (Bachchan) and the son (Kumar).

page27.title: Dilwale
page27.description: A bright young boy named Arun murders a woman named Jyoti and is sentenced to death after confessing to the crime. Inspector Vikram, an upright officer reopens Arun's case after finding the circumstances leading to the murder a little strange.

page27.title: Chal Chalein
page27.description: The rising stress levels in teenagers due to the ever-increasing competition for seats in colleges in India is a well-known fact. Chal Chalein analyzes the issue and tries to provide the appropriate solutions to the problem.

page28.title: Bullet: Ek Dhamaka
page28.description: Bullet - Ek Dhamaka revolves around the character Arjun (Iqbal Khan) an intelligence officer whose sole aim in life is to get Don Raja [Aseem Merchant], the badshaah of the underworld, back to India from Bulgaria.

page28.title: Gollu aur Pappu
page28.description: Two innocent brothers are muddled in the midst of executing a bomb threat. What's worse than a national bomb scare? When the bomb is in the hands of two idiots.

page28.title: Bewafaa
page28.description: A young woman (Kareena Kapoor) must choose between her wealthy but inattentive husband (Anil Kapoor) and the musician (Akshay Kumar) she truly loves.

page28.title: Bas Ek Pal
page28.description: The lives of an ex-convict, an abusive man (Rehaan Engineer) and others intertwine.

page28.title: Akhiyon Se Goli Maare
page28.description: A crook's daughter hatches a crazy plan to trick her father into accepting her straight-arrow lover.

page28.title: Aan : Men at Work
page28.description: A young police officer disillusioned with the corrupt and incompetent force pushes for reform but finds that his ideas do more harm than good.

page29.description: A couple moves into a haunted mansion, unaware of the danger that awaits them. However, when the girl gets possessed by a demonic spirit, her partner decides to save her.
A gangster deputes two of his men to recover money from an out of town compulsive gambler.

page29.title: Begum Jaan
page29.description: The story of eleven prostitutes who refuse to part ways with their brothel and each other during the partition between India and Pakistan.A Hindi remake of the critically acclaimed Bengali film Rajkahini (2015).

page29.title: Padmashree Laloo Prasad Yadav
page29.description: A woman named Padmashree Divakar Kashya, along with her boyfriend, Lalchand Dilachand alias Laloo, begin a search for some family diamonds that were reportedly stolen by a Mr. Saxena.

page29.title: Page 3
page29.description: A look at Mumbai's socialite party circle world through the eyes of a Page 3 journalist.The film won three National Film Awards, including the Golden Lotus Award for Best Film.

page29.title: Paying Guests
page29.description: To fool their landlord, four friends must pretend to be married in order to live together under one roof.

page30.title: Qayamat: City Under Threat
page30.description: Akram asks his superiors to get Rachit, a man double-crossed by the Ramani brothers, to help him with a case.A remake of the 1996 film The Rock.

page30.title: Rahul
page30.description: A 5-year-old must decide where his loyalties stand for a mother and father who hate each other.

page30.title: Rakht
page30.description: A psychic has a vision of the mayor's missing daughter's dead body in a lake and though a man is charged, only she knows he's not the real murderer.

page30.title: Rakhtbeej
page30.description: The movie is based on the two men Abhay and Ajay whose fate take them to powerful positions in business and politics. Due to a love triangle and their enmity with other powerful politicians and business men their life goes for a toss.

page30.title: Saala Khadoos
page30.description: A former boxer (Madhavan) trains a rebellious young woman (Ritika Singh) to become a top fighter. It was simultaneously released in Tamil-language as Irudhi Suttru.

page30.title: Sahi Dhandhe Galat Bande
page30.description: Criminals abduct a politician's son to use him against land grabbing by the Government. A critically acclaimed action- comedy movie!!

page31.title: Sandwich
page31.description: Shekar has moved to Mumbai and has fallen in love with Nisha. However, he is called back to his home to hear that his disabled sister is to marry a young man named Harpreet, but on the condition that Shekar marries Harpreet's sister.

page31.title: Yeh Saali Zindagi
page31.description: Two gangsters commit a blunder and get their love lives entangled with their criminal deeds.A critically acclaimed thriller- drama film directed by Sudhir Mishra.

page31.title: Shaapit: The Cursed
page31.description: Trapped in a generational curse, a young woman cannot marry her lover, who intends to put an end to the affliction.

page31.title: Slumdog Millionaire
page31.description: A Mumbai teen reflects on his upbringing in the slums when he is accused of cheating on the Indian Version of "Who Wants to be a Millionaire?" (Hindi Dubbed Version). It won eight awards at the Academy Awards in 2009.

page31.title: Sssshhh..
page31.description: A college student (Tanisha) becomes the quarry of the same serial killer who murdered her sister six months earlier. Inspired by the 1996 Hollywood thriller Scream.

page31.title: Stumped
page31.description: Raghav Seth (Aly Khan), a young army officer, shifts to Delhi with his wife Reema (Ravina Tandon) to "Happy Home Society". They soon realize that the society is home to many cricket fans.

page32.title: Tum Se Achcha Kaun Hai
page32.description: The daughter of a rich tycoon aids an aspiring singer in becoming a singing star. In the process, she falls in love with him, but he loves somebody else.

page32.title: Will You Marry Me
page32.description: Three young men (Shreyas Talpade, Rajeev Khandelwal, Muzamil Ibrahim) enjoy their bachelor status, until one of them decides to marry the love of his life.

page32.title: Yaadein
page32.description: After his doting wife dies, an East Indian (Jackie Schroff) living in London must look after his three daughters.

page32.title: Zid
page32.description: Jay gets a horse from his grandmother and riding becomes his obsession and he ends up getting injured. His grandmother gives away his horse; thus, changing their lives forever.

page32.title: 26th July at Barista
page32.description: Two individuals out of a group of people, who take shelter at a coffee shop during the July 2005 flood in Mumbai, help the others gathered there, to get over the fear that is caused by the calamity.

page32.title: Fast Forward
page32.description: A dance group faces challenges and betrayal after competing against reigning champions in an underground dance competition.

page33.title: Hawa
page33.description: Sanjana and her daughters move to a remote home and soon become the victims of odd situations culminating in the rapes of the three women in the house by an unseen force.Inspired by 1983 American horror film The Entity.

page33.title: Inaam Dus Hazaar
page33.description: A salesman crashes the parties of the rich and famous to get a taste of the glamorous life. It is inspired by Alfred Hitchcock's classic North by Northwest.

page33.title: Kyaa Dil Ne Kahaa
page33.description: U.S. settled Esha is attracted to fellow-student Rahul, and he is attracted to her too. Esha returns home to India and tells her parents about her love for Rahul. Her family is pleased, and proceeds to finalize the marriage.

page33.title: Sarphira
page33.description: Sarphira is a 1992 Bollywood film directed by Ashok Gaekwad. The film stars Vinod Mehra, Sanjay Dutt, Madhavi, Sumeet Saigal, Kimi Katkar, Kiran Juneja and Shreeram Lagoo.

page33.title: Tere Naam
page33.description: Problems arise when Radhey Mohan, a delinquent falls in love with a girl named Nirjara.A remake of Tamil blockbuster Sethu (1999).

page33.title: Dhund: The Fog
page33.description: A mysterious killer rises from the grave and terrorizes two couples in seeking revenge for his murder.The film is a remake of I Know What You Did Last Summer.

page34.title: Pyaar Ishq Aur Mohabbat
page34.description: Three men (Sunil Shetty, Aftab Shivdasani, Arjun Rampal) go crazy for a beautiful woman who sends out conflicting signals.The film is notable for introducing Arjun Rampal and launching him as a popular actor in Bollywood.

page34.title: Chashme Buddoor
page34.description: The film is about three students; Siddharth (Farooq Shaikh), Omi (Rakesh Bedi) and Jai (Ravi Baswani) at Delhi University, who don't go home during summer vacation and how a girl Neha (Deepti Naval) comes in their life.

page34.title: Fool N Final
page34.description: Criminals (Shahid Kapoor, Ayesha Takia) collide when the nephew of a British don steals a diamond.The film is a remake of the British film Snatch.

page34.title: Grahan
page34.description: The film follows the story of Parvati, a rape victim who quests for justice and comes to know that it is not such a simple task.

page34.title: Albela
page34.description: A happy-go-lucky tourist guide (Govinda) falls for a beautiful woman (Aishwarya Rai) in search of her mother's grave.

page34.title: Dharam Veer
page34.description: Dharam-Veer takes place in a mythical kingdom and tells the tale of twin brothers separated at birth who still become best friends when they are older, not knowing that they were real brothers.A gigantic blockbuster at the 1970s Indian box office.

page35.title: Jawani Diwani
page35.description: A 1972 Bollywood movie directed by Narender Bedi, and starring Randhir Kapoor, Jaya Bhaduri, Balraj Sahni, Nirupa Roy, as leads.The film was a musical hit and the eighth highest grossing film at the Indian Box Office.

page35.title: Kis Kis Ki Kismat
page35.description: When a famous stockbroker throws his wife's sapphire necklace off the roof of their mansion to prove he is not a miser, it lands him in more trouble.

page35.title: Pyar Jhukta Nahin
page35.description: Pyar Jhukta Nahin is a 1985 Hindi-language Indian feature film directed by Vijay Sadanah, starring Mithun Chakraborty, Padmini Kolhapure, Danny Denzongpa, Asrani and Bindu.The film is a remake of 1977 Pakistani Film Aina.

page35.title: U R My Jaan
page35.description: Love transforms the lives of a ruthless billionaire (Mikaal Zulfiqar) and a woman (Priti) from a middle-class background who wants to be a Bollywood star.

page35.title: Kabali
page35.description: Kabali is a gangster film starring Rajinikanth and Radhika Apte in the lead. This crime action film depicts the eternal victory of good over evil. The protagonist fights to bring justice to the people who suffer.(Hindi Dubbed Version)

page35.title: Newton
page35.description: A government clerk on election duty in the conflict-ridden jungle of Central India tries his best to conduct free and fair voting despite the apathy of security forces and the looming fear of guerrilla attacks by communist rebels.

page36.title: Ittefaq
page36.description: An acclaimed writer and a young homemaker become the prime suspects in a double murder. Police officer Dev must figure out who's telling the truth when both offer conflicting stories about the events of that fateful night.

page36.title: Missing On A Weekend
page36.description: A Weekend in Goa with friends is a dream but what when they go missing? With a New undercover inspector in town? Find out the story of Laksh and his friends.

page36.title: Phullu
page36.description: Phullu is about Phullu, an errand boy who eventually makes low-cost menstruation pads.The film is meant to teach the viewer about menstruation,a taboo subject in India.

page36.title: Shab
page36.description: "Shab" is a story that revolves around multiple characters' search for happiness and love in a complex, unforgiving, and cold city. *MATURE CONTENT*

page36.title: Shubh Mangal Saavdhan
page36.description: Remake of Kalyana Samayal Saadham (2013), a couple fall in love but then the groom discovers that he suffers from erectile dysfunction.

page36.title: Prague
page36.description: Chandan prepares to move to Prague for a job and discovers his girlfriend is cheating with a friend. He arrives in his new city disappointed and depressed and is lucky to find love again until his friend arrives to cause problems.

page37.title: Half Girlfriend
page37.description: Madhav Jha (Arjun) a rustic boy from Bihar who is drawn to his college-mate, Riya Somani (Shraddha), an affluent English-speaking girl from Delhi.Based on the novel of the same name written by Chetan Bhagat.

page37.title: Golmaal Again
page37.description: Golmaal Again is yet another fun filled ride about two gangs who are unable to stand each other since their childhood and how they repulse each other even after they grow up.

page37.title: Patel Ki Punjabi Shaadi
page37.description: Patel ki Punjabi Shaadi is a feel good  comedy which answers basic issues of our diverse culture with  lots of family values & funny moments , spiced up with Bhangara & Garba, Dhokla & Paratha.

page37.title: Bhoomi
page37.description: A single father battles injustice after his daughter is raped and the perpetrators are found not guilty.

page37.title: Poster Boys
page37.description: Three men face ridicule from their families and fellow villagers after they appear on a poster that promotes vasectomies. They soon embark on a mission to prove that they are victims of the system.A remake of the 2014 Marathi hit Poshter Boyz!!

page37.title: Mukti Bhawan
page37.description: Faced with his father's untimely and bizarre demand to go and die in the holy city of Varanasi and attain Salvation, a son is left with no choice but to embark on this journey.

page38.title: Sameer
page38.description: An Engineering student is nabbed by the Anti-Terrorism Squad after his roommate is found to be a terrorist mastermind.

page38.title: Simran
page38.description: A socially criticized girl who is financially cornered, becomes an outlaw to dodge the situation. Based on a real incident!!

page38.title: Mirza Juuliet
page38.description: A story of star-crossed lovers battle misogyny, hate and caste tensions amidst a politically-charged environment.

page38.title: Toilet: Ek Prem Katha
page38.description: A woman leaves her husband on the first day of their marriage after discovering that he doesn't have a toilet. He desperately sets out on a mission to win back his love by standing up to the age-old traditions and values of India.

page38.title: Lucknow Central
page38.description: After being accused of murder, Kishen Mohan is thrown inside the Lucknow Central Jail, where he is awaiting death penalty. Gayatri, an NGO worker, visits the jail with the idea of holding a band competition in order to form a Band of Prisoners.

page38.title: Baadshaho
page38.description: An Indian queen asks her bodyguard to steal back gold taken from her by the Indian government during The Emergency period in 1975.

page39.title: Bareilly Ki Barfi
page39.description: Set in the small-town of Bareilly, Bitti is a free-spirited young girl who lives life on her own terms and refuses to be pressured into getting married. Her life takes a shift when she meets Chirag Dubey and Pritam Vidrohi.

page39.title: Lipstick Under My Burkha
page39.description: Set in the crowded lanes of small town India, this story chronicles the secret lives of four women in search of a little freedom. *MATURE CONTENT*

page39.title: A Gentleman
page39.description: Gaurav, a simple hard working guy for a white collar job visits Mumbai for a meeting where his doppelganger is about to bring chaos in his life.

page39.title: Blue Mountains
page39.description: A talented teenager from a small-town, whose mother is a yesteryear vocalist, gets chosen for a singing reality show in Mumbai. He faces a miserable defeat after which life back home becomes unbearable for him.

page39.title: Tubelight
page39.description: The story of one man's unshakable belief in himself and love for his family.  An adaptation of the 2015 Hollywood film, Little Boy.

page39.title: Mom
page39.description: The bliss of a biology teacher’s family life in Delhi is shattered when her daughter, Arya is physically assaulted by Jagan and gang. Does Devki Sabarwal wait for the law to take its course?

page40.title: Mubarakan
page40.description: Identical twin brothers turn to their eccentric uncle for help to make sure that they each marry the woman they love.

page40.title: Qaidi Band
page40.description: Sanju and Bindu are few of the undertrials, who refuse to be 'institutionalised'. In the absence of a good lawyer and big money to support their court proceedings, they continue to rot in jail. Some of these qaidis accidentally find solace in music.

page40.title: Munna Michael
page40.description: This film follows the story of a boy from the streets of Teen Batti who idolizes Michael Jackson.

page40.title: Samjhauta
page40.description: Gopal has been gifted with a wonderful voice and sings in the village drama company. With the encouragement of his sister he shifts to Mumbai where he is helped by Shiva who is car polisher, Pradeep Kumar and Shanno, who are very poor.

page40.title: Shaadi Ke Baad
page40.description: Choudhury (Shatrughan Sinha) fails to foresee the outcome of his meddling when he promises to find villager Masterji (Paintal) a match for his sister, Shobha (Raakhee), if he'll agree to wed Choudhury's daughter.

page40.title: Sharafat
page40.description: A woman meets a college professor while searching for her long-lost father. Hema Malini plays the role of a feisty courtesan Chanda in search of her father, in this satire about society's hypocritical moral standards.

page41.title: Son of India
page41.description: Son of India is a 1962 Bollywood film written and directed by Mehboob Khan.The movie is remembered for the patriotic song for children nanha munna rahi hoon desh ka sipahi hoon composed by by Naushad and the lyrics by Shakeel Badayuni.

page41.title: Swati
page41.description: Sharda, a nurse and single mother, raises her daughter Swati as an independent, articulate young woman. Swati is a strong advocate of women's rights in a society where there is significant male domination.

page41.title: Talash
page41.description: Talash is a Hindi film by O. P. Ralhan starring Rajendra Kumar and Sharmila Tagore. This movie was the first movie in Bollywood which was publicized as having a budget of Rs 1 Crore.

page41.title: Taxi Driver
page41.description: A cabbie (Dev Anand) helps a damsel in distress look for a musical director .Dev Anand's taxi in the movie was the British made Hillman Minx black car with number 1111.

page41.title: The Pool
page41.description: A boy in abject poverty works in a hotel and becomes obsessed with a swimming pool in the opulent hills of Panjim, Goa, India. His life gets turned upside-down when he attempts to meet the mysterious family who lives at the house.

page41.title: Trinetra
page41.description: Raja is an aspiring singer and gets a chance to sing in Dubai, but his drug-smuggling mentor has other plans.

page42.title: Triveni
page42.description: A prosecutor agrees to fight the case of a man who he believes to be a killer. Later, things take a turn when he comes across the evidence which proves his innocence.

page42.title: Uff! Yeh Mohabbat
page42.description: The college students plan a trip to Sikkim, Northern India, except Raja, so he decides to go on his own. Once in Sikkim, Sonia and Raja falls in love, which enrages Chiclets, and she schemes to break-up their relationship.

page42.title: Unlimited Nasha
page42.description: Madhumati is an ambitious poetess who falls in love with a politician Amar wth the sole aim of fulfilling her dreams. Amar's wife Madhubala is ambitious too, but to usurp her husband's wealth. An Adult Thriller!!

page42.title: Utt Pataang
page42.description: Five people are thrown into a game of cat and mouse after a money deal goes horribly wrong. A 2011 Bollywood Comedy thriller film, written and directed by Srikanth V. Velagaleti.

page42.title: Vivah
page42.description: Poonam, a traditionally brought-up young woman, is to marry Prem, a groom chosen by her uncle. Poonam and Prem's faith and love are to be tested however, when an accident occurs and Poonam might be scarred for life.

page42.title: Woh 7 Din
page42.description: A kindly doctor (Naseeruddin Shah) offers to reunite his unhappy wife (Padmini Kolhapure) with the man (Anil Kapoor) she truly loves.

page43.title: Tumko Na Bhool Paayenge
page43.description: An amnesiac (Salman Khan) has no recollection of his ex-girlfriend (Sushmita Sen), a policeman or an old friend.

page43.title: Sadaa Suhagan
page43.description: Rajshekhar, a wealthy man, falls in love with Laxmi. Years later, the couple is blessed with two boys and a girl. Rajshekhar is proud of his children and is shocked to find one day that his eldest son, Ravi is having an affair with the daughter of a prostitute.

page43.title: Saajan Chale Sasural
page43.description: A village-based singer attempts to find love and fame in the big city. Saajan Chale Sasural is a 1996 Indian Hindi comedy film which is a remake of the Telugu movie Allari Mogudu.

page43.title: Rishtey
page43.description: A one-time boxer (Anil Kapoor) battles for custody of the 7-year-old son he kidnapped from in-laws.

page43.title: Rihaee
page43.description: The film dealt with the promiscuity of male migrant workers to urban India, and also the sexuality of women, left behind the rural regions.

page43.title: Revati
page43.description: The story of a trash picker living in the slums of Bombay India. She dreams of being able to have simple luxuries. One day she gets her opportunity through a drug smuggler of Bombay and quickly learns all that glitters is not gold. Adult entertainer!!

page44.title: Ram Balram
page44.description: A conniving man plans to use his two nephews (Dharmendra, Amitabh Bachchan) in an illegal scheme to get rich.

page44.title: Rajput
page44.description: When his kingdom is taken over by the government, the Maharaja kills himself, leaving his son, Jaipal, to protect his heritage from being confiscated.

page44.title: Raja
page44.description: A young man (Sanjay Kapoor) meets and falls in love with the woman (Madhuri Dixit) he was supposed to marry several years earlier.

page44.title: Pyar Ki Jeet
page44.description: Pyar Ki Jeet is a 1987 Indian Bollywood film directed by Sawan Kumar Tak. The film stars Shashi Kapoor, Vinod Mehra, Rekha, Ashok Kumar, Moon Moon Sen.

page44.title: Pardesi Babu
page44.description: A servant (Raveena Tandon) and a previously engaged woman (Shilpa Shetty) fall in love with the same man (Govinda).

page44.title: Zameen Aasmaan
page44.description: A widower has a run of good luck; a sudden increase in his fortunes, and a new woman in his life whose resemblance to his late wife seals the deal. However, the new bride may not have the best intentions towards him.

page45.title: Zor Lagaa Ke...Haiya!
page45.description: Zor Lagaa Ke...Haiya! is a 2009 Indian children's film starring Meghan Jadhav, Mithun Chakraborty and Mahesh Manjrekar. The film attracted media attention for its environmental message of Save our Trees. Amitabh Bachchan narrated the film.

page45.title: Paigham
page45.description: Paigham is a 1959 Hindi film produced and directed by S. S. Vasan. The film stars Dilip Kumar, Vyjayanthimala, Raaj Kumar, Saroja Devi, Motilal, and Johnny Walker. The film's music is by C. Ramachandra.

page45.title: Nannha Farishta
page45.description: Criminals Govind (Pran), Joseph (Ajit) and Nazir (Anwar Hussain) break into a house, kill the head of the household and kidnap a young girl, Gita (Baby Rani). With the police on their trail, the trio tries to remain inconspicuous.

page45.title: Muqaddar
page45.description: Muqadar is a 1996 Indian Hindi film. Produced by Rajiv Babbar and directed by T L V Prasad, it stars Mithun Chakraborty, Puneet Issar and Kiran Kumar in lead roles and Moushumi Chatterjee, Simran, Ayesha Jhulka and Hemant Birje in supporting roles.

page45.title: Mr. Black Mr. White
page45.description: Gopi's dying father asks him to locate Kishen and hand-over a piece of land to him; Gopi heads out to Goa where he will be taken for a ride not only by Kishen, but also by Kishen's look-alike hoodlum brother, Hari.

page45.title: Mera Pati Sirf Mera Hai
page45.description: Prakash is a poor tailor who finds success with the help of Sharda with whom he falls in love.The film is a remake of Tamil Movie En Purushan Enakku Mattumthaan (1989).

page46.title: Mera Saaya
page46.description: Rakesh (Sunil Dutt), a successful lawyer, comes home to find his wife succumbing to a fatal illness, and she dies only a few hours later, but he is soon contacted by a woman claiming to be the same wife he just watched die.

page46.title: Mehbooba
page46.description: Mehbooba is a Bollywood romance film written, produced and directed by Afzal Khan. The story of the movie is based on a love-triangle, lead protagonists being Ajay Devgn, Sanjay Dutt and Manisha Koirala.

page46.title: Mai
page46.description: The children of an old woman (Asha Bhosle) who has Alzheimer's disease shuffle her back and forth until the eldest takes over her mother's care.

page46.title: Mahaadev
page46.description: An honest and upstanding Police Inspector resigns after he faces criticism from his corrupt colleagues.

page46.title: Maha Chor
page46.description: Neetu Singh's life is turned upside down when she is abducted only to be rescued by a man named Raju, who then claims to be the heir to the palace in which she lives.

page46.title: Kohinoor
page46.description: Kohinoor is a 1960 Bollywood film produced by Dr V. N. Sinha and directed by S U Sunny. The film stars Dilip Kumar, Meena Kumari, Leela Chitnis and Kumkum. The films music is by Naushad.

page47.title: Kishen Kanhaiya
page47.description: Twin brothers, Kanhaiya and Kishen, grow up in different classes of society until Kanhaiya rescues his unknown twin from his brutal stepmother.

page47.title: Khel Khel Mein
page47.description: A mysterious person follows three collegians after the murder of a jeweler.The story has been adapted from the English novel "Good children don't kill", written by Louis Thomas, the blind writer, and published in 1967.

page47.title: Kaun Kare Kurbanie
page47.description: Inspector Arjun Singh is assigned to a case involving the murders and sexual molestation of young girls, only to find that his son may be the prime suspect.

page47.title: Kasam
page47.description: In aid of seeking revenge for his dad's death, against a bandit called Kala Daku, Shankar team up with two men, a police inspector, Mangal and a run away convict, Vijay.

page47.title: Kartavya
page47.description: Karan and his mother live a happy life and he is soon to be married to Kajal. But on the day of his engagement, he discovers his mother is not his biological mother.

page47.title: Kaash Mere Hote
page47.description: A man is caught between one woman's love and another's obsession.

page48.title: Kaash
page48.description: Following a serious box office flop,producer Ritesh and his wife, Pooja are forced to downgrade to a simpler lifestyle. This leads to the husband becoming an alcoholic, and their young child being forced to watch as his parents' relationship disintegrates.

page48.title: Jaagruti
page48.description: Years after the brutal killing of his older brother, a man faces an uphill battle as he seeks vengeance for his brother's death.

page48.title: Indrajeet
page48.description: A police inspector (Amitabh Bachchan) must arrest the father of the woman he intends to marry.

page48.title: Hum To Mohabbat Karega
page48.description: A creative waiter tries to win an investigative journalist's heart by pretending to be a murder witness.

page48.title: Hum
page48.description: Three brothers (Amitabh Bachchan, Govinda, Rajnikant) with a troubled past fight against injustice.

page48.title: Hindustan Ki Kasam
page48.description: Twin brothers separated at birth find themselves on opposite ends of a rivalry based on country and religion.

page49.title: Hero Hiralal
page49.description: Hero Hiralal, a cabdriver, happens to meet an up-and-coming starlet. He becomes her tourist guide and they fall in love.

page49.title: Haseena Maan Jayegi
page49.description: A woman (Babita Kapoor) suspects that she is living not with her husband (Shashi Kapoor), but with his exact double.

page49.title: Good Luck
page49.description: A woman blessed with 'good luck' loses it by kissing a male, and must not only locate him but also kiss him in order to get it back.

page49.title: Ginny Aur Johnny
page49.description: Johny makes his living by conning people. Ginny enters his life and then nothing in the world can separate them from each other.The film is based on Hollywood movie Paper Moon.

page49.title: Gharwali Baharwali
page49.description: Married to a woman (Raveena Tandon) who cannot conceive, a man (Anil Kapoor) takes a second wife (Rambha) to father a child.The film is a remake of the Tamil film Thaikulame Thaikulame (1995) starring Pandiarajan.

page49.title: Geet Gaya Patharon Ne
page49.description: Not realizing she is his wife, a millionaire asks a woman to pose as a model for a statue.A 1964 drama film starring Jeetendra, V. Shantaram's daughter Rajshree in the lead roles which was first marked debut to both of them.

page50.title: Farz
page50.description: A gangster (Jackie Shroff) seeks revenge against the brave and reckless cop (Sunny Deol) who killed his brother.

page50.title: Faraar
page50.description: On the run from police after avenging his sister's murder, a fugitive (Amitabh Bachchan) takes a hostage who turns out to be the son of his former lover.

page50.title: Elaan
page50.description: A man (Rahul Khanna) assembles a team to capture the criminal (Mithun Chakraborty) who killed his adoptive father.

page50.title: Ek Mahal Ho Sapno Ka
page50.description: Vishal is a poet in love with Aruna, who works with a publishing company. She tries in vain to get him to work at her firm, then decides to marry her boss.

page50.title: Diljale
page50.description: Radhika is impressed with Shyam's patriotism. Her father gets Shyam's father arrested and killed, which makes them face a tough time.

page50.title: Dil Tera Diwana
page50.description: Mohan sends his friend Anokhe in his place when asked by his dad to go to an army officer's house to get disciplined.

page51.title: Dil Kabaddi
page51.description: Set in contemporary Mumbai, the movie takes a close look at the evolving equations among urban couples and paints the metamorphosis amongst the relationships with a comic stroke.

page51.title: Dhokha
page51.description: The film revolves around a moderate Indian Muslim cop, who wakes up and to his horror, discovers that his wife, who had recently been killed in a bomb blast, is accused of being a suicide bomber and had killed 20 people in the club.

page51.title: Daava
page51.description: A gangster causes a rift in a family of three brothers by framing the oldest for the murder of the youngest, agitating the relationship between the two survivors.

page51.title: Coolie
page51.description: When Iqbal was young he was separated from his mother and brother by a flood, and he becomes a coolie at Mumbai railway station. Coolies are at the bottom of the social ladder and treated badly by others, so Iqbal pledges to fight for Coolie rights.

page51.title: CLUB 60
page51.description: Though still grieving the death of his son, a doctor (Farooq Shaikh) joins a group of cheerful gym pals (Raghuvir Yadav, Satish Shah).

page51.title: Chor Machaaye Shor
page51.description: Vijay, an optimistic engineer, is in love with Rekha. However, Rekha's multimillionaire father does not approve, and before they can marry, Vijay finds himself on trial -- with Rekha as key witness for the prosecution.

page52.title: Brahmachari
page52.description: A man (Shammi Kapoor) who cares for orphans falls for a woman (Rajshree) rejected by a wealthy playboy (Pran).

page52.title: Babu
page52.description: Babu is a naive young man who likes to go out of his way to help people. He has fallen in love with Kammo, but in the process of helping another, he lands himself in jail for two years. A remake of 1971 Tamil movie of the same name.

page52.title: Anokhi Ada
page52.description: A ruthless gangster worms his way into the affections of a timber merchant.Anokhi Ada is a 1973 Bollywood Action film produced & directed by Kundan Kumar on Kundan Films banner.

page52.title: Andaz
page52.description: Tragedy strikes when a widower (Shammi Kapoor) falls in love with a widow (Hema Malini).Andaz is a 1971 Hindi romantic movie starring Shammi Kapoor, Hema Malini, Rajesh Khanna and Simi Garewal.

page52.title: Amar Deep
page52.description: An arrogant man, adopted son of a criminal don, begins to long for the daughter of his servant.

page52.title: Acid Factory
page52.description: A group of people wake up in an abandoned warehouse, battered and bruised and unaware as to why they are there at all.A remake of 2006 Hollywood thriller Unknown.

page53.title: Achha Bura
page53.description: Two people fall in love and decide to get married; the couple faces opposition from the man's parents, who demand a hefty dowry. Two truck drivers decide to help them and come up with a plan, but the plan is severely flawed.

page53.title: Aashirwad
page53.description: Shivnath Choudhary has a wealthy lifestyle in Chandanpur along with his wife, Leela, and 8-year-old daughter, Neena. He enjoys mingling with the poorer folk of the village -- much to his wife's annoyance.

page53.title: Aarzoo
page53.description: Pooja causes a love triangle filled with deceit and lies to form when she falls in love with Amar while she is engaged to Amar.

page53.title: Aansoo Aur Muskan
page53.description: Aansoo Aur Muskan is a 1970 Hindi film directed by P. Madhavan. The film stars Padmini and Bindu. The films playback music was sung by Mukesh. The memorable fun song "Guni Jano Bhakt Jano" was rendered by Kishore Kumar.

page53.title: Aan
page53.description: A dashing peasant (Dilip Kumar) sets out to melt the heart of an icy princess (Nadira) whose evil brother has seized power.

page53.title: Aaj Ka Arjun
page53.description: Powerful landlords Bhupendra and Ajit oppress a helpless community of villagers.It is a remake of 1988 Tamil film En Thangachi Padichava starring Prabhu Ganesan and Rupini.

page54.title: Mohenjo Daro
page54.description: In 2016 B.C., a farmer in the Indus Valley travels to a city and saves the life of a beautiful woman.

page54.title: 36 China Town
page54.description: When Sonia Chang (Isha Koppikar), a wealthy casino owner in Goa, India, is found dead in her luxurious home at 36 China Town, Chief Inspector Karan (Akshaye Khanna) investigates. A comedy-mystery-thriller!!

page54.title: Paying Guest
page54.description: After being evicted, an incompetent lawyer disguises himself to get a room, and falls in love with the landlord's daughter.

page54.title: Umrao Jaan
page54.description: An acclaimed courtesan and poet (Aishwarya Rai) dreams of love and marriage.J.P. Dutta's adaption of the Urdu novel "Umrao Jan Ada" by Mirza Haadi Ruswa (1905).

page54.title: Jab Harry Met Sejal
page54.description: A search for Sejal's engagement ring makes Harry understand love and relationships better, while Sejal experiences newfound freedom, security and solace in Harry's company.

page54.title: Guest Iin London
page54.description: Two Londoners struggle to live with their aunt and uncle, who overstay their welcome. A comedy entertainer!!

page55.title: Let's Talk
page55.description: A woman and her sister imagine various scenarios as they discuss revealing one's marital infidelity.(English) First ever Indian feature film that was shot in the digital format!!

page55.title: Sachin: A Billion Dreams
page55.description: A tale of a small boy with dreams and his journey to becoming the God of Cricket and the most celebrated sportsperson in his country. A docudrama-biographical film!!

page55.title: Bank Chor
page55.description: A comic-caper, that tells the story of 3 morons trying to rob a bank who pick the worst day possible when everything that can go wrong, goes wrong and how they're inadvertently caught in the crossfire.

page55.title: Baahubali 2: The Conclusion
page55.description: When Shiva, the son of Bahubali, learns about his heritage, he begins to look for answers. His story is juxtaposed with past events that unfolded in the Mahishmati Kingdom.(Hindi Dubbed Version)

page55.title: Raabta
page55.description: Shiv and Saira are drawn to each other like long lost lovers, mostly because they are. Their love dates back centuries, and the reason why they drifted apart, has drifted back into their lives.

page55.title: Sarkar 3
page55.description: The third film in Ram Gopal Varma's Sarkar trilogy, which chronicles the exploits of a powerful political figure.

page56.title: Hindi Medium
page56.description: A couple from Chandni Chowk aspire to give their daughter the best education and thus be a part of and accepted by the elite of Delhi.

page56.title: Wrong Number
page56.description: A group of friends love to prank-call random people from the phone book...until a chance connection leads to a serious entanglement.

page56.title: Chillar Party
page56.description: A gang of innocent but feisty kids who lead carefree lives in Chandan Nagar colony takes on the big bad world of politics when one of their friend's life is endangered.

page56.title: Dildaar
page56.description: A wealthy farmer's marriage to a city-born woman sparks chaos and drama. A remake of the 1975 film "Soggadu."

page56.title: Hanste Khelte
page56.description: Three friends who don't take their life seriously are suspended from college so they decide to take revenge on the principal. On reaching his house they find that someone has already killed him.

page56.title: Aag
page56.description: When Kewal is thrown out of the house for failing his law exams, he sets out to write the play of his dreams.

page57.title: Ustadon Ke Ustad
page57.description: Ustadon Ke Ustad is an Action flick, where Mithun plays the lead role, supported by Jackie Shroff.

page57.title: Dil Ne Phir Yaad Kiya
page57.description: A toy store salesman dreams of marrying a village-based girl whom he is in love with; when he goes to the village to meet her, he discovers that she is abducted.

page57.title: Trikon Ka Chautha Kon
page57.description: Manisha is in a live-in relationship with a married man Prakash. However, she does not want to break Prakash's marriage with Anuradha. Anuradha also finds her marriage unhappy. Prakash wants both, his marriage and relationship with Manisha.

page57.title: Duniya Na Mane
page57.description: Geeta lives a wealthy lifestyle with her father, Rattan. She falls in love with Raja, and their engagement is finalized. However, Rattan cancels the engagement at the last minute after meeting Raja's mother, Chanchal.

page57.title: Chal Mere Bhai
page57.description: Unknown to each other, two brothers (Sanjay Dutt, Salman Khan) become involved with the same woman (Karisma Kapoor).

page57.title: Bichhoo
page57.description: A small-time criminal (Bobby Deol) falls in love with the woman next door (Rani Mukherjee), and together they plot revenge for the murder of her family.

page58.title: Dil Ek Mandir
page58.description: The film was a remake of Tamil film, Nenjil Or Aalayam (1962).Dil Ek Mandir is a 1963 Hindi movie directed by C. V. Sridhar.

page58.title: Nadiya Ke Paar
page58.description: A family love triangle unfolds when one brother's wife dies in an accident.The movie is in the local language which is spoken at country side of Uttar Pradesh and Bihar.

page58.title: Naujawan
page58.description: Kamala Das is the daughter of Shobharam, a rich guy. Her friend Bimla also stays with her. Kamla's marriage gets fixed to Kishore and it was only for money and status symbol. To avoid this she tells that she is in love with a rich guy from Burma.

page58.title: Staying Alive
page58.description: Two strangers in a hospital grieve the possible deaths of their husbands, who both had heart attacks.

page58.title: Adhikar
page58.description: Vishal and Jyoti both spent their childhood in different manner from each other but they fall in love, and in spite of stiff oppositions from their parents they get married. After marriage, they have misunderstandings with each other frequently.

page58.title: Swades
page58.description: Living in America, a NASA engineer (Shah Rukh Khan) returns to India and reconnects with a childhood friend (Gayatri Joshi) and his former wet nurse.

page59.title: Suraj Ka Satvan Ghoda
page59.description: Young writer Manek Mulla recounts the story of three very different women to an enthusiastic group of friends; the three-in-one story of the poor villager, the intellectual, and the middle class wife unfolds in flashback.

page59.title: Tejaa
page59.description: A man (Sanjay Dutt) seeks revenge against three thieves (Ranjeet, Puneet Issar) who killed his family 20 years earlier.

page59.title: Tumsa Nahin Dekha: A Love Story
page59.description: Daksh, is a complete spoilt brat of a rich father, leads a life full of pleasure.On a rainy day, he sees a girl, called Jiya standing at a bus stop. He finds the girl too beautiful and kisses her.

page59.title: Uvaa
page59.description: Worried about their future, five wayward teens from remote villages in UP are enrolled in an English medium school in Faridabad by their respective families in order to reform them. But can the youngsters adapt to their new posh surroundings?

page59.title: Vachan
page59.description: Vachan is a 1955 Indian Bollywood film directed by Raj Rishi and produced by Devendra Goel. The film stars Geeta Bali, Rajendra Kumar and Balraj in lead roles. The film marked the debut of composer Ravi.

page59.title: Waqt Hamara Hai
page59.description: Former rivals Vikas Sabkuchwala and Sunil are now friends and in love with sisters Ayesha and Mamta Vidrohi.

page60.title: The Dirty Relation
page60.description: A husband who cannot keep his wife happy, a wife who is unhappy with her husband, a guy who loves someone else's wife in spite of being engaged to a girl, the film is a story of entangled, illicit relations. These relations land all of them in trouble.

page60.title: Zulm Ki Hukumat
page60.description: A father and two sons cross an underworld don who launches a vendetta against them.

page60.title: Zakhmee
page60.description: The story revolves around 3 brothers – Anand, Amar, and Pawan. Just when Anand is to tie the knot with Asha, news of his business partner being murdered comes through, leading to his incarceration.

page60.title: Ab... Bas
page60.description: Soumya is a former beauty queen who shies away from marriage and thinks guys are not to be taken seriously. In comes Karan whose attitude and respect for women has Soumya floored in no time. The inevitable happens and the two get married.

page60.title: Aksar
page60.description: Complications arise when a business tycoon (Dino Morea) asks a fashion photographer (Emraan Hashmi) to seduce his wife (Udita Goswami).

page60.title: Anaarkali Of Aarah
page60.description: A village dancer is harassed by a local politician and is ridiculed by the police, but ends up plotting revenge to clear her name.

page61.title: Allah Rakha
page61.description: A gangster's driver takes the fall for an accident, leaving his wife and child destitute. "Allah-Rakha" was Ketan Desai's directorial debut.

page61.title: Do Ankhen Barah Haath
page61.description: Progressive, reform-minded young warden gets permission to take six surly murderers from prison to dilapidated country farm, to rehabilitate it and themselves through hard work and kindly guidance.

page61.title: Ek Bar Mooskura Do
page61.description: A man and a woman are in love with each other and dream of living together, but her father puts an obstacle in their path.

page61.title: Insaaf Ki Awaaz
page61.description: Jhansi Rani is an honest police officer and her husband is an honest man who works in a factory. Mahendranath and Kailashnath are two wicked men. Chandra Shekhar is killed by these two wicked people and they play a cat and mouse game with Jhansi.

page61.title: Shaitan
page61.description: Five substance-abusing friends decide to fake a kidnapping in order to bribe a police constable for covering-up a hit-and-run accident.

page61.title: Gopi Kishan
