page61.description: Kishan (Sunil Shetty) is a hardened criminal who is in search of his father, after knowing that his father is still alive. Suraj Malhotra (Suresh Oberoi), a dreaded gangster, is supposedly the father of Kishan, whom Kishen wants to avenge for deserting his mother.

page62.title: Hattrick
page62.description: The 2007 Cricket World Cup serves as the backdrop for a collection of stories.Hattrick is a story about five people: Madhav Anna, Dr Satyajeet Chavan, Hemu Patel and newlyweds Saby and Kashmira.

page62.title: Daal Mein Kuch Kaala Hai
page62.description: The ambition of a budding actress (Veena Malik) to become a star attracts the attention of a newly rich man.

page62.title: Koshish
page62.description: The movie depicts a deaf and mute couple and their conflicts, pain and struggles to carve out a niche for themselves in a desensitized society.

page62.title: Mera Pehla Pehla Pyaar
page62.description: Rohan is the dreamboat and bad boy. Ayesha is the sweet and well-behaved girl. The mismatched pair fall head over heels in love. In spite of jealousy and arguments split them apart, Rohan proposes marriage to the love of his life at the Eiffel Tower.

page62.title: Mirch
page62.description: A story-writer attempts to convince a producer to accept four erotic stories from the Panchtantra.

page62.title: Phir Janam Lenge Hum
page62.description: The film Phir Janam Lenge Hum released in the year 1977. It is directed by Mehul Kumar. The story revolves around a boy who saves a girl from committing suicide. The story takes a turn when they both fall in love with each other.

page63.title: Pyar Ki Pyas
page63.description: Geeta a five-year-old orphan gets adopted by a wealthy couple believes them to be her missing birth parents and moves in with them in their palatial house.  But when her step mom gives birth, Geeta is traumatized by abuse and neglect.

page63.title: Janwar
page63.description: A wealthy man tries to prevent his son (Shammi Kapoor) from marrying the daughter (Rajshree) of one of his employees.

page63.title: Kabuliwala
page63.description: A poor Afghani leaves his family behind to earn a living as a dried fruit vendor in India. Profoundly homesick, he befriends a young girl who reminds him of his own daughter. Meanwhile, the locals are distrustful of all foreigners.

page63.title: Red Rose
page63.description: A wealthy exporter falls in love with a shop clerk, but their married bliss is threatened by a secret from his past.

page63.title: Meenaxi: A Tale Of Three Cities
page63.description: Delving into the limitless world of creative endeavors, and vicissitudes in the way of such endeavors, this tale of an artist and his muse, like a painting, leaves itself open to interpretations and readings by every viewer...

page63.title: Dushman
page63.description: A woman must overcome her inner weakness to take revenge on the crazed killer who raped and murdered her twin sister.

page64.title: Swayamvar
page64.description: Durgadevi rules her household with her brother, Makhanlan, and treats daughter Shanti worse than she treats servants; her other daughter is Roopa. When the younger women are approached for marriage, Durgadevi refuses.

page64.title: Tere Mere Sapne
page64.description: The story is based on The Citadel, a novel by A.J. Cronin. In 1972 it was made as Bengali film Jiban Saikate with Soumitra Chatterjee and Aparna Sen and in 1982, it was remade into the Telugu film Madhura Swapnam.

page64.title: Toofan
page64.description: A man (Amitabh Bachchan) who helps the poor tries to prove his father is innocent of stealing gold.

page64.title: Soundtrack
page64.description: Loud music, substance and alcohol abuse wreck the life and career of a talented music DJ, but Gauri helps him overcome his difficulties. An official remake of the Canadian independent film It's All Gone Pete Tong.

page64.title: Manorama Six Feet Under
page64.description: An amateur detective in a small sleepy town from Rajasthan finds himself caught in a web of lies, deceit and murder.Based on Chinatown (1974) by Roman Polanski. A neo-noir thriller movie!!

page64.title: Mirch Masala
page64.description: Set in rustic rural India, Mirch Masala is the story of emancipation from colonial tyranny.  Forbes included Smita Patil's performance in the film on its list, 25 Greatest Acting Performances of Indian Cinema.

page65.title: A Wednesday
page65.description: A retired police commissioner recounts the most memorable case of his career, wherein he was informed about a bomb scare in Mumbai.

page65.title: Debshishu
page65.description: This powerful and realistic film is a study of poverty, illiteracy, natural calamities and the toll they take on the human soul

page65.title: Apne Paraye
page65.description: This is a story of two lawyer brothers, their half brother, their wives and children. Apne Paraye is a 1980 Indian Bollywood film directed by Basu Chatterjee and produced by Mushir Alam. It stars Amol Palekar and Shabana Azmi in pivotal roles.

page65.title: Half Ticket
page65.description: A diamond thief hides his loot on an innocent child, but the child turns out to be an adult posing as a youngster to purchase a half-priced train ticket. Now, the thief will have to outwit the eccentric in a series of wacky misadventures.

page65.title: Bhai Bahan
page65.description: A tangled epic of misplaced loyalties and self-sacrifice starring Ashok Kumar Ganguly, Nutan Samarth, Sunil Dutt.

page65.title: Kama Sutra: A Tale of Love

page66.title: Yeh Lamhe Judaai Ke
page66.description: A successful singer (Shahrukh Khan) and his childhood friends become entangled in deception and treachery.A 2004 Bollywood romance mystery film directed by Birendra Nath Tiwari.

page66.title: Meri Pyaari Bindu
page66.description: Favorite songs, past memories and an ex-girlfriend inspire a successful writer to pen an old-fashioned love story.

page66.title: Phillauri
page66.description: A young man, Kanan, ties the knot with a tree, in order to get rid of a curse which might affect his married life. But, by marrying the tree, he also marries the spirit that haunts it.

page66.title: Naam Shabana
page66.description: This Spin-off from Baby (2015) provides the back-story of intelligence agent Shabana and chronicles how she becomes a spy.

page66.title: Noor
page66.description: Noor is a journalist who juggles her work, love and personal life on a day-to-day basis. One day, Noor's life takes a dramatic turn when she comes across an eye-opening investigative news story.

page66.title: Trapped
page66.description: ​ Shaurya must pluck up the courage to stay alive after he accidentally locks himself up in his new rented apartment in a desolate Mumbai high-rise, for almost a week. A survival drama film directed by Vikramaditya Motwane.

page67.title: X: Past Is Present
page67.description: A filmmaker with a mid-life crisis meets a mysterious young girl who reminds of every woman in his past.

page67.title: Jallaad
page67.description: An unscrupulous politician collaborates with an 'illiterate' and simple man to win an election.The film was the remake of Tamil film Amaithipadai starring Satyaraj.

page67.title: Khelein Hum Jee Jaan Sey
page67.description: Children who are not allowed by the oppressive British colonists to play football decide to join a group of freedom fighters.

page67.title: Pappu Can't Dance Saala
page67.description: The film revolves around a man Vidyadhar Acharya, who moves to Mumbai from Varanasi, and finds it difficult to adjust to a place away from his city that’s rich with cultural heritage. A rom-com entertainer!!

page67.title: Paraya Ghar
page67.description: A young, engaged couple meet with an accident, leading to a series of complex situations that change their lives forever. Will they be able to overcome their situation, to finally be married?

page67.title: Sabki Bajegi Band
page67.description: An aspiring filmmaker requests his group of friends to go on camera and answer some personal questions — mostly about their sex life, which he intends to compile and turn into a full-fledged film. *MATURE CONTENT*

page68.title: Bhouri
page68.description: A tragic love story of Bhouri, a 23-year old who is married to a 55-year old, the film highlights the exploitation of women in male dominated society.

page68.title: Army
page68.description: Newly-wed Arjun, an army man, is brutally killed by gangster Nagraj. His wife, determined to avenge her husband, raises an army of dedicated young men to kill the gangster.

page68.title: Rangoon
page68.description: In 1943, an Army spy, Malik, who is on a mission, falls in love with an actress Julia. However, Malik's mission is jeopardized when Julia's fiance, Rusi, finds out about their affair, while Malik reveals his identity in front of the opposite army.

page68.title: Dangal
page68.description: Dangal is an extraordinary true story based on the life of Mahavir Singh and his two daughters, Geeta and Babita Phogat. The film traces the inspirational journey of a father who trains his daughters to become world class wrestlers.

page68.title: Rock On 2
page68.description: Adi, the lead singer of the rock band 'Magik', quits music and shifts his base to Meghalaya after an incident that leaves him guilt-ridden for years. However, he finds himself confronting his past, which eventually leads him to make music again.

page68.title: Humko Deewana Kar Gaye
page68.description: Aditya, an engineer, travels to Canada for training. There he meets Jia, a beautiful woman from an influential family. Fate keeps pushing the pair together, and even though both are already betrothed to others, Adi and Jia fall in love.

page69.title: Humshakals
page69.description: Three sets of look-alike friends cause much confusion to those around them and it leads to a comedy of errors.

page69.title: Water
page69.description: Water is a dark introspect into the tales of rural Indian widows in the 1940s and covers controversial subjects such as misogyny and ostracism.

page69.title: Tamasha
page69.description: A man (Ranbir Kapoor) falls in love with a woman (Deepika Padukone) after spending one week with her on the French island of Corsica.

page69.title: Rock On
page69.description: Aditya, Joe, Kedar and Rob form a band and break up after they cannot make it. They establish regular lives until they decide to reunite and take another shot at fulfilling their dreams.

page69.title: Badrinath Ki Dulhania
page69.description: Badrinath Bansal from Jhansi and Vaidehi Trivedi from Kota belong to small towns but have diametrically opposite opinions on everything. This leads to a clash of ideologies, despite both of them recognizing the goodness in each other.

page69.title: Dukhtar
page69.description: It is the story of a mother and her ten-year-old daughter, who leave their home to save the girl from an arranged marriage to a tribal leader. It was selected as Pakistan's Official entry in the category Best Foreign Language Film for the 87th Academy Awards.

page70.title: Bal Ganesh 3
page70.description: The popular film franchise , Bal Ganesh is back again with 3 times more fun and adventure. In this 3rd installment the exploits of Bal Ganesh have spread beyond the planet Earth to other planets in the Universe.

page70.title: I Am
page70.description: I Am is a 2011 Indian anthology film by Onir. It consists of four short films: "Omar", "Afia", "Abhimanyu", and "Megha". Each film shares the common theme of fear, and each film is based on real-life stories.

page70.title: Sachaai
page70.description: Long-separated friends meet after several years, each unaware that one is a criminal and one is a police inspector.

page70.title: Mangalsutra
page70.description: Mangalsutra is the story of a woman and her husband's life. Vijay (Anang Nag) and Gayatri (Rekha) are deeply in love with each other and their parents are family friends related to each other. Soon very strange things started happening in Vijay's life!!

page70.title: Luck
page70.description: An underworld kingpin recruits people endowed with 'Luck' from across the globe to take part in a series of challenges designed to test their 'Luck' factor, as gamblers around the world bet on them.

page70.title: Jai Veeru
page70.description: A con-man befriends a stranger at a bar when he comes to his rescue in a brawl. As they grow to be inseparable friends, the con-man is left dumbstruck when his friend reveals his true identity.

page71.title: Vaada Raha... I Promise
page71.description: Duke is abandoned by his friends after an accident, then a young boy brings hope back into his life.

page71.title: Love in Tokyo
page71.description: An orphan meets a runaway (Asha Parekh) who wants to escape from an arranged marriage. Love in Tokyo is a part of Joy Mukherjee's "Love in trilogy" -  Love in Simla(1960), Love in Tokyo(1966) and Love in Bombay(2013), though made in 1971.

page71.title: Khoon Bhari Maang
page71.description: A man marries a rich widow for her money and tries to murder her but she survives, gets a new face due to plastic surgery and returns for revenge.

page71.title: Hamesha
page71.description: Yash falls in love with his childhood friend, Raja. When Raja falls in love with Rani, Yash kills him. When Raja hears about this, she jumps to her own death leaving Yash heartbroken.

page71.title: Drona
page71.description: Aditya is an orphaned and lonely young man. He soon learns that he belongs to a family of ancestral warriors who guard a mystic source of cosmic energy, and he must now take up his responsibilities.

page71.title: Dil Kya Kare
page71.description: A mysterious woman (Kajol) enters the lives of a married couple (Ajay Devgan, Mahima Chaudhry) with an adopted child.

page72.title: Aap Ki Khatir
page72.description: Anu, a London-based NRI who is living in India with her boyfriend Danny ditched her at the altar. Now, she has come back to London to be a part of her sister Shirani’s marriage, to Kunal Shah, who is also Danny's best friend.

page72.title: Charas
page72.description: A smuggler's former friend betrays him by helping the police bust his crime ring.

page72.title: Josh
page72.description: Two gangs fight for control of the streets: the Scorpions, led by Prakash, and the Eagles, fronted by Max. When Prakash's brother Rahul  comes to visit, he meets and quickly falls in love with Shirley, not realizing she's the sister of his brother's rival, Max.

page72.title: Pyaar Ke Side Effects
page72.description: Scared of commitment, a disc jockey (Rahul Bose) receives a wedding proposal from his longtime girlfriend (Mallika Sherawat).

page72.title: Life Partner
page72.description: An experienced divorce attorney (Govinda) tries to warn his friends about the pitfalls of marriage before they tie the knot.

page72.title: Guddu
page72.description: A car accident changes the lives of a young woman (Manisha Koirala), her boyfriend (Shahrukh Khan) and their parents.

page73.title: Irada
page73.description: An NIA officer tries to unravel the conspiracy that led to the bombing of a business tycoon's factory. A drama thriller!

page73.title: Kaabil
page73.description: This is the story of a man who lived, laughed and loved just like everyone in this world. Until one day, a terrible tragedy struck. Driven by the fire of vengeance, nothing will stop him. Not even the fact that he has been blind since birth.

page73.title: Waqt
page73.description: Members of a family are separated in a natural disaster. Several years down the line, they aren't united but their lives are strangely interconnected.

page73.title: Commando 2
page73.description: Commando Karanveer Singh Dogra, is skilled in many aspects of survival, weaponry, and hand-to-hand combat. He is on a mission to eradicate black money, which has been siphoned to banks abroad.

page73.title: Armaan
page73.description: A doctor (Anil Kapoor) reluctantly agrees to marry a tycoon's daughter (Preity Zinta) to receive funding for a small hospital.

page73.title: Zameer
page73.description: A young man (Amitabh Bachchan) claims to be a horse breeder's (Shammi Kapoor) long-lost son, but all is not as it seems.

page74.title: Trishul
page74.description: An engineer visiting a town has a brief affair with a local girl and walks off, leaving her with a child. The son grows up to avenge his deserted mother. Vijay (Bachchan) is the angry young man playing the son. Sanjeev Kumar plays the father.

page74.title: Yaraana
page74.description: Lalita escapes her loveless, abusive marriage and starts her life over again with a new identity.A remake of the American film Sleeping with the Enemy.

page74.title: Viruddh... Family Comes First
page74.description: An ordinary 60 plus couple - Vidhyadhar Patwardhan and his wife are forced to search for their faith in human values and society after the death of their only son Amar. In the process, they undergo the most testing struggle of their lives.

page74.title: Ziddi
page74.description: The story revolves around a stubborn & hot-tempered young man, Deva, who ends up in jail after thrashing a man for molesting his sister, Guddi. Post his release, he is astonished to learn that his family disapproves of him.

page74.title: Tahkhana
page74.description: A dying Thakur Surjeet Singh bequeaths the entire estate to his son, Raghuvir, disowning the other, Dhurjan, the family's black sheep, who also indulges in black magic.

page74.title: Tere Naal Love Ho Gaya
page74.description: It is an endearing tale of how unusual circumstances bring people together and change their lives forever. A free-spirited tomboy instantly wins your heart with her bubbly personality and charming giggles.

page75.title: Adi Shankaracharya
page75.description: The first and only Indian movie to be made in Sanskrit. The movie follows the life and times of Sankara - the founder of the non-duality (Advaita) school of Indian philosophy.(Hindi Dubbed version)

page75.title: Ta Ra Rum Pum
page75.description: Ace car racer RV and his wife have the world at their feet. But he has an accident and his world is turned upside down. Can he reclaim his lost glory?

page75.title: Swami Dada
page75.description: Swami Dada is the story of Hari Mohan, a saintly person who organizes prayers and discourses in a warm and welcoming atmosphere. He is called "Swami Dada" by everyone.

page75.title: Ram Tera Desh
page75.description: Ramdas, his wife, Savitri, son, Prakash, and daughter, Sunita, live a lower middle-class existence in Bombay. They would like to get Sunita get married, and soon receive a proposal through Champabai for her to be married to Prem Kumar Saxena.

page75.title: Sooryavansham
page75.description: A man (Amitabh Bachchan) marries a woman in defiance of his father's wishes, then must struggle alone to make a living.It is the Hindi remake of the Tamil film Suryavamsam (1997).

page75.title: Race
page75.description: Destiny makes two brothers- Ranvir and Rajiv - enemies of each other. Everything is fair in love and war. Race explores themes of sibling rivalry, betrayal, and passion.It is the first installment of Race film series.

page76.title: Rocket Singh: Salesman of the Year
page76.description: A story of a fresh graduate trying to find a balance between the maddening demands of the 'professional' way, and the way of his heart.

page76.title: Kaalapani
page76.description: Govardhan, a doctor by profession, is wrongly accused of bombing a train and is jailed by the British in Cellular Jail, also known as Kala Pani, in the Andaman and Nicobar Islands. He witnesses the sufferings of hundreds of Indian prisoners there.

page76.title: Shaktiman
page76.description: Businessman Laxmi Narayan lives a wealthy lifestyle in Bombay along with his wife, Lakshmi. Although they have been married for several years, they have no children. While on a trip to Simla, they get to adopt their servant's son, re-name him, Vicky.

page76.title: Prem
page76.description: Sanjay Verma is an eligible young man, who has been having hallucinations of a past life as Shantanu. He travels to a small community and meets with Sonia Verma, and recognizes her as the girl named Lachi in his hallucinations.

page76.title: Prahaar: The Final Attack
page76.description: Peter D'Souza wants to join the Indian Army. His father John D'Souza  wants Peter to run their bakery after him, his fiancée Shirley wants him to marry her while his neighbor Kiran  tells Peter to follow his heart.

page76.title: Purani Haveli
page76.description: A rich family eagerly buys an abandoned mansion in a rural area, but later discover that the mansion has a very disturbing and horrifying past.

page77.title: My Friend Ganesha 2
page77.description: Vashu is a lonely boy. Gangutai introduces him to Ganesha. Vashu and Ganesha embark on exciting adventures.

page77.title: Pyaasa
page77.description: A talented but indigent poet Vijay struggles for love and recognition in this selfish world.

page77.title: Lootmaar
page77.description: Indian Air Force pilot Bhagat lives with his wife, Raksha and a young son. While going to the bank one day, the family find that the bank is being held up. The bank-robbers panic at the arrival of the police, and fire randomly killing Raksha instantly.

page77.title: Mashaal
page77.description: A chain of events changes Raja's life - from black marketer to journalist to an underworld Don and a Racketeer in order to combat Vardhan.

page77.title: Luv Ka The End
page77.description: Rhea, the girl next door falls in love with Luv Nanda, only to find out he is not as nice as she thought he was. She decides to get even with Luv Nanda.

page77.title: Mahakaal
page77.description: A demon torments the family and friends of Anita in order to take revenge on his death, which was caused by her police-officer father.

page78.title: Kick
page78.description: An adrenaline junkie walks away from a whirlwind romance and embraces a new life as a thief, though he soon finds himself pursued by veteran police officer and engaged in a turf war with a local gangster.

page78.title: Jolly LLB 2
page78.description: Inspired by true events that have happened in India, the sequel to the national award-winning film Jolly LLB will see Jolly take up a huge case where he will fight against the corrupt and the powerful.

page78.title: Raees
page78.description: A determined police officer (Nawazuddin Siddiqui) threatens to destroy a crime lord's (Shah Rukh Khan) powerful empire in Gujarat, India.

page78.title: Mumbai Meri Jaan
page78.description: `Mumbai Meri Jaan` deals with the unpleasant and gloomy days post the serial bomb blasts of 2006 that ripped through the city of dreams.Five people whose lives are affected by the 2006 Mumbai train bombings.

page78.title: The Legend of Bhagat Singh
page78.description: Jailed for a bombing, the freedom fighter (Ajay Devgan) organizes protests and a hunger strike before British officials hang him at age 23.

page78.title: Kareeb
page78.description: Birju is a young man from an upper-middle-class family in Himachal Pradesh. His father insists on him being responsible, while Birju is interested in petty theft, lies, and romancing a beautiful young woman named Neha.

page79.title: Kal Kissne Dekha
page79.description: Nihal from Chandigarh lands in the cosmopolitan city of Mumbai to realize his dreams. Seeing his genius, the professor of his college takes him under his tutelage. But a series of visions help him to realise that he can actually see the future.

page79.title: Kissi Se Na Kehna
page79.description: Kailashnath is a widower and father of Ramesh. He feels that his son has come of age and must get married. He goes to see a number of young ladies for him but is disappointed with them as he feels they are too modern.

page79.title: Lakhon Mein Ek
page79.description: An abused homeless male and a mentally-challenged woman become friends.This film was based on a very sensitive topic of Hindu-Muslim love story. The film was a remake of 1968 Tamil film Ethir Neechal.

page79.title: Kabhi Haan Kabhi Naa
page79.description: A man (Shah Rukh Khan) belongs to a middle-class family and is intent on pursuing his career with a music group, despite his dad's disapproval. He is also in love with the lead singer (Suchitra Krishnamoorthi), but she sees him mainly as a friend.

page79.title: Fashion
page79.description: A small-town girl finally realizes her dream of becoming a famous supermodel but soon finds out that there's a price for her glamorous new life.

page79.title: Issaq
page79.description: A contemporary adaptation of Romeo and Juliet set in the backdrop of Varanasi in the UP heartland, complete with naxalism, sand mining mafia and of course the timeless love story.

page80.title: Dostana
page80.description: Vijay, a police officer, and Ravi, a lawyer are best friends who do not question each other about their careers. One day both Vijay and Ravi meet Sheetal at different places and times, and both fall in love with her.

page80.title: Gunga Jumna
page80.description: The film is about two brothers, Ganga and Jamuna, growing up in a village controlled by an evil landlord. When Ganga joins a band of bandits, his younger brother, Jamuna, is sent to the city for his education and becomes a police officer.

page80.title: Ek Ajnabee
page80.description: A remake of Tony Scott's 2004 film Man on Fire.Colonel Surya Singh is a bitter man and ex-Army officer, hired by his friend Captain Shekhar Verma to protect a little girl, Anamika, who resides in Bangkok, Thailand with her family.

page80.title: Darna Mana Hai
page80.description: Seven friends, after their car breaks down in the middle of the night, find shelter and tell one another stories to kill time till dawn.

page80.title: Chameli
page80.description: On a rainy night, when an investment banker's car breaks down in the red light district, he takes shelter where he meets and later befriends a prostitute.

page80.title: Cheeni Kum
page80.description: An egotistical 64-year-old chef and confirmed bachelor fall for a woman 30 years his junior.

page81.title: Dil Maange More
page81.description: Dil Maange More!!! is the story of Nikhil Mathur’s quest for true love. His passions are his village Samarpur and football. He is desperate to fall in love with one woman but ends up with three women in his arms ready to swear undying love for him.

page81.title: Dharm Adhikari
page81.description: Dharamraj, known as an honest and ethical man, has to distance himself from his family after being accused of having an extramarital affair.

page81.title: Apna Sapna Money Money
page81.description: Alvarez House in Bombay is a quiet lodging place, until it is suddenly filled with eccentric characters who wreak havoc in the neighborhood.

page81.title: Apne
page81.description: A disgraced ex-boxer attempts to make his two sons champion boxers in order to clear his name. One son agrees with this goal, but the other does not, causing family conflicts.

page81.title: Balwaan
page81.description: Arjun Singh comes from a very poor family. He lives in a small and shabby tenement with his mom and sister. Despite his circumstance, he is honest and helpful. This puts him into conflict with Bhai, a notorious gangster.

page81.title: Angaaray
page81.description: A police inspector (Akshay Kumar) learns that his childhood friends are working for a criminal and goes under cover to bring the crook to justice.

page82.title: Bandh Darwaza
page82.description: The movie story is about Neola, a Dracula-like vampire he sleeps in a coffin by day, and transforms into a bat at night to hunt humans from the neighboring villages. He craves a steady supply of human blood, and a supply of fresh young women.

page82.title: The Ghazi Attack
page82.description: In 1971, a submarine called the PNS Ghazi ventured into Indian waters with the ambition of destroying the INS Vikrant. What stopped them? The heroes aboard the Indian submarine S-21. It's the war you did not know about. A war-thriller!!

page82.title: Baar Baar Dekho
page82.description: A love-story, which unfolds through flash-backs and flash-forwards.What would you do if you could see the future of your relationship? Jump on this roller coaster ride with Jai and Diya as they ride the ups and down of their relationship.

page82.title: Ankhen
page82.description: Shortly after independence, India faces terrorist attacks in Assam, resulting in many deaths and casualties. A group of concerned citizens, who are not connected with the government, decide to do something to stop this carnage. A spy thriller!!

page82.title: Yeh Jawaani Hai Deewani
page82.description: It is the story of the relationship between Bunny  & Naina, at two separate but defining times in their lives, first when they are just out of college and standing on the crossroads of multiple decisions that will shape who and what they become.

page82.title: Parched
page82.description: In the arid landscape of Rajasthan, four women navigate their way through personal and cultural difficulties.What happens when you break free? *MATURE CONTENT*

page83.title: Kyaa Kool Hain Hum 3
page83.description: A porn actor uses his fellow adult movie stars in creating a fake traditional family, in order to impress his girlfriend's conservative father.An Adult Entertainer!!

page83.title: Ekkees Toppon Ki Salaami
page83.description: Joshi, an honest man, who has two sons who are good for nothing. Fate puts Joshi in a tough spot, where all his life`s work goes down the drain, and in his near-death condition, he was but one wish, that he gets honored with 21 guns.

page83.title: Buddha in a Traffic Jam
page83.description: Vikram Pandit(Arunoday), is a management student who believes that correct ideology can help to create a world of equals. His noble ideas land him in the Naxal radar, inviting trouble from all quarters.

page83.title: Running Shaadi
page83.description: Two friends, Ram Bharose and tech genius Cyberjeet, create a website that helps lovers to elope. The site is an instant hit; young couples line up for the opportunity to escape strict families and run away with the ones they love.

page83.title: Satyagraha (Bluray)
page83.description: A corporate go-getter sees his priorities shift when a personal tragedy brings him face-to-face with political corruption.

page83.title: Mirzya
page83.description: Inspired by the folk tale of "the legend of Mirza Sahiban", MIRZYA is an epic action romance set in contemporary times.A horse groom reconnects with his childhood love, but she is engaged to marry the local prince.

page84.title: Force 2
page84.description: Force 2, brings back ACP Yashvardhan who teams up RAW Agent KK to bring down a master mind terrorist Shiv. The sequel directed by Abhinay Deo promises to pack in as much action as possible in this highly awaited action film

page84.title: Kahaani 2: Durga Rani Singh
page84.description: The story revolves around Vidya Sinha (Vidya Balan) and her daughter Mini who live peacefully in the sleepy town of Chandan Nagore. Things take a dramtic turn when Sinha (Balan) has an accident and enters Arjun Rampal, the cop.

page84.title: Ajanabee 1974
page84.description: Middle-classed Rohit Kumar Saxena falls in love with wealthy and lovely Reshmi, and both decide to get married. Reshmi's dad, the wealthy Diwan Sardarilal is strongly opposed to this marriage but relents when Reshmi refuses to marry anyone else.

page84.title: Muqabla
page84.description: Brothers Suraj and Deepak re-locate to the city and join the police force where their two different positions and experiences drive them apart.

page84.title: Charas
page84.description: A police officer gets embroiled in a deadly game with drug mafia, while searching for his long lost friend from London.

page84.title: Border
page84.description: Soldiers come together on the eve of war and tell one another about their families and lives. An adaptation from real life events that happened at the Battle of Longewala in the year 1971.

page85.title: Barsaat
page85.description: Badal comes from a rural village to take an enrollment into a college in the city. He meets his fellow collegian, Tina Oberoi and both gets acquainted with each other

page85.title: Agneepath
page85.description: A young boy's quest for revenge leads him to become a gangster as an adult, and with each day he becomes more and more like his enemies. Can he find vengeance and redemption?

page85.title: Love in Goa
page85.description: Teenage love story of a Catholic girl from Goa and a Hindu boy.

page85.title: Haan Maine Bhi Pyaar Kiya
page85.description: Friends (Karisma Kapoor, Akshay Kumar, Abhishek Bachchan) develop a love triangle and interpret the meaning of their relationships differently.

page85.title: Gang
page85.description: Four boys from different backgrounds form a street gang called GANG, but things fall apart when one of them is arrested, and they all decide to leave the world of crime.

page85.title: English Babu Desi Mem
page85.description: A wealthy businessman (Shahrukh Khan) travels to India to meet his brother's son (Sunny Singh).

page86.title: Daulat Ki Jung
page86.description: Rajesh and Asha, the children of business rivals, study at the same college and fall in love; when their parents forbid them to see each other, they elope.

page86.title: Daud
page86.description: Two runaways are chased by cops and robbers who think that they have real gold.

page86.title: Dastak
page86.description: A police inspector (Mukul Dev) must protect Miss Universe (Sushmita Sen) from a dangerously unstable fan (Sharad Kapoor)

page86.title: Besharam
page86.description: In order to prevent honest Ramchandra from being elected as Mayor, Digvijay Singh alias Dharamdas sets his men upon him, his son, Ram Kumar, and his wife, all in vain, as Ramchandra wins.

page86.title: Abhay
page86.description: A psychopath believes his twin brother has married an evil woman and escapes from the hospital to hunt her down.

page86.title: Aatish: Feel the Fire
page86.description: Two brothers lead different lives, one as a criminal and the other as a policeman, until a murder plot forces them to reunite to take down a killer.

page87.title: Kyun! Ho Gaya Na
page87.description: A woman decides to marry her childhood friend, after getting her heart broken by her sweetheart.

page87.title: Khalnayak
page87.description: The movie follows the reckless chase of villain. Ballu Balram, a young terrorist who escaped from the jail, causing distress and anguish for his jailor, Ram. Ram's fiancee Ganga in order to help him join Ballu's gang to lure him back into custody.

page87.title: Ilzaam
page87.description: Orphaned and poor Ajay (Govinda) meets with wealthy Aarti (Neelam), and both fall in love. Their hopes to marry are dashed to the ground, when Aarti's dad, Dhanraj (Prem Chopra), opposes Ajay and Aarti's marriage until he gets wealthy.

page87.title: Gunaah
page87.description: A police inspector (Bipasha Basu) tries to find out why a compassionate murder suspect (Dino Morea) would kill a noted industrialist.

page87.title: Naukar Biwi Ka
page87.description: The movie story deals with Inspector Amar Nath who apprehends and arrests a notorious gangster who goes by different aliases, and gets him sentenced to prison for several years.

page87.title: Mother India
page87.description: In this melodrama, a poverty-stricken woman raises her sons through many trials and tribulations. But no matter the struggles, always sticks to her own moral code.

page88.title: M Cream
page88.description: A motley crew of university students set out on a journey in pursuit of a mythical form of hash, confronting a series of encounters that begin to unravel the myriad realities of rebellion.

page88.title: Lal Baadshah
page88.description: Lal Singh, a man who lives for others, believes that every person lives for himself but this man helps others. Lal Singh lives alongside his foster mother in a small basti in Mumbai, Lal grew up with poor and needy persons in the same basti.

page88.title: Shikari
page88.description: In order to take revenge for the death of his family at the hands of multi-millionaire Virendra Singh Rawal; Om Srivastav escapes from jail, with the help of a mask assumes the identity of a man called Mahendra Pratap Singh and travels to South Africa

page88.title: Roop Ki Rani Choron Ka Raja
page88.description: Friends (Anil Kapoor, Sridevi) from an orphanage meet as adults and look for the man (Anupam Kher) who killed their fathers.

page88.title: Ram Aur Shyam
page88.description: A rich man (Dilip Kumar) suffers beatings from his brother-in-law to spare other family members.

page88.title: Zamaana Deewana
page88.description: A police commissioner enlists the aid of an eccentric inspector to end a gang war between bitter enemies.

page89.title: Woodstock Villa
page89.description: A businessman is distraught after refusing to follow the instructions of his wife's kidnapper.

page89.title: Watan Ke Rakhwale
page89.description: A secret agent (Dharmendra) tracks a criminal organization that plans to kill him.

page89.title: Tum Haseen Main Jawaan
page89.description: A navy officer who has had a number of affairs with attractive young women meets a beautiful girl and falls in love. Though she loves him in return, another admirer of hers tells the officer that she is deceiving him and is the mother of a child.

page89.title: Thikana
page89.description: An unemployed alcoholic decides to get his life back together and returns to practicing law. While investigating a case, he falls in love with a dancer whose brother was murdered, and he sets out to find the killers.

page89.title: Taqdeer
page89.description: Taqdeer is a 1983 Hindi-language Indian feature film directed by Brij, starring Shatrughan Sinha, Mithun Chakraborty, Hema Malini, Zeenat Aman, Nadira, Seema Deo, Madhu Malini and Ranjeet.

page89.title: Sindoor Ki Saugandh
page89.description: Orphaned Roshni lives a poor-lifestyle with her maternal uncle, Gulal, and his wife, and they do Nautanki (singing and dancing) from village to village for a living. She is in love with Sharad and both want to get married.

page90.title: Meri Aawaz Suno
page90.description: Meri Aawaz Suno is Bollywood Action thriller film directed by S. V. Rajendra Singh. Starring Jeetendra, Hema Malini in lead roles and music composed by Laxmikant Pyarelal.

page90.title: Film Star
page90.description: A snobbish actress is dismayed when her career slumps, so she stages a lavish comeback by making a film based on another woman's life.

page90.title: Bachpan
page90.description: It is about three friends, Ram (Master Sachin), Rahim (Mahboob Master) and Tom (Master Alankar)Ram is an orphan who lives with his aunt; Rahim lives with his father and horse (badshah); Tom lives with his father  and mother very unhappilly

page90.title: Saugandh
page90.description: Rivalry between families where Ganga takes an oath that she will make her son marry Sarang's daughter.

page90.title: Global Baba
page90.description: A conman finds refuge in becoming a baba and carries out his various criminal activities under the guise. A policeman, a journalist and politicians get entangled in his Web of deceit.

page90.title: Aks
page90.description: Raghavan Ghatge, a psychotic terrorist, and Manu Verma, the cop who tracks him down, shoot each other simultaneously, the result being that Raghavan's soul is transferred into Verma's body...

page91.title: Akalmand
page91.description: Tamil-speaking Priya and Punjabi-speaking Dr. Kiran meet and fall in love with each other, and get married. Kiran likes to drink and likes the company of women, Priya is aware of this and always suspects him of having an affair.

page91.title: Aadmi
page91.description: Rajesh (Dilip Kumar) is orphaned at a very young age and comes from a very wealthy and noble family, but is very insecure. His childhood sweetheart Meena tragically dies and Rajesh substitutes her with a doll.

page91.title: Banphool
page91.description: A deadly rivalry emerges between an elephant handler and a tea heir when both men fall for the same woman.

page91.title: Deedar
page91.description: On the engagement of Anand and Sapna, their life takes a wrong turn, connected to their parents' past. This drama stars Akshay Kumar and Karishma Kapoor.

page91.title: De Taali
page91.description: Friends of wealthy 26-year-old Abhishek Aggarwal try to warn him off marrying gold-digger Kartika, but when he refuses to listen, they take her captive.

page91.title: Chaar Maharathi
page91.description: Raju, John, Suleman and Shakti seize a hidden treasure of the deceased Anil Kumar. They face Kumar's widow Sharada who identifies Raju as her lost son. They then have to deal with Bandit Devi Singh.

page92.title: Ek Se Badhkar Ek
page92.description: Ek Se Bhadkar Ek is a 1976 Hindi movie. Directed by Brij the film stars Ashok Kumar, Sharmila Tagore and Navin Nischol. The films music is by Kalyanji Anandji.

page92.title: Duplicate
page92.description: Seeking vengeance on those who double-crossed him, an escaped prisoner (Shah Rukh Khan) impersonates an unsuspecting chef.

page92.title: Dost
page92.description: An orphan who was brought up by a Roman Catholic priest returns to his home from university and discovers that his mentor is dead.

page92.title: Disco Dancer
page92.description: Jimmy promises to return to Bombay and become a famous entertainer so that he can exact revenge on Mr. Oberoi for having insulted and imprisoned his mother on false charges.

page92.title: Dil Jo Bhi Kahey...
page92.description: A young man (Karan Sharma) falls in love with a woman but faces parental opposition.

page92.title: Honeymoon Travels Pvt. Ltd.
page92.description: Six newly-married, diverse, honeymooning couples face marital bliss and discord, finding out more about themselves, their significant others and life in this happy-go-lucky, quirky drama.

page93.title: Gurudev
page93.description: A police inspector and and his friend have grown up together, but the inspector's father works as the right-hand man of a crime boss who also happens to be the friend's father.

page93.title: Farz
page93.description: An agent in India's Secret Service probes the death of a fellow agent said to have had some evidence that would incriminate a terrorist leader.

page93.title: Justice Chaudhury
page93.description: An honest and upright lawyer becomes a judge; marries his disabled daughter to a crook, and is blackmailed to compromise his judicial judgements.

page93.title: Julie
page93.description: Julie, a young Anglo-Indian, decides to marry her Hindu boyfriend, but their parents all refuse to accept their engagement, and Julia fears that her past may be the cause.

page93.title: Janbaaz
page93.description: Drugs, gangsters and a woman (Dimple Kapadia) affect the lives of a dedicated policeman (Feroz Khan) and his wayward brother (Anil Kapoor).

page93.title: Jaan Se Pyaara
page93.description: A cop looks after his retarded twin brother and devoted mother. However, his dangerous police work gets in the way of family life, causing tragedy.

page94.title: Izzat
page94.description: Adivashi returns home from college to learn that his mother has passed away and that she had been having an affair.

page94.title: Hum Saath - Saath Hain
page94.description: An anniversary, marriages and engagements are the background for the story of three brothers

page94.title: Kurukshetra
page94.description: A determined police officer (Sanjay Dutt) dedicates his life to high-profile cases and the pursuit of justice.

page94.title: Kismat
page94.description: Rajan (Kabir Bedi) gets Geeta (Raakhee) pregnant and wants her to get an abortion, but Geeta refuses, and gives birth to a baby boy and leaves him in an orphanage. Fate plays a strange trick and the baby is adopted by Geeta and her new husband ACP Anand.

page94.title: King Uncle
page94.description: Wealthy businessman Ashok Bansal governs his house-hold with certain rules and regulations presiding over his younger brother Anil and sister Sunita. Fed up of his dictatorship Anil decides to leave the house and seeks employment in a garage.

page94.title: Khatta Meetha
page94.description: Factory worker with 4 sons marries middle aged woman with 2 sons and a daughter.Hell breaks loose as both the families are informed of the alliance.

page95.title: Naya Zamana
page95.description: A struggling writer falls in love with a wealthy girl. The girl's brother secretly burns the houses to evict the poor and blames the writer for it. The girl's father forbids the girl to see him, now she has to choose between her lover and her father.

page95.title: Phool Aur Patthar
page95.description: Circumstances have made Shaka a career criminal. When plague empties a town of its inhabitants, he takes the opportunity to burgle a house. He finds nothing except Shanti, a widowed daughter-in-law who has been left to die by her cruel relatives

page95.title: Pasand Apni Apni
page95.description: Hoping to capitalize on free publicity, a theater company owner spreads rumors of romance between a wealthy industrialist and a beautiful actress.

page95.title: One 2 Ka 4
page95.description: After his work partner, Javed, is killed, Arun takes care of the four orphaned children with the help Geeta. He discovers Javed's death was a homicide, and as he investigates, he learns that Geeta is leading a double life.

page95.title: Roti Kapda Aur Makaan
page95.description: After the retirement of his dad, the onus is on Bharat to look after the Delhi-based family. He has two younger college-going brothers, Deepak and Vijay, and a sister of marriage age, Radha.

page95.title: Ram Lakhan
page95.description: Two brothers (Jackie Shroff, Anil Kapoor) become policemen after their mother raises them to avenge their father's murder.

page96.title: Rakhwala
page96.description: This was a remake of Kaavalkaaran (1967 film).

page96.title: Raja Hindustani
page96.description: Family tensions arise when the daughter (Karisma Kapoor) of a rich tycoon falls in love with a cab driver (Aamir Khan).India's biggest box office hit of 1996!!

page96.title: Pyar Ki Kahani
page96.description: A well-qualified man working as a peon helps another young man get a job in his office as a manager. When the peon's marriage is arranged, his friend doesn't approve of the girl, but the groom discovers the truth behind the disapproval.

page96.title: Sharafat Chod Di Maine
page96.description: Sharafat Chod Di Maine is a 1976 Bollywood film directed by Jagdev Bhambri.

page96.title: Sawan Ki Ghata
page96.description: A man arranges his daughter's marriage to prevent her from marrying the man who truly loves her.

page96.title: Saudagar
page96.description: Moti marries Mahjubhi whom he exploits to make enough money, before divorcing her to marry another girl he loves.

page97.title: Satya
page97.description: A young man named Satya (J.D Chakravarthy) comes to Mumbai from South India in search of a job. Jailed for something he did not do, the once-honest young man meets an underworld boss, Bhiku Mhatre (Manoj Bajpai) in jail and joins his gang.

page97.title: Swarg Narak
page97.description: Three couples, each with their own troubles, attempt to fix their relationship problems

page97.title: Sheen
page97.description: The Kashmiri Pandits are subjected to indignity at the hands of their neighbors, their government and mujahedeen extremists; they become refugees in their own country.

page97.title: Yeh Zindagi Ka Safar
page97.description: A singer (Amisha Patel) finds out she was adopted when the editor (Gulshan Grover) of a struggling tabloid publishes the story.

page97.title: Yeh Ishq Nahin Aasaan
page97.description: Yeh Ishq Nahin Aasaan is a 1984 Indian Bollywood film directed by Tinnu Anand. It stars Rishi Kapoor and Padmini Kolhapure in pivotal roles.

page97.title: Waris
page97.description: Due to disagreements in the King's household, his wife and son decide to move away from his kingdom. Years later, the King passes away and the palace decides to locate the Prince

page98.title: Tu Chor Main Sipahi
page98.description: A lawman (Akshay Kumar) jeopardizes his life while playing cat-and-mouse games with a deadly criminal (Amrish Puri).

page98.title: Ok Jaanu
page98.description: A young couple living together in Mumbai (Aditya Roy Kapur and Shraddha Kapoor) are torn between their love for each other and their desire to pursue career opportunities abroad -- she plans to study architecture in Paris, while he wants to break into the U.S. tech industry.

page98.title: Aaj Aur Kal
page98.description: After India attains independence from Britain, several maharajas continue with their oppressive regimes.

page98.title: Buddha Mil Gaya
page98.description: A couple of unemployed slackers find a millionaire, who according to several newspaper advertisements has gone missing. They decide to use him in a grand scheme to get hold of his fortune, but things go horribly wrong.

page98.title: Dil Ne Jise Apna Kaha
page98.description: Rishabh and Parineeta are both deeply in love with each other. Both marry and soon Pari is pregnant. Tragically, Pari is involved in an accident, and both the baby and she die in hospital. Pari's last wish was to donate her heart to a patient.

page98.title: Phir Teri Kahani Yaad Aayee
page98.description: A movie director falls in love with a mentally unstable woman, but he becomes demented following her tragic death.

page99.title: Babul 1986
page99.description: A 1986 Hindi movie directed by Govind Moonis starring  Aakash, Akashdeep, Brahmachari.

page99.title: Lucky Kabootar
page99.description: After he thinks his wife has died, Lucky falls into the arms of another woman. He discovers how unlucky he is when his wife returns.

page99.title: Kya Love Story Hai
page99.description: The story of a woman's plan to find and marry a successful and self-made male.

page99.title: Rudaali
page99.description: The film is set in a small village in Rajasthan, India. It tells the story of a woman named Shanichari, who was abandoned by her mother shortly after her father's death. Bad fortune follows her throughout her life.

page99.title: Rang Rasiya
page99.description: A look into the life of 19th century Indian painter Raja Ravi Varma.

page99.title: Ramchand Pakistani
page99.description: A 7 year old Pakistani boy and his father belonging to the untouchable Hindu caste accidentally cross the border and spend years in an Indian jail while the mother on the other side doesn't know what has happened to them.

page100.title: P Se PM Tak
page100.description: In this comedy of errors, Kasturi is a prostitute who gets caught in the middle of an elaborate scheme orchestrated by two warring political parties

page100.title: Naach
page100.description: An actor (Abhishek Bachchan) and a choreographer (Antara Mali) fall in love, but professional problems cause them to drift apart

page100.title: Mumbai Se Aaya Mera Dost
page100.description: A man's (Abhishek Bachchan) innocent gift to his grandfather sparks a power struggle in a village that recently received electricity.

page100.title: Aah!
page100.description: Love letters bind Raj and Chandra, but tragedy awaits them after Raj is diagnosed with tuberculosis.

page100.title: Kisse Pyaar Karoon
page100.description: Sheetal plans to entice John and make him fall in love with her so she can usurp all of his wealth; Sid and Amit realize her game and plan to foil her.

page100.title: Contract
page100.description: After witnessing the brutal death of his family, an embittered ex-army officer agrees to infiltrate a gang of terrorists.

page101.title: Bhumika
page101.description: A woman who learned music from her courtesan grandmother breaks into the burgeoning show business industry of 1930s Bombay.

page101.title: Badmashiyaan
page101.description: Dev's girlfriend leaves him on the night he was planning to propose to her. Months later, a private investigator is trying to track her down.

page101.title: Asambhav
page101.description: When the President of India is kidnapped by Kashmiri terrorists in Locarno, Switzerland, an Indian secret agent is sent to find him and set him free. With the help of an Indian singer he will make the "Impossible" to complete the mission.

page101.title: Aggar
page101.description: A married woman (Udita Goswami) has an affair with a man (Tusshar Kapoor) who becomes obsessed with her.

page101.title: Khudai
page101.description: Raj Anand is director of many popular hit movies of Hindi Cinema and lives in India with his wife Padmini and son Varun. Raj decides to launch Varun in a film named "Nagar Vadhu" (Prostitute) and pair him opposite actress Sakhi.

page101.title: 16 December
page101.description: White collar crimes that drain the nation of precious foreign exchange is connected to the funding of international terrorism. The much-told Hollywood theme is retold in the Indian context with much needed technical wizadry.

page102.title: Doodh Ka Karz
page102.description: A women plans to avenge her snake charmer husband's death, but her plans fall apart when she realizes that her son might not help her.

page102.title: Dil Hi Dil Mein
page102.description: An impoverished collegian (Kunal) falls in love with his wealthy benefactor's daughter (Sonali Bendre) via the Internet.

page102.title: Darwaaza Bandh Rakho
page102.description: Four men form a gang with a plan of making a quick buck by kidnapping a rich girl for ransom. Not being prepared for unforeseen situation, they are forced to barge in and take shelter in a house and take the people in the house as hostages

page102.title: Salaakhen
page102.description: A young man takes the law into his own hands after his father, a trial witness, commits suicide.

page102.title: Sawan Ko Aane Do
page102.description: A village boy with singing talent is encouraged by his love Chandrika and fights to win her father's approval.

page102.title: Sangeet
page102.description: A blind, orphan girl aspires to be a successful singer. With the help of another street performer, she sets out to make a mark and in the process discovers her real parents.

page103.title: Pyaasa Sawan
page103.description: While looking for employment, Chandrakant is mistaken for the son of a wealthy landlord.

page103.title: Namak Haraam
page103.description: The wealthy son (Amitabh Bachchan) of a factory owner and his middle-class friend (Rajesh Khanna) become involved in worker strike.

page103.title: Mai Baap
page103.description: Maai Baap is a 1957 Bollywood film starring among others Shyama, Balraj Sahni.

page103.title: Katti Batti
page103.description: A romantic comedy that follows Maddy and Payal's live-in relationship until a sudden turn of events creates a distance between them.

page103.title: Kasum Khoon Ki
page103.description: Kishan has to come up with Rs.25,000/- in less than six months in order to get his sister married to Dharamdas' son. He is told that it is virtually impossible to come up with this amount, unless one is involved in smuggling, drugs, and robberies.

page103.title: Kaagaz Ke Phool
page103.description: As a debutante develops into an acclaimed actress, the director (Guru Dutt) who discovered her sinks into oblivion.

page104.title: Geet
page104.description: A stage performer with a widowed father falls in love with a flute-player from scenic Kulu.

page104.title: Do Dil
page104.description: Manu is the princely heir to the kingdom ruled over now by Ranimaa. He likes to know what his going on and changes his princely get up and dresses up as an ordinary man and goes around the territory

page104.title: Aayee Milan Ki Raat
page104.description: A Tantrik converts two lovers into a snake, one at sunset and one at sunrise.

page104.title: Aap Mujhe Achche Lagne Lage
page104.description: A girl who hails from a very conservative family is terrified at the thought of falling in love with a man she has feelings for.

page104.title: Aamdani Atthani Kharcha Rupaiyaa
page104.description: Comedy about a neighborhood where families are struggling to make ends meet, and how the wives attempt to augment their income.

page104.title: Aansoo Ban Gaye Phool
page104.description: Vidyanand, a likeable and trustworthy young man, is framed and sent to prison. When he is released, he plots revenge on the people who sent him away.

page105.title: Monica
page105.description: An accused and three politically-connected suspects are prosecuted for their involvement in the homicide of a journalist.

page105.title: Door Ka Raahi
page105.description: Door Ka Rahi is story of a person named "Prashant" who is on the travel for the wellness of society, and the end of Journey is to watch. The angle of the movie focused on expressing the internal feelings.

page105.title: Moh Maya Money
page105.description: A young real-estate broker tries to pull off a huge scam, which goes horribly wrong. To fix everything he involves his begrudging wife leading to an end neither could imagine.

page105.title: Befikre
page105.description: Set in the vibrant and sensual Paris, Befikre is a contemporary romance that follows Dharam (Ranveer Singh) and Shyra (Vaani Kapoor) as they impulsively explore new adventures and fall in love in the city of lights.

page105.title: Shaque
page105.description: Shaque ("doubt") - A story of a marriage worn down by fear and suspicion

page105.title: Major Saab
page105.description: An officer (Amitabh Bachchan) foils a reluctant recruit's (Ajay Devgan) attempts to get a discharge.

page106.title: Classic Dance of Love
page106.description: An orphaned girl is taught all forms of dance at a dance school run by a lady. She grows up to be a pretty woman and meets a London returned young man and falls in love with him. The boy's father despises this relation.

page106.title: Devi Ahilya Bai
page106.description: Devi" Ahilyabai is not just a bio-epic or docu-drama, but with scintillating music including sixteen songs, a historic film that integrates facts, folklore and legend that together underline the inherent contradictions between the rights and duties of rulers in our society.

page106.title: Wajah Tum Ho
page106.description: A group of people get entangled in a mystery when a murder is committed on live television.

page106.title: Dear Zindagi
page106.description: Kaira, a budding cinematographer is constantly searching for what she believes is a "perfect life," meaning social, personal, and financial success. But when she meets free-thinker Jug, her entire perspective on life changes.

page106.title: Raaz Reboot
page106.description: Raaz Reboot is a horror film that revolves around a married couple living in Romania. Shaina and Rehaan begin to hide something from each other...

page106.title: Beiimaan Love
page106.description: BEIIMAAN LOVE is a dark love story exposing the `Beiimaani` (betrayal) of love in current times. The story revolves around today`s strong independent woman and deals with human relationships and values of life.

page107.title: Tum Bin 2
page107.description: 'Tum Bin 2' promises the same romance that we got hooked to in the original. It seems to be a love triangle that is expected to be romantic and mystic with serene locations and mesmerizing music.

page107.title: Ae Dil Hai Mushkil
page107.description: A story about unrequited love - the shapes it takes, the ways it changes us and the exhilarating and often heartbreaking ride it takes us on. It is the journey of three characters, Ayan, Alizeh and Saba.

page107.title: M.S. Dhoni: The Untold Story
page107.description: The untold story of Mahendra Singh Dhoni's journey from ticket collector to trophy collector - the world-cup-winning captain of the Indian Cricket Team.

page107.title: Naya Kadam
page107.description: Madhukar and Jaggu are Hitler-like tyrants who rule over a small community with an iron hand. They prefer to keep the inhabitants illiterate, so that they can continue to oppress and abuse them over time.

page107.title: Oh Bewafa
page107.description: A spurned woman concocts an elaborate plan of revenge against a pilot who made love to her and then betrayed her trust.

page107.title: Prem Qaidi
page107.description: A teenage couple fall in love, but their relationship is opposed by the girl's father because the boy is not from a wealthy family.

page108.title: Rakhwala
page108.description: A little girl comes from her village to Bombay to find her father. She meets Vikram a kind hearted person who could help her. But Vikram is helpless as she doesn't know her father's name nor has his photograph.

page108.title: Aaina
page108.description: "Mirror" is the dramatic story of a Brahmin girl, Shalini, who becomes a prostitute to support her mother, 4 sisters and 3 brothers. It's about sacrificial love, family, and ambitions. It is Mumtaz's next to the last film.

page108.title: Ab Ke Baras
page108.description: U.S. based Anjali Thapar has repeated dreams of a parallel life in India, the temple of Devi Maa Durga.

page108.title: Benaam
page108.description: Amit and Sheela Srivastav witness an attempted murder as they are driving to a party one night. Their arrival scares off the assailant, whose face they do not see, and they take the unconscious man to the hospital.

page108.title: Naseem
page108.description: Relationship between Naseem, a 15-year-old schoolgirl belonging to a Muslim family and his ailing grandfather takes the story forward as the family watches with increasing horror on their TV the news of the growing tension between Muslims and Hindus.

page108.title: Rabba Main Kya Karoon (2013)
page108.description: Rabba Main Kya Karoon story revolves around two brothers Arshad Warsi & his younger cousin brother Akash Chopra who is getting married lavishly in a typical Indian style in Delhi.

page109.title: Khushi (2003 Hindi Film)
page109.description: While helping mutual friends on the road to marriage, two collegians (Fardeen Khan, Kareena Kapoor) develop feelings for each other.

page109.title: Loha (1987 Film)
page109.description: Loha is a 1987 Hindi film directed by Raj N. Sippy. It was released in India on 23 January 1987. It stars Dharmendra, Shatrughan Sinha, Karan Kapoor, Madhavi, Mandakini and Amrish Puri. The film was one of that year's highest grossing films.

page109.title: Mammo
page109.description: An Indian woman (Farida Jalal) tries to return to her native Bombay after becoming a Pakistani citizen.

page109.title: Maqsad
page109.description: Maqsad is a 1984 Hindi film produced by D. Rama Naidu on Suresh Productions banner, directed by K. Bapaiah. Starring Rajesh Khanna, Jeetendra, Jaya Prada and Sridevi in the lead roles and music composed by Bappi Lahari.

page109.title: Mashooka (2005)
page109.description: Vicky loves Sonia (Vidya) but Sonia loves Jeet (Amit Behl). Sonia gets married to Jeet and leaves Vicky (Aditya Bal). Vicky gets depressed and goes to a new city. Vicky take a room on rent in Sanjana's (Meghna Naidu) bungalow.

page109.title: Ujala Hi Ujala
page109.description: Anuradha lost her mother at a very young age, and her father re-married a much younger woman named Anita, who wanted Anuradha out of their lives, and forced her to drink alcohol at a very young age.

page110.title: Saheb, Biwi Aur Gangster Returns
page110.description: The Royal Scandal continues with the return of `Saheb Biwi Aur Gangster`. Aditya Pratap Singh is crippled and his wife, Madhavi Devi is now an MLA, her relationship with Aditya may be strained but her relation with alcohol continues.

page110.title: Yamraaj
page110.description: Yamraaj is a 1998 released Indian action film starring Mithun Chakraborty and Jackie Shroff as thieves and their conflict between each other on their Goal.

page110.title: Zakhmi Zameen (1990)
page110.description: Wealthy and aristocratic Thakur Pratap Singh lives in a palatial mansion, and has a dream of building a dream house, similar to the Taj Mahal, with the help of his Architect brother.

page110.title: Zulmi
page110.description: Dutt has a daughter, Komal. He is also the guardian of Nihal. Balraj once sees a young man, Raj fighting with a bunch of goons. He is impressed by Raj and hires him as Komal's bodyguard. Eventually, Raj and Komal fall in love.

page110.title: Pyaar To Hona Hi Tha
page110.description: A woman (Kajol) seeking a lost love meets a charming thief (Ajay Devgan), who helps her find her stolen airline-baggage.The film is a remake of the 1995 Hollywood film French Kiss.

page110.title: Satya 2 (2013)
page110.description: By the year 2013 Mumbai underworld was erased by Mumbai Police. Sharwanand, a man without a past, comes to the city envisions the rebirth of his company.

page111.title: Ankhon Dekhi
page111.description: Ankhon Dekhi centers around Raje Bauji, played by Sanjay Mishra who, after a dramatic incident, decides that he will only believe what he sees with his eyes.

page111.title: Andaz Apna Apna
page111.description: Two slackers competing for the affections of an heiress, inadvertently become her protectors from an evil criminal.

page111.title: Shahid
page111.description: The account of Human Rights lawyer Shahid Azmi, an ordinary citizen with an extraordinary commitment to justice.

page111.title: Bada Kabutar
page111.description: Bada Kabutar is a 1973 Bollywood action comedy film produced and directed by Deven Verma.

page111.title: Ek Doctor Ki Maut
page111.description: When Dr. Roy discovers a vaccine for leprosy, his superiors in the health ministry suppress him and transfer him to a remote village. Will he ever receive credit for his discovery?

page111.title: Ek Ghar
page111.description: Rajanna and Geeta arrive in the city with the hope of building a cozy little home. When they find their dream house, their happiness knows no bounds. Things are fine till, one day, a loud workshop opens up next door.

page112.title: Sachai Ki Taqat
page112.description: Hawaldar Ram, an honest cop, finds out that a gangster has influential connections and decides to expose them. However, he ends up becoming a victim of deception as he tries to expose their misdeeds.

page112.title: Xcuse Me
page112.description: In order to marry their girlfriends, two brothers (Sahil Khan, Sharman Joshi) must re-open a hotel that a local don would like to acquire.

page112.title: Gaman
page112.description: Gaman is a Bollywood film released in 1978 starring Farooq Sheikh and Smita Patil in the lead roles and introducing Nana Patekar in a supporting role. It is the directorial debut of Muzaffar Ali, who went on to make Umrao Jaan.

page112.title: Shorts
page112.description: The film includes 5 short films namely Hidden Cricket,Geek Out,Chai,Moi Murjani, andEpiphany. All the films though deal with different issues yet highlight the core values of India.

page112.title: Gandhi
page112.description: Gandhi's character is fully explained as a man of nonviolence. Through his patience, he is able to drive the British out of the subcontinent. And the stubborn nature of Jinnah and his commitment towards Pakistan is portrayed.

page112.title: Hamara Dil Aapke Paas Hai
page112.description: A good Samaritan (Anil Kapoor) shelters a rape victim (Aishwarya Rai) after her own family casts her out. A remake of the Telugu film Pellichesukundam.

page113.title: Deedar
page113.description: A traumatized and blind young man makes a living singing and searching for his childhood sweetheart.

page113.title: Daag
page113.description: A heavy drinker (Dilip Kumar) gives up alcohol to marry his true love, then discovers that she is betrothed to another man.

page113.title: Chandni
page113.description: A classic Yash Chopra love story - the story of how love takes the lives of three people and weaves them together - softly lyrical, throbbingly beautiful and filled with the sound of three hearts hopelessly in love.

page113.title: Bhoot Bungla
page113.description: Ghost stories surround a house which appears to be haunted; someone decides to find out the truth of the situation.

page113.title: Balidaan
page113.description: The film is remake of Telugu Movie Balidanam (1982).Balidaan is a 1985 Bollywood, Action film directed by S.A.Chandra Shekaran. Starring Jeetendra, Sridevi in the lead roles and music composed by Bappi Lahari.

page113.title: Woh Chokri
page113.description: Tunu lives and spends her time at the Howrah Railway Station, searching desperately for her father Dinesh Roy, a small-time politician. He abandoned her and her mother, Geeta, who is now a bootlegger and prostitute in order to survive.

page114.title: Tarpan
page114.description: Forgiveness for a community's past sins is tied to the fate of a sick girl whose parents are searching for a cure.

page114.title: Tum A Dangerous Obsession
page114.description: After taking advantage of a drunk housewife, an obsessive photographer proceeds to make her life a living hell.

page114.title: Thokar
page114.description: Thokar also called The Kick is 1939 Hindi/Urdu film directed by A. R. Kardar. Produced by Chandulal Shah for his production banner Ranjit Movietone, it had music by Gyan Dutt. The story writer was M. Sadiq, with cinematography by Gordhanbhi Patel.

page114.title: The Stoneman Murders
page114.description: In 1980s Bombay, a serial killer starts targeting homeless street dwellers, whilst a suspended police officer attempts to solve the case.

page114.title: Hyderabad Blues 2
page114.description: A woman (Jyoti Dogra) leaves her husband (Nagesh Kukunoor) after the man's co-worker (Tisca Chopra) tries to seduce him.

page114.title: Imaandaar
page114.description: A businessman faces challenges when he unknowingly permits his daughter to get engaged to the son of the man who betrayed him.

page115.title: Isi Ka Naam Zindagi
page115.description: A treacherous son attempts to obtain his father's land through unlawful means. It is based on an acclaimed Bengali play Sajano Bagaan (The Arranged Garden) by Manoj Mitra, which was first filmed in Bengali by Tapan Sinha’s as Banchharamer Bagaan.

page115.title: Ittefaq
page115.description: Efficient ex cop-turned hit man Shiva takes on a contract to find a young man who has been an eyewitness to a murder committed by a criminal and bring him back to Mumbai.

page115.title: Trishagni
page115.description: The film is set in a Central Asian desert in the 1st Century B.C. A sandstorm strikes the Buddhist town of Sariput, leaving just four survivors - two monks and two children - in the upper floor of a monastery.

page115.title: Sindoor
page115.description: A man (Shashi Kapoor) from her past threatens a woman's domestic happiness.A 1987 Indian Bollywood film directed by K. Ravi Shankar.

page115.title: Triyacharitra
page115.description: A daughter of poor parents was engaged to a man when she was 13. The man is away working in Calcutta. In the meanwhile, she befriends a truck-driver who promises her parents a huge amount of money.

page115.title: Ghanchakkar
page115.description: A safe cracker claims he has lost his memory when two criminals come calling for their cut of the bank heist loot.

page116.title: Sasural
page116.description: Sasural is a 1960 Hindi movie produced by L. V. Prasad and directed by T. Prakash Rao. The film stars Rajendra Kumar, B. Saroja Devi, Mehmood and Lalita Pawar. The music is by Shankar Jaikishan. It is a remake of the Telugu film Illarikam.

page116.title: Santaan
page116.description: Sarju and Laxmi have done everything to educate their son Amar and have lots of hope from him but the but Amar desires to become rich and disowns his parents who then face only sufferings in their life.

page116.title: Samadhi
page116.description: Samadhi is a 1972 Hindi film directed by Prakash Mehra. The film stars Dharmendra in a dual role as father and son, Asha Parekh and Jaya Bhaduri as the love interests. Music is by R.D. Burman.

page116.title: Sahib Bibi Aur Ghulam
page116.description: A lowly servant, Bhootnath gets close to the wife of his employer, and narrates her story through his eyes and perspective.

page116.title: Sabse Bada Rupaiya
page116.description: A Multi-millionaire turned fisherman discovers that his financial ruin was a deliberate and deceptive plot.

page116.title: Saaransh
page116.description: An old couple lends a room on rent after the recent death of the bread earner of the family, their only son. A budding actress starts living with them, who is in love with a local politician's only son. The movie shows what later ensues.

page117.title: Rudraksh
page117.description: A doctor (Bipasha Basu) and her team of scientists investigate a gifted man (Sanjay Dutt) who sees an evil force that threatens humans.

page117.title: Hawas
page117.description: Hawas is a 1974 Hindi film. Produced, directed and written by Sawan Kumar, the film stars Anil Dhawan, Neetu Singh, Bindu, Vinod Mehra and Rekha special appearance in the song "Aao Yaro Gao". The film's music is by Usha Khanna.

page117.title: Aar-Paar
page117.description: An ex-convict gets a job as a taxi driver to change his girlfriend's prejudiced father's view of him, and becomes embroiled with a criminal gang in the process.

page117.title: Aap Ke Saath
page117.description: A devious woman (Smita Patil) brings strife to two brothers (Anil Kapoor, Vinod Mehra).

page117.title: Boss
page117.description: A man fights for people's rights. In Delhi, he will have to deal with a corrupt police officer.

page117.title: Dharavi
page117.description: A taxi driver is caught up in a street war after borrowing money from Bombay slumlords to finance his dye factory

page118.title: Banjo
page118.description: Taraat, a local banjo player seeks fame, success, and money. In his pursuit, he crosses path with Christina who helps him accomplish his goals.

page118.title: Topless
page118.description: Maya, a sexy & beautiful girl, comes to Mumbai to become famous and rich. After some struggle she joins a modeling agency & in a short span of time she becomes successful as a top Model in the Advertising and Fashion World.

page118.title: Zanjeer (1973)
page118.description: After witnessing the murder of his parents at a young age, Vijay grows up to become a respected police detective. His days are spent shutting down gambling dens, until an outburst of gang violence kills a group of innocent children.

page118.title: Hera Pheri (1976 Film)
page118.description: Vijay and Ajay sever their relationship after Vijay learns that his father's killer may be Ajay's long-lost father. Once the friendship is over, a bloody saga of familial revenge is set into motion.

page118.title: Jodhaa Akbar
page118.description: A sixteenth-century love story about a marriage of alliance that gave birth to true love between a great Mughal emperor, Akbar, and a Rajput princess, Jodha.

page119.title: Stanley Ka Dabba
page119.description: A school-teacher, who forces children to share their food with him, forbids one from entering the school until he brings his own Tiffin/Lunch-box.

page119.title: Raja Natwarlal
page119.description: A small-time con man seeks assistance from his mentor with the intention of settling scores with a gangster.

page119.title: Luv Shuv Tey Chicken Khurana
page119.description: A fugitive returns to his native village and tries to recover a lost chicken recipe that made his family's restaurant famous.

page119.title: Gippi
page119.description: It is a coming-of-age story of an ordinary, overweight girl, who through the course of the film learns to love herself for exactly who she is. It is also a tale of an underdog who picks herself up from nothing and finds herself at the top of her own little world

page119.title: Chitkabrey
page119.description: 7 couples are brought together by chance. They will face each other's past, present, and future. The movie breaks down a number of stereotypes prevalent in our society.

page119.title: Man Pasand
page119.description: A man meets a poor woman and claims that he can transform her into a classy lady. She agrees, thinking that the man is in love with her, but her heart breaks when she realizes that she is the subject of a bet between the man and his friend.

page120.title: Ghayal
page120.description: After he is wrongly accused, a man (Sunny Deol) seeks revenge for his brother's (Raj Babbar) murder.

page120.title: Daddy Cool
page120.description: A wealthy man passes away while exercising on his treadmill. A funeral is arranged, relatives are notified, and his eldest son prepares a farewell speech.

page120.title: Anand Ashram (Hindi)
page120.description: A wealthy Indian man expects his son to marry a woman of equally high status, but the son falls in love with a poor woman.

page120.title: Supermen Of Malegaon
page120.description: Malegaon, a small town tucked away near the heart of India geographically, is fraught with communal tension and under severe economic depression.To escape the harsh reality of their world, people seek refuge in the world of cinema.(Documentary)

page120.title: Sparsh
page120.description: A visually impaired principal and a sighted teacher in a school for the blind fall in love though soon their complexes tag along and they struggle to get past them to reconnect with the "touch" of love.

page120.title: Saraswatichandra
page120.description: Complications arise for a young couple (Nutan, Manish) about to enter into an arranged marriage.

page121.title: Saare Jahaan Se Mehnga
page121.description: `Saare Jahaan Se Mehnga` is a satire on inflation that is told through the eyes of a family. The satire explores what happens when the family tries to deal with it through a unique idea, not realizing the mess they`re further getting themselves involved in.

page121.title: 23rd March 1931: Shaheed
page121.description: When his mentor Lala Lajpatrai is mercilessly beaten to death by the police Bhagat Singh is enraged and he sets about to avenge his death

page121.title: Salaam-e-Ishq: A Tribute To Love
page121.description: Six couples who do not know each other are brought together by destiny, fate, and love.A 2007 Bollywood romantic drama anthology film. An unofficial remake of 2003 British film Love Actually.

page121.title: Naram Garam
page121.description: An old man and his young daughter, Kusum, are looking for a place to live, when they come across a large estate where a man offers to let them stay if he is allowed to marry Kusum.

page121.title: God Only Knows
page121.description: Fast-talking, shifty eyed Chief Minister is due for surgery but develops complications and passes away. He is whisked away by Yumraaj, the God of Death, to the heavenly gates, where the Minister must make a choice between Heaven and Swarg.

page121.title: Dhoondte Reh Jaaoge
page121.description: A failed film producer and an unemployed Chartered Accountant decide to make a 'sure flop' movie

page122.title: Daag 1973
page122.description: Defending the honor of his new bride, one man kills another by accident, beginning a series of troubling incidents.

page122.title: Bhuvan Shome
page122.description: Bhuvan Shome is a 1969 Indian Hindi drama film directed by Mrinal Sen. The cast includes Utpal Dutt and Suhasini Mulay. Sen based his film on a Bengali story by Banaphool. The film is considered a landmark in modern Indian cinema.

page122.title: Pyaasa
page122.description: Pyaasa is a love triangle with revenge as its base. Suraj aspires to be a millionaire some day, but all hopes of making it big are squashed by his father, and uncle, who don't approve of selling their ancestral land.

page122.title: Jurm
