page122.description: Jurm is a 1990 Bollywood movie directed by Mahesh Bhatt and produced by his brother Mukesh. It stars Meenakshi Sheshadri, Vinod Khanna, and Sangeeta Bijlani in the leading roles.

page122.title: Dulhe Raja
page122.description: Disliking his daughter's (Raveena Tandon) choice of a spouse, a hotel owner (Kader Khan) tries to match her with another man (Govinda).

page122.title: Dil Apna Aur Preet Parai
page122.description: A surgeon is obliged to marry the daughter of a family friend, but he is in love with a nurse who works tirelessly by his side.

page123.title: Daag: The Fire
page123.description: Karan is a former soldier. One day when Karan finds out that his father committed suicide in prison after he is falsely charged with a crime, he suspects Ravi Verma, a city attorney who has a wife and a kid.

page123.title: Bewafa Sanam
page123.description: Later during the imprisonment, Sundar came to know about such facts about Sheetal which left him in ultimate misery and pain.

page123.title: Aashiq Banaya Aapne
page123.description: An introvert is unable to express his feelings to the girl he loves. His friend proposes and she accepts but ditches him when she discovers he is a flirt. Problems arise as destiny has other plans.

page123.title: Suhagan
page123.description: Suhagan is a Social hindi movie, directed by K. S. Gopal Krishnan, starring Guru Dutt, Feroz Khan, David, Leela Chitnis along with others.

page123.title: Shahenshah
page123.description: A corrupt police officer is chasing a notorious criminal, whose identity has always been obscure and whom the police have always feared, although strangely enough, the criminal is highly respected by the poor.

page123.title: Sarhad Paar
page123.description: Sarhad Paar examines the connection between a brother and his sister. Major Ranjeet Singh (Sanjay Dutt) crosses the border between India and Pakistan chasing a terror suspect Bhaktawar (Rahul Dev). He is captured and brutally tortured for five years

page124.title: Sangram
page124.description: Sangraam is 1993 Hindi movie directed by Lawrence D'Souza and starring Ajay Devgn, Karishma Kapoor, Ayesha Jhulka, Amrish Puri.

page124.title: Platform
page124.description: Wrongfully imprisoned for murder, a man (Prithvi) escapes and looks to reunite with his brother.

page124.title: Nehle Pe Dehla
page124.description: A kingpin smuggler kills a police officer and succeeds in separating his teen-aged sons. The elder son who had vowed to take revenge, accidentally meets his younger brother. The two join forces to bust the smugglers gang.

page124.title: Musafir (Hindi)
page124.description: A drug lord (Sanjay Dutt) and a corrupt policeman search for a criminal (Anil Kapoor) looking to reform his ways.

page124.title: Dil Diya Hai
page124.description: Emraan, a tour guide is in need of money to treat his mother. Neha is Saahil's client and because of his desperation is sold by him to a pimp.

page124.title: The Blue Umbrella
page124.description: Based on a novella by Rushkin Bond, and set in the picturesque Himachal Pradesh, Chatri Chor tells the story of the turmoil caused in a small village...

page125.title: Paar
page125.description: Pregnant Rama (Shabana Azmi) and her husband, Naurangia (Naseeruddin Shah), flee their village after Naurangia vengefully kills a man who had murdered a kindly schoolteacher.

page125.title: Mere Hamdam Mere Dost
page125.description: Sunil lives with his mom and sister in Delhi. He comes across a pretty lady, Anita and both are attracted to each other.

page125.title: Dil (Hindi)
page125.description: Raja lives a poor lifestyle along with his dad, Hazariprasad and mom. He attends college where he has several run-ins with wealthy fellow-collegian, Madhu Mehra.

page125.title: Dasvidaniya
page125.description: Amar lived a mundane life -like millions of others. His existence was non-existent to people around him, until one day his doctor told him that he will die in 3 months.He makes a list of things to do before he dies.

page125.title: Chupke Chupke
page125.description: Mischievous Parimal plays a little trick on his brother-in-law Raghav. Jealous of the high esteem in which his own wife, Sulekha, holds the other man, Parimal decides to impersonate Raghav's new driver.

page125.title: Chennai Express
page125.description: What could have been a sad journey turns joyful for Rahul when he falls in love with a woman en route to submerging his grandfather's ashes.

page126.title: Andaz
page126.description: After rescuing Neena, Dilip falls head over heels for her. As time passes, Dilip becomes more involved in Neena's life, ingratiating himself with her good friend  but not with her father, who disapproves of Neena and Dilip's interactions.

page126.title: We Are Family
page126.description: A divorced mother of three children runs a happy household - until her former husband brings his new career-oriented girlfriend into the picture.

page126.title: Wake Up Sid
page126.description: A spoiled young adult living in Mumbai experiences a change in his lazy ways when he meets a woman at a party, who inspires him to "wake up".

page126.title: Ragini MMS
page126.description: Out to relax and have fun at a farmhouse, a couple experience horror at the hands of an unknown entity.

page126.title: Phantom
page126.description: A disgraced Indian soldier carries out a series of assassinations in the hope of restoring his honor.

page126.title: Morning Raga
page126.description: It is a story that brings the modern and traditional together, unites the past with present, Carnatic music with Western music, as never before in the history of humanity, fate and coincidence with individual choices.

page127.title: Karle Pyaar Karle
page127.description: Karle Pyaar Karle is an adrenaline gushing, action packed, edgy love story of two rebels, Kabir & Preet, playing the game of life.

page127.title: Do Anjaane
page127.description: An amnesiac (Amitabh Bachchan) learns that his wife (Rekha) is a famous actress and that his best friend (Prem Chopra) tried to kill him.

page127.title: Videsh
page127.description: An Indian woman's (Preity Zinta) optimism about her new life in Canada quickly disappears when her husband begins to vent his frustrations by beating her.

page127.title: Umrao Jaan
page127.description: A courtesan (Rekha) embarks on an ill-advised love affair with an aristocrat (Farooque Shaikh).Based on the 1905 Urdu novel Umrao Jaan Ada, the film tells the story of a Lucknow courtesan and her rise to fame.

page127.title: Maine Pyar Kiya
page127.description: A wealthy man (Salman Khan) falls in love with a working-class woman (Bhagyashree).

page127.title: C.I.D.
page127.description: A newspaper editor, Shrivastav, is killed when he was about to expose the underworld links of a very rich and influential person. C.I.D. Inspector Shekhar is assigned to this case, an investigation of which leads him to suspect Dharamdas and his men.

page128.title: Aiyyaa
page128.description: A woman goes on the hunt for her dream man, armed with her wild imagination, her passion for Masala-films, and her ultra-sensitive sense of smell.

page128.title: Tirangaa
page128.description: A brigadier general (Raaj Kumar) and a police officer (Nana Patekar) work together to thwart a terrorist (Deepak Shirke).

page128.title: Sardar
page128.description: Depicting the life of Vallabhai Patel, who played an important role in the partition and creation of India and Pakistan.

page128.title: Kati Patang
page128.description: Madhvi is an orphan living with her uncle, but when he arranges a marriage for her, she flees to the man she truly loves. She decides to leave town with her friend Poonam, who later dies, leaving Madhvi to care for Poonam's child.

page128.title: Ishk Actually
page128.description: Gia is at a crossroads in her life, with the arrows pointing towards Neil in one direction and Kabir in the opposite direction.

page128.title: Barsaat Ki Ek Raat
page128.description: A man (Amitabh Bachchan) must deal with a vicious criminal (Amjad Khan) who attacked his blind wife (Rakhee Gulzar).

page129.title: Arzoo
page129.description: Arzoo is a 1950 Bollywood film produced by Hiten Chaudhary and directed by Shaheed Latif. The film stars Dilip Kumar, Kamini Kaushal and Shashikala. The films music is by Anil Biswas.

page129.title: Qurbani
page129.description: Blackmailed by two villains, a thief (Feroz Khan) must help a crime boss in order to save his lover (Zeenat Aman).

page129.title: My Friend Ganesha 3
page129.description: Abused by his relatives, a young boy seeks the help of a truck-driver's wife, and Bhagwan Shri Ganeshji.

page129.title: Krantiveer
page129.description: A crusading journalist (Dimple Kapadia) inspires an aimless man (Nana Patekar) to fight for the rights of the poor.

page129.title: Delhi-6
page129.description: A story about love, hope and self-discovery set in the walled city of Delhi (zip code 6) and its chaotic but touching life that forces us to ask questions about ourselves.

page129.title: Chandni Bar
page129.description: A displaced woman is forced to become a beer-bar dancer and sire children of a gangster.

page130.title: Barfi!
page130.description: Three young people learn that love can neither be defined nor contained by society's definition of normal and abnormal.

page130.title: Bhagawat
page130.description: Robbed of his heritage as a child, a prince tries to regain his father's kingdom.Baghavat (1982) is a Hindi language film starring Dharmendra, Reena Roy, Hema Malini and Amjad Khan.

page130.title: Ankur
page130.description: A married man seduces his servant but is unable to accept the responsibilities of her resulting pregnancy.

page130.title: Aamir
page130.description: A doctor of Indian origin returning to Mumbai from London is forced to participate in a terrorist plot.

page130.title: Taal
page130.description: A young couple fall in love, but because of the difference in social class, the boy's father disapproves, which insults the girl's family and causes a rift in the relationship.

page130.title: PK
page130.description: A stranger in the city asks questions no one has asked before. His childlike curiosity will take him on a journey of love, laughter, and letting go.

page131.title: Lalkaar
page131.description: During World War II, two army officers who are also brothers fall for the lady doctor and one of them proposes marriage to her. As war intensifies, both are sent on different secret mission and one of them is assumed to be dead.

page131.title: Junoon
page131.description: Javed Khan (Shashi Kapoor) emerges as one of the leaders of a mutiny in the East India Company.

page131.title: Johny Mera Naam
page131.description: Kept apart by destiny, brothers Mohan and Sohan both grew up without a father. While Mohan sets out to kill the man who murdered their dad, Sohan follows in his father's footsteps by becoming a police officer.

page131.title: Ghulam-E-Mustafa
page131.description: Ghulam, a gangster and a hit man, is asked to move into the home of Dayanand and force his family out.

page131.title: Andha Kanoon
page131.description: One day while on duty, Jan Nissar Akhtar Khan, a forest officer, comes across some poachers who are cutting sandal wood trees illegally.

page131.title: Ab Ayega Mazaa
page131.description: A man (Farooq Shaikh) falls for a beautiful woman (Anita Raj), then becomes jealous when her childhood friend (Ravi Baswani) shows up.

page132.title: Welcome To Sajjanpur
page132.description: An educated man spends his days writing letters for the varied inhabitants of his small, poor, and illiterate village, in this political and social satire.

page132.title: The Path Of Zarathustra
page132.description: A young Parsi woman's quest exploring the mysteries of a magical book which contains the essence of the message of the first prophet and addresses the concerns of her dwindling community.

page132.title: Sharaabi
page132.description: The son (Amitabh Bachchan) of an uncaring and ruthless businessman is a kindhearted drunk.

page132.title: Rajaji
page132.description: A man (Govinda) hopes to marry for money but loves a poor woman, while his father wants him to be a workaholic.

page132.title: Raaz: The Mystery Continues
page132.description: An artist comes to realize that the woman he has been been painting is real and is being haunted by a ghost.

page132.title: Naya Daur
page132.description: A rift develops between two lifelong friends when they fall in love with the same woman.

page133.title: Main Aur Mr. Riight
page133.description: A slice of life, a romantic comedy that talks about love, relationships, and singlehood. It is a story of 8 friends from different fields living their individual and successful lives.

page133.title: Baiju Bawara
page133.description: A young singer, in the time of Emperor Akbar the Great, sets out to avenge his father, killed in a disturbance near the house of a member of the Court.

page133.title: Aya Sawan Jhoom Ke
page133.description: Wealthy Jaishankar meets and falls in love with Aarti, successfully woos her and agrees to meet with her dad to discuss their marriage. On the way there he ironically runs over him, killing him instantly.

page133.title: Lagan
page133.description: A widower finds out that one of her sons has been abusing his pregnant wife. She and her other son try to rein him in, but their intervention complicates matters further and the brothers end up becoming arch rivals.

page133.title: Lok Parlok
page133.description: A poor man who lives with his widowed mother causes a lot of trouble in the village and as a result, the village panchayat leader puts a hit out on him.

page133.title: Manzil
page133.description: A man (Amitabh Bachchan) lies about his finances to impress the daughter of a wealthy lawyer.

page134.title: Mohabbat Ke Dushman
page134.description: In the 18th Century, the reputation of a woman's incredible beauty is spread throughout the region, to the point where a wealthy man decides to include her in his harem.

page134.title: Neel Kamal
page134.description: Long-buried memories of love from a past life resurface when a woman visits the ruins of Rang Mahal.

page134.title: Parakh
page134.description: Villagers vie for a large amount of money which was sent to the postmaster.

page134.title: Satte Pe Satta
page134.description: After the death of their parents, Ravi Anand, the eldest of seven, takes it upon himself to raise his brothers.

page134.title: Shaadi Karke Phas Gaya Yaar
page134.description: Ayaan tricks a model into marrying him, when she leaves her diary in his family's garage, allowing him to follow her around.

page134.title: Jab Andhera Hota Hai
page134.description: Jab Andhera Hota Hai hindi full movie starring Vikram, Prema Narayan, Madan Puri, Jalal Agha, Helen, Prem Chopra. Directed by Deepak Bahry. Produced by Kailash Chopra. Music composed by Sapan Chakraborty.

page135.title: Ghar Sansar
page135.description: A beggar is asked to pose as the wealthy Girdharilal, who has accumulated a number of enemies, resulting in the kidnapping of the real Girdharilal.

page135.title: Gehra Daag
page135.description: While defending his sister's honor, Shanker kills a man. His ashamed family say he is away in Africa, while he spends the next ten years in prison. What happens when the truth comes out, can he ever find forgiveness or acceptance?

page135.title: Tamacha
page135.description: Tamacha is a 1988 Indian Bollywood film produced by Prasan Kapoor on Tirupati Pictures Enterprises banner and directed by Ramesh Ahuja. Starring Jeetendra, Rajinikanth, Amrita Singh and Bhanupriya in pivotal roles and music composed by Bappi Lahiri.

page135.title: Train To Pakistan
page135.description: A small Punjab community deals with political and ethnic tensions in the wake of India's independence from Britain.

page135.title: Vaah! Life Ho Toh Aisi
page135.description: Adi Chachu faces a dilemma - and it's a big one! What if YOU were told by the God of Death himself you had only 15 minutes of life left? What would YOU do?!

page135.title: Chaska
page135.description: Chaska- An Addiction is a movie based on crime. The story revolves around Rani and Vicky who are in love. Vicky decides to call his father on his birthday and propose rain for marriage. An Adult Entertainer!!

page136.title: Jwalamukhi
page136.description: A police inspector (Shatrughan Sinha) and a customs officer (Vinod Mehra) confront a criminal possessing a secret document.

page136.title: Lorie
page136.description: A woman, depressed that she in unable to bear children, abducts a child, and wants to keep him for her own. The child belongs to a large family consisting of 11 other children.

page136.title: ChaalBaaz
page136.description: Separated in infancy by a kidnapping, twin sisters (Sridevi) reunite as adults after a series of mistaken identities.

page136.title: Dulari
page136.description: Prem Shankar lives a wealthy life-style circa after the British Rule in India, with his parents. He is now of marriageable age, and his parents would like him to marry Seth Heerachand's daughter, but Prem wants to marry someone of his own choice.

page136.title: Bhanwar
page136.description: Bhanwar is a 1976 Bollywood film directed by Bhappi Sonie. The film stars Ashok Kumar, Parveen Babi and Randhir Kapoor.

page136.title: Be-Shaque
page136.description: Shyam Sunder has taken to alcohol and womanising after becoming bored of his wealthy lifestyle in a small village.

page137.title: Bepanaah
page137.description: After leaving his small town for Bombay, India, Bajrang finds himself getting sucked into the city's dark underbelly while simultaneously getting involved in a brutal love triangle.

page137.title: Bandini
page137.description: The movie explores the human conflicts of love and hate intertwined in the mind of Kalyani  (Nutan). The film is based on the Bengali novel Tamasi by Jarasandha (Charu Chandra Chakrabarti).

page137.title: Afsana Pyar Ka
page137.description: Two college students (Aamir Khan, Neelam) meet and fall in love, unaware of their respective families' mutual animosity.

page137.title: Mem-Didi
page137.description: In a small village two tough, but good-hearted men preside over the day to day lives of the inhabitants, namely Bahadur Singh and Sher Khan. One of the rooms is soon going to have a new tenant, and everyone gathers to welcome her.

page137.title: Jhuk Gaya Aasman
page137.description: Jhuk Gaya Aasman is a 1968 film directed by Lekh Tandon. The film stars Rajendra Kumar, Saira Banu, Rajendranath and Prem Chopra. Music is by Shankar Jaikishan. The film is a remake of the Hollywood film Here Comes Mr. Jordan.

page137.title: Dharam Kanta
page137.description: Bhavani's gang has spread terror and fear throughout the region, and their reign reaches its peak when they kidnap the son of a wealthy man and demand a hefty ransom.

page138.title: D
page138.description: A mechanic from Dubai comes to Mumbai and gets entangled in a web of crime by accident. Soon, he goes on to become a dreaded underworld kingpin.

page138.title: Chalo America
page138.description: Three college boys think that everything American is fabulous; everything Indian is backward. Determined to get to America, they cook up one hair-brained scheme after another to get the all-important 'letter of sponsorship' from America.

page138.title: Arpan
page138.description: A man (Jeetendra) returns from a trip abroad to find that his intended bride (Reena Roy) has married someone else.

page138.title: Ahista Ahista
page138.description: Ankush is an aimless youth and scrapes by as a witness in Delhi's marriage-registrar bureau; Megha has run away from her home in Naintal to wed Dheeraj.

page138.title: Teen Batti Char Raasta
page138.description: Teen Batti Char Raasta is a 1953 Hindi social family drama on national integration directed by V. Shantaram. There are six sons of which five are married. One of the brides is Tamil.

page138.title: Razia Sultana
page138.description: A 1961 Hindi Movie starring Nirupa Roy, P. Jairaj, Nisar Ahmad Ansari .

page139.title: Oye Lucky! Lucky Oye!
page139.description: A cunning con man (Abhay Deol) hobnobs with the rich and famous, then proceeds to rob them blind.

page139.title: O Teri
page139.description: O Teri is a satire produced by Atul Agnihotri. The film stars Pulkit Samrat and newcomer Bilal Amrohi as two journalists, who come across a big scam.Two journalists, one scam - a life changing event!

page139.title: Kaminey
page139.description: The desperate lives of two estranged twin brothers converge over missing drugs, politics, racial prejudice, corrupt cops and an unplanned pregnancy.

page139.title: Dastaan
page139.description: Dastaan is a 1972 film produced and directed by B. R. Chopra. The film stars Dilip Kumar, Sharmila Tagore, Prem Chopra, Bindu, Sachin, Iftekhar, I. S. Johar and Madan Puri. The film's music is by Laxmikant Pyarelal.

page139.title: Aadmi Aur Insaan
page139.description: Aadmi Aur Insaan is a 1969 Hindi film produced by B. R. Chopra and directed by Yash Chopra. The film stars Dharmendra, Saira Banu, Feroz Khan, Mumtaz, Johnny Walker, Ajit, Anwar, Iftekhar, Kamini Kaushal and Nazima. The film's music is by Ravi.

page139.title: 2 States
page139.description: Krish and Ananya belong to two different states of India. Krish, a North Indian Punjabi boy from Delhi, and Ananya, a Tamilian Brahmin from Chennai. They take a conscious decision; they won`t get married until their parents agree.

page140.title: Batwara
page140.description: Vikram & Sumer are two close friends, who's close bond is well known in village. Vikram belongs to upper caste Thakurs, who are landlords. Sumer belongs to lower caste & serves as a cop.

page140.title: Dhanak
page140.description: Believing actor and goodwill ambassador Shah Rukh Khan can help her brother get an operation to restore his sight, a 10-year old girl takes her blind 8-year old brother on a trek across Rajasthan in search of the superstar.

page140.title: Shadow 2009
page140.description: A series of high-profile murders committed by a super-smart killer leave the police flummoxed. Who is he and how is he finally captured?

page140.title: Zabak
page140.description: Zabak is a 1961 Hindi/Urdu action costume drama film produced and directed by Homi Wadia for his Basant Pictures under the Wadia Productions banner. The story and dialogue were by C. L. Cavish with screenplay by JBH Wadia.

page140.title: Chitchor
page140.description: Chitchor is a 1976 Indian Hindi romantic musical film. The film's title means "Heart Stealer" in Hindi. The film is a Rajshri Productions film produced by Tarachand Barjatya. It is based on a Bengali story, Chittachakor by Subodh Ghosh.

page140.title: Fight Club
page140.description: Four college friends starts an underground fight club in order to earn quick money, nevertheless they become suspects of a murder of a man, who turns out to be the mob boss' brother.

page141.title: Family
page141.description: A slacker abducts the family of a crime kingpin to avenge the death of his brother.

page141.title: Ekka Raja Rani
page141.description: Barkha is in love with Sagar - then she saves the life of underworld king Vicky. Vicky offers her a job & falls in love with her. When he proposes, Barkha turns him down and tells him she loves Sagar. Will Vicky tolerate this?

page141.title: Kasam
page141.description: Inspector Krishna is betrayed by other policemen after saving a village to stop collateral damage from the opium trade.

page141.title: Jimmy
page141.description: Jimmy, a mechanical engineer by day and a dancing sensation by night, is implicated in the murder of a young woman and seems destined to be sent to prison.

page141.title: Gomti Ke Kinare
page141.description: Gomti Ke Kinare is a 1972 Bollywood drama film directed by Saawan Kumar Tak in a directorial debut. The film stars Meena Kumari and Mumtaz. It was the last release of Meena Kumari, and was released posthumously.

page141.title: Gunahon Ka Devta
page141.description: Gunahon Ka Devta is a 1990 Hindi-language Indian feature film directed by Kawal Sharma, starring Mithun Chakraborty, Sangeeta Bijlani, Aditya Pancholi, Danny Denzongpa, Shakti Kapoor and Paresh Rawal.

page142.title: Nafrat
page142.description: A young man grows up estranged from his mother, only to discover that years later he is employed by the man with whom she once had an affair, which caused her marriage to fall apart.

page142.title: Mili-1975
page142.description: Curmudgeonly Shekhar is new to the block, and it doesn't take long before the street noise, as well as the children playing nearby, push his tolerance to the limit. To the rescue comes Mili ,who has the exact opposite disposition.

page142.title: Mazloom
page142.description: Purnima is raped by a stranger in a train and is too ashamed to talk about the incident. She becomes pregnant and her parents find out.

page142.title: Shukriyaa
page142.description: A quirky cocktail of love, life and death.A 1988 Hindi movie directed by A.C. Trilogchander starring  Rajiv Kapoor, Amrita Singh, Asrani .

page142.title: Ram Jaane
page142.description: Ram Jaane is arrested by a security guard after stealing cargo from a train with his best friend. Later, he becomes one of the biggest hustlers in the city. He falls in love with a childhood girlfriend Bela but also goes back to his old ways.

page142.title: Prem Tapasya
page142.description: A man falls in love with an attractive woman, reluctant at first; she accepts his proposal for marriage. They plan to get married in secret, but he does not turn up at the wedding and she is left distressed.

page143.title: Naya Nasha
page143.description: A young woman runs away from her house to avoid marriage; in her adventure outside home she meets nine men with different professions and stories. She meets one more man and this changes her life for good.

page143.title: Zeher
page143.description: A husband and wife are cops, investigating a murder where all the evidence points to the husband.

page143.title: Ustad 420
page143.description: After three criminals break out of prison, one of them is murdered. A 1969 movie starring  Sheikh Mukhtar, Sudhir, Zeb Rehman.

page143.title: Tumhara Kalloo
page143.description: This is a coming of age movie based on the life of a young man named Kalloo, who lives with his wealthy family in a small village in India.

page143.title: Teen Devian
page143.description: Teen Devian is a 1965 Bollywood film directed by Amarjeet starring Dev Anand. Filmed mostly in black and white, with some colour scenes, the movie tells the story of a poet who falls in love with three different women.

page143.title: Anwar
page143.description: A Muslim who is researching ancient Hindu mandirs falls in love with a woman.

page144.title: Aakraman
page144.description: As war breaks out between India and Pakistan, two army officers (Sanjeev Kumar, Rakesh Roshan) clash over their love for the same woman (Rekha).

page144.title: Zameen Ke Tare
page144.description: Zameen Ke Tare is a 1960 Hindi-language children's drama film directed by Chandulal Shah and starring Daisy Irani, Honey Irani, Motilal and Achala Sachdev, with music by S. Mohinder.

page144.title: Tahaan
page144.description: A tender fable about childhood innocence amid the realities of war is set against the rugged landscape of Kashmir, so long a flash point for the territorial claims of neighboring two nations.

page144.title: Mississippi Masala (English Movie)
page144.description: An Indian family is expelled from Uganda when Idi Amin takes power. They move to Mississippi and time passes. The Indian daughter falls in love with a black man, and the respective families have to come to terms with it.

page144.title: Madhumati
page144.description: A man relates the story of a painter (Dilip Kumar) haunted by the ghost of the woman (Vyjayantimala) he loves.

page144.title: Hisss
page144.description: Based on the Far Eastern myth of the snake woman who is able to take on human form. She's Sexy... Venomous... And She'Ll Swallow You Whole...

page145.title: Akeli Mat Jaiyo
page145.description: A light, romantic, fun film about a working girl, staying in a hostel, pretends to be on a date, and when about to be found out, takes the help of a handsome stranger. They fall in love, he is mistaken for a prince, and things go wrong.

page145.title: 15 Park Avenue
page145.description: An exploration of the impact of schizophrenia on a young woman and her family in today's Calcutta. The narrative pivots around the relationship of two sisters, older sister Anjali is a successful professor with a powerful personality.

page145.title: Yeh Teraa Ghar Yeh Meraa Ghar
page145.description: A man (Sunil Shetty) falls for the difficult tenant (Mahima Chaudhry) he tries to evict from his father's house. This story of the film is an adaptation of the Mohanlal starrer movie Sanmanassullavarkku Samadhanam.

page145.title: Yeh Dillagi
page145.description: A workaholic (Akshay Kumar) falls in love with the model (Kajol) his irresponsible brother (Saif Ali Khan) has already claimed for himself.

page145.title: Yaadgaar
page145.description: A politician and his son try to kill the leader of a group that exposes corruption.

page145.title: Uttar Dakshin
page145.description: Uttar Dakshin is a 1987 Hindi film produced by Ashok Khanna and Subhash Ghai and directed by Prabhat Khanna and featuring Bharathi, Madhuri Dixit, Jackie Shroff, Anupam Kher and Rajinikanth in the lead roles.

page146.title: Ugly Aur Pagli
page146.description: An Engineering student's life changes drastically after the entry of an alcoholic and spunky woman.

page146.title: Trimurti (1974)
page146.description: Starring Sanjay Khan, Rakesh Roshan, Asrani, Parveen Babi, Arpana Choudhary and others. Directed & Produced by Rajendra Bhatia.

page146.title: Saudagar
page146.description: Growing up together, Veeru and Raju are lifelong friends until the devious Chuniya exploits their relationship for his own ends. Veeru and Raju become bitter rivals, but then Veeru's grandson Vasu and Raju's granddaughter Radha fall in love.

page146.title: Prem Pujari
page146.description: Ramdev, the son of a veteran war hero, loves peace and detests war; he struggles to reconcile his own emotions with his father's legacy.

page146.title: Narsimha
page146.description: After his entire family is killed, Narasimha (Sunny Deol) spirals into drunkenness and criminal behavior, finally becoming a hired killer for the city's most feared criminal boss, Baapji (Om Puri)

page146.title: The Rising: Ballad Of Mangal Pandey
page146.description: Based on the life and times of Mangal Pandey, 1857: The Rising is a film about the leader of the 1857 mutiny and his fight against the British rule.

page147.title: Maati Maangey Khoon
page147.description: A man has no knowledge of his birth, parents nor of a family home; during a skirmish with some hoodlums, he is left unconscious at the entrance of a temple where an elderly unhinged woman prays to God for his sake.

page147.title: Laadla
page147.description: Laadla is a Bollywood film released on 17 April 1994, starring Sridevi, Anil Kapoor and Raveena Tandon.

page147.title: Khwahish
page147.description: The sexy and intense relationship of Amar and Lekha progresses from the time they met, through their quirky marriage.

page147.title: Khud-Daar
page147.description: Khud-Daar is a 1982 Indian Hindi movie directed by Ravi Tandon. The music is by Rajesh Roshan and the lyrics by Majrooh Sultanpuri.

page147.title: Khuda Gawah
page147.description: An Afghan warrior (Amitabh Bachchan) seeks final reckoning with his enemies after spending time in an Indian prison.

page147.title: Karmayogi
page147.description: Separated by their philosophical differences, a devout woman and her atheistic husband each take one son to raise alone.

page148.title: Jigar
page148.description: Middle-class Raju joins a martial arts school to take revenge on the local champion, who raped his sister.

page148.title: Janasheen
page148.description: A man (Fardeen Khan) falls in love with a famous violinist (Celina Jaitley) who has a tragic past.

page148.title: Gulaal
page148.description: A law student witnesses the struggles of the Rajputs, deception, homicide and crime after being elected as General Secretary of his college.

page148.title: Guide
page148.description: A tour guide, Raju (Dev Anand), takes a serious-minded archaeologist, Marco (Kishore Sahu), and his beautiful but troubled wife, Rosie (Waheeda Rehman), on an excursion to look at ancient caves.

page148.title: Geet
page148.description: Geet is a 1992 Bollywood Hindi film released on 20 November 1992 starring Divya Bharti, Avinash Wadhawan in lead roles. Shakti Kapoor, Laxmikant Berde & Dharmesh Tiwari play supporting roles.

page148.title: Dream Girl
page148.description: Dream Girl is a 1977 Indian Hindi film, directed by Pramod Chakravorty. The movie stars Hema Malini, Ashok Kumar, Dharmendra and Prem Chopra.

page149.title: Chalta Purza
page149.description: Chalta Purza is a 1977 Bollywood action thriller film directed by Bhappi Sonie. The film stars Rajesh Khanna and Parveen Babi.

page149.title: Chaahat
page149.description: Naseer will go to any lengths to get the man his sister has fallen for to reciprocate her feelings.

page149.title: Mehboob Ki Mehndi
page149.description: A husband and wife find that a child has brought drastic changes to their lives.

page149.title: Bedardi
page149.description: A professor teaches his students to avoid violence but uses it himself to avenge killers.Bedardi is a 1993 movie starring Ajay Devgn, Urmila Matondkar, Naseeruddin Shah, Reena Roy, Ashok Banthia and Kiran Kumar in pivotal roles.

page149.title: Barah Aana
page149.description: Three impoverished room-mates kidnap middle-classed men and demand small ransoms to improve their respective lifestyles.

page149.title: Aur Pyaar Ho Gaya
page149.description: Kailashnath turns to his childhood friend Malhotra, whose son Rohit to make a match for his daughter Ashi. Ashi, however, wants to meet Rohit before she commits to, and when she travels to Switzerland to do so, a case of mistaken identity ensues.

page150.title: Aap Ke Deewane
page150.description: Inseparable friends Ram and Rahim both fall in love with Sameera, forcing her to choose between the childhood friends.

page150.title: Aanch
page150.description: The movie story deals with Nana Patekar and Paresh Rawal belong to two different villages. They hate each other for reasons best known to them. Suchindra's father and Sharbani's brother decide to get them Suchindra and Sharbani Mukherjee married.

page150.title: Sunghursh
page150.description: The grandson (Dilip Kumar) of a powerful priest resists initiation into the elder's religion, which entails human sacrifice.

page150.title: Life Mein Kabhie Kabhiee
page150.description: Five years after pledging to make the most of their lives, five college friends reunite only to find that while they've all achieved their goals, they are paying a heavy price for success.

page150.title: Kochadaiiyaan-The Legend
page150.description: Rana, a ruthless warrior, returns to his homeland to avenge the death of his father, who was unjustly put to death by the reigning king of Kotaipattinam. An epic historical animated fiction film!!

page150.title: Insan Jaag Utha
page150.description: A village girl falls in love with newcomer Ranjeet, unaware that he is there to retrieve the smuggled gold that he buried in her front-yard many years ago.

page151.title: Yamla Pagla Deewana
page151.description: A married Canadian travels to India to re-unite with his estranged father and brother but faces obstacles and challenges.

page151.title: Himmatwala
page151.description: When a temple priest commits suicide after being dishonored by an evil landlord, his son returns to his native village on a mission of vengeance.

page151.title: Highway (Hindi)
page151.description: Right before her wedding, a young woman finds herself abducted and held for ransom. As the initial days pass, she begins to develop a strange bond with her kidnapper.

page151.title: Gair
page151.description: A man begins to despise his father when an uncle suggests that his father's new best friend may be an illegitimate son.

page151.title: Fitoor
page151.description: A modern adaptation of Charles Dickens' Great Expectations; a poor but talented boy falls in love with a girl from an affluent family.

page151.title: Drohkaal
page151.description: Drohkaal is a 1994 Indian crime drama film directed and produced by Govind Nihalani which deals with India's fight against terrorism.

page152.title: Baabul
page152.description: A man tries to help his widowed daughter-in-law regain some happiness after the death of his son.

page152.title: Muskaan
page152.description: Muskaan is a 2004 Indian Bollywood film directed by Rohit- Manish. It stars Aftab Shivdasani and Gracy Singh in pivotal roles.

page152.title: Lal Dupatta Malmal Ka
page152.description: Lal Dupatta Malmal Ka is a Hindi made-for-television movie released in 1989. Although, it was just a telefilm and not released on big screen, it was a huge success. The movie is known for its popular songs sung by Mohd. Aziz.

page152.title: Jeena Teri Gali Mein
page152.description: A musical love story of two couples who attend the same college and have to face many reality as they go through a road that is called life.

page152.title: Home Delivery
page152.description: Sunny works as a writer and is very cynical toward everyone until a pizza delivery man teaches him some of life's simple lessons.

page152.title: Ek Khiladi Ek Haseena
page152.description: A feared gangster (Gulshan Grover) targets a con artist (Fardeen Khan) after a scheme goes awry. A remake of the 2003 Hollywood crime drama movie Confidence.

page153.title: Chocolate 2005
page153.description: On a snowy Christmas Eve in London, a couple of Indians are arrested by the police and made scapegoats -- or so it seems.

page153.title: Chitralekha
page153.description: A king ignores his wife and continues his frequent visits to the royal dancer. Fed up with his ill-behavior, his wife decides to abandon the royal life and starts living in an ashram whereas he marries the dancer.

page153.title: Chand Aur Suraj
page153.description: After a disgraced man's accidental death, the lives of his family change drastically when they receive money from his insurance company.

page153.title: Bhai-Bhai 1956
page153.description: Mistaken for a criminal, a man lands in jail while searching for his brother.The film starred real-life brothers Ashok Kumar, who played the lead role, and Kishore Kumar as the two brothers.

page153.title: Ankahee
page153.description: A doctor who is a happily married man falls for a beauty queen; however, the beautiful woman does not have noble intentions.

page153.title: Sau Crore
page153.description: Sau Crore is an Indian film from 1991 starring, produced, and directed by Dev Anand. It also debuts newcomers Fatima Sheikh and Raman Kapoor.

page154.title: Latt Saheb
page154.description: A woodcutter, Jangu lives a poor lifestyle in Kashmir along with his widowed mother, who fears that he is going to die soon after Dassera. She keeps on praying for his well-being and safety, and cautions him to be careful all the time.

page154.title: Heeralaal Pannalal
page154.description: Heeralal Pannalal is a 1978 Bollywood film directed by Ashok Roy. The film is a Bollywood action comedy released in 1978.

page154.title: First Love Letter
page154.description: Thakur Ajit Singh believes that women should always listen to a man; however, he grows angry when his only daughter falls in love with a poor man.

page154.title: Dost Garibon Ka
page154.description: Dost Garibon Ka is a Hindi language movie produced by Firoz A. Nadiadwala starring Govinda and Neelam. The movie was directed by C.P. Dixit and was released in 1989.

page154.title: Doli Saja Ke Rakhna
page154.description: Two young lovers (Akshaye Khanna, Jyotika Sadanah) whose families disapprove of their union run away to a fishing village to elope.

page154.title: Dil Hai Ke Manta Nahin
page154.description: Runaway heiress in search of her beloved falls in love with another man on the way.

page155.title: Speedy Singhs
page155.description: An ethnic Canadian hockey player struggles against traditional family values and discrimination from mainstream hockey players.

page155.title: Red Swastik
page155.description: Police hunt a femme fatale who preys on adulterous husbands and leaves a bloody swastika on their bodies.

page155.title: Phir Bhi Dil Hai Hindustani
page155.description: Two television reporters (Shahrukh Khan, Juhi Chawla) must put aside their rivalries when things heat up during an election campaign.

page155.title: Kurbaan (2009)
page155.description: A woman finds that her neighbors are terrorists, and her husband is not who he claims to be.

page155.title: Chahat
page155.description: Chaahat is a 1971 Bollywood romance film produced by G.P. Roshan on New Film Corporation banner, directed by Moni Bhattacharjee. Starring Jeetendra, Mala Sinha, Biswajit, Mumtaz in the lead roles and music composed by Laxmikant-Pyarelal.

page155.title: Badi Didi
page155.description: Badi Didi is a 1969 Bollywood, drama film produced by Narindra Suri and Nand Kumar on Archana Films banner, directed by Narindra Suri. Starring Jeetendra, Nanda in the lead roles and music composed by Ravi.

page156.title: Sutradhar
page156.description: Sutradhar translation: Impresario is an Indian colour Drama film of 1987. It was a feature film directed by Chandrakant Joshi starring Smita Patil, Girish Karnad and Nana Patekar in the lead roles.

page156.title: Margarita With A Straw
page156.description: A rebellious young woman with cerebral palsy leaves her home in India to study in New York, unexpectedly falls in love, and embarks on an exhilarating journey of self-discovery.

page156.title: Jis Desh Mein Ganga Behti Hai
page156.description: Orphaned Raju makes a living by singing songs. His life takes a sudden twist when he saves the leader of a band of bandits. Raju falls in love with his daughter Kammo but soon realizes that she belongs to a violent world. What will Raju do now?

page156.title: Haider
page156.description: A young man returns to Kashmir after his father's disappearance to confront his uncle - the man he suspects of playing a role in his father's fate.

page156.title: Ek Ruka Hua Faisla
page156.description: A juror uses his personal prejudices and biases to influence the verdict of a murder trial.

page156.title: Chaudhvin Ka Chand
page156.description: The setting is the city of Lucknow in northern India, where Islamic culture flourished. Two of the three best friends who live in this city have fallen in love with the same woman named Jameela unknowingly.

page157.title: Bawre Nain
page157.description: Bawre Nain is 1950 Indian Hindi-language romance film directed by Kidar Nath Sharma. It was produced under the Ambitious Pictures banner at Shree Sound Studios.

page157.title: B.A. Pass
page157.description: A young small town boy moves to Delhi to stay with his aunt and finish his college. Soon he is seduced by a mysterious married woman known to him as Sarika `Aunty`.

page157.title: The Lunchbox
page157.description: A mistaken delivery in Mumbai's famously efficient lunchbox delivery system connects a young housewife to an older man in the dusk of his life as they build a fantasy world together through notes in the lunchbox.

page157.title: Rowdy Rathore
page157.description: A con man uncovers a deadly secret and must save his lady love, the small-town locals and the little girl who insists she's his daughter, from the mob.

page157.title: Pizza (2014)
page157.description: A Pizza delivery boy's mundane life takes a horrifying turn when he is sent to make a delivery to the home of a family who have a dark secret. Will he be able to overcome the evil that lurks in the shadows and live to tell his tale?

page157.title: Nagin (1954)
page157.description: Nagin is a 1954 Hindi film, directed by Nandlal Jaswantlal, and written by Hameed Butt and Bijon Bhattacharya.Lovers from two warring snake-charming tribes face life-threatening challenges.

page158.title: Joker
page158.description: Joker is an out of this world comedy about an NRI (Akshay Kumar) and his beautiful wife (Sonakshi Sinha) who return home to discover that their village has dropped off the map of India.

page158.title: Heroine
page158.description: The film is based on the life and times of a superstar heroine from the dream factory we call Bollywood. The film is a daring, emotional, shocking, scandalous, behind the scenes account of the reality of the glamor world that our film stars inhabit.

page158.title: Race 2
page158.description: Ranvir treads through the world of the Indian mafia in Turkey as he looks to avenge the death of his lover and partner in crime.

page158.title: Paan Singh Tomar
page158.description: The story of Paan Singh Tomar, an Indian athlete and seven-time national steeplechase champion who becomes one of the most feared dacoits in Chambal Valley after his retirement.

page158.title: Haathi Mere Saathi
page158.description: A man (Rajesh Khanna) shares a strong bond with his elephant companions, but his wife (Tanuja) soon becomes jealous of the animals.

page158.title: Gol Maal
page158.description: It is a cult comedy film about a young man Ram Prasad who finds a job with a finicky man, Bhavani Shankar, who believes that a man without a moustache is a man without a character.

page159.title: Deewane Huye Paagal
page159.description: Natasha Mulchandani has three admirers Rocky Hiranandani, Sanju Malwani and Karan. Rocky and Sanju has always managed to outwit each other and other lovers in order to attain her love at any and all costs.

page159.title: Arth
page159.description: A woman (Shabana Azmi) must pick up the pieces of her shattered life after her husband (Kulbushan Kharbanda) confesses that he is having an affair.

page159.title: Trikal
page159.description: An influential family sees the transition of Goa from a Portuguese colony to an Indian district.

page159.title: Tera Jadoo Chal Gayaa
page159.description: A woman (Kirti Reddy) falls for her boss' son (Sanjay Suri), who mistakenly thinks she is already betrothed to another (Abhishek Bachchan).

page159.title: Shirdi Ke Sai Baba
page159.description: A woman travels with her seriously ill son as she seeks a cure for a disease that does not respond to medication.

page159.title: My Friend Ganesha
page159.description: A story about an 8-year-old boy who feels lonely since his parents don't have time for him and he doesn't have any friends. 'Ganesha' becomes his friend and together they resolve so many problems around and have a lot of fun.

page160.title: Kurbaan
page160.description: Maan Singh and Prithvi Singh's families have been locked in a property dispute in a court in India. When the Court gives a verdict in favor of Prithvi, Maan hires a bandit named Panna Singh to kill Prithvi and all of his family.

page160.title: Kandahar 2001
page160.description: After an Afghanistan-born woman who lives in Canada receives a letter from her suicidal sister, she takes a perilous journey through Afghanistan to try to find her.(Hindi Dubbed)

page160.title: Jumbo 2
page160.description: Jumbo is back with his family to delight your family so sit back and enjoy this animated family drama directed by Taweelap Srivuthivong.

page160.title: Jumbo
page160.description: Jumbo is a small blue elephant who grows up with his mother.His mother never reveals any details of his father and neither do the rest of the elephants in the herd. He is a happy go lucky elephant, who loves to play with the other animals of the jungle.

page160.title: Gumnaam
page160.description: A vacation turns deadly when a group of young adults is stranded on a deserted island and seeks refuge in a mansion with a sinister butler.

page160.title: Jhoom Barabar Jhoom
page160.description: A crazy love story full of lies, deceits and a complicated quadrangle where each one has to think quickly and dance around each other's emotions.

page161.title: Hero No. 1
page161.description: Rajesh Malhotra and Meena are two Indians who meet in Europe. They fall in love with each other though they didn't get along initially. They decide to get married once they get back to India.

page161.title: China Town (1962)
page161.description: A singer is asked to impersonate and take over the life of a Calcutta-based China Town gangster.

page161.title: Bandhan
page161.description: A poor young woman weds a wealthy man and moves her family in with his, but her inability to conceive causes a number of problems.

page161.title: Anupama
page161.description: Uma Sharma's birth brought the death of her mother, something which her father has never forgiven her for. However, when she meets Ashok, a sensitive poet, she begins to come out of the shell her father put her in.

page161.title: Amar Prem
page161.description: Nandu returns to the village where he grew up, looking for his childhood love Pushpa. However, Pushpa's reputation has been forever tarnished.

page161.title: Yeh Vaada Raha
page161.description: Vikram and Sunita plan to marry, but Vikram's mother opposes it because of Sunita's poor background. They decide to go through with the wedding anyway, but on their way to the temple, they are both injured in a car accident.

page162.title: Vishwanath
page162.description: An honest lawyer is implicated and imprisoned at the behest of a powerful underworld don. After his release from prison, Vishwanath decides to seek vengeance but finds out that it is virtually impossible to do this through due process of law.

page162.title: Ek Nazar
page162.description: Akash, who dreams of becoming a poet, is constantly disappointing his lawyer father. When Akash falls for a prostitute, Shabnam , the relationship between father and son worsens.

page162.title: Chamku
page162.description: A traumatized child becomes a Naxalite, and upon being captured must agree to become a police-assassin.

page162.title: Chakra
page162.description: Amma lives in Bijapur with her husband and son, Benwa. When a man attempts to sexually molest her, he is killed by her husband, the trio flee, but the husband is shot dead by the police.

page162.title: Anita
page162.description: A heartbroken man (Manoj Kumar) investigates the supposed death of the woman he loves.

page162.title: Aap Ki Kasam
page162.description: Poor Kamal and wealthy Sunita Bhatnagar meet, fall madly in love and get married. But their newlywed bliss is short-lived, as Kamal soon grows irrationally jealous over the friendship between his wife and his best friend, Mohan.

page163.title: Char Adhyay
page163.description: The film is set in the late Bengali Renaissance of the 1930s and 1940s, and a group of young intellectuals and revolutionaries involved with the Indian independence movement. It deals with the impact of political issues on personal lives.

page163.title: Karz Chukana Hai
page163.description: For most of his existence, Atmaram has lived off his wife and two sons, but when he is suddenly left alone, he must atone for his past.

page163.title: Kai Po Che!
page163.description: Three friends growing up in India at the turn of the millennium set out to open a training academy to produce the country's next cricket stars.

page163.title: ABCD 2
page163.description: Based on the true story of the Fictitious Dance group; their rise to fame, sudden downfall, and their heroic attempt to seek vindication by regaining their lost pride and glory.

page163.title: Thoda Pyaar Thoda Magic
page163.description: God sends a rambunctious angel to help a businessman and the four orphans, whose parents he accidentally kills, become a family.

page163.title: Payal Ki Jhankar
page163.description: A jungle beauty, conniving employees, mother's pressure to get married and memory loss complicate a wealthy male's life.

page164.title: Fire
page164.description: Sita and Radha are two Indian women stuck in loveless marriages.The two women grow closer, and their relationship becomes far more involved than either of them could have anticipated.*MATURE CONTENT*

page164.title: Kabeela
page164.description: Kabeela is a 1976 Hindi film. Produced and directed by Bholu Khosla it stars Feroz Khan, Rekha, Premnath and Bindu. The music of the film is by Kalyanji Anandji.

page164.title: Hum Ho Gaye Aap Ke
page164.description: Rishi is a womanizer who tries to win over Chandni, but Chandi loves Mohan, a man whose parents forbid their marriage.A remake of Tamil movie Gokulathil Seethai (1996).

page164.title: Hamara Khandan
page164.description: A young boy falls for a Catholic girl and wishes to marry her but his wealthy father is against it. His father wants him to marry a girl of an equal status and same religion.

page164.title: Gumsum
page164.description: Ganga and Paro lead a poor life in a small village. Ganga is vocally impaired from birth. Paro is in love with a blacksmith named Shankar. One day Dharamdas the village money lender rapes Ganga and threatens to kill her family if she ever revealed the truth.

page164.title: Maha-Sangram
page164.description: Maha-Sangram is a 1990 Bollywood romance film directed by Mukul Anand and starring Vinod Khanna, Aditya Pancholi, Govinda and Madhuri Dixit.

page165.title: Locket
page165.description: Two lockets each contain half of a secret map that leads to hidden treasure.A 1986 Bollywood, Action film directed by Ramesh Ahuja.

page165.title: Khilaaf
page165.description: A poor college student, Vikram Veerpratap Singh, living with his widowed grandmother, becomes infatuated with a wealthy beauty, Shweta Sangwan, initially woos her unsuccessfully but is able to win a place in her heart when he comes to her rescue.

page165.title: Saath Saath
page165.description: Saath Saath is a story about Geeta who falls in love with Avinash for his idealistic ways and outlook.Geeta believes that if they are together all the problems could be handled. But after marriage things between them are not the same.

page165.title: Rules: Pyaar Ka Superhit Formula
page165.description: A photographer's assistant (Meera Vasudevan) falls in love with a famous model (Milind Soman) who has a girlfriend (Namrata Barua).

page165.title: Pyaar Tune Kya Kiya
page165.description: When a photographer (Fardeen Khan) ends his affair with an unbalanced model (Urmila Matondkar), she becomes determined to take him from his wife (Sonali Kulkarni).

page165.title: Dr. Kotnis Ki Amar Kahani
page165.description: The film is based on the life of Dwarkanath Kotnis, an Indian doctor who worked in China during the Japanese invasion in World War II.

page166.title: Dada
page166.description: A story of a simpleton whose life changes when he witnesses a shoot-out of a Don and rescues him. The don takes him as his successor. How the negative elements of the underworld influence him forms the film's finale.

page166.title: Beqasoor
page166.description: Beqasoor is a 1950 Bollywood film about a simple girl caught in the cross-fire of a deep-rooted sibling rivalry between her upright husband and her scheming brother-in-law. The film is directed by K. Amarnath and stars Madhubala.

page166.title: Benny And Babloo
page166.description: The story is about two good-hearted samaritans Benny (Kay Kay Menon) and Babloo (Rajpal Yadav) smitten by the glamour of Mumbai.

page166.title: Anamika
page166.description: A woman-hating writer rescues a young woman lying injured on the road. When she regains consciousness, she insists that she is his wife.

page166.title: Lootere
page166.description: Karan, a decorated police officer are given the duty to protect Anjali who is the only witness against one of the underworld bosses. In order to safeguard Anjali, Karan has to take her far away in the wilderness.

page166.title: Lal Haveli
page166.description: Mukta and Anand are childhood friends and love each other. But Mukta belongs to higher social class than Anand and her family wants to arrange her marriage with Jawahar, son of a rich man.

page167.title: Karishma Kali Kaa
page167.description: A devotee of Devi Maa Kali searches for her attackers to recover stolen jewelry.

page167.title: Kali Salwaar
page167.description: Sultana, a small town prostitute, and her pimp Khudabaksh migrate to the metropolis, bringing with them their dreams and meager belongings. The film is based on several short stories by Saadat Hassan Manto, one of the greatest modern Urdu writers.

page167.title: Jugaad
page167.description: The film recaptures the chaos and the convoluted officialese through the experiences of a small advertising company that was on the threshold of a big break before the padlocks and the bulldozers arrived.

page167.title: Juari
page167.description: A young man falls into the path of gambling and fraud after experiencing betrayal in love from one woman after another. But, finally he finds out that honesty is the best path.

page167.title: Jaya Ganga
page167.description: Nishant, a young Indian writer living in Paris, is journeying down the Ganges, from its source in the Himalayas to the sea. Haunted by the fantasy, or the memory, of a beautiful Parisian woman called Jaya, he plans to write a book around his voyage.

page167.title: Insaan Aur Shaitan
page167.description: Insaan Aur Shaitan is a 1970 Bollywood action film directed by Aspi Irani. The film stars Sanjeev Kumar and Aruna Irani.

page168.title: Hanste Zakhm
page168.description: Hanste Zakhm is a 1973 Indian Hindi film produced and directed by Chetan Anand. The film stars Navin Nischol, Priya Rajvansh, Balraj Sahni, and Nadira in lead roles. The film has music composed by Madan Mohan and lyrics penned by Kaifi Azmi.

page168.title: Dilruba
page168.description: Efforts are underway by the owner of a dancer troupe to ensnare an Engineer in the theft of a necklace.

page168.title: Agar Tum Na Hote
page168.description: A disabled photographer (Raj Babbar) becomes jealous when the wealthy employer (Rajesh Khanna) of his wife (Rekha) falls for her.

page168.title: Aranyaka
page168.description: Based on a short story Aranyaka by Manoj Das, the film is set in rural Orissa, where a formal local ruler organizes a hunt for his invited guests, which goes wrong. The film highlights the clash between ruling class and indigenous people of the region.

page168.title: Akira
page168.description: A gripping action thriller about a college girl Akira, who has grown up with the ideals of being self reliant. Her life spirals out of control when she becomes unwittingly involved in a crime involving four corrupt police officers.

page168.title: Dil-Ki-Rani (Sweet-Heart)
page168.description: A comic tale of a poet and his fan both in love with each other and relentless efforts by his would be father in law to not let them marry each other. Instead, he wants his daughter to be married to the poet's friend.

page169.title: Deshdrohi
page169.description: The theme of the film "Desh Drohi " consists of politics, prostitution, pimp business, and corruption. It was scripted and produced by Kamaal Rashid Khan.

page169.title: Dard
page169.description: Dard was a Muslim social romantic melodrama which involved a love triangle in the form of two girls, Munnawwar Sultana and Suraiya, both in love with a doctor played by Nusrat.The film was Suraiya's first "big hit".

page169.title: Dahej
page169.description: The story is set in the city of Lucknow and involves the social issue of dowry. The film is about a young bride who faces suffering and humiliation for not bringing a dowry and then makes the "ultimate sacrifice" with her death.

page169.title: Usne Kaha Tha
page169.description: Usne Kaha Tha is a 1960 Bollywood drama film directed by Moni Bhattacharjee starring Sunil Dutt and Nanda in lead roles. This film is Bhattacharjee's first independent directorial venture.

page169.title: Tu Hi Meri Zindagi
page169.description: A patriotic musical film released in 1965 starring  Deb Mukherjee, Nivedita.

page169.title: Traffic Signal
page169.description: A dark and powerful portrayal of signal squatters uncovers the politics involved in their daily lives.

page170.title: Swarag Se Sunder
page170.description: A family is torn apart when two members become pregnant and only one can give birth.

page170.title: Suryavanshi
page170.description: At an archaeology site, Sonia and Vicky unearth the ancient palace of the cruel queen, Suryalekha. Resurrected, the jilted queen seeks revenge against Vicky, a lookalike of the man who spurned her.

page170.title: Sapnay
page170.description: A mother superior's nephew (Arvind Swamy) falls in love with a young woman (Kajol) who has intentions of becoming a nun.

page170.title: Saajan Bina Suhagan
page170.description: Saajan Bina Suhagan is a 1978 Hindi drama film produced and directed by Saawan Kumar Tak. The film stars Rajendra Kumar, Nutan, Vinod Mehra, Padmini Kohlapure and Shreeram Lagoo, the films music is by Usha Khanna

page170.title: Raja Rani 1973
page170.description: On the run from police, a thief (Rajesh Khanna) crashes a wedding and winds up marrying the bride (Sharmila Tagore).

page170.title: Parivar
page170.description: Parivar is the story of an Indian joint family consisting of 4 brothers, their wives, and their respective children. They live in harmony till one day when an argument breaks out over a trivial issue.

page171.title: Panch Ratan
page171.description: Randhawa as Raja takes an oath along with his four companions to finish Sangram played by Kamran. Sangram is a traitor and forcibly overtook the kingdom of Shamgarh. As fate would have it Sangram's sister Chandralekha and Raja fall in love with each other.

page171.title: Mayor Sahab
page171.description: G.K Rayadu (Kamal Haasan) is a corrupt Mayor and along with his assistant Charan Raj takes bribe and sells a market to a rich businessman and forces the poor people doing business in the land to move out threatening physical harm.

page171.title: Maha Badmaash
page171.description: Maha Badmaash is a 1977 Bollywood film directed by RG Thake.

page171.title: Krodhi
page171.description: A man avenges the death of the woman he loves, who commited suicide after she was sold to men who planned to rape her.

page171.title: Khela (Hindi Dubbed)
page171.description: Khela is a Hindi Dubbed Bengali film by Rituparno Ghosh. The film is about an idealistic director's quench to make a film with a boy who he thinks is just perfect for the role.

page171.title: Karm Yodha
page171.description: Sameer returns to his city and witnesses a murder. Later, he and his family are attacked thinking that the dead victim has shared a secret with him.

page172.title: Jaane Bhi Do Yaaro
page172.description: Two photographers (Naseeruddin Shah, Ravi Baswani) experience the shady side of real estate when they stumble upon a murder.

page172.title: I Proud To Be An Indian
page172.description: I is an Indian. He travels to London for a family wedding and finds his family live in fear of the terrorism by National Front Skinheads and finds he has to become involved which escalates the situation.

page172.title: Do Aur Do Paanch
page172.description: Chaos ensues when two rival thieves (Amitabh Bachchan, Shashi Kapoor) become mixed up in a kidnapping plot.

page172.title: Diwana
page172.description: A harmless man is charged with murder; to everyone's surprise he pleads guilty in court and demands the death penalty for his act.

page172.title: Chhoti Si Mulaqat
page172.description: A 1967 film starring Vyjayanthimala, Uttam Kumar, Rajendra Nath .

page172.title: Biradari
page172.description: A woman running a boarding house in Bombay, renting out rooms to the city's poor, discovers that her daughter sold the building while she was on vacation, leaving the boarders destitute.

page173.title: Bheja Fry 2
page173.description: Kind hearted but not worldly-wise, the roly-poly tax inspector, Bharat Bhushan is back to fulfill his long cherished dream of becoming a singer. To further his ambition, he enters a game show hoping to win a cash prize with which he can make his own music album.

page173.title: Laaga Chunari Mein Daag
page173.description: A small town girl lands in big bad Mumbai to earn an honest living but faces a confrontation she would've never dreamt of in her wildest dreams.

page173.title: Pink
page173.description: When three young women are implicated in a crime; a retired lawyer steps forward to help them clear their names.

page173.title: Dil Hai Tumhaara
page173.description: Two half sisters compete for the affections of a businessman's son (Arjun Rampal).

page173.title: Rustom
page173.description: Story of Naval Commander Rustom Pavri. Was he a Patriot? Was he a Traitor? Was he a Murderer?Based on true events, Rustom is a gripping tale about Pride, Passion and Power, and a man who must his uphold his own integrity and that of the nation.

page173.title: Vallah Kya Baat Hai
page173.description: A gambler with a big heart becomes a suspect after a child goes missing.

page174.title: Charitraheen
page174.description: Charitraheen is a 1974 Bollywood drama film directed by Shakti Samanta. The film stars Sanjeev Kumar and Sharmila Tagore .The film was on the program of the cinema S.Gabriel in Lourenço Marques, Mozambique in May 1975.

page174.title: Ek Chhotisi Love Story
page174.description: A woman (Manisha Koirala) with a boyfriend seduces a teenager (Aditya Seal) after he spies on her.

page174.title: Ghar Ek Mandir
page174.description: A joint family consisting of three brothers Prem, Vijay and Ravi are leading a happy and prosperous life. They consider their house Temple of Love. However, destiny has its own plans for them when Prem gets killed.

page174.title: Ghar Ki Izzat
page174.description: The milieu is upper middle-class joint family, with the mother treating her son's wife shabbily. The son, an educated man working as a lawyer, is unable to handle the situation at home and turns to drink.

page174.title: Kamla Ki Maut
page174.description: Kamla Ki Maut is a 1989 Hindi drama film directed by Basu Chatterjee. The film set in Mumbai, deals with issue of love, pre-marital sex and relationships in modern India. It stars Pankaj Kapoor, Supriya Pathak and Roopa Ganguly in lead roles.

page174.title: Jhoothi
page174.description: Jhoothi is a 1985 Bollywood Hindi comedy film directed by Hrishikesh Mukherjee. The film stars Rekha, Raj Babbar, Amol Palekar, Supriya Pathak and Deven Verma in the lead roles.

page175.title: Hum Aapke Dil Mein Rehte Hain
page175.description: A man (Anil Kapoor) rejects his wife (Kajol) after one year of an arranged marriage but then desperately tries to win her back.

page175.title: Ek Din Achanak
page175.description: One day a retired professor (Dr. Sreeram Lagoo) decides to go out for unknown work but don't come back, even there is no clue left behind. Family members, relatives and friends try hard but unable to come up with any satisfactory result.

page175.title: Dattak
page175.description: Sunil is an NRI married to an American girl. His father lives in Kolkata with an old servant Shambhu. When Sunil returns home after fifteen years he sees the house is locked and his father has disappeared.

page175.title: Yatra
page175.description: A successful writer (Nana Patekar) searches for the woman (Rekha) who inspired a character in his past novel.

page175.title: Tansen
page175.description: The film was based on Tansen, the 16th century musician in the court of Mughal emperor, Akbar.It was the second highest grossing Indian film of 1943.

page175.title: Sangharsh
page175.description: A special agent (Preity Zinta) seeks the advice of an imprisoned killer (Akshay Kumar) to catch another (Ashutosh Rana) who has been murdering children.

page176.title: Oh Darling! Yeh Hai India!
page176.description: A man tries to foil an evil mastermind (Amrish Puri) who has cloned the president (Anupam Kher) of India.

page176.title: Main Intequam Loonga
page176.description: Main Intequam Loonga is a 1982 Bollywood sports film starring Dharmendra, Reena Roy, Amrish Puri and Nirupa Roy. Dharmendra plays the role of a boxer in the film

page176.title: Shaukeen
page176.description: Three friends in their 60's, decide to go away for a while to have some enjoyment late in their lives.

page176.title: Sadhna
page176.description: A college professor (Sunil Dutt) hires a woman to pose as his bride-to-be to please his ailing mother.

page176.title: Jab Pyaar Kisise Hota Hai
page176.description: A wealthy womanizer (Salman Khan) falls in love, mends his ways and meets his illegitimate son.

page176.title: Bend It Like Beckham
page176.description: The daughter of orthodox Sikh rebels against her parents' traditionalism and joins a football team.

page177.title: Kahin Pyaar Na Ho Jaaye
page177.description: After a singer's (Salman Khan) fiancee (Raveena Tandon) jilts him on their wedding day, he finds romance with another (Rani Mukherjee).

page177.title: Apradhi Kaun?
page177.description: A wealthy man, suspected of murder, is killed before he can be arrested. Everyone in his household is under suspicion. A private investigator looks into the case and finds himself falling in love with one of the suspects.

page177.title: Bewaffa Se Waffa
page177.description: A married couple's harmony is disrupted after the wife is told by a doctor that she is incapable of conceiving a child.

page177.title: Banjaran
page177.description: A 50-year-old mystery comes to light when two strangers, haunted by images of each other, meet for the first time.

page177.title: Miya-Bibi Razi
page177.description: A 1960 Comedy movie starring Mehmood, Manorama and David Abraham.

page177.title: Karma Aur Holi
page177.description: The film is based on the inner conflicts of relationships, which hitherto never spoken earlier, but in a festive atmosphere of Holi, each one loses the inhibitions. The relationships eventually come out stronger.

page178.title: Jajantaram Mamantaram
page178.description: A young man (Jaaved Jaaffery) helps save an island's tiny residents from an evil army captain (Gulshan Grover) and a giant cannibal (Joy Fernandes).

page178.title: Jagte Raho
page178.description: A naive peasant enters an apartment block to find a drink, and the residents mistake him for a thief. As he evades capture, he exposes the venality and dishonesty of the building's residents.

page178.title: Humayun
page178.description: Two men form an unlikely friendship after they fight on opposite sides of a battle.A 1945 Indian Bollywood historical epic film directed by Mehboob Khan. It was the seventh highest grossing Indian film of 1945.

page178.title: Gattu
page178.description: In a small town in central India, kids and adults are equally obsessed with kite-flying. The airspace is dominated by a black kite called Kali with mysterious origins

page178.title: Door Ki Awaaz
page178.description: Prakash lives in Chandan Nagar along with his sister Mala his and widowed mom. During a train ride, Mala has an accident and is brought to hospital.

page178.title: Dev
page178.description: A young Muslim (Fardeen Khan) seeks vengeance against a lawman (Amitabh Bachchan) after his father dies during a police crackdown.

page179.title: Dastan
page179.description: The story, a tragic melodrama, was a narrative in flashback.It was inspired from the film Enchantment (1948) directed by Irving Reis. Cited as "one of the biggest commercial hits" in the year 1950

page179.title: Aurat
page179.description: Radha (Sardar Akhtar), has to earn the livelihood for her family, which consists of her husband and three children. Some time later, her husband abandons Radha and the children after he gets to know that she's pregnant with a child.

page179.title: Aakhir Kyon?
page179.description: After discovering her husband's infidelity, a woman (Smita Patil) abandons him and her newborn child and flees to another city.

page179.title: Happy Bhag Jayegi
page179.description: After fleeing an arranged marriage, a feisty Indian woman finds herself stranded in Pakistan where the ex-governor's son helps reunite her with her boyfriend.

page179.title: Dhai Akshar Prem Ke
page179.description: Karan Khanna is an orphan and a captain in the Armed Forces. He's madly in love with beautiful model Nisha, with whom he plans to tie the knot during his next leave.On the way to Nisha, he bumps into Sahiba Grewal who is an eye-witness to a murder.

page179.title: Shriman Satyawadi
page179.description: Though wronged as a child, a young man proves his honesty in the face of greed and corruption.

page180.title: Bhavnao Ko Samjho
page180.description: After his deceased father disowns him, and wills the estate to his unmarried grand-niece, the son bribes a matrimonial agent to come with a groom who will handover the entire estate for a fee.

page180.title: Aunty No. 1
page180.description: An actor poses as a wealthy aunt in order to get a prospective father-in-law to allow his daughters to marry.

page180.title: Ghungroo
page180.description: As he is dying, the Emperor tells Vikram Singh (Sashi Kapoor) that he will become his heir and marry into royalty, as long as he takes orders from his beloved wife, the empress.

page180.title: The Dirty Dancer
page180.description: Mona a small time young prostitute is forced into flesh trading due to her poor financial background. During her meetings once she comes across a director who praises her looks.

page180.title: Himalay Se Ooncha
page180.description: Vijay vows never to climb another mountain after his two brothers are killed during a climbing expedition. When a plane crashes in the deep Himalayas, he initially refuses to aid in the search, until a mother's tears move him to help.

page180.title: Jeevan Dhaara
page180.description: Jeevan Dhaara is a 1982 Indian Bollywood film directed by Tatineni Rama Rao. The film is a remake of the 1974 Tamil film Aval Oru Thodar Kathai. The film stars Rekha, Raj Babbar, Amol Palekar, Sulochana Latkar, Simple Kapadia and Rakesh Roshan.

page181.title: Taqdeer
page181.description: The story is a romantic comedy based on the lost and found formula set against an entertaining backdrop. It was the ninth-highest-grossing Indian film of 1943.

page181.title: Saathi
page181.description: Having seen their father killed by police, two siblings turn to a life of crime but go their separate ways when they cross paths with a gangster.

page181.title: Naya Din Nai Raat
page181.description: A young woman runs away from her house to avoid marriage; in her adventure outside home she meets nine men with different professions and stories. She meets one more man and this changes her life for good.

page181.title: Rafoo Chakkar
page181.description: Two brothers run away from their home with five lack rupees and disobey their fathers order to marry the girls of his choice. After their cash is stolen, they take to crime and are arrested in the false charges of attempted murder and rape.

page181.title: Takkar
page181.description: A convict studies law in prison and becomes a lawyer to seek revenge against the corrupt police officer who framed him on the very day of his marriage.

page181.title: ABCD: Any Body Can Dance
page181.description: When a capable dancer is provoked by the evil design of his employer, naturally he will be out to prove his mettle.

page182.title: Naughty @ 40
page182.description: A 40 year old male virgin with sleep-walking problems finds true love after getting married to a naive child-like woman.

page182.title: Bumper Draw
page182.description: Sunderlal and Farooq who befriend each other in a strange situation. After which, they both encounter Pestonji, an old Parsi man who adds to their existing list of problems.

page182.title: Agni Pareeksha
page182.description: A man (Amol Palekar) falls in love with his mother's (Veena) caretaker (Rameshwari).A 1981 Bollywood film produced by B.R. Chopra and directed by Kamal Majumdar.

page182.title: Jeevan Ek Sanghursh
page182.description: Jeevan Ek Sanghursh is a 1990 Bollywood film directed by Rahul Rawail and produced by D. Rama Naidu. It stars Raakhee, Anil Kapoor and Madhuri Dixit in the leading roles.

page182.title: Babul
page182.description: Two fathers, one poor and the other rich, hope that a wealthy postmaster weds one of their daughters'.

page182.title: Horror Story
page182.description: Seven youngsters decide to spend a night in an abandoned haunted hotel. What they mistook as merely rumors, dawns on them to be the truth as they realize they are not alone inside.

page183.title: Phhir
page183.description: With the help of the police and a psychic, a husband attempts to try and locate his missing wife.

page183.title: Safed Haathi
page183.description: Safed Haathi is an Indian Hindi film made by Tapan Sinha in 1978. It was awarded National Film Award for Best Children's Film in 1978.

page183.title: Tum Mere Ho
page183.description: Shiva is blessed with magical powers of charming snakes. He falls head-over-heels in love with Paro.

page183.title: Kyaa Kool Hai Hum
page183.description: Karan and Rahul are fashion designers and surives on food of others functions. But some twists and confusion changes their life.

page183.title: College Campus
page183.description: This is one college where students do not attend classes at all. Instead, they do all the bad things like consuming liquor and drugs, or fighting among themselves.

page183.title: Bewafa
page183.description: Bewafa is a 1952 Indian film directed by M.L Anand starring the hit Bollywood pair Nargis and Raj Kapoor. It is considered as one of the best films of Raj Kapoor.

page184.title: Roti
page184.description: An escaped criminal finds refuge with the family of a man he killed accidentally.

page184.title: Indian (Hindi)
page184.description: A police commissioner (Sunny Deol) fights a dreaded terrorist, an influential industrialist and corrupt officers.

page184.title: Afsana
page184.description: Afsana is a 1951 Bollywood family drama film. It was the directorial debut of Baldev Raj Chopra and starred Ashok Kumar as twin brothers, starting a trend for such dual roles.

page184.title: Sapoot
page184.description: Traditional rivals Dhaneshwar and Singhania will do anything in their power to kill each other. Each forms a gang and creates chaos in society.

page184.title: Sanam Harjai
page184.description: Raj meets a lawyer K.K. Varma an expert in rape cases pays him the fees on the tips of how not to get caught even if he rapes a girl. Then he meets a beautiful girl Neelu & makes her fall in love.

page184.title: Charnon Ki Saugandh
page184.description: A peasant's son campaigns against a wealthy tyrant, who offers his daughter as a prize.Charanon Ki Saugandh is an action drama, featuring Mithun Chakraborty and Amrita Singh in lead roles.

page185.title: Anokhi Ada
page185.description: A smitten professor (Surendra) lies to a woman (Naseem) who lost her memory in a train accident and tells her that they are a couple.

page185.title: Adalat
page185.description: Village bred farmer, brave, and honest, Dharamchand alias Dharma is thrilled when his wife, Radha, gives birth to a baby boy, who they decide to call Raju.

page185.title: Khauff
page185.description: Neha witnesses the Mafia slaying of a police officer and is forced to give a confession to the police, putting her life in danger. Meanwhile, Neha falls in love with Vicky aka babu and gets married.
