page185.title: Benazir
page185.description: Benazir is a Hindi film released in 1964, Starring Ashok Kumar, Meena Kumari, Shashi Kapoor and Tanuja. Directed by S.Khalil and music by Sachin Dev Burman.

page185.title: Teri Maang Sitaron Se Bhar Doon
page185.description: Kamini accepts the biggest challenge thrown by fate for the sake of her only daughter. She is the symbol of virtue. Sultanbhai, an Emperor of the underworld, whose terror reigns over the entire city, decides to help her in his own way. Why does he do this?

page185.title: Chhailla Babu
page185.description: Chhailla Babu is a suspense thriller, 1977 Bollywood film. The film script was written and produced by Shomu Mukherjee and directed by Joy Mukherjee. Rajesh Khanna plays the title role of Chhailla Babu.

page186.title: Asli-Naqli
page186.description: Seth Laxmi Narayan and his wife had a son who was taken from them when he was very young. They only know that he has a locket around his neck.

page186.title: Souten Ki Beti
page186.description: A young girl's peaceful life is disturbed when her controversial family background is brought out into the open.

page186.title: Shera
page186.description: Shera is a 1999 Hindi-language Indian feature film directed by T L V Prasad and produced by Rajiv Babbar, starring Vinitha, Rami Reddy and Gulshan Grover

page186.title: Meherbaan
page186.description: Meherbaan is the story of a family man, who has to decide between commitment, ethics and love between his 2 women.

page186.title: Market
page186.description: The film follows the story of Muskaan Bano from her life in Indian brothels after being sold there by her Arab husband to her attempts at revenge later in life.

page186.title: Fiffty Fiffty
page186.description: Thakur Virendra Singh lives a wealthy lifestyle in India along with his wife and a son, Kumar (Ranjeet). His relative Bihari (Om Shivpuri) is envious, and successfully switches his son, Kishan (Rajesh Khanna), with Kumar, and also ends up killing Virendra.

page187.title: Aan Baan
page187.description: Ruler Raja Bahadur spends his days indulging in women and alcohol with borrowed money, making many enemies.

page187.title: Gair Kaanooni
page187.description: When police officer Kapil Khanna discovers that his son was abducted at birth, and switched with a girl, he spends the next 20 years trying to track down his missing son, and finally finds him living with his enemy.

page187.title: Do Chor
page187.description: When a mysterious burglar robs the homes of several important people, leaving behind only a swastika, the police go on a massive hunt to track down the criminal.

page187.title: Dil Aur Deewar
page187.description: Dil Aur Deewar is a 1978 Bollywood film produced by D. Ramanaidu on Vijaya & Suresh Productions Combines banner, directed by K. Bapaiah. Starring Jeetendra, Moushumi Chatterjee, Rekha in lead roles and music composed by Laxmikant–Pyarelal.

page187.title: Barsaat: A Sublime Love Story
page187.description: Arav travels to America and falls in love with Anna. He returns to India when his father becomes ill and reunites with his wife.

page187.title: Sangdil
page187.description: A loose adaptation of Charlotte Bronte's classic, Jane Eyre. In this version childhood sweethearts are separated and grow up in different worlds. The girl is brought up to be a priestess while the boy grows up to be a dejected 'thakur'.

page188.title: Dulha Bikta Hai
page188.description: Deepak has to get his two sisters married but is in a fix as the grooms demand dowries. So Deepak plans to marry the grooms' sisters to get the money.

page188.title: Do Premee
page188.description: Do Premee is a 1980 Indian Bollywood film directed by Raj Khosla and produced by Kundan A. Thadani. It stars Rishi Kapoor and Moushumi Chatterjee in pivotal roles.

page188.title: Dilwaala
page188.description: Ravi and his sister Soumitra strive to bring justice although in very different ways.

page188.title: Dil Pardesi Ho Gayaa
page188.description: A soldier from the Indian army is abducted and held hostage by the Pakistani army. His brother changes his identity and enters Pakistan to rescue him.

page188.title: Dekha Pyar Tumhara
page188.description: Dekha Pyar Tumhara is a 1985 Hindi-language Indian feature film directed by Virendra Sharma, starring Kamal Haasan and Rati Agnihotri in leading roles.

page188.title: Yun Hota Toh Kya Hota
page188.description: Fate links the lives of a newlywed (Konkona Sen Sharma), a stockbroker (Irfan Khan) on the lam, a student and a talent agent.

page189.title: Sikandar
page189.description: Sikandar or Sikander is a 1941 epic Bollywood film directed by Sohrab Modi and starring Prithviraj Kapoor as Alexander the Great.

page189.title: Naunihal
page189.description: Naunihal was a 1967 Hindi drama film directed by Raj Marbros and starring Sanjeev Kumar, Balraj Sahni, and Indrani Mukherjee in lead roles.

page189.title: Anurodh
page189.description: After the accidental death of her husband (Rajesh Khanna), a woman struggles to raise their child by herself.

page189.title: Jai Vikraanta
page189.description: When Choudhary Amar Singh is killed because of the money he owes a cruel landowner, his son decides to avenge him.

page189.title: Dulaara
page189.description: When Raja and Priya fall in love, Priya's brother frames Raja for murder. The only way Raja can clear his name is to find the real killer.

page189.title: Ayee Milan Ki Bela
page189.description: Shyam and Ranjeet have been friends since childhood, but when they fall in love with the same woman, Ranjeet makes furious attempts to ruin Shyam's reputation.

page190.title: Thanedaar
page190.description: When the notorious crime boss Thakur (Kiran Kumar) discovers he's being pursued by Insp. Chandra (Dalip Tahil), he hires hit men to get Chandra out of the way. When Chandra is assassinated, it leaves his two sons to grow up without a father.

page190.title: Mohabbat
page190.description: Mohabbat is a 1985 Indian Bollywood film directed by Bapu. It stars Anil Kapoor and Vijeta Pandit in pivotal roles. It's a remake of 1982 Tamil movie Thooral Ninnu Pochchu

page190.title: Kanyadaan
page190.description: The plot revolved around the social issue of child marriage. Rekha and Amar are married off as children, they grow up to fall in love with different people and are ultimately unacceptable of the marriage performed in childhood.

page190.title: Dariya Dil
page190.description: Dhaniram, a wealthy businessman, is known for being a miser, and is hated by even his own family, who plot to kill him and take over his fortune.

page190.title: Professor Ki Padosan
page190.description: Vidyadhar consumes a potion to become invisible in order to escape his wife Shobha's ire when she learns of his affair with Menka.

page190.title: Khuda Kay Liye
page190.description: Two brothers, both artistes, experience major changes at the hands of Islamic fundamentalists and the U.S. Government; while their female cousin is abducted, forced to marry, and sexually molested.

page191.title: Fun 2shh
page191.description: Watch Fun2ssh a comedy movie where a trio of hapless security guards travels backwards in time to a 10th century royal court. CHindi Chor, the well-known thief wins a challenge to steal the Emperor’s fabled crown.

page191.title: Akayla
page191.description: When inspector Vijay meets club dancer Sapna, he falls in love with her and wants them to get married, but he has to gain permission from a gangster.

page191.title: Tathastu
page191.description: A poor family's only child is diagnosed with an ailment of the heart, and the only way for him to survive is by undergoing heart transplantation.

page191.title: Sangam
page191.description: A woman must choose between two very different men, each of whom claims to love her.

page191.title: Natak
page191.description: Natak is a 1975 Bollywood film directed by Sohanlal Kanwar. The film stars Vijay Arora and Moushumi Chatterjee.

page191.title: Mera Faisla
page191.description: Mera Faisla is an Indian film directed by Rajendra Singh Babu and released in 1984. The movie stars Sanjay Dutt, Rati Agnihotri, Jayapradha, Kader Khan.

page192.title: Jawaab
page192.description: A journalist, Mehta, on the run from Jagmohan's men, leaves an envelope with singer, Ramprasad Singh, and asks him to deliver it to Inspector J.S. Sharma at Bandra (Bomay) Police Station. Subsequently, Mehta is killed.

page192.title: Rattan
page192.description: Rattan or Ratan is a 1944 Indian Bollywood film starring Swaran Lata, Karan Dewan and Amir Bano. It was a highly successful movie of 1944.

page192.title: Udhaar Ki Zindagi
page192.description: After the wealthy Sitaram refuses to allow his son to marry the woman he loves, his son elopes leaving Sitaram to clear up the mess with the family he had arranged his son's marriage with

page192.title: Aaram
page192.description: Aaram is a 1951 Indian Hindi film directed by D.D. Kashyap and starring Dev Anand, Madhubala, Prem Nath and Talat Mahmood.

page192.title: Shatranj Ke Khilari
page192.description: In 1856, two obsessive chess players fail to notice British rule extending into their Indian province.

page192.title: Jab Jab Phool Khile
page192.description: When Rita goes to Kashmir to relax, she meets and falls in love with Raja, but her father disapproves of their relationship, and wants Rita to marry a man he has chosen for her.

page193.title: Dhoop Chhaon
page193.description: Concerned about the outbreak of plague in a distant rural village in India, Dr. D.D. Sinha asks a number of prominent doctors to go there and treat the ailing and prevent the disease from spreading.

page193.title: Chingari 1971
page193.description: Chingari hindi fulll movie starring Sanjay Khan, Leena Chandavarkar, Shatrughan Sinha, Pran, Rehman, Mehmood Directed by Ram Maheswary. Produced by Pannalal Maheswary. Music composed by Ravi.

page193.title: Bobby
page193.description: The neglected son (Rishi Kapoor) of a wealthy couple finds comfort in the arms of a teenage schoolgirl (Dimple Kapadia).

page193.title: Shagoon
page193.description: A man and woman go through with their wedding even though the astrological charts foretell disaster.

page193.title: Samrat Chandragupt
page193.description: This movie depicts the personal life of Samrat Chandragupt, his trials, tribulations, and frustrations, as well as the challenges he faces to reclaim his kingdom; face-off the threat from Sikander.

page193.title: Parama (Hindi)
page193.description: The movie is about a 40-year-old married woman, Paroma whose well-settled, very normal and predictable life turns upside down when Rahul, an expatriate photo-journalist working for a magazine chooses her to pose for a photo essay.

page194.title: Daasi
page194.description: When the groom is killed on the morning of an arranged wedding, the bride's aunt quickly arranges a marriage to a blind singer.

page194.title: Bombai Ka Babu
page194.description: While posing as a family's long-lost son, a fugitive criminal falls in love with their daughter.

page194.title: Bahurani
page194.description: Amit (Rakesh Roshan) is a big city boy, but his parents want him to marry a village girl, Madhuri (Rekha). Amit reluctantly agrees and goes through the wedding ceremony, but on the pretext that the dowry gold is not genuine, leaves his bride.

page194.title: Antim Nyay
page194.description: Journalist Adesh has made it his personal mission to take on corrupt businessman Lala Ranjan in the police department. One fateful night, Adesh is killed in front of his would-be son-in-law, Jai Singh, who finds himself framed for the terrible murder.

page194.title: Teesri Kasam
page194.description: A naive villager (Raj Kapoor) falls in love with a traveling performance artist (Waheeda Rehman).

page194.title: Shakka
page194.description: Shakka is a 1981 Bollywood, Action film produced by Kailash Chopra on The Roop Enterprises banner and directed by Sham Ralhan. Starring Jeetendra, Simple Kapadia in the lead roles and music composed by Rajesh Roshan.

page195.title: Janam Janam Ke Phere
page195.description: A man's childhood sweetheart marries him, hoping to convert him from an atheist into a believer, but all her efforts go in vain.

page195.title: Deewaar (2004)
page195.description: A man (Akshaye Khanna) sneaks into Pakistan to rescue his father (Amitabh Bachchan), a prisoner of war for the past 33 years.

page195.title: Bluff Master
page195.description: A con man (Shammi Kapoor) tries to give up his shady ways to marry the woman of his dreams.

page195.title: Aakhri Badla
page195.description: Aakhri Badla is a 1989 Hindi-language Indian feature film directed by Mangal Chakraborty, starring Mithun Chakraborty, Yogita Bali, Prem Chopra, Tom Alter, Jayshree T. and Shiva Rindani.Aakhri Badla is also dubbed in Bengali as "Swarna Trishna.

page195.title: Nazrana
page195.description: A scheming woman (Priti Sapru) and a housemaid (Sridevi) play pivotal roles in the rocky marriage of an advertising executive (Rajesh Khanna) and his wife (Smita Patil).

page195.title: Mera Karam Mera Dharam
page195.description: Ajay lives in poverty with this mother until a rich uncle bequeaths him a small fortune, but little does Ajay know that the fortune comes with consequences.

page196.title: Commando
page196.description: Chander, a commando in the army, attempts to expose the corruption of his commander who is in cahoots with an international crime don.

page196.title: Aanchal
page196.description: Romantic complications abound when a man plots to separate his cousin (Rekha) and her suitor (Rajesh Khanna).

page196.title: Champion
page196.description: A policeman must protect a child whose parents were killed in a plane bombing.The film CHAMPION is a tale about a man who has a quest, a dream to be the best of the best.

page196.title: Trimurti
page196.description: Brothers (Shahrukh Khan, Anil Kapoor, Jackie Shroff) band together for a time, separate, then reunite for revenge on the man who killed their father and jailed their mother.

page196.title: The Great Gambler
page196.description: Gambling expert Jai is discovered by a crooked casino owner, who hires him to play, and easily defeat, rich businessmen. But Jai also gets mixed up in a more elaborate scheme involving an arranged marriage to Mala, the daughter of a wealthy man.

page196.title: Sanam Bewafa
page196.description: Salman falls in love with Ruksar but their fathers, despite being neighbours, are sworn enemies. The couple end up marrying but they are shocked when they finally discover the reason why their fathers allow the marriage to take place.

page197.title: Saajan Ki Saheli
page197.description: A woman (Nutan) rejects her illegitimate baby but meets her years later as an adult (Rekha).

page197.title: Rui Ka Bojh
page197.description: When an elderly man (Pankaj Kapur) decides to divide his property, he realizes his family values him only for his wealth.

page197.title: Raat
page197.description: The Sharma move to a semi-urban location to a house which has a reputation. When strange things start happening in the house, the family begin to wonder if what is happening is supernatural.

page197.title: Raaste Kaa Patthar
page197.description: A bachelor (Amitabh Bachchan) falls in love with a woman (Neeta Khayani) who's engaged to his boss (Prem Chopra).

page197.title: Prem Kahani
page197.description: Prem Kahani is a 1975 Hindi film produced by Lekhraj Khosla, and directed and written by Raj Khosla. The film stars Rajesh Khanna in lead role opposite Mumtaz and supporting cast includes Shashi Kapoor, Vinod Khanna and K. N Singh.

page197.title: Pestonjee
page197.description: A fussbudget (Naseeruddin Shah) falls in love with the masochistic wife (Shabana Azmi) of his best friend (Anupam Kher).

page198.title: Arvind Desai Ki Ajeeb Dastaan
page198.description: A rich businessman's son enjoys many dalliances until a marriage is arranged.Directed by Saeed Akhtar Mirza and starring Dilip Dhawan, Anjali Paigankar, Sriram Lagoo, Rohini Hattangadi, Satish Shah and Om Puri.

page198.title: Anuradha
page198.description: A well known singer gives up her trade to marry a young doctor but is later forced to make a decision about the worth of her marriage.

page198.title: Ab Dilli Dur Nahin
page198.description: A youth (Romi) enlists the aid of a pickpocket to help him prove that his father did not commit murder.

page198.title: Aaye Din Bahar Ke
page198.description: Ravi is an eligible bachelor, who lives with his mother. He meets with beautiful Kanchan and both fall in love. But fate has other plans for them, as Ravi soon finds out that Kanchan is already married and has a child.

page198.title: Masti
page198.description: Complications arise when three frustrated men (Vivek Oberoi, Ritesh Deshmukh) plan to cheat on their wives.

page198.title: Majboor
page198.description: Honest retired judge justice Deenanath lives a happy life with his wife and two sons, lawyer Ravi and inspector Sunil. One day Ravi brings home a poor girl Sharda, to rehabilitate as she has no place to live after her father's death.

page199.title: Kanhaiya
page199.description: Kanhaiya is a 1959 Bollywood film produced by Sant Singh Pachhi and directed by Om Prakash. The film stars Raj Kapoor, Nutan and Lalita Pawar

page199.title: Jalwa
page199.description: Kapil's younger brother, Buntu, dies as a result of a drug overdose. Kapil vows to put an end to drugs and drug-dealers, by joining the police. He soon attains the title of C.I.D. Inspector. He lives in Bombay with his mom.

page199.title: Damini
page199.description: A down-and-out lawyer (Sunny Deol) helps a woman (Meenakshi Sheshadri) after her brother-in-law rapes a maid.

page199.title: Ship Of Theseus
page199.description: The film explores questions of identity, justice, beauty, meaning and death through an experimental photographer, an ailing monk and a young stockbroker.

page199.title: Mere Apne
page199.description: Anandi lives in a small village, until one day when a distant relative asks her to move to the big city with him and his family.

page199.title: Manzil Manzil
page199.description: Mr. Malhotra would like his daughter to marry Pawan. She likes that idea, and agrees to meet Pawan. On her way to see him, she meets another man and both fall in love.

page200.title: Khwab
page200.description: A man (Mithun Chakraborty) rises to fame and fortune, but his world comes crashing down when he is arrested for the murder of a pregnant woman.

page200.title: Joroo Ka Ghulam
page200.description: Joroo Ka Ghulam is a 1972 Hindi-language comedy film. Directed by A. Bhimsingh, it stars Rajesh Khanna, Nanda, Om Prakash, Ramesh Deo and Jayshree T. The music is by Kalyanji Anandji.The movie was remade in Kannada as Anukoolakkobba Ganda.

page200.title: Aap Kaa Surroor
page200.description: A famous rock star must prove that he cares about his true love after he is framed for murder.

page200.title: Inkaar 1978
page200.description: A kidnapper refuses to release his victim after receiving ransom money from a businessman.

page200.title: Ghar Dwaar (1985)
page200.description: Chanda and her mother face humiliation at the hands of Dhanraj and his family. Chanda swears to avenge this by destroying the love that binds this family.

page200.title: Dillagi (1978)
page200.description: Dillagi is a 1978 romantic comedy directed by Basu Chatterjee, based on Bengali novel 'Chemistry O Kahaani' by Bimal Kar. It stars Dharmendra playing SwarnKamal - a newly appointed Sanskrit professor in a girls' college.

page201.title: Pyaar Ka Saaya
page201.description: A wealthy man is killed by his vile cousin with the intention of taking over his property. When his widow is abused by the cousin, his soul returns to caution her and protect her from other dangers.

page201.title: Mr. And Mrs. Iyer
page201.description: A woman (Konkona Sensharma) saves a photographer (Rahul Bose) from religious extremists, and together they become stranded in a town under martial law.

page201.title: Grand Masti
page201.description: Meet, Prem and Amar look to have a blast at their college reunion, though they soon find themselves in another predicament.

page201.title: Zindagi Zindagi
page201.description: Zindagi Zindagi is a 1972 Bollywood romance film directed by Tapan Sinha. The film stars Deb Mukherjee, Waheeda Rehman, Farida Jalal and Ashok Kumar. The film revolves around life in a village hospital and has casteism as an issue at its core.

page201.title: Zakhmi Aurat (1988)
page201.description: A raped cop abandons her uniform to get revenge against her attackers by devastating means.

page201.title: Uski Roti
page201.description: A woman delivers food to her husband who works as a bus driver and lives with a mistress.

page202.title: Tumhari Kasam
page202.description: Siblings Vidya and Raja are separated when Raja takes up a life of petty theft and runs away; Vidya loses her sight in a car accident, leaving her alone and unable to locate her brother, fearing she won't meet him again.

page202.title: Tango Charlie
page202.description: Army Sepoy Tarun Chauhan crosses a dangerous combat zone in Northern India while on duty, and he suddenly finds himself in the middle of a war.

page202.title: Sweekar
page202.description: Sweekar is a Social hindi movie, directed by Sudhendu Roy, starring Mahendra Sandhu, Hansa Maker along with others.

page202.title: Ram Shastra
page202.description: Honest cop Ram is on a quest to wipe out the Mafia's Don Donga, but soon finds himself on the other side of the law.

page202.title: Pyar Ke Naam Qurbaan
page202.description: A man decides to avenge his humiliation by abducting a woman who had him beaten up and arrested, but his action invites the wrath of her brothers, who now want him dead at any cost.

page202.title: Paayal
page202.description: Paayal is a 1992 Bollywood film starring Bhagyashree along with her real life husband Himalaya Dasani. She plays a spoilt brat of a rich father.

page203.title: Nazar
page203.description: An antique dealer-cum-money lender lives in a spacious flat in a multi-storied building in Mumbai with his aunt. Though middle-aged himself, he marries a 17-year-old orphan girl and brings her home. The film starts off with the young wife committing suicide.

page203.title: Nagin
page203.description: Vijay saves the life of a man who is attacked by a wild hawk. He then realizes that he has saved the life of a miraculous snake that has the power to appear human and has been courting Vijay's beloved.

page203.title: Nadaan
page203.description: Nadaan is a 1971 Bollywood drama film directed by Deven Verma. The film stars Asha Parekh and Madan Puri.

page203.title: Nachnewala Gaanewale
page203.description: Story of Jaggu and Maggu who are two friends who live together; sing and dance at weddings, anniversaries, births, and parties for a living.

page203.title: Mr. X In Bombay
page203.description: Shobha Mathur's father is a professor who is carrying out experiments on various issues. One day while doing so, he makes an employee named Manohar drink a portion, which results in his death.

page203.title: Mother
page203.description: When Asha becomes pregnant, after having had affairs with three men simultaneously, she moves to Mauritius to raise her daughter, content that no one knows about her past.

page204.title: Mera Muqaddar
page204.description: Laxmi lives happily with her sons Krishna and Jeet; jealous Veerendra Pratap wants to take away Laxmi's business and create a rift between the two brothers.

page204.title: Massey Sahib
page204.description: Massey Sahib is a 1985 Hindi drama film directed by Pradip Krishen, starring Raghubir Yadav in the title role. It was Krishen's first film, and was an adaptation from Joyce Cary's 1939 novel Mister Johnson.

page204.title: Luck By Chance
page204.description: When Vikram gets tapped to play the male lead in a Bollywood film, he can't believe his luck. But it may ruin his relationship with his girlfriend.

page204.title: Lover Boy (1985 Film)
page204.description: Lover Boy is a 1985 Indian Bollywood film produced and directed by Shomu Mukherjee. It stars Rajiv Kapoor, Meenakshi Seshadri and Anita Raj in pivotal roles.

page204.title: Khota Paisa
page204.description: Khota Paisa is a Social hindi movie, directed by M. Sadiq, starring Dhumal, Johnny Walker, Rajan Haksar, Shyama along with others.

page204.title: Jaan
page204.description: Police Commissioner Suryadev Singh appoints Karan as Kajal's bodyguard as she is facing danger from Vishamber. The truth is that Karan is Vishamber's man who is sent to kill Kajal.

page205.title: International Crook
page205.description: Superintendent of police, Rajesh, is asked to look after a police station in Goa, where he meets his old friend; Rajesh finds himself in a dilemma where he must re-evaluate his commitment to their friendship.

page205.title: Hum Naujawan
page205.description: Hum Naujawan is a 1985 Bollywood drama film directed by Dev Anand. He himself played the central character in the film dedicated to young students.

page205.title: Hum Hain Lajawaab
page205.description: A strict man throws his son out of the house for marrying out of his consent; years later, when his grandson is born, he decides to forgive his son, who dies soon leaving his grandson behind. He then sends his second son to get his grandson home.

page205.title: Heer Ranjha
page205.description: An epic Love story in which two lovers Heer and Ranjha get along with each other but unfortunately their Love story is not easy. Ranjha fights his way to get Heer but he is not able to do so.

page205.title: Hatyara
page205.description: One day Daulat accidentally kills a man, and overcome with remorse, he turns himself in and receives a life sentence. While in jail he provides for the man's widow and son and is released early for good conduct, but although free, his past interferes with his life.

page205.title: Hariyali Aur Rasta
page205.description: Hariyali Aur Rasta is a 1962 Hindi film produced and directed by Vijay Bhatt. It had Manoj Kumar and Mala Sinha as leads. The film has music by Shankar Jaikishan.

page206.title: Humjoli
page206.description: Humjoli is a 1970 Bollywood drama film, produced by Prasan Kapoor on Tirupati Pictures banner and directed by T. R. Ramanna. The film stars Jeetendra, Leena Chandavarkar in the lead roles and music is composed by Laxmikant Pyarelal.

page206.title: Haqeeqat
page206.description: Inspector Arjun Singh is assigned as inspector-in-charge of a police station, but his actions soon put him into the bad books of a local politician.

page206.title: Do Bigha Zamin
page206.description: A debt-ridden family moves to Calcutta to raise the money it needs to save land from a greedy overlord.

page206.title: Dekh Bhai Dekh
page206.description: A woman faces challenges after she and her associates steal a Murthy of Bhagwan Shri Kishan from her estranged in-laws.

page206.title: Duvidha
page206.description: A young man's marriage is challenged by a ghost that falls in love with his wife.

page206.title: Chaand Kaa Tukdaa
page206.description: A wealthy young man fulfills his mother's dying wish by traveling to India to find a suitable bride.

page207.title: Biwi O Biwi
page207.description: A colonel wants his daughter to marry a military man instead of the civilian she loves.

page207.title: Aulad
page207.description: Believing his wife to be dead, a man lets a woman nurse and bring up his infant son - until he finds out that his wife is still alive, and wants the baby back.

page207.title: Anpadh
page207.description: An illiterate woman decides to educate herself after a series of events leave her homeless, widowed and pregnant.

page207.title: Anari
page207.description: A tale of revenge by three overprotective brothers unfolds when they learn that their sister, Rajnandini, has married her bodyguard.

page207.title: Andolan
page207.description: Two brothers attend the same college. One brother falls in love, while the other prefers to joke around. Where will their paths take them when they leave college?

page207.title: Alaap
page207.description: A widowed lawyer wants his wayward son to join his law firm, but the son is more concerned with spending time in the slums.

page208.title: Achanak
page208.description: A surgeon tries to save an escaped convict who has been shot. However, if the escapee survives, the surgeon's efforts would be in vain, since the patient had been sentenced to death.

page208.title: Aao Pyaar Karen
page208.description: Aao Pyaar Karen is a 1964 Hindi-language film starring Joy Mukherjee and Saira Banu. Produced by S. Mukherjee. Directed by R. K. Nayyar. Music composed by Usha Khanna and songs penned by Rajendra Krishna

page208.title: Aaj Ke Sholey
page208.description: A former prisoner kidnaps the child of the man who committed the crime for which he served ten years; demanding ransom for the child's release, the father starts a desperate search for his son.

page208.title: Aaghaaz
page208.description: The film is the story of Govind Narang, an honest and chivalrous man from a small village in Punjab. He falls in love with Sudha, but marries Masterji's daughter, Pushpa, to save her from public ridicule.

page208.title: Aag Aur Shola
page208.description: A police inspector and a beaten man ask Vishal (Jeetendra) for help in bringing Nagesh (Shakti Kapoor) to justice.

page208.title: Suraj
page208.description: Sangram seeks revenge by the making the king's son a bandit. The bandit kidnaps Princess Anuradha and is soon caught.

page209.title: Dishoom
page209.description: When India's top batsman goes missing in the Middle East, two mismatched cops must team up for a 36-hour manhunt before the cricket final.

page209.title: Madaari
page209.description: When Nirmal loses his family in a disaster caused by government corruption, he embarks on a journey seeking accountability and revenge.

page209.title: Laal Rang
page209.description: A social drama full of black humor set in the milieu of Karnal's blood theft mafia.

page209.title: Budhia Singh Born To Run
page209.description: A biopic about Budhia Singh, the world's youngest marathon runner whose story garnered controversy and inspiration around the world.

page209.title: 7 Hours To Goo
page209.description: The film is a fast-paced investigative thriller set in Mumbai, present day. Inspired by the true event, the film revolves around a hostage crisis and what happens within 7 hours after that incident.

page209.title: Bollywood Diaries
page209.description: The passionate journey of three Bollywood fanatics who wish to make it big in the industry.

page210.title: Meri Jung
page210.description: When lawyer Thakral falsely accuses Deepak Verma of murder, Deepak is executed, leaving behind a wife, who goes insane with grief, and a son with a need for vengeance. Deepak's son, Arun, goes through rigorous training to become a defense lawyer.

page210.title: Tum Bin
page210.description: Shekhar accidentally kills his associate Amar, and decides to watch over Amar's company and take care of his family and friends. However, he falls in love with Amar's fiancé Piya.

page210.title: BHK Bhalla@Halla.Kom
page210.description: The story of a common man who is struggling to have his own house in the city of dreams Mumbai, It's a light hearted situational comedy.

page210.title: Jugni
page210.description: Vibhavari, a young woman music director from Mumbai, is working on her first big break in the Hindi film industry. When work and home affairs with her live-in boyfriend, Sid, hit a high tide, she hits the road with a glint of hope; to find music.

page210.title: Great Grand Masti
page210.description: Amar, Meet and Prem go into a small town where they encounter a 'femme fatale' in the form of Ragini. Ragini is everything they had dreamed of, but she slowly turns into their worst nightmare!

page210.title: Sultan
page210.description: Sultan is a classic underdog tale about a wrestler's journey, looking for a comeback by defeating all odds. Will he emerge victorious?

page211.title: Junooniyat
page211.description: Captain Jahan Bakshi rescues a Punjabi girl, Suhani. This starts a friendship that evolves into a passionate love affair.

page211.title: Housefull 3
page211.description: A father doesn't want his three daughters to get married. Now, it's up to three men to try to and convince the father that they're a good fit for his daughters.

page211.title: Phobia
page211.description: An agoraphobic young woman, traumatized by past events, finds herself trapped and terrorized in her own home.

page211.title: Udta Punjab
page211.description: A story that revolves around drug abuse in the affluent north Indian State of Punjab and how the youth there have succumbed to it en-masse resulting in a socio-economic decline.

page211.title: Waiting
page211.description: A retired professor whose wife has been in a coma for eight months meets a terrified young wife whose husband has slipped into a coma after a sudden accident. Will grief drive them both insane, or can two lonely strangers support each other?

page211.title: Raman Raghav 2.0
page211.description: Set in present day Mumbai the story follows the life of a serial killer Ramanna who is inspired by an infamous serial killer from the 1960s, Raman Raghav. A young cop keeps growing as he closely follows him without his knowledge

page212.title: Guddu Ki Gun
page212.description: It tells the tale of Guddu who shamelessly flirts with the married women of the town. One day, during one of his sexcapades, he is cursed by a woman's grandfather, after which his manhood turns to solid gold!  A Bollywood Adult comedy film !!

page212.title: Sarbjit
page212.description: Biopic of Sarabjit Singh, a farmer residing at Bhikiwind, Punjab, near the Indo-Pak border, crossed the border after having a couple of drinks. However, he was mistaken to be an Indian spy and was sentenced with capital punishment.

page212.title: One Night Stand
page212.description: The story is about Urvil Raisingh and Celina who meet at an event and a memorable night later. Returning back home they continue with their lives. The memories of Celina haunt Urvil. What happens next forms the crux of the unfolding drama.

page212.title: 1947 Earth
page212.description: It's 1947 and the borderlines between India and Pakistan are being drawn. A young girl bears witnesses to tragedy as her ayah is caught between the love of two men and the rising tide of political and religious violence.

page212.title: Satyagraha
page212.description: A corporate go-getter sees his priorities shift when a personal tragedy brings him face-to-face with political corruption.

page212.title: Apaharan
page212.description: Story of a tumultuous and complex relationship between a father (Mohan Agashe) and son (Ajay Devgan), set against the backdrop of a thriving kidnapping industry in the Hindi heartland of Bihar.

page213.title: Awara
page213.description: Judge Raghunath is a wealthy district judge who convicts Jagga, a man whose father was a criminal, of rape, on little evidence. Jagga later escapes and kidnaps the judge's wife Leela for revenge. Globally, it was the second highest-grossing 1951 film.

page213.title: Pyaar Kiya To Darna Kya
page213.description: A wealthy collegian (Kajol) falls in love with an heir apparent (Salman Khan), but her domineering cousin (Arbaaz Khan) orders her to end the affair.

page213.title: Rann
page213.description: Rann is about a battle between large unorganized forces (news channels), political parties and industrial czars. Truth Is Terrible

page213.title: Lage Raho Munna Bhai
page213.description: Hari Prasad Sharma and his wife Parvati come from their village to Mumbai to visit their son, Dr. Murli. They also decide to get Murli married so they meet Dr. Asthana, but their son is actually an underworld don known as Munna Bhai.

page213.title: Vidhaata
page213.description: A man (Sanjay Dutt) uncovers dark secrets while seeking revenge for the death of a friend (Sanjeev Kumar).

page213.title: Anand
page213.description: The story of a terminally ill man who wishes to live life to the full before the inevitable occurs, as told by his best friend.

page214.title: Shaurya
page214.description: Maj. Siddhant Chaudhary, an Indian Army lawyer, attempts to defend Capt. Javed Khan who is accused of killing a decorated officer. The problem is that Khan does not wish to be defended and freely admits to his crime.

page214.title: Lamhe
page214.description: Yash Chopra's most cherished film with soul stirring music is a story of moments - moments of passion, of ecstasy and of life-changing love.

page214.title: Vivah
page214.description: Poonam, a traditionally brought-up young woman, is to marry Prem, a groom chosen by her uncle. Poonam and Prem's faith and love are to be tested however, when an accident occurs and Poonam might be scarred for life.

page214.title: Geet Gaata Chal
page214.description: A couple take in an orphan boy, who flees their home when he learns they want him to marry their daughter.

page214.title: Aa Ab Laut Chalen
page214.description: An Indian (Akshaye Khanna) encounters misfortune as he seeks friends, love and fortune in the United States.

page214.title: Amanush
page214.description: Amanush is a 1975 Indian action drama film made in both Hindi and Bengali produced and directed by Shakti Samanta. The film stars Sharmila Tagore, Uttam Kumar, Utpal Dutt and Asit Sen. Both the versions were a hit.

page215.title: Chhalia
page215.description: The story is loosely based on the "White Nights" written by Fyodor Dostoyevsky but is focused on the issue of estranged wives and children in the aftermath of Partition.

page215.title: Taqdeerwala
page215.description: A remake of 1994 Telugu film Yamaleela.A young man resorts to mischievous antics and shortcuts to earn money so he can please his widowed mother and gift her the palace that she once lived in.

page215.title: SilSila
page215.description: A man (Amitabh Bachchan) feels obliged to marry the pregnant fiancee of his late brother (Shashi Kapoor).Can an unconventional love that runs afoul of societal expectations survive?

page215.title: Dhoom 2
page215.description: Back in action DHOOM:2 reinvents the action comedy genre and propels it into the 21st century. Go on and enjoy the ride once again with Jai and Ali.

page215.title: Gangs Of Wasseypur
page215.description: A clash between Sultan and Shahid Khan leads to the expulsion of Khan from Wasseypur, and ignites a deadly blood feud spanning three generations.

page215.title: Gangster A Love Story
page215.description: In love with a gangster, a woman abuses alcohol and has an affair with a bar singer (Emraan Hashmi).

page216.title: Badmaash Company
page216.description: In the 1990s, Four young friends get together in Mumbai to start a company, which turns out to be an instant hit due to their unorthodox methods.

page216.title: Omkara (2006)
page216.description: A politically-minded enforcer's misguided trust in his lieutenant leads him to suspect his wife of infidelity in this adaptation of Shakespeare's 'Othello'.

page216.title: Mere Yaar Ki Shaadi Hai
page216.description: Sanjay wakes up to the truth that he loves his best friend Sanjana reluctantly but surely and sets off on a noble mission - to break her wedding.

page216.title: OMG Oh My God
page216.description: A shopkeeper takes God to court when his shop is destroyed by an earthquake.Based on the acclaimed Gujarati play, `Kanji Virrudh Kanji` and Hindi play, `Kishen v/s Kanhaiya`.

page216.title: Baaghi (2016)
page216.description: Shortly after arriving at a martial arts academy, a troubled young man falls for the girl being wooed by his rival.

page216.title: Barefoot To Goa
page216.description: A parable on the moribund human bonds in a fast-paced world, which is a warning that poignantly highlights the futility of life and death.

page217.title: Te3n
page217.description: A grandfather, a priest, and a police officer investigate the case of a kidnapped child. A gripping thriller that brings together these two parallel investigations into the 2 kidnappings and builds up into an explosive, emotionally-charged film.

page217.title: Saagar
page217.description: A woman's (Madhur Jaffrey) scheme against her grandson (Rishi Kapoor) threatens the livelihood of town fishermen.

page217.title: Rocky Handsome
page217.description: When a drug mafia abducts an eight-year-old, Kabir Ahlawat sets out on a mission to hunt down the abductors.

page217.title: Bade Dilwala
page217.description: A man (Sunil Shetty) upsets his wife by splitting a winning lottery ticket with a waitress (Priya Gill).

page217.title: Hu Tu Tu
page217.description: A young woman (Sunil Shetty) finds herself kidnapped by a former flame whose gang is demanding that her chief minister mother release one of their members.

page217.title: Bandit Queen
page217.description: The movie tells the story of the bandit queen Phoolan Devi who was sent to prison in 1983 and got free in 1994.(Mature Content)

page218.title: Miss Teacher
page218.description: Rose Dey is the new teacher at the university. She is very attractive and is a nymphomaniac. At the university, Rose meets Tanvesh and an affair begins.

page218.title: Hum Dono
page218.description: An army officer (Dev Anand) must break the news to the fragile wife (Nanda) of his look-alike colleague that her husband was lost in battle.

page218.title: Hulchul
page218.description: Deva's parents die when he is very young, and he is adopted by ACP Siddhant. As he grows up, he assists his adoptive father in his police work, and even helps free his half brother who was framed for murder.

page218.title: Hip Hip Hurray
page218.description: Sandeep Chowdhary is waiting to start his first job, so he takes up a temporary job as a sports instructor in a school at Ranchi, where he encounters an apathetic school principal and develops a relationship with a history teacher named Anuradha Roy.

page218.title: Hijack
page218.description: A plane flying to Delhi is commandeered by 6 terrorists who order the release of their accomplice. They threaten to kill the hostages otherwise.

page218.title: Hero (1983 Film)
page218.description: A hit man kidnaps the daughter of a police commissioner, then falls in love with her. Jackie Shroff played the lead role, also called "Jackie", and achieved stardom through this film.

page219.title: Goal
page219.description: The story of a struggling Southall club facing closure, where the manager takes his players to the home of the Premier League champions, Manchester United, to inspire them to winning ways.

page219.title: Gehrayee
page219.description: When a successful manager decides to sell his plantation in his ancestral village to another company, his young daughter begins acting very strangely.

page219.title: Funtoosh
page219.description: Ram goes crazy after death of his mother and sister, once released from mental hospital comes across Mr Kirorimal who insures him and wants him dead for the money. However Ram ends up marrying his daughter.

page219.title: Faulad
page219.description: A maharaja orders the killing of all newborn infants to prevent a disturbing prophecy from coming true.

page219.title: Dus (2005)
page219.description: A team of specialists (Sanjay Dutt, Abhishek Bachchan, Zayed Khan) must catch a terrorist before he can carry out an attack.

page219.title: Do Raaste
page219.description: A lower-middle-class Indian family has issues that touch on respect for elders, the sanctity of family, and the paramount status of the mother.

page220.title: Do Phool
page220.description: Do Phool is a 1973 Indian Hindi-language comedy film directed by S. Ramanathan. The film stars Ashok Kumar, Vinod Mehra and Mehmood. The film was a remake of Tamil film Anubavi Raja Anubavi which was also later remade in Kannada as Kittu Puttu.

page220.title: Dil Deke Dekho
page220.description: When three young men attempt to woo a wealthy heiress, one of them turns out to be a fraud.

page220.title: Diksha
page220.description: A student witnesses an improper relationship between a scholar's daughter and a teacher.

page220.title: Current
page220.description: Velu owns a small sugarcane field and has immense faith in the establishment, in this case, the Electricity Board, to condone a delay in payment of his electricity bill. But when the power is severed he and his wife Sita are devastated.

page220.title: Caravan
page220.description: On the run from her scheming husband, a wealthy woman (Asha Parekh) takes refuge with a band of drifters.

page220.title: Boot Polish
page220.description: Preteen brother and sister, abandoned by their father to care of an abusive prostitute aunt, survive life in an Indian squatters' camp, aided by a friendly cripple, by learning to shine shoes instead of begging.

page221.title: Bhoot
page221.description: A woman (Urmila Matondkar) sees a ghost after she and her husband (Ajay Devgan) move into an apartment where the previous tenant committed suicide.

page221.title: Betaabi
page221.description: Sameer falls in love with a rich girl, Sheena. Vicky, a small time crook, tries to kidnap and hold the girl for ransom -- but it's Sheena's suggestion.

page221.title: Bazaar
page221.description: A young couple is in love, the girl's father has arranged her marriage to an older and wealthier man. The young lover has to now convince the groom to be and the bride's father that he is better suited to the girl and call off the marriage.

page221.title: Bawarchi
page221.description: Shivnath is the head of the Sharma family, who are so thoroughly argumentative that they have succeeded in scaring away every single cook they've ever employed. So when plucky young chef Raghu shows up, nobody expects him to last long.

page221.title: Bandit Queen (1994)
page221.description: The movie tells the story of the bandit queen Phoolan Devi who was sent to prison in 1983 and got free in 1994.*Mature Content*

page221.title: Bahar
page221.description: Bahar is a 1951 Hindi Black-and-white social guidance film written and directed by M. V. Raman. It was a remake of the 1949 South Indian blockbuster film Vazhkai.

page222.title: Arjun (1985 Film)
page222.description: The film is about a young educated but unemployed man named Arjun. He has a group of friends who are also unemployed. They are all frustrated with the system that thrives on corruption and exploitation of the weak.

page222.title: Anokhi Raat
page222.description: In order to save her grandfather's mansion, Rama agrees to marry a much older male, Madanlal, who decides to sell some artifacts to prospective wealthy buyers, including Mr. and Mrs. Rai.

page222.title: Anmol Ghadi
page222.description: Heartbroken when his childhood sweetheart moves away, Chandrabhan tries to win her back when they meet again years later.

page222.title: Aladin
page222.description: Since he was a child, Aladin Chatterjee has been teased for his fairytale name. As a college student he follows his namesake's footsteps; unleashing genie Genius and wooing exchange student Jasmine. But the evil Ringmaster approaches.

page222.title: Ashad Ka Ek Din
page222.description: Ashadh Ka Ek Din is a 1971 Hindi film based on play of the same name by Mohan Rakesh.The film's story as in play is centered on a love triangle between Sanskrit poet Kalidas, Mallika and Priyangumanjari.

page222.title: Hum Kisise Kum Nahin (2002 Film)
page222.description: The movie revolves around Munnabhai a dreaded but good-hearted underworld don. Once while beating up one of his foes, he sees Komaland is so smitten by her beauty that he starts visualizing her wherever he goes and in whatever he does.

page223.title: Jaali Note
page223.description: Inspector Dinesh goes undercover in order to infiltrate a gang that is counterfeiting banknotes. In the course of his investigation he becomes romantically entangled with a female reporter.

page223.title: Shaheed
page223.description: Circa 1940s India, a young freedom fighter faces opposition from his own father as well as an ambitious police officer, who is also his rival for affection of a mutual childhood sweetheart.

page223.title: Tumsa Nahin Dekha
page223.description: Tumsa Nahin Dekha is a 1957 Indian film produced by Sashadhar Mukherjee for Filmistan and written and directed by Nasir Hussain. The film marked Hussain's evolution into a director. He had written films like Munimjee and Paying Guest.

page223.title: Parvarish
page223.description: After an hospital accident, a wealthy male is compelled to adopt a prostitute's son.Parvarish is a 1958 Bollywood film starring Raj Kapoor and Mala Sinha.

page223.title: Woh Kaun Thi?
page223.description: One stormy night, a doctor offers a ride to a ghostly woman he meets on the side of the road. Later, he discovers his intended bride is identical in appearance to the ghost. Who was she and why does she haunt him?

page223.title: Zamane Ko Dikhana Hai
page223.description: A wealthy man's son marries a poor girl against his father's wish. Years later, the younger son tries to find his brother and learns that the couple is no longer alive, but they have a son who is taken care of by the woman's sister.

page224.title: Tere Ghar Ke Samne
page224.description: Children of two life-long rivals fall in love and try to make their fathers see the error of their ways.

page224.title: Adventures Of Tarzan
page224.description: The Lord of the Apes (Hemant Birje) rescues a woman (Kimi Katkar) from jungle perils, falls in love with her, and is later kidnapped and shipped off to a circus.

page224.title: Sunehre Din
page224.description: The story revolves around the Renu, asha and lata who are close friends. Premendra is a popular  singer and renu, asha and lata fall in love with him.  A 1949 triangular love story!!

page224.title: Sujata
page224.description: A wealthy Indian family takes in a lonely and destitute untouchable (Nutan) after a plague wipes out her kin

page224.title: Suhaag
page224.description: Suhaag is 1994 Indian Hindi action thriller drama film directed by Kuku Kohli starring Ajay Devgan, Akshay Kumar, Karisma Kapoor and Nagma. Suhaag was one of the highest grossing Bollywood films of 1994.

page224.title: Sharabi (1964)
page224.description: Alcoholic Keshav (Dev Anand) promises to give up the bottle for his fiancée (Madhu Bala) and his mother (Lalita Pawar), but keeping his word proves impossible. After his father's death, Keshav gets clean and remains sober for a long time.

page225.title: Rajnigandha
page225.description: A woman (Vidya Sinha) must choose between two men (Amol Palekar, Dinesh Thakur) after she encounters an old flame during a trip to Bombay.

page225.title: Quick Gun Murugun (2009)
page225.description: A once-dead vegetarian cowboy is sent back to life to battle a beef-eating villain.A spoof on Indian western movies, featuring songs, melodrama and action sequences including a duel in a traffic jam.

page225.title: Purnima
page225.description: Prakash and Purnima end up with very different lives than they'd planned for, but when both of their spouses die in a car crash, they're presented with a new chance for happiness.

page225.title: Plan
page225.description: To pay off their debts, four men (Dino Morea, Sanjay Suri) kidnap a gangster (Sanjay Dutt) and hold him for ransom.

page225.title: Patita
page225.description: Patita is a 1953 Hindi film produced and directed by Amiya Chakrabarty. The film stars Dev Anand, Usha Kiran, Agha and Lalita Pawar. The films music is by Shankar Jaikishan.

page225.title: Parichay
page225.description: Ravi teaches five obstinate and spoiled grandchildren of the wealthy Rai Saheb.The film is based on a Bengali novel, Rangeen Uttarain by Raj Kumar Maitra.

page226.title: Night In London
page226.description: When her father is taken hostage, a woman is forced into a life of crime; and soon, everyone is after the priceless necklace in her possession.

page226.title: Muqaddar Ka Sikandar
page226.description: Homeless and orphaned, Sikandar rarely finds compassion, as he lives one day to the next doing whatever he can to survive. When he finds work at the house of the wealthy Ramanath , Sikandar quickly falls for his employer's daughter, Kaamna.

page226.title: Munimji (1955)
page226.description: Roopa lives a wealthy lifestyle with her widowed dad, Captain Suresh, and brother, Shekhar. After she returns from abroad, she is told that she must now prepare to get married to her betrothed, Ratan, who is the son of a close friend of Suresh.

page226.title: Mujrim
page226.description: A man comes back home and tries to help his poor family after serving his term in jail for murdering his uncle, but all his efforts go in vain because of his reputation.

page226.title: Mr. India
page226.description: A journalist is unaware that an invisible hero who fights gangsters is really the man with whom she shares a house.

page226.title: Shakti (1982)
page226.description: A policeman's son (Amitabh Bachchan) becomes a criminal after a childhood incident creates a rift between them.

page227.title: Azaad
page227.description: After her widower dad, Kedarnath, passes away, Shobha goes to live with her father's friend Charandas and his wife Shanta, who had their son go missing as a child. It was the top grossing Hindi film in the year of its release, and one of the biggest Hindi film hits in the decade.

page227.title: Jhumroo (1961)
page227.description: Jhumroo (Kumar) is a poor boy who falls in love with a rich girl, Anjana (Madhubala). Anjana's father Dwarkanath (Jayant) vehemently opposes the match, and machinates to drive a wedge between them.

page227.title: Jurmana (1979)
page227.description: A notorious lady's man (Amitabh Bachchan) makes a bet with an old college friend (Vinod Mehra) that he will date their ex-professor's daughter (Raakhee).

page227.title: Souten
page227.description: A woman (Tina Munim) becomes extremely jealous after the daughter (Padmini Kolhapure) of her husband's (Rajesh Khanna) accountant shows affection for him.

page227.title: Satyam Shivam Sundaram
page227.description: A man (Sashi Kapoor) falls in love with a woman (Zeenat Aman) who conceals her partially burned face with a veil.

page227.title: Satta
page227.description: A liberal woman from Delhi weds a politician in Mumbai, only to find herself standing for election in his place when he is sent to prison.

page228.title: Sanshodhan
page228.description: One man challenges corrupt politicians, influencing women to contest the requirement for women in village government.

page228.title: Ram Teri Ganga Maili
page228.description: Ganga (Mandakini) journeys from Gangotri to Calcutta to search for Narendra (Rajiv Kapoor), the love of her life.The film became very controversial because of Mandakini's bold scenes.

page228.title: Mr. & Mrs. '55
page228.description: A young, naive heiress, in custody of a martinet and flamingly feminist aunt is forced into a 'marriage of convenience' with an unemployed cartoonist in an attempt to save her millions - a move orchestrated by the scheming aunt.

page228.title: Miss Lovely
page228.description: A Hindi feature film set in the lower depths of Bombay's "C" grade film industry. Miss Lovely follows the devastating story of two brothers who produce sleazy horror films in the mid-1980s.

page228.title: Maya Memsaab
page228.description: Dissatisfied with her life, a married woman embarks on a series of affairs that always end in disaster.

page228.title: Mahal (1969 Film)
page228.description: To pay for his sister's marriage, a brother enters into a criminal conspiracy to impersonate the nephew of a wealthy male.

page229.title: Love Story 2050
page229.description: Karan Malhotra is a spirited and happy-go-lucky boy who does not follow the rules. Sana is the opposite of Karan: a sweet and shy girl who lives life by the rules. Even though they are completely opposite, they fall in love, leading to a magical love story.

page229.title: Kissa Maut Ka (1999)
page229.description: Kissa Maut Ka is a Hindi Dubbed Horror movie.

page229.title: Kisaan
page229.description: Dayal decides to send his elder son, Aman, to the city to study and become a lawyer, while his second son, Jiggar, lives with him to help him farm.

page229.title: Ajay (1996 Film)
page229.description: Ajay is a 1996 Hindi language Movie produced and directed by Suneel Darshan and starring Sunny Deol, Karisma Kapoor, Reena Roy, Sadashiv Amrapurkar.

page229.title: Khoon Pasina
page229.description: Separated during their youth, former friends (Amitabh Bachchan, Vinod Khanna) become enemies years later.

page229.title: Katha(1983 Film)
page229.description: A middle-class clerk living in a chawl in Bombay is secretly in love with his neighbor.The film is loosely based on the classical Indian folktale of the hare and the tortoise, providing a modern interpretation of the same.

page230.title: Kasam Paida Karne Wale Ki
page230.description: At the age of 5, Satish Kumar becomes the heir of a large estate, which is placed in the custody of his greedy uncle until Satish turns 20.

page230.title: Kal Aaj Aur Kal
page230.description: Widower Ram Kapoor frequently throws lavish parties to overcome his loneliness. That changes when his son, Rajesh, returns home with a proposition. Ram's life soon spirals out of control.

page230.title: Kabhie Kabhie (1976 Film)
page230.description: Kabhi Kabhie is a movie about the love story of generations and how a chain of events brings together old lovers as friends.

page230.title: Aas Ka Panchhi
page230.description: A man joins the army after the death of his father leaving his college sweetheart behind with a promise of marrying her when he returns. When he returns, he discovers that his lover is engaged to another. Dejected, he again joins the army.

page230.title: 27 Down
page230.description: While traveling to India's holy city of Benares, a railroad conductor re-examines his life.The film is based on a Hindi novel Athara Sooraj Ke Paudhe by Ramesh Bakshi about a railways employee who meets a girl on the train.

page230.title: Aandhi
page230.description: Aarti leaves her husband after a few years of marriage and becomes a well-known politician. When she runs into her ex after a few years, their romance rekindles, but she fears her reputation will suffer if she stays with him.

page231.title: Azhar
page231.description: Biographical sports drama based on the life of former Indian international cricketer, Mohammad Azharuddin.

page231.title: Jurmana
page231.description: A Family action film about Love between Inspector Vijay Saxena (Mithun Chakraborty) and Pooja Kumari Tiwari (Rambha).Jurmana is a 1996 Hindi-language Indian feature film directed by T L V Prasad, starring Mithun Chakraborty, Rambha.

page231.title: Kidnap
page231.description: Sanjay Dutt plays a father whose daughter is kidnapped. The film follows his struggle to get her back.

page231.title: Mahal
page231.description: A man (Ashok Kumar) becomes obsessed with a beautiful ghost (Madhubala) after moving into a mansion that is said to have a tragic history.

page231.title: Maharaja
page231.description: A prince that grew up in the jungle seeks revenge after learning of his royal family's long-ago murders.

page231.title: Main Prem Ki Diwani Hoon
page231.description: Two men (Hrithik Roshan, Abhishek Bachchan) vie for the love of the same woman (Kareena Kapoor), even though one is already engaged to her.

page232.title: Mera Naam Joker
page232.description: Having helped shape his destiny, three women view a circus clown's (Raj Kapoor) final performance.

page232.title: Mrityudata
page232.description: Mrityudaata is a 1997 Bollywood musical action movie directed by Mehul Kumar with music by Anand Milind. The film is considered to be a comeback role for Amitabh Bachchan who temporarily left the industry in 1992.

page232.title: Naajayaz
page232.description: Police Inspector Jay Bakshi has been asked to track down and arrest the notorious criminal Raj Solanski, but little does he know that Raj plays a significant role in his life.

page232.title: Noorjehan
page232.description: An epic love story of Empress Noor Jehan(Meena Kumari) and her husband(Pradeep Kumar), the Mughal Emperor Jehangir. The favourite wife of the Emperor, it was often rumoured that Noor Jehan was the real power behind his throne.

page232.title: Out Of Control
page232.description: When his work permit expires in New York, Jaswinder Bedi gets married to a bar dancer, Sally Turner, and moves in with her.

page232.title: Paap Aur Punya
page232.description: Paap Aur Punya is a Bollywood film directed by Prayag Raj. The film stars Shashi Kapoor, Sharmila Tagore and Ajit. Shashi Kapoor also appears in dual role.

page233.title: Main Khiladi Tu Anari
page233.description: A Bombay police officer seeks revenge when his brother is killed by a powerful underworld figure. Things get complicated when a matinee movie idol begins to tag along the policeman so he can research a movie role.

page233.title: Maachis
page233.description: The title of the film is used as a metaphor that conveys that the youth of any nation are matchsticks that could get ignited due to the deficiencies in the political and policing systems.

page233.title: Love Ke Liye Kuch Bhi Karega

page233.title: Life In A... Metro
page233.description: Six different stories, about nine people, each with different issues and problems, all occurring within one place: the METRO.

page233.title: Lamhaa

page233.title: Laawaris
page233.description: An illegitimate son's quest for love and respect brings him in contact with his biological father.

page234.title: Knock Out
page234.description: Knock Out is inspired by Hollywood thriller movie Phone Booth.A businessman in a phone-booth is held hostage by a sniper.

page234.description: Karan and Arjun reincarnate in the different parts of the country. But the faith of their previous mother brings them together in order to avenge their death.

page235.title: Kala Bazaar
page235.description: Kala Bazaar is a 1989 Hindi film directed by Rakesh Roshan. It stars Kader Khan, Anil Kapoor and Jackie Shroff in lead roles.

page236.description: Jab Yaad Kisi Ki Aati Hai is a 1967 Bollywood film starring Dharmendra, Mala Sinha in a double role, Abhibhattacharya and M. Rajan. It is a love story with little suspense.

page236.description: Jay doesn't believe in love Stories, and Simran is a girl who's in love with the idea of Love itself.

page236.title: Hum Aapke Hain Koun

page236.title: Giddh

page237.title: Do Bhai
page237.description: Do Bhai is a 1969 Bollywood action film produced and directed by Brij Sadanah. Starring Ashok Kumar, Mala Sinha, Jeetendra in the lead roles and music composed by Laxmikant–Pyarelal.

page240.title: Judaai

page241.title: Amaanat

page242.title: China Gate

page242.description: A mysterious woman (Ayesha Jhulka) changes the lives of those she meets.

page245.title: Taxi No. 9 2 11: Nau Do Gyarah

page246.title: Bhoot Returns (2012)

page246.title: Arjun: The Warrior Prince (2012)
page246.description: The tale of how Arjuna fought his inner self and became the legendary archer.

page247.title: Ziyarat (2011)
page247.description: This movie is an untold story of Kashmir.Kashmir is not all about bombs and guns and terrorists and that will be shown in this movie. It has been directed, produced and written by Suresh K Goswami.(Documentary)

page248.description: When Shankara is asked by Rani to pretend to be engaged to her only child, Seema, little does he realize that he has entered a deep, dark conspiracy.

page248.title: Shagird
page248.description: A rookie cop questions the tactics of his superior, and attempts to track the abductors of his girlfriend.

page249.description: Duped by a con artist, three friends (Akshay Kumar, Sunil Shetty, Paresh Rawal) must find a way to repay a gangster.

page249.description: Sapna runs away from her aristocratic home, fed-up of the hatred and family politics. She meets with Raj, who she is attracted to. Raj, at first wants to get rid of her, then eventually falls in love with her.

page250.title: Deewaar

page250.title: Crook
page250.description: The film is based on the controversy regarding the allegedly racial attacks on Indian students in Australia between 2007 and 2010.

page250.description: When Sunder loses everything, he seeks refuge in a graveyard, where he befriends a ghost.

page250.description: Three woman-hating brothers face changes in their respective lifestyles when two of them fall in love.

page250.description: Tikku sees a woman leaving her child in the garbage and decides to take care of the young girl, whom he names Tamanna, but it turns out that the girl is actually the daughter of a well-known politician.

page251.description: An alluring housewife (Bipasha Basu) ensnares a boozy lawyer (John Abraham) in her trap.An Erotic Thriller!!

page251.title: Gupt
page251.description: Governor Jaisingh Sinha is murdered and the needle of suspicion points towards his estranged son, Sahil Sinha who must prove his innocence.

page251.title: Gangster
page251.description: In love with a gangster, a woman abuses alcohol and has an affair with a bar singer (Emraan Hashmi).

page252.title: Baaghi
page252.description: A gangster (Sanjay Dutt) receives orders from his boss to kill a collegian whom he reveres.

page252.title: Agni Sakshi(Hindi)

page252.title: Sham Ghansham
page252.description: Arbaz and Chandrachur plays two intimate brothers who take revenge of their murdered father.Sham Ghansham is a 1998 Hindi film starring Raakhee, Arbaz Khan, Chandrachur Singh in the lead.

page252.title: Tarana
page252.description: Tarana is a 1951 Hindi movie produced and written by K S Daryani and directed by Ram Daryani. The film stars Dilip Kumar and Madhubala for the first time together, along with Shyama and Jeevan.

page253.title: Baseraa

page253.description: The story of a deprived boy, who is brought up in a privileged family and indebted for virtually everything he has.

page253.title: Thodisi Bewafaii
page253.description: A young man (Rajesh Khanna) must start over when he loses his house and his business.

page253.description: What happens when you throw 2 guys who hate each other together? Add for good measure a beauty and a gangster and the trouble is no one can be trusted.

page254.title: Griha Pravesh

page254.title: Humraaz
page254.description: A millionaire (Bobby Deol) falls in love with a dancer (Amisha Patel) whose boyfriend (Akshaye Khanna) performs in her troupe.

page254.title: Bhrashtachar

page254.title: Badmaash

page255.title: Badal
page255.description: A man (Bobby Deol) seeks revenge on the police officer (Ashutosh Rana) who helped slaughter a village, including his family.

page255.title: Bachelor Party 2009
page255.description: A man decides to have a wild bachelor party before his marriage. A  comedy drama directed by Ishaan Trivedi

page255.title: Aradhana (Hindi)
page255.description: Dashing pilot Arun romances Vandana Tripathi, and both in love with each other, become very intimate, and as a result Vandana gets pregnant.

page255.title: Anokha Rishta

page256.title: Tezaab

page256.title: Dhobi Ghat
page256.description: The video diaries of a former tenant of his apartment fascinate the artist (Aamir Khan) who currently lives there, while an investment banker (Monica Dogra) befriends a pair of workers for a research project.

page257.title: Paheli

page257.title: Phool Aur Aag
page257.description: Deva's good deeds and actions are generally misunderstood by a lot of people, and his deeds are also deliberately twisted by his enemies.

page257.title: Prem Patra

page258.title: Gangs Of Wasseypur 2

His parents ask him to either get married to a certain Sweety or move to Goa and work under his father's friend. Considering the first option unimaginable, Raftaar chooses the second.

page283.description: In order to escape crime and clutches of a ruthless mafia, a Bangkok based hit man seeks the help of his lookalike, a Mumbai based goon.

page283.title: I (Hindi)
page283.description: A bodybuilder (Vikram) plans revenge after his various enemies inject him with a substance that deforms his body. (Hindi Dubbed Version)

page283.title: Mumbai Delhi Mumbai
page283.description: Pia, a girl from Mumbai, has stereotypical notions about people from Delhi. Her mother insists that she visit Delhi in order to meet a prospective groom, but she is determined to refuse him.

page284.title: Tevar
page284.description: Caught in the middle of a lethal unrequited love, an athlete protects a young woman from an unwanted marriage.

page284.title: Ungli
page284.description: Ungli is a sleek, edgy, vigilante drama loaded with action. It is a story about friendship and what happens when a gang of friends decides to take justice into their own hands.

page284.title: The Shaukeens
page284.description: Three friends in their 60s try to do everything that they couldn't do in their younger days - before death arrives.

page284.title: Happy Ending
page284.description: A confused writer goes on the search of inspiration for his next story and falls in love with a best seller author who doesn't believe in love.

page284.title: Zid
page284.description: A journalist, who is still in love with his ex-girlfriend, becomes the obsession of his landlord's daughter. One accident. A series of lies and secrets.

page284.title: Kill Dil
page284.description: Abandoned when young, Bhaiyaji gives shelter to Dev and Tutu. A game of defiance, deception and love follows when free-spirited Disha enters their life.

page285.title: Finding Fanny
page285.description: A story about childhood love and regret. A man in the waning years of his life decides to find his long-lost love - Stefanie `Fanny` Fernandes. But nobody knows if she is still alive or dead or just made-up.

page285.title: Khoobsurat 2014
page285.description: A hopelessly romantic physiotherapist meets a handsome young Rajput prince who is the complete opposite of her and engaged to someone else.

page285.title: Fugly
page285.description: Four friends fight against a corrupt police officer who extorts money from them for not framing them in a murder which the officer committed himself.

page285.title: Bang Bang
page285.description: A young bank receptionist gets mixed up with Rajveer Nanda, a man who has a mysterious background.The official remake of Knight and Day!

page285.title: Happy New Year
page285.description: A team of losers wins the love of millions in their quest to pull off the biggest diamond heist ever by team India. Iss Diwali, Todenge Taale, Indiawale!

page285.title: Daawat-E-Ishq
page285.description: A story of Gullu, a Hyderabadi girl frustrated with dowry-seeking men and Taru (a charming Lucknawi cook), who crush old-fashioned world-view.

page286.title: Samrat And Co
page286.description: A small town tycoon gets murdered by his son. The daughter hires a private investigator to catch the real culprit.Get ready for the Dilchasp Rahasya Ride!!

page286.title: Darr At The Mall
page286.description: During the inaugural party of one of the largest malls in Asia, a newly recruited security guard must work to stop a supernatural threat.

page286.title: Ghatothkach 2
page286.description: Presenting the sequel to the very popular Ghatothkach movie. Ghatothkach, the son of Bhima is blessed with extra-ordinary powers. The film is the magical and adventurous journey of this cute prince and his elephant friend 'Gajju'.

page286.title: Shool
page286.description: An honest and diligent police inspector Samar Pratap Singh is transferred to Motihari, in Bihar, along with his wife, Manjari and daughter Sonu. Here, the law is in the hands of a politician called Bachchu Yadav.

page286.title: Roja (Hindi)
page286.description: A woman from a village in Tamil Nadu marries a sophisticated city dweller and moves with him to Kashmir, where all is rosy - until he gets kidnapped by militants.

page286.title: Raja Ki Aayegi Baraat
page286.description: A woman is forced to marry a man who beat and raped her. The abuse continues when she moves in with his family.

page287.title: Policewala Gunda
page287.description: This movie revolves around a policeman who is a kind and honorable person. After arresting the henchmen of a notorious crime leader, the crime lord sets out to kill the policeman with the minister. His wife is helped by a policeman Ajit Singh.

page287.title: Mary Kom
page287.description: A chronicle of the life of Indian boxer Mary Kom, who went through several hardships before audaciously accomplishing her ultimate dream.

page287.title: Creature
page287.description: In the midst of the hilly terrains of Summer Hill, Ahana, launches her new, warm and cozy boutique hotel. Here, she meets Kunal, a famous author who is one of the first guests at the hotel. Fear has a new face!!

page287.title: Karar: The Deal
page287.description: Nikita, the granddaughter of a rich and old man, is asthmatic and resides in South Africa. While her family is just about her Dadaji and their caretaker Annie, their life changes when Dr. Aryan enters.

page287.title: Sirf
page287.description: Fated to meet one another in a variety of ways, four families face their own problems but find their lives intertwining, changing them forever.

page287.title: Road To Sangam
page287.description: Amidst bomb explosions, fake arrests, police brutality and protests, a determined mechanic attempts to repair an antique truck to transport the last remains of Mahatma Gandhi in modern day India.

page288.title: Raghuveer
page288.description: A man, who lives with his brother, keeps getting into fights and gets arrested for assaulting a man. Even after getting bailed, he does not stop and eventually get arrested for a murder he did not commit.

page288.title: Leela
page288.description: Leela is a professor from Bombay. Married to a popular poet, her life has always been prefixed with the title 'Nashaad's wife'. She wins a chance to be sent as a visiting professor to California, where she rediscovers herself, the woman she is.

page288.title: Jaal: The Trap
page288.description: Redoubtable son of the soil Sunny Deol battles terrorists. Jaal: the trap is a 2003 Hindi thriller film directed by Guddu Dhanoa.

page288.title: Entertainment
page288.description: Akhil finds out that he is the heir of 3000 crore rupees as he and his mother were abandoned by his diamond baron father who is now dead. However, his life goes Topsy-turvy when he learns that the empire goes to entertainment (a dog).

page288.title: Singham Returns
page288.description: Owing to the wrongdoings affiliated with evils similar to black money, an honest but ferocious police officer returns as the Deputy Commissioner of Police with the prospect of wiping out injustice.

page288.title: Jeet Lengey Jahaan
page288.description: Jeet Lengey Jahaan movie is story of such three youngsters who meet at a point of time when all three are frustrated with their career and life. But they decide to choose an alternate career for them rather getting into depression.

page289.title: Super Model
page289.description: he film shows how ambition when becomes obsession can lead to disaster. With aim to be a super model when five gorgeous girls come together one of them commits a big folly.

page289.title: Mardaani
page289.description: A story of Shivani Shivaji Roy, Crime Branch, who sets out to confront the mastermind behind a child trafficking mafia.

page289.title: Chintuji
page289.description: Hoping to branch out into politics, actor Rishi Kapoor (Rishi Kapoor) visits the primitive village in which he was born.

page289.title: Chehraa
page289.description: Two college mates, who are studying psychology, plan to marry each other after their education. The guy, however, falls for another girl, who mysteriously disappears and returns after five years but as his patient

page289.title: Benaam Badsha
page289.description: Abandoned by his parents, a child grows into a life of crime, only to have one of his victims offer him redemption and a better life.

page289.title: Humpty Sharma Ki Dulhania
page289.description: Two spoiled brats meet over the purchase of an expensive wedding skirt in Delhi. Thus begins a romance under the shadow of her arranged marriage.

page290.title: Kashmakash
page290.description: Months after an accident following his marriage, a husband finds that the veiled woman he brought home is not his wife. A Hindi Dubbed Version of Noukadubi (2011 Bengali film).

page290.title: Zameen
page290.description: Two men (Abhishek Bachchan, Ajay Devgan) work together to capture a group of terrorists planning to hijack an airplane.

page290.title: Vinashak-Destroyer
page290.description: ACP Amar finds that Jailer Lankeshwar is using jailed convicts as hit men for a fee, by letting them leave the jail, and be back with a perfect alibi. Inspector Arjun is jailed to find out the truth.

page290.title: Lambu Dada
page290.description: The Movie story deals with Lavina who lives a wealthy lifestyle in Raigarh along with her widower dad, Pratap. After her birthday, their lives are shattered by the entry of Pratap's brother, Vikram who kills Pratap, and his mother, but fails to kill Lavina.

page290.title: Hathyar
page290.description: Ostracized by society for his late father's past, a man (Sanjay Dutt) follows in his footsteps and becomes a gangster.

page290.title: Jeevan Yudh
page290.description: A truck driver flees from police and a vengeful family after he is accused of murder.

page291.title: Anth
page291.description: Students are harassed at college by Kali whose father is one of the biggest gangsters in town. When Kali rapes the principal's daughter, Pooja, and hides behind a corrupt inspector, Pooja's brother, Vijay, is enraged and goes after the criminals.

page291.title: Aisha
page291.description: Chaos results after a wealthy woman decides to turn match-maker for a naive village belle.

page291.title: Youngistaan
page291.description: A young man (Jackky Bhagnani) refuses to get rid of his live-in lover (Neha Sharma) after he succeeds his father as India's prime minister.

page291.title: Lekar Hum Deewana Dil
page291.description: Afraid that their parents will make them adhere to arranged marriages, a young couple tie the knot and run away. However, they are unprepared for the challenges ahead.

page291.title: Paapi Ek Satya Katha
page291.description: The film is a story of a small town girl, Pia, who falls in an Internet trap. She falls in love with a friend, Rahul, whom she has never seen but met on the Internet.

page291.title: Filmistaan
page291.description: An affable Bollywood buff and wanna-be-actor, Sunny, goes to remote areas in Rajasthan to work on a documentary film. One day after pack-up, a terrorist group kidnaps him. Cinema might just be the universal solution for co-existence!!

page292.title: Heropanti
page292.description: Will Bablu and Dimpy`s love blossom under the terror of a brutal clan and the violent landscape it is set against. Heropanti is the story of today`s youth, and the coming of age of its conflicting protagonists.

page292.title: Ek Villain
page292.description: When his lover becomes the latest victim of a serial killer, Guru blurs the line between good and evil in his pursuit of revenge.

page292.title: The Xpose
