page292.description: The Xpose is a film set in the 1960s, a decade when film stars tasted success and carried their larger- than- life screen image on to real life with unbridled pomp and splendor.A pulsating human mystery with a love story at the core.

page292.title: Bobby Jasoos
page292.description: Bobby Jasoos starring Vidya Balan, is a film that celebrates the aspiration of Bobby, who wants to become the number one detective in the old city area of Hyderabad.

page292.title: Holiday: A Soldier Is Never Off Duty
page292.description: A military officer attempts to hunt down a terrorist, destroy a terrorist gang and deactivate the sleeper cells under its command.

page292.title: Jal: Water
page292.description: Jal is the story of young, willful BAKKA who is gifted with a special ability to find water in the desert. With the backdrop of water scarcity, the film tells a complex and intriguing story of love, relationships, enmity, deceit.

page293.title: U Me Aur Hum
page293.description: This is the love story of Ajay (Ajay Devgan) and Pia (Kajol). They meet at a cruise fall and love and marry, only to later realize that Pia is suffering from Alzheimer.

page293.title: Sur: The Melody Of Life
page293.description: A music teacher (Lucky Ali) becomes jealous when his protege's (Gauri Karnik) talent eclipses his own.

page293.title: CityLights
page293.description: Deepak Sing is a farmer in Rajasthan. After a tragedy, he migrates to Mumbai with his wife and child to lead a better life. However, upon arriving, he soon discovers the challenges of life in a big city. A remake of the British film Metro Manila (2013).

page293.title: Poochho Mere Dil Se
page293.description: A police inspector is assigned to track down a notorious gangster who has kidnapped four women, but discovers that he has close ties to the mob.

page293.title: Paappi Devataa
page293.description: A cop's integrity is tested when he befriends a gangster's employee and falls in love with the man's sister.

page293.title: Mithya
page293.description: A two-bit actor faces challenges after he is asked by Police to impersonate a look-alike gangster.

page294.title: Raqeeb: Rivals In Love
page294.description: Remo is an intelligent rich bachelor and an aspiring entrepreneur, who falls in love with Sophie. The pair soon marry and their world seems to be full of happiness.

page294.title: Ramji Londonwaley
page294.description: Ramji Tiwari a skilled cook, struggled because he had to get his sister married and yet could not manage to collect the dowry amount. On the wedding, a guest, Pandey, gets impressed by Ramji's cooking and offers him a job in U.K.

page294.title: Love Ke Chakkar Mein
page294.description: Unemployed Vicky meets Neha on the internet, and when they meet in person, they fall in love and wish to get married. Neha's father approves of the union, but in order for him to bless the marriage, he requires Vicky to obtain employment within 7 days.

page294.title: Koi Aap Sa
page294.description: An emotional Mumbai-based football player, Rohan, seeks the assistance of childhood friend, Simran, to successfully woo fellow-collegian, Preeti. Simran herself is about to be engaged to U.S.-based Vicky.

page294.title: Chupke Se
page294.description: A wealthy entrepreneur (Syed Zulfi) falls for a woman (Masumi Makhija) competing in a beauty pageant.

page294.title: Hum Jo Keh Na Paaye
page294.description: A young woman (Gauri Karnik) learns that the man she loves has been having an affair with her friend, who is now pregnant.

page295.title: Hanan
page295.description: Dreaded gangster Shamsher Singh pretends to be a mad man to elude the police. He manages to woo a girl and exploit her to meet his own ends.

page295.title: Manjunath
page295.description: 'Manjunath' is a warm inspirational film based on the true story of Manjunath Shanmugam, a sales officer from a petroleum company who was killed by the oil mafia in 2005 for his stand against fuel adulteration.

page295.title: Yakeen
page295.description: Left with amnesia after a car accident, a man (Arjun Rampal) believes his wife (Priyanka Chopra) is having an affair.

page295.title: Reshma Aur Shera
page295.description: A pair of star-crossed lovers find their romance jeopardized by family rivalries

page295.title: Ek Hasina Thi
page295.description: A man (Saif Ali Khan) tries to help his girlfriend (Urmila Matondkar) after she is arrested and imprisoned.

page295.title: Kya Dilli Kya Lahore
page295.description: In 1948, a cross-fire erupts at an isolated stretch of Indo-Pak border, leaving only two soldiers alive. One is an Indian soldier of Pakistani origin while the other happens to be a Pakistani soldier of Indian origin.

page296.title: Trishna
page296.description: After several years of trying to have a child, Aarti, wife of the successful Dr.Sunil Gupta, travels to their Khandala bungalow. When a workman pursues her because she's alone, she believes she has killed him & gets help to dispose of the body.

page296.title: Teri Kasam
page296.description: A rich girl falls in love with an aspiring musician, but after they marry, their egos cause them to drift apart.

page296.title: Tehzeeb
page296.description: A young woman (Urmila Matondkar) carries a grudge against her mother (Shabana Azmi), a well-known singer, whom she suspects of causing her father's death.

page296.title: Haasil
page296.description: A collegian (Jimmy Shergill) falls in love with a young woman on a campus where students with political connections rule.

page296.title: Chhal
page296.description: Secret Service Agent, Karan Menon (Kay Kay) has been assigned the task of penetrating the gang and winning the confidence of underworld don, Shastri (Vallabh Vyas).

page296.title: Hawaa Hawaai
page296.description: Hawaa Hawaai is a story of the triumph of the human spirit; friendship and enjoying the journey of making one`s dream come true.

page297.title: Chatur Singh Two Star
page297.description: Chatur Singh 2 Star (Sanjay Dutt) is an infamous member of the Mumbai Police Department who, in his career, has been botching up cases and making a fool of himself. He is sent to South Africa to solve a high profile case involving the murder of a politician.

page297.title: Pathar Ke Insan
page297.description: Two sisters, Asha and Lata, want to be successful singers and dancers, but a competition drives their rivalry to tragic consequences.

page297.title: Johnny Gaddaar
page297.description: Police officers recount a tale of missing money which results in lies, deceit, betrayal and death.

page297.title: Bardaasht
page297.description: An army officer investigates the murder of his brother, whom he believes was killed to cover up a secret police action.

page297.title: American Desi
page297.description: It is a fun-loving rom-com focusing on the lives of second generation Indians in America. The story is set on a college campus and follows the exploits of an Indian freshman whose path in life takes a sharp detour down a road to self-discovery.

page297.title: Shootout At Lokhandwala
page297.description: It is based upon the 1991 Lokhandwala Complex shootout, a real-life gun battle between gangsters and Mumbai Police.

page298.title: Revolver Rani
page298.description: Alka Singh, the leader of a political party, and her obsessive love for Rohan Mehra, a rising star of Bollywood. Even if she is deadly, Revolver Rani needs love too!

page298.title: The Namesake
page298.description: American-born Gogol, the son of Indian immigrants, wants to fit in among his fellow New Yorkers, despite his family's unwillingness to let go of their traditional ways.

page298.title: Monsoon Wedding
page298.description: A stressed father, a bride-to-be with a secret, a smitten event planner, and relatives from around the world create much ado about the preparations for an arranged marriage in India.

page298.title: What The Fish
page298.description: A woman Sudha, before leaving for a month-long holiday, instructs Sumit to regularly feed her pet fish. But when she returns home, she is shocked to see her house in an utter mess. What could have happened?

page298.title: Purani Jeans
page298.description: Sidharth, his best friend Sam and their gang of friends rediscover bonds of friendship and love.Rediscover and relive the youthful days with Purani Jeans.

page298.title: Kaanchi
page298.description: The inner power of a woman who represents over one million suppressed youth against injustice in the country.

page299.title: Ragini MMS 2
page299.description: A sleazy film director's decision to shoot his latest erotic horror movie in a notorious haunted house angers the vengeful spirit of its past inhabitant.

page299.title: Main Tera Hero
page299.description: A mischievous collegian (Varun Dhawan) believes that Krishna sent him a beautiful woman (Ileana D'Cruz) to woo.

page299.title: Bhoothnath Returns
page299.description: A ghost returns back from his world to prove something. But on earth, he has something more to do for his country.

page299.title: Dekh Tamasha Dekh
page299.description: A social and political satire about a true incident,it revolves around the search for the religious identity of a poor man crushed under the weight of a politician's hoarding. The film explores an Impossible India where bizarre is normal.

page299.title: Paranthe Wali Gali
page299.description: The film is a love story which captures the food culture of the Moghul city, Delhi. A chemistry that sizzles between a Sikh girl and a Rajasthani boy make up a great treat which brings out many parts of Delhi leaving the viewers nostalgic.

page299.title: Dedh Ishqiya
page299.description: Two lousy crooks find paradise in the seven stages of love.A poetic escapade caught in the web of crime, suspense, passion & deceit.

page300.title: War Chhod Na Yaar
page300.description: Not only is the movie a satirical take on the conditions of the armed forces of two countries engaged in a war, but it also tries to shed some light on some `So Called` reasons behind one such unwanted war. India's First War Comedy!!

page300.title: Vaastav: The Reality
page300.description: Desperate for work in Mumbai, Raghu (Sanjay Dutt) and Dedh (Sanjay Narvekar) chip in to work a food cart together until an accident inadvertently leaves the friends caught between organized-crime families.

page300.title: Road
page300.description: A stranded motorist (Manoj Bajpai) menaces the two unwary lovers (Vivek Oberoi, Antara Mali) who stopped to help him.

page300.title: Tum: A Dangerous Obsession
page300.description: After taking advantage of a drunk housewife, an obsessive photographer proceeds to make her life a living hell.

page300.title: Rakta Charitra 2
page300.description: After avenging the death of his father and brother, a man must now content with another vengeful male.

page300.title: Prem Rog
page300.description: Manorama, the daughter of a rich, orthodox family is married off, leaving her childhood friend Deodhar and his secret love for her, in despair. When tragedy befalls her, and traditions seem unfair, Deodhar must fight for what's right.

page301.title: My Wife's Murder
page301.description: When Sheela goes missing, Ravi, her husband, seeks help from the police to track her down. When her dead body is found, all fingers point to Ravi.

page301.title: Bewakoofiyaan
page301.description: Bewakoofiyaan is a slice-of-life comedy when recession strikes and the lack of money tests love. Is living on love and fresh air really possible?

page301.title: Dhoom 3
page301.description: Jai and Ali return to catch the clown thief, Sahir, who has the City of Chicago captive. It's an unconventional battle of revenge that will thrill you.

page301.title: Gunday
page301.description: The lives of Calcutta's most powerful Gunday - Bikram and Bala, changes when Nandita enters it. Then a counter-force takes charge and a thriller unfolds.

page301.title: Queen
page301.description: A Delhi girl from a traditional family sets out on a solo honeymoon after her marriage gets cancelled.

page301.title: Gulaab Gang
page301.description: A fearless woman fights social injustice; creating a sanctuary for abused women and battling a crooked politician.

page302.title: Dishkiyaoon
page302.description: Vicky wanted to be the godfather of Mumbai underworld. He gains everything and also looses everything. He gains respect, power, and leadership but he loses love, friendship.

page302.title: Arundhati (Hindi)
page302.description: A brave queen battles an evil mystic. Three generations later, he comes back to haunt the queen's descendants.(Hindi Dubbed Version)

page302.title: Mokssh
page302.description: Once you go on a pilgrimage (Waari), you won't come out as the same person that walked in. Mokssh, Hindi adaptation of the multiple award-winning Marathi film 'Gajar', is a fascinating tale of spirituality and self-discovery.

page302.title: Chor Ho To Aisa
page302.description: A swindler tries to help his ladylove prove the innocence of her brother who's been accused of murder, but is himself arrested and put behind bars.

page302.title: Yaarana
page302.description: Multi-millionaire Bishan Kumar and orphan Kishan are inseparable friends and live in the same house with Bishan's widowed mother and a maid servant.

page302.title: Paandav
page302.description: Paandav is a 1995 Indian Bollywood film directed by Raj N. Sippy. It stars Akshay Kumar and Nandini

page303.title: Gauri
page303.description: Orphaned Sanjeev lives with his comically parsimonious paternal uncle, Maniram, who offers to look after him on the condition that a contested Last Will and Testament, will benefit him.

page303.title: Shaadi Ke Side Effects
page303.description: A complicated relationship develops between a man and woman after getting married and having a baby.

page303.title: Total Siyapaa
page303.description: A young musician hopes to marry his beautiful girlfriend, but his plans hit a snag when her family learns he's from a neighboring country.A marriage plan goes wrong!!

page303.title: Prateeksha
page303.description: A story of a lovely married couple Vijay Kumar & Laxmi who performs musical shows together with his friend Tom Dacosta and their son Raja s their means of living.

page303.title: Dum (Hindi)
page303.description: A police officer's (Vivek Oberoi) unfailing honesty and determination to clean up the system earn him both friends and enemies.

page303.title: Badla
page303.description: Former convict, Kumar, returns to the town where he was arrested. He spends the night at a hotel with a woman named Nisha. In the morning, he wakes up with a gun in his hand, and the lifeless body of police officer, Lobo, shot dead in his room.

page304.title: Aap Aye Bahar Ayee
page304.description: Aap Aye Bahar Ayee is a 1971 Bollywood film produced, directed and written by Mohan Kumar. It stars Rajendra Kumar, Sadhana Shivdasani, Rajendranath and Prem Chopra. The film's music is by Laxmikant Pyarelal.

page304.title: Heroes
page304.description: Two film students document their journey as they deliver the final letters of three fallen soldiers to the men's families.

page304.title: Jail Yatra
page304.description: Raju comes from a middle-class family, and lives with his mother. He meets with nurse Shobha, and both fall in love. The only problem is that Raju somehow or other always gets mixed up in problems, and ends up getting in trouble with the police.

page304.title: Hey Ram (Hindi)
page304.description: Saketh Ram's wife is raped and killed during direct action day riots in Calcutta. He is convinced that Mahatma Gandhi is responsible for all the problems happening in the country and sets out to kill him.

page304.title: Khoobsurat
page304.description: A con man (Sanjay Dutt) who donates money to orphanages tries to win over a family he plans to rob.

page304.title: The Killer
page304.description: A cabdriver (Emraan Hashmi) unwittingly transports an assassin (Irrfan Khan) to multiple victims.

page305.title: Krazzy 4
page305.description: 4 mental patients formulate the plan to rescue their kidnapped doctor and teach the kidnappers a lesson.

page305.title: Jaanam Samjha Karo
page305.description: Love slowly develops between a spoiled young rich man (Salman Khan) and a nightclub dancer (Urmila Matondkar) he tries to impress.

page305.title: Dillagi
page305.description: Ranvir and Rajvir along with their parents move to Mumbai. They endure numerous hardships, but their will to survive prevails and they succeed.

page305.title: Anjaan Raahen
page305.description: Anand faces trouble when one of his female students becomes pregnant.

page305.title: Geeta Mera Naam
page305.description: Geeta sets out to prove her estranged sister's innocence in a murder case, which leads to the gang of their estranged brother Johnny.

page305.title: Mere Jeevan Saathi
page305.description: An amnesiac artist (Rajesh Khanna) falls in love with the doctor who helps him regain his memory.

page306.title: Aaja Sanam
page306.description: A doctor (Feroz Khan) travels from a big city to a small village, where he can serve the poor who cannot afford medical treatment.

page306.title: Yaar Meri Zindagi
page306.description: A story of two friends, one is Thakur and the other a doctor. A journey how two friends egos clash and they turn foes. The movie started making in 1971 and censored in 1996 and finally got its theatrical release in 2008.

page306.title: Dil Ka Rishta
page306.description: A man (Arjun Rampal) cares for the woman (Aishwarya Rai) he loves after a car accident leaves her with amnesia.

page306.title: Shareef Budmaash
page306.description: The Indian government's plan for a new kind of super aircraft is procured by a gangster and he hides in his safe. When police investigate, it goes missing from him. The suspicion goes towards the gangster's trusted man.

page306.title: Mera Vachan Geeta Ki Kasam
page306.description: A bandit accidentally shoots and kills a woman; to make amends, he decides to adopt her daughter, vowing to secure the little girl's future.

page306.title: Mission Kashmir
page306.description: A boy (Hrithik Roshan) trains with a militant leader (Jackie Shroff) in order to punish the police officer (Sanjay Dutt) who killed his parents.

page307.title: Pyari Behna
page307.description: Kaali is suspended by his boss, Vinay, for an accident. Kaali's sister Seeta loves Vinay, but Kaali won't let them marry.

page307.title: Naukri
page307.description: The story features a person getting help of an angel after his death.The God Sent person makes the hero realize that when he was alive he was so important and loved by all around him but he couldn’t recognize it.

page307.title: Mann
page307.description: A young woman falls in love with a handsome playboy, while aboard a Singapore to India cruise. They make plans to meet again, but fate may have other plans...

page307.title: God Tussi Great Ho
page307.description: A TV anchor keeps on blaming God for his unsuccessful life. God appears and he is given the God's Power for 10 days just to see how he manages to keep everyone happy.

page307.title: Falak
page307.description: Ramnath is killed at his job and his employers do not offer compensation. The man's two sons grow up and plot revenge against the corrupt businessmen.

page307.title: Kaajal
page307.description: A story of two women, Madhavi (Meena Kumari), self-effacing, spiritual and totally steeped in indegenous culture. Bhanu (Padmini), sensuous, independent, possessive and passionate. They both love Kumar Rajesh (Dharmendra).

page308.title: Jaal
page308.description: Shankar's father leaves the family for Meenabai. He later learns that his father is dead. He sets out to find out Meenabai, who he thinks is behind his father's death.

page308.title: Hasee Toh Phasee
page308.description: Nikhil is re-introduced to Meeta nearly ten years after their first meeting. Now, as Nikhil has one week to prove himself worth enough to marry Meeta's sister Karishma, the old acquaintances become quite close to each other.

page308.title: Chooran Goli
page308.description: "At the dead of night kidnappings are happening in the city and Chulbuli’s Uncle Phatphate is also mysteriously Kidnapped by the Dangerous Don Rasiya assisted by his stylish Secretary Chameli and Their Rustic goons.

page308.title: Jai Ho
page308.description: An ex-army officer initiates a unique idea of propagating social responsibility among ordinary people and in doing so, crosses paths with a powerful political family.

page308.title: One By Two
page308.description: Aspiring musician Amit and dance fanatic Samara get a better insight of what life has in store for them.

page308.title: Jackpot
page308.description: The film has a casino boat backdrop and follows a card game between the players in con. Who will come out Aces and who will end up being the Joker? Try your luck, here at Jackpot.

page309.title: Yaariyan
page309.description: A college student must win an inter college competition to save his college from being demolished by property builders.

page309.title: Goliyon Ki Raasleela Ram Leela
page309.description: A man (Ranveer Singh) from a crime family falls in love with a woman (Deepika Padukone) who is resistant to her family's choice of a husband for her.

page309.title: Singh Saab The Great
page309.description: A common man works as a tax collector in a small city. A TV journalist uncovers the mysterious hero's back story.

page309.title: Naksha
page309.description: Following an ancient map, Vicky is lost and kidnapped in the jungles of India, but rescued by his older brother.

page309.title: Koyla
page309.description: A street girl agrees to a marriage to a king she has never met after he sends her a photograph of himself. But the man in the photograph is not the king; it is his most loyal slave, the handsome but mute Shankar.

page309.title: Kora Kagaz
page309.description: A woman (Jaya Bhaduri) has problems with her husband (Vijay Anand) after her mother interferes with their marriage.

page310.title: R. Rajkumar
page310.description: An aimless youth starts working for drug baron and his mission is to kill is rival.R Rajkumar its a Romantic Action Love story set in the dusty and rugged backdrop of the Hindi Heartland.

page310.title: Luv U Soniyo
page310.description: Mark & Soniyo, after having been brought together by fate, have to win over their parents' consent.A Christian boy falls for a Punjabi girl, can the two get together and keep the parents happy?

page310.title: Bullet Raja
page310.description: A common man who transforms into a gangster revolts against the very system he once obediently followed by declaring war on the police, the government, and the industrialists.

page310.title: Gori Tere Pyaar Mein
page310.description: A self-centered man (Imran Khan) must learn how to care about others in order to win back his ex-girlfriend (Kareena Kapoor Khan), a dedicated social activist.

page310.title: Elaan
page310.description: Elaan is a declaration of war against the reign of terror unleashed by the ganglords. The story revolves around an upright and principled Police Officer, A.C.P. Ramakant Chaudhary whose eldest son Vikas is killed in a pre-planned accident.

page310.title: Bluffmaster
page310.description: A conman Roy, gets dumped by his girl-friend. Then he finds out he has a fatal disease. On the verge of death, he resolves to do some good, by helping his apprentice Dittu hoodwink the mobster who hurt his (Dittu's) family.

page311.title: Bachna Ae Haseeno
page311.description: Raj is a heartbreaker. His love stories with Mahi, Radhika and Gayatri finally teach him about love and life in their own sweet, sexy and sassy way.

page311.title: Aashiqui.in
page311.description: Cyrus is a college swim champ who has difficulty in setting his future. He aspires to become a writer, but as his father wishes him to take his swimming skills to a national level, Cyrus hides his aspirations so as not disappoint his dad.

page311.title: Krrish 3
page311.description: Krrish and his scientist father have to save the world and their own family from an evil man named Kaal and his gang of mutants, led by the ruthless Kaya.

page311.title: Satya (Hindi)
page311.description: An innocent man is embroiled in underworld after being falsely charged and sets out to punish the perpetrators who subjected his life to misery.

page311.title: Chor Chor Super Chor
page311.description: In the crowded bylanes of Old Delhi, Shuklaji runs a photo studio that is a front for small time crime. Satbir, who is a part of this gang now wants to give up a life of vice and make a new beginning with his love interest - Neena.

page311.title: Sooper Se Ooper
page311.description: Ranvir`s fortune is in dumps and selling his ancestral land in Mumbai is the only way to survive & Kukreja who has put all on stake has to get this land to stay away from the wrath of a don and also achieve his dream of becoming a builder eventually!

page312.title: John Day
page312.description: The film`s story revolves around the mysterious death of a young girl. The god fearing father of the girl and a lawless cop get trapped in the case and should save themselves, but how will they?

page312.title: Mickey Virus
page312.description: The cops are cracking a cyber crime case and they hire hacker Mickey to crack the plot. It opens a lethal can of worms that no ordinary anti-virus can kill.

page312.title: Jayanta Bhai Ki Luv Story
page312.description: Jayantabhai is a street-thug and small time gangster, who unexpectedly falls in love with his enemy, who is Simrin. A romantic caper about how people unknowingly fall in love with people they least expect to.

page312.title: Ramaiya Vastavaiya
page312.description: Ram falls in love with Sona, who lives on the fields of Punjab. He follows her to her farm, where her elder brother challenges him to produce more seed on their fields. If he wins, he will be allowed to marry her.

page312.title: Warning
page312.description: Seven school friends reunite in Fiji after many years on a yacht retreat. Their adventure takes a shift when they go into sea.

page312.title: Madras Cafe
page312.description: An Indian intelligence agent journeys to a war-torn coastal island to break a resolute rebel group and meets a passionate journalist.

page313.title: Bombay Talkies
page313.description: One hundred years of Hindi cinema is celebrated in four short stories showcasing the power of film.Karan Johar, Anurag Kashyap, Zoya Akhtar and Dibakar Banerjee - four top notch directors come together to redefine Indian Cinema...

page313.title: Phata Poster Nikla Hero
page313.description: After Vishwas Rao (Shahid Kapoor) is raised up by his Mother (Padmini Kolhapure), who apparently dreams for him to become a Police Inspector. However, he has different plans in mind. Vishwas wants to become a film hero.

page313.title: Besharam
page313.description: Babli (Ranbir Kapoor) is a street smart car mechanic living in a Delhi orphanage. He is charming and lives life to the fullest. He also steals cars to support his orphanage.

page313.title: Once Upon Ay Time In Mumbaai Dobara!
page313.description: The story of Shoaib, an underworld don who came to power by killing his mentor and has extended his kingdom with the help of his best friend, Javed, and his former lover, Mumtaz.

page313.title: Ishq
page313.description: Harbans Rai and Ranjit Rai are two wealthy businessmen who absolutely *loathe* poverty and poor people . As fate would have it , Harbans Rai's daughter Madhu falls for a poor mechanic Raja while Ranjit Rai's son Ajay romances a poor girl Kajal . When Harbans and Ranjit come to know of it they try various ways to separate the lovers .

page313.title: Filhaal
page313.description: Problems ensue after a woman (Sushmita Sen) becomes a surrogate for her friend (Tabu) to have a child.

page314.title: Sixteen
page314.description: The film starring Zakir Hussain in the lead is a teenage drama set in Urban India showing the modern times that have slaughtered innocence and brought forth an era of internet, page 3 and television.

page314.title: Shuddh Desi Romance
page314.description: A romantic comedy which tells the journey of three restless young people who junk society's syllabus for finding love and decide to follow their heart.

page314.title: Zanjeer
page314.description: ACP Vijay Khanna is transferred to Mumbai where he will have do deal with the oil mafia led by Rudra Pratap Teja.

page314.title: Stupid 7
page314.description: Seven stories interweave to create this relatable tale of the gap between teenagers and the older generation.

page314.title: Lootera
page314.description: An aristocrat's daughter falls in love with a visiting archaeologist, but he holds a secret that could drive them apart.

page314.title: Corporate
page314.description: Two corporate rivals and an ambitious executive (Bipasha Basu) try to outsmart one another as they vie for power.

page315.title: Big Brother
page315.description: A docile man gets enraged when a politician's son throws acid on her face and later kills the miscreant. He is then hunted by the police and politicians who wants him dead.

page315.title: Lajja
page315.description: A man searches for his pregnant wife (Manisha Koirala) after she tries to escape from their feeble marriage.

page315.title: Dosti
page315.description: The story revolves around two inseparable friends who are very distinct from each other. Both friends eventually find their true love and decide to get married on the same day as a promise. The story takes a dramatic turn when the would-be brides find about their dark secrets.

page315.title: Nasha
page315.description: The film starring Kingfisher model Poonam Pandey is a film that revolves around teenage life. It is when an 18-year-old lad falls for a much older woman, the thrill ensues. The film is directed by Amit Saxena.

page315.title: Bajatey Raho
page315.description: Surviving family members and friends of a man who was conned by the cunning businessman Sabbarwahl string together a series of their own cons in an attempt to bring him down.

page315.title: Fukrey
page315.description: The paths of four dream-chasing college friends cross with an array of colourful characters, from a tough-talking Punjabi female don to a Jugaad Baaz college watchman. Mayhem ensues.

page316.title: D-Day
page316.description: A team of experts dispatched to bring in The Most Wanted Man in India almost achieves the unthinkable ... until something goes horribly wrong.

page316.title: Raanjhanaa
page316.description: A small-town boy needs to break through the class divide to gain acceptance from his childhood sweetheart who is in love with big city ideals.

page316.title: Ankur Arora Murder Case
page316.description: Dr Asthana's medical negligence costs an eight-year-old Ankur his life. When Dr Romesh, an intern who is in awe of Asthana, learns about it, he decides to support Ankur's mother and fight for justice.

page316.title: Go Goa Gone
page316.description: A group of friends, just looking to have a good time in a rave party on a remote island in Goa, find out that the island is infested with Zombies.

page316.title: Policegiri
page316.description: Policegiri movie is the remake of Tamil movie Sammy.Police officer Rudra is transferred to a new station to bring law and order back to a violent part of the city.

page316.title: Listen... Amaya
page316.description: In this poignant Bollywood-styled indie interpretation about family ties and growing up, fiery 22-year old writer Amaya struggles to balance working life with family life after finding out that her mom is dating her current collaborator at work.

page317.title: Yamla Pagla Deewana 2
page317.description: Dharam, Paramveer and Gajodhar reunite in the United Kingdom to open a new club.  A sequel to the 2011 hit film, Yamla Pagla Deewana.The film opens in Scotland, travels to Varanasi and eventually makes its way to the UK.

page317.title: Zila Ghaziabad
page317.description: In the city of Ghaziabad, gang war breaks between two rival groups led by Satbir Singh and Fauji. Thakur Pritam Singh, a corrupt police officer, is transferred to the city to handle the situation.

page317.title: Shootout At Wadala
page317.description: The first-ever registered encounter by the Mumbai Police, where gangster Nitesh Dhamne was shot dead,which took place on November 1, 1982. Based on a true story.

page317.title: Aurangzeb
page317.description: Kingship knows no Kinship and there can be only one Emperor in Aurangzeb's world. In Gurgaon, to bring down a criminal the law has to think like one.

page317.title: Ek Thi Daayan
page317.description: Bobo is India`s leading magician. But unknown to even his girlfriend, Tamara, Bobo's life is falling apart. His constant hallucinations leave him with no option but to seek psychiatric help.Everything Comes Full Circle!!

page317.title: Aashiqui 2
page317.description: Rahul loses his fans and fame due to alcoholism. But he then decides to turn a small time singer into a rising star.

page318.title: Commando - A One Man Army
page318.description: Karan Dogra, an Indian commando, lands in China due to a plane crash. But Indian government term him as a terrorist.

page318.title: Jolly LLB
page318.description: The story follows a struggling lawyer named Jolly (Arshad Warsi) who wants to make it big in life like his idol (Boman Irani). But when he has signed a court case against his own idol, Jolly must prove his worth and his skills as a lawyer and win the case!

page318.title: Nautanki Saala
page318.description: An actor's life changes dramatically when he saves a stranger from suicide.It is a comedy of errors where all of his acting skills are tested to the limit as he improvises his way through a hilarious real life drama.

page318.title: Chashme Baddoor
page318.description: When pretty new neighbor Seema falls for their shy roommate Sid, jealous womanizers Omi and Jai plot to break up the new lovebirds.

page318.title: I, Me Aur Main
page318.description: As Ishaan, a music producer who has commitment issues with the women in his life, feels a connection with Gauri, his next-door neighbor, he begins to learn the importance of relationships.

page318.title: Mere Dad Ki Maruti
page318.description: In the midst of a loud Punjabi wedding, a boy sneaks his dad's fancy new car to impress the college hottie and all hell breaks loose when he loses it.

page319.title: 3G A Killer Connection
page319.description: 3G is the nightmarish story of Sam Arora and Sheena, a couple, who become victims of a series of events when Sam buys a 3G enabled second hand phone in Fiji islands while on a holiday.

page319.title: Saheb Biwi Aur Gangster
page319.description: Hired to kill a nobleman, the assassin instead falls for the former's unstable wife.

page319.title: The Attacks Of 26/11
page319.description: The real-life story of eight terrorists, who sail to Mumbai and wage war on the populace for the next 24 hours.

page319.title: David (Hindi)
page319.description: David is the tale of 3 men from different parts of the world, timed in 3 different eras.While in 1975 London, a 30-year-old David is the protege of a mafia don, his namesake in 1999 Mumbai is a musician and the third David stays in present Goa, and is 40!

page319.title: Murder 3
page319.description: A hot-shot fashion and wildlife photographer Vikram gets into a relationship with Nisha. She moves in with him in his palatial house outside of the city. The old world house, made decades ago is as beautiful as it is scary.

page319.title: Ek Duuje Ke Liye
page319.description: A set of vastly different neighboring families are shocked when two of their children fall in love and strengthen their relationship in the face of opposition.

page320.title: Ek Chalis Ki Last Local
page320.description: A comic thriller about two people who miss the last local train at 1:40 am and how missing of their train changes their course of life forever.

page320.title: Baaz
page320.description: This film revolves around a killer who suffers from a mental disorder which causes him to kill those who he is attracted to. Neha Chopra gets a new job as an interior designer in Nainital and moves to a lonely neighborhood to pursue her career.

page320.title: Baat Ban Jaye
page320.description: Nisha Singh is a single rich businesswoman. She hates rich men and wants to marry a pauper. Her uncle plays match-maker, trying to find the perfect groom for his one and only niece.

page320.title: Kaalia
page320.description: A young man (Amitabh Bachchan) becomes obsessed with avenging a tragedy involving his brother.

page320.title: Hastey Hastey
page320.description: A colorful, energetic and humorous depiction of how globalization and technology have made the world a really small place.

page320.title: Aas Paas
page320.description: A woman (Hema Malini) grapples with the decision to inform her fiance (Dharmendra) of a grave secret which could destroy his entire family.

page321.title: Raja Saab
page321.description: An orphan dreams of being a wealthy man and a prince, but to do so he must humiliate the woman he has fallen in love with, who happens to be a princess.

page321.title: Ishq Vishk
page321.description: It is about Rajiv (Shahid Kapoor) and Payal (Amrita Rao) who are friends since childhood. While Payal is in love with Rajiv, it takes him a bit longer to return her feelings.

page321.title: Ahankaar
page321.description: A mute man trying to support his family after his father is sent to jail exposes a fraudulent man and sends him to jail. The criminal's sister hatches a plan to exact revenge.

page321.title: Yeh Nazdeekiyan
page321.description: Sunil Verma, head of an advertising agency, Shobhna, his wife and their daughter, studying in a boarding school, lead a happy, middle-class life. During an outdoor shooting session for a commercial, Sunil falls for the charms of a beautiful model, Kiran.

page321.title: Woh Saat Din
page321.description: A kindly doctor (Naseeruddin Shah) offers to reunite his unhappy wife (Padmini Kolhapure) with the man (Anil Kapoor) she truly loves.

page321.title: Tum Milo Toh Sahi
page321.description: A retired law clerk defends an encroaching restaurant owner against a multinational company.

page322.title: Talaq
page322.description: Talaq or Talaaq is a 1958 Indian Bollywood film starring Rajendra Kumar and produced by Anupam Chitra studios. Director Mahesh Kaul was nominated for a Filmfare Award for Best Director and it was also nominated for a Filmfare Award for Best Movie.

page322.title: Sohni Mahiwal
page322.description: Mirza Izzat Beg has dreamt of meeting a beautiful girl, and in order to make this a reality he travels to seek her out. Will he be lucky in his quest for love?

page322.title: Talaash The Hunt Begins
page322.description: A high-profile vigilante must evade his enemies to find the medicine that his ailing mother needs.-The Hunt Begins- For them it was revenge. For him it was a challenge. A timeless ride on a ferocious mission.

page322.title: Shree 420
page322.description: Raj (Raj Kapoor), travels to the big city to earn a living. He falls in love with the poor but virtuous Vidya (Nargis), but is soon seduced by the riches of unethical lifestyle presented to him by Seth and Maya. He eventually becomes a swindler, or "420."

page322.title: Shoot On Sight
page322.description: A Muslim police officer has to display courage at work during terrorist attacks and deal with family conflict at home.

page322.title: Shakti The Power
page322.description: A couple visits the husband's family in India and finds itself in the middle of a fratricidal battle.

page323.title: Santosh
page323.description: A manipulative and cold woman marries a poor man and also has a child with him. She soon gets tired of living in poverty and abandons her family and returns to her wealthy father.

page323.title: Sailaab
page323.description: Krishna is suffering from memory loss and is under the guidance of Dr Sushma. They fall in love and get married, but when Krishna gains his memory he tries to kill Dr Sushma.

page323.title: Saat Rang Ke Sapne
page323.description: A remake of Thenmavin Kombath, a Malayalam movie.  Best friends fall in love with the same girl.

page323.title: Rangeela
page323.description: A poor young woman, who dreams of Bollywood fame, is caught in a love triangle between her childhood friend and a famous actor.

page323.title: Parampara
page323.description: The grandchildren of sworn enemies want to be friends, but the old family feud must be settled by one of them dying in a duel.

page323.title: Nayee Padosan
page323.description: Three young men try to impress a beautiful young woman who comes to live in their neighborhood.

page324.title: Nayak The Real Hero
page324.description: A man accepts a challenge by the chief minister of Maharashtra to run the state for one day, and makes such a success of it that soon he is embroiled in political intrigue.

page324.title: Namak Halaal
page324.description: Arjun must save the hotel owner from killers and win his true love, Poonam.It was also remade in Tamil as Velaikaran by veteran director S.P. Muthuraman in 1986 with Rajnikanth.

page324.title: Nagina
page324.description: While wandering through a ruined part of his ancestral mansion, Rajeev almost tramples on a snake. A few days later, Rajeev is now strangely drawn towards the old mansion and keeps visiting it, meets a mysterious girl, Rajani (Sridevi). Rajeev finds that he is becoming obsessed with thoughts of Rajani.

page324.title: Mumbai Matinee
page324.description: Debu (Rahul Bose) is a 32-year-old advertising agent, but has a serious problem in that he is still a virgin. He meets Baba Hindustani (Vijay Raaz) in a hotel who promises to cure him of the teasing he gets from being a virgin. An Adult Comedy!!

page324.title: Mujhe Kucch Kehna Hai
page324.description: Karan, a struggling artist, goes out of his way to rescue strangers and friends, regardless of the consequences.

page324.title: Morning Walk
page324.description: One morning walk in Joymohan's life changes it all. After suffering a heart-attack one morning, on his birthday, Joymohan realizes that he needs to spend more time with his family - son, daughter-in-law, and granddaughter.

page325.title: Mehbooba
page325.description: Complications arise when a man (Rajesh Khanna) learns about his love for a woman (Hema Malini) in a previous life.

page325.title: Mere Baap Pehle Aap
page325.description: Gaurav and Sheekha fall in love as Gaurav arranges a reunion between old flames, his father and Anuradha.

page325.title: Mast
page325.description: A young man (Aftab Shivdasani) goes out of his way to meet a film star (Urmila Matondkar), an obsession that caused him to flunk his final exams.

page325.title: Lahu Ke Do Rang
page325.description: Inspector Raj Singh's father was killed by Shankar and his men for gold. Years later he locates them but also finds that he has a step brother Suraj who works for Shankar now known as Devi Dayal.

page325.title: Kasme Vaade
page325.description: Amit and Suman love each other and have somewhat spoiled Amit's younger brother, Raju. When Raju falls in with bad company, Amit is killed trying to rescue him. A criminal who looks like Amit now enters the lives of Suman & Raju.

page325.title: Jung
page325.description: Honest police officer Veer Chauhan believes in arresting law-breakers and placed them in the lock-ups for trial in a court of law while his colleague Khan feels that the police should take action upon apprehending the criminals that are shooting them to death.

page326.title: Joshila
page326.description: Jailor Manmohan Krishan is responsible for looking after convicts serving sentences of rigorous imprisonment.

page326.title: John Jani Janardhan
page326.description: John Jani Janardhan is a Hindi film is directed by T.Rama Rao. Rajinikanth played the main lead in a triple role. John being the father and johnny and janardhan being the two sons.

page326.title: Jodi No 1
page326.description: Tells the story of two friends, Jai (Sanjay Dutt) and Veeru (Govinda), who are basically con men. While gambling in a club, Jai picks a fight with Tiger (Rajat Bedi), the younger brother of a don (Ashish Vidyarthi), who gets killed due to his undoing.

page326.title: Itihaas
page326.description: A poor villager falls in love with a woman (Twinkle Khanna) and saves her from the clutches of an evil man (Raj Babbar).

page326.title: Hawayein
page326.description: The film, set against the backdrop to the anti-Sikh riots of 1984.It is the story of his journey from innocence to disillusionment, from being a simple, music loving student to becoming one of the most wanted terrorists in the country.

page326.title: Fox
page326.description: Arjun Kapoor (Arjun Rampal) is a successful criminal defense lawyer. The film opens with him defending his friend Raj Thakur, who has been accused of rape and murder. Arjun's defense strategy involves suggesting the victim had dubious morals.

page327.title: Eeshwar
page327.description: Eeshwar is an autistic man beloved in his hometown .He's not respected by everyone, however.He finds solace in Lalita, a widow taking care of her son on her own. Eeshwar bonds with the boy, an artistic prodigy, and falls in love with Lalita.

page327.title: Dharti
page327.description: Dharti is a 1970 Bollywood action film directed by C.V. Sridhar. The film stars Rajendra Kumar and Waheeda Rehman. It is a remake of the 1969 Tamil language film Sivandha Mann that starred Sivaji Ganesan.

page327.title: Darling
page327.description: A man cheats on his wife with his secretary, but things take a major shift after he accidentally kills her.

page327.title: Chandni Chowk To China
page327.description: An action-comedy about a simple cook from Chandni Chowk mistaken for the reincarnation of an ancient peasant warrior Liu Shengh by residents of an oppressed Chinese village.

page327.title: Biraj Bahu
page327.description: Biraj Bahu is a 1954 Hindi film produced by Hiten Choudhury and directed by Bimal Roy, and based on a Bengali novel by Saratchandra Chattopadhyay. The film stars Kamini Kaushal, Abhi Bhattacharya and Pran and has music by Salil Choudhury.

page327.title: Banaras
page327.description: A mystic love story... between two people of different castes... set in the oldest living city on Earth...

page328.title: Alibaba Aur 40 Chor
page328.description: Set in the days of 12th century, Abu Hassan, a notorious bandit, is having a reign of terror on the people of Gulabad (city of flowers).  Check out how fate united Alibaba, Marjina and Fatima to free the people of Gulabad out of the reign of terror of Abu Hassan.

page328.title: Aasha
page328.description: The story is about Kishore who is good-hearted person and always helps poor people even though he is from rich Zamindar family. The film was remade in Tamil as Athisaya Penn.

page328.title: Main Krishna Hoon
page328.description: An abandoned baby boy is rescued from floodwaters by Kantaben and Nattubhai, the kindly proprietors of a small orphanage. In answer to an orphan boy's prayers, the divine Lord Krishna comes to Earth, befriends the boy, and helps him find a loving family.

page328.title: Matru Ki Bijlee Ka Mandola
page328.description: Harry is an industrialist who loves his daughter Bijlee, and the bond they share with Harry's man friday, Matru. Bijlee's plan to wed the son of a politician, however, brings twists and turns in the lives of Matru, Bijlee and Mandola.

page328.title: Aashiqui
page328.description: Rahul and Anu fall in love with each other, but before they unite, they have their own problems to deal with.

page328.title: Zubeida
page328.description: Zubeidaa, an aspiring Muslim actress, marries a Hindu prince to become his second wife. Her tumultuous relationship with her husband, and her inner demons lead her to a decision which has fatal consequences for them all.

page329.title: Yeh Dil
page329.description: The parents of a wealthy man (Tusshar Kapoor) and a poor woman try to prevent their children from marrying.

page329.title: Yaar Gaddar
page329.description: A police inspector finds himself in a dilemma when his brother robs a bank and kills a person, without being able to offer a credible reason for his actions.

page329.title: Three Love Lies And Betrayal
page329.description: A struggling married couple, Rajeev (Akshay Kapoor) and Anjini Dutt (Akshay Kapoor), decide to rent out a room in their house to singer Sanjay (Ashish Chowdhry) in the hope of relieving financial pressures.

page329.title: Tawaif
page329.description: The film mainly is about a tawaif (courtesan or someone who willingly or otherwise adopts the profession of entertaining others for a living), who accidentally enters the life of Dawood who already has fallen in love with an upcoming writer.

page329.title: Shor In The City
page329.description: Shor in the city revolves around three loosely interconnected stories set in the midst of the noise and grime of Mumbai during the Ganpati festival.

page329.title: Sherni
page329.description: A 1988 Hindi film produced by Pawan Kumar and directed by Harmesh Malhotra. The film stars Sridevi and Shatrughan Sinha in lead roles along with Pran, Ranjeet, Master Rinku, Tej Sapru & Lalita Pawar.

page330.title: Raju Chacha
page330.description: Siddhant Rai is a wealthy architect, living a comfortable lifestyle with his 3 children.Because they have no mother, Siddhant has arranged for many governesses or teachers to take care of them, but the children always drive any of those away.

page330.title: Rajkumar
page330.description: Family rivalries get in the way of the romance between a prince and an enemy's daughter.

page330.title: Qila
page330.description: When a seemingly brutal landowner is murdered, the case is brought up in court to none other than his own twin brother, Judge Amarnath Singh, who rounds up all suspects, but is yet unable to determine who the murderer is.

page330.title: Pyar Koi Khel Nahin
page330.description: Brothers (Sunny Deol, Apoorva Agnihotri) conflict over business and love when they realize they have fallen for the same woman (Mahima Chaudhury).

page330.title: Phoonk
page330.description: An atheist is forced to consult an exorcist after his daughter shows signs of being possessed.

page330.title: Paap
page330.description: A policeman (John Abraham) falls for a beautiful woman (Udita Goswami) while investigating a murder witnessed by a boy.

page331.title: Maine Dil Tujhko Diya
page331.description: A jealous tycoon schemes to shatter the romance between his business partner's daughter (Sameera Reddy) and the leader (Sohail Khan) of a campus security group.

page331.title: Main Aurr Mrs Khanna
page331.description: Samir Khanna, based in Melbourne, meets with an orphan named Raina. The pair fall in love, marry and live blissfully until Samir loses his job, forcing him to return to his parents in Delhi.

page331.title: Keemat They Are Back
page331.description: After a man is killed when a mugging goes wrong, the two small-time crooks responsible try to make amends by pretending to be his best friends and helping his village.

page331.title: Kasoor
page331.description: A lawyer (Lisa Ray) walks a dangerous line by falling in love with her client (Aftab Shivdasani), a wealthy man accused of murdering his wife.

page331.title: Kabul Express
page331.description: A thrilling story spanning 48 hours of five individuals linked by hate and fear but brought together by fate to finally recognize each other.

page331.title: Julie
page331.description: A broken hearted Julie comes to Mumbai to make a living,But the fast moving City will force her to take prostitution as her profession.

page332.title: James
page332.description: James, who comes to Mumbai seeking a successful life, and ends up working as a bouncer at a club there, and fighting gangsters. He then encounters the brother of an MP who is always causing crime.

page332.title: Insaaf The Justice
page332.description: Police and a family have a hard time bringing a politicians son to justice

page332.title: Hogi Pyar Ki Jeet
page332.description: Thakur visits Surjit and kills him and his wife in broad daylight; Surjit's last dying wish is that his two sons, Raju and Kishan, must get married to Thakur's two daughters, Megha and Preeti.

page332.title: Hindustani
page332.description: Senapathy, a veteran freedom fighter, is angry. He is angry about the rampant corruption at every level of the bureaucracy. He will clean it up at any cost.

page332.title: Hathyar: Face To Face With Reality
page332.description: Ostracized by society for his late father's past, a man (Sanjay Dutt) follows in his footsteps and becomes a gangster.

page332.title: Guzaarish
page332.description: A paralyzed Magician-turned-Radio Jockey makes a petition to the Court that shocks the world and leaves Sofia, his nurse,and lover, in an impasse that challenges their relationship and their love.

page333.title: Gundaraj
page333.description: Ajay is framed for the rape of three young girls and must find out the conspiracy behind the plot to frame him.

page333.title: Fruit And Nut
page333.description: Monica Gokhale works for Bombay Heritage Society. Her plans for revamping the city's old buildings go against Maharaja Harry Holkar. To stop Gokhale, Holkar has her kidnapped. However, she is rescued by Jolly Maker, an innocent and not so smart person.

page333.title: EMI
page333.description: Sattar (Sanjay Dutt), owner of Good Luck Recovery Agency, is the saviour and the solution for all those caught in the debt trap. From Bhaigiri to business to politics to social work—that's how Sattar wants to progress in life.

page333.title: Des Pardes
page333.description: Samir gets an offer to work in the U.K. As the years go by, his family stops receiving letters from him and wants to know what has happened.

page333.title: Chorni
page333.description: A judge (Shreeram Lagoo) adopts a young woman to prevent her from becoming a career criminal.

page333.title: Chori Chori
page333.description: Khushi (Rani Mukerji) is a careless worker always conning her boss and making excuses to not do her duty. She meets Ranbir Malhotra (Ajay Devgan) and learns that the home he plans to build for his love is now a dream fulfilled.

page334.title: Chalo Ishq Ladaaye
page334.description: A woman must learn to coexist with the grandmother of her new boyfriend (Govinda).

page334.title: Banjaran
page334.description: A 50-year-old mystery comes to light when two strangers, haunted by images of each other, meet for the first time.

page334.title: Aao Wish Karein
page334.description: A 12-year-old boy makes a wish to be older so he can woo a beautiful 22-year-old.

page334.title: Aadmi Khilona Hai
page334.description: Sharad and Punam are devastated to learn they cannot have children until Ganga, their sister-in-law, gives them her child to care for. When Sharad lands a great job, Ganga's true reasons for being generous come out.

page334.title: Talaash
page334.description: Inspector Surjan Shekhawat, who is dealing with a depressing past, has to investigate a high profile murder case, deal with his crumbling marriage and use the help and solace of a prostitute by the name of Rosie.

page334.title: Table No 21
page334.description: A couple live a mediocre life and are thrilled to have won an exotic vacation to Fiji & their excitement increases when they get a chance to play "Tell all truth" game for a mind boggling prize money.

page335.title: Deewana Main Deewana
page335.description: Basant (Govinda) does everything he can to get the girl he loves.How far can you go for the person you love?

page335.title: Dabangg 2
page335.description: Chulbul Pandey is back in Dabangg 2! The sequel to `Dabangg` stars Salman and Sonakshi Sinha in leading roles. Chulbul Pandey has to battle the evil goon turned politician Baccha Bhaiyya.

page335.title: Gangoobai
page335.description: Gangoobai, a Maid-in-Matheran, has lived a life with simple aspirations, until one day she finds a new purpose of buying a designer sari. She follows her dream to the big city of Mumbai.

page335.title: Chakradhaa
page335.description: Shravan, a student, gets embroiled in the world of crime, after he is falsely accused of murdering his principal Shrivastav. He then decides to fight back for justice and change in the society, thus becoming 'Pandit' from 'Shravan'.

page335.title: Son Of Sardaar
page335.description: This tale of two warring Sardar families features Ajay Devgn who plays Rajveer an innocent Sikh, torn between a family feud. His bad luck leads to a comedy of errors which makes this film a rip-roaring laugh riot!

page335.title: Khiladi 786
page335.description: The underachieving son of a marriage bureau owner attempts to marry a don's daughter to a supposed police officer in an effort to prove his worth to his father.

page336.title: Delhi Safari
page336.description: A group of animals plan a trip to Delhi in order to ask the parliament why the forest they live in is on the verge of destruction.

page336.title: Jab Tak Hai Jaan
page336.description: An uncompromising film on true love from the legendary and unforgettable director Yash Chopra which is fascinatingly distinctive and contemporary.

page336.title: Kismet Love Paisa Dilli
page336.description: Lucky is a college going guy and Lovina is the girl next door who misses their last metro back home and a series of on the edge moments occur through the night where Lokesh and Lovina run across Delhi on this roller coaster of a ride.

page336.title: Harud
page336.description: Rafiq and his family are struggling to come to terms with the loss of his older brother Tauqir, a tourist photographer, who is one of the thousands of young men who have disappeared, since the onset of the militant insurgency in Kashmir.

page336.title: Raaz 3
page336.description: When an ingénue's sudden popularity threatens to shove her out of the spotlight, a movie star uses black magic in an attempt to derail her career.

page336.title: 1920: Evil Returns
page336.description: The film is a supernatural thriller which revolves around Jaidev Varma, a famous poet who lives the life of a loner as he is unable to meet the love of his life. He meets Smruti near the lake under mysterious circumstances.Possession Is Back!!

page337.title: Student Of The Year
page337.description: Several alumni reminisce about their final year at St. Theresa's College and the events that shaped their lives.

page337.title: Chakravyuh (2012)
page337.description: On the request of his friend Kabir, SP Adil Sends him to the Naxal group as an informer. When Kabir finds the truth he becomes one of their gang leaders.

page337.title: I Am 24
page337.description: Saying the truth was always difficult, and lying, they say, is much simpler. Shubendu lives by the tougher option. But when this honest, 42 year old balding writer falls in love with a 22 year old beauty queen, he is tempted to lie.

page337.title: Yes Boss
page337.description: Rahul Joshi wants to be a successful businessman so he works hard for his boss Siddharth. One day Rahul meets Seema, an up and coming model, and he feels like he's finally met his match. Will Seema fall for Rahul?

page337.title: The Train (1970)
page337.description: An honest and dedicated police inspector is assigned to solve some very difficult crimes - some that have been committed only on the train. It's even more difficult than it should be because not everyone is who they claim to be.

page337.title: The Train (2007)
page337.description: Vishal and his wife try to make their crumbling marriage work until he meets Roma, an unhappily married woman, on a train and the two instantly fall in love.

page338.title: That Girl In Yellow Boots
page338.description: Ruth (Kalki Koechlin), an illegal immigrant in Mumbai, refuses to return to England unless she finds her father, an Indian who abandoned the family when she was a kid. Does Ruth manage to find her father?

page338.title: Raju Ban Gaya Gentleman
page338.description: Holding a degree in engineering; Raj Mathur alias Raju finds that his talent is wasted in the village so he decides to re-locate to Bombay.

page338.title: Fiza
page338.description: In 1993 Fiza's brother disappears during the riots in Mumbai. In 1999 Fiza is tired of waiting and goes looking for him.

page338.title: Ek Shrimaan Ek Shrimati
page338.description: Deepali rejects a proposal of marriage from eligible bachelor Pritam, as she is in love with another; Pritam refuses to give up and tries to win her over by proving his unconditional love, while also attempting to win over her family.

page338.title: English Vinglish (Hindi)
page338.description: A quiet, sweet tempered housewife endures small slights from her well-educated husband and daughter every day because of her inability to speak and understand English.

page338.title: Rush
page338.description: Story of a struggling news reporter engulfed by the veneer of glamour, money, power and the enviable life of media.

page339.title: Yeh Jo Mohabbat Hai
page339.description: Yeh Jo Mohabbat Hai is a dramatic love story of two young people who are caught between love for each other and the generations old enmity between their respective Rajput families.

page339.title: 2001: Do Hazaar Ek
page339.description: Following the brutal slaying of a call-girl named Julie in Bombay city, two police inspectors, namely Anil Sharma and Rajat Bedi, are assigned to investigate and bring the culprit(s) to book.

page339.title: Supari
page339.description: Four friends agree to pay off their debts to a crime boss (Nandita Das) by becoming her hit men.

page339.title: Sirf Tum
page339.description: Kind-hearted Deepak finds a purse belonging to Aarthi, who works in Delhi. After he mails back her bag, the two begin corresponding and decide to meet, but the two strangers have difficulty finding each other in the large city.

page339.title: Parineeta
page339.description: A young girl Lolita, orphaned at an early age is sent to live with her uncle’s family, where destiny introduces her to Shekhar, a budding musician, and son of an affluent businessman.The arrival of another man into their life changes everything.

page339.title: Love Breakups Zindagi
page339.description: A couple and many of their friends experience changes and challenges in their respective lives after attending a wedding.

page340.title: Kismat
page340.description: Tony works as a hit-man for a gangster, Vikas Patil, who owes his alliance to the wealthy Raj Mallya, who is involved in marketing outdated drugs.

page340.title: Karzzzz
page340.description: A singer/dancer, while on tour, starts hallucinating and having visions of having been there before.

page340.title: Ganga Ki Saugand
page340.description: When a cruel landowner, Jaswant Singh, assaults an old woman, her son, Jeeva, steps in to intervene, and is forced to leave the village. Years later he returns to execute revenge on Jaswant.

page340.title: Sunday
page340.description: Sehar's world turns topsy-turvy when she gets a clue about the missing Sunday of her life, which points to possible violent attacks on her. A.C.P. Rajveer takes up the case to sort out the complicated and jumbled up threads of Sehar's life.

page340.title: Zakhm
page340.description: Amidst religious riots, a son deals with his mother's life-threatening injuries, and her last request.

page340.title: Yeshwant
page340.description: After arresting a drug dealer during an undercover operation, police officer Yeshwant Lohar (Nana Patekar) is framed for murder and imprisoned by his corrupt supervisor, Salim Shaikh (Mohan Joshi), who is involved in distributing narcotics.

page341.title: Tridev
page341.description: A framed police inspector (Sunny Deol) joins forces with other victims to liquidate a Hong Kong gangster

page341.title: Taarzan: The Wonder Car
page341.description: Deven tries to sell the design of a futuristic car to Four Fox, who steals his design and kills him. Twelve years later his son rebuilds the car, which avenges his death.

page341.title: Pran Jaye Par Shaan Na Jaye
page341.description: Chawl dwellers in Mumbai mistake a researcher's (Aman Verna) kindness for wealth and try to get loans and gifts from him.

page341.title: Sangdil Sanam
page341.description: Falsely accused of robbery and sent to prison for 12 years, a bank manager realizes upon his return that a person whom he trusted had betrayed him.

page341.title: Salma Pe Dil Aa Gaya
page341.description: Salma Pe Dil Aa Gaya is a 1997 Bollywood Romantic Drama film Produced and Directed By Sawan Kumar Tak. The Film Starring Ayub Khan, Saadhika Randhawa, Milind Gunaji in the lead role and Pran in supporting role.

page341.title: Ram-Avtar
page341.description: A happy-go-lucky alcoholic (Anil Kapoor) and his friend (Sunny Deol) fall in love with the same woman (Sridevi).

page342.title: Qayamat Se Qayamat Tak
page342.description: Raj Singh and Rashmi Rajput embark on a passionate romance. Unfortunately, their respective families are the bitterest of enemies. Desperate to be together, the two try to escape their families by fleeing to the countryside.

page342.title: Prem Aggan
page342.description: Families that are upset at the untraditional affair between Sapna and Suraj conspire to manipulate the lovers into arranged marriages.

page342.title: Pratiggya
page342.description: The story revolves around Dharmendra out to avenge his parents' brutal murder by Ajit in this "violent revenge" story.

page342.title: Pinjar
page342.description: On the eve of the India/Pakistan partition, a man (Manoj Bajpai) abducts a woman (Urmila Matondkar) awaiting an arranged marriage to a scholar (Sanjay Suri).

page342.title: Once Upon A Time In Mumbai
page342.description: A smuggler rises to power in 1970s Mumbai, a younger gangster seeks to overthrow him, and a police officer is caught in the middle.

page342.title: Naseeb
page342.description: Naseeb is a 1981 Bollywood action comedy film produced and directed by Manmohan Desai. The film is a typical Manmohan Desai film with his regular star Amitabh Bachchan and a large cast, lavish sets, memorable music and the lost and found theme.

page343.title: My Brother Nikhil
page343.description: Swimmer Nikhil Kapoor deals with the repercussions of announcing the fact that he has HIV.

page343.title: Maryada
page343.description: Lalita, a young woman who lives with her widowed mother, becomes stranded while traveling but is assisted by Raja and they instantly fall in love. However, when the couple meet again, Raja admits to not being everything he seems.

page343.title: Malamaal Weekly
page343.description: The struggles of the inhabitants of a rural town stricken by poverty may be alleviated with the winnings of a local lottery, but only if Lilaram can find the winning ticket.

page343.title: Karamdaata
page343.description: A wealthy man is left to bring up his granddaughter and is devastated when she falls in love with a poor cabdriver.

page343.title: Kaho Naa... Pyaar Hai
page343.description: "Kaho Naa... Pyaar Hai" is a tender-hearted love story about an upright young man who brings cheer, music and warmth into the life of a sweet-natured girl. For the innocent twosome, life is almost like paradise till fate intervenes.

page343.title: Jugnu
page343.description: Ashok Roy, a wealthy and respected member of his community, moonlights as a disguise-wearing philanthropist while his alter ego, Jugnu, robs others to finance his orphanage.

page344.title: Jheel Ke Us Paar
page344.description: Kulwant Rai runs over a little girl with his carriage. His son eventually falls in love with her.

page344.title: Jeevan Mrityu
page344.description: After his release from prison for theft, Ashok learns his mother has died, his fiance has married someone, and he was framed by his colleagues. Ashok changes his identity, searches for his fiance, and plots his revenge on his former co-workers.

page344.title: Jeans  (hindi)
page344.description: When Nasser declares that he would marry his sons to twin girls only, Lakshmi fibs that Aishwarya too is one of a pair of twins. Aishwarya begins to pose as Vaishnavi, the second twin. How the love pair come out of this tangle is the rest of the story.

page344.title: Jaisi Karni Waisi Bharnii
page344.description: Tricked by his son and in-laws, Gangaram Verma ends up homeless and penniless, but years later, his grandson decides to avenge him.

page344.title: Ishqiya
page344.description: Two thieves, Khalujan (Naseeruddin Shah) and Babban (Arshad Warsi), feeling frustrated with the lives they are leading under their ruthless ganglord Mushtaq (Salman Shahid), steal 25 lakhs from him to flee to their home.

page344.title: International Khiladi
page344.description: A gangster is sentenced to death. But some of the witnesses were not telling the truth.Crime bosses worldwide stump authorities by disappearing simultaneously as they gather to choose a leader.

page345.title: Insaf Ka Tarazu
page345.description: After inheriting his wealthy father's estate, a man pursues a beauty queen. Things turn sinister when he is charged with sexual assault the morning after visiting her.

page345.title: Hum Hain Rahi Pyar Ke
page345.description: While caring for his late sister's children, a man is torn between true love and saving his floundering factory.

page345.title: Shirin Farhad Ki Toh Nikal Padi
page345.description: Shirin and Farhad are two over-forty middle aged Parsi people, leading their lives amidst a fast dwindling Parsi community. Self-content and enveloped in their daily worldly affairs, they have not had the time to pause and think about love.

page345.title: Ek Tha Tiger
page345.description: India's top spy Tiger and his love Zoya battle the dark world of intelligence and espionage that forbids its soldiers from loving the enemy.

page345.title: Khushboo
page345.description: It was based on the Bengali novel "Panditmashai" by Sharat Chandra Chattopadhyay. Directed by Gulzar, who had a prolific year, with two more releases in the same year, Mausam and Aandhi.

page345.title: Haath Ki Safai
page345.description: Raj Kumar ends up a penniless orphan on the streets of Mumbai. Here he is taken in by a pickpocket who trains him to steal.

page346.title: God And Gun
page346.description: God and Gun is a 1995 Indian Bollywood film directed by Esmayeel Shroff and produced by Kulbhushan Gupta. It stars Raaj Kumar, Raj Babbar, Jackie Shroff and Gouthami in pivotal roles.

page346.title: Ghulami
page346.description: When a man refuses to comply with the regulations set by his father's former employer, he is labeled a bandit and chased by police.

page346.title: Do Ladke Dono Kadke
page346.description: A couple of thieves coincidentally rob a house, in which a child is being kidnapped; in the midst of the ensuing chaos, the child ends up with the thieves, while both parties try to claim ransom.

page346.title: Bombay (hindi)
page346.description: A Hindu man and a Muslim woman fall in love in a small village and move to Mumbai, where they have two children. However, growing religious tensions and erupting riots threaten to tear the family apart.

page346.title: Black Mail
page346.description: A villain (Shatrughan Sinha) uses his own innocent fiancee (Raakhee) in a scheme against the inventor (Dharmendra) of a solar-power device.

page346.title: Bhabhi (1991)
page346.description: Bhabhi is the saga of an Indian woman Seeta who is tormented and tortured by her in-laws. Sita is the most hated member of the family and is subjected to both physical and verbal abuse. Her only support is her brother-in-law Amar who tries to protect her.

page347.title: Bol Bachchan
page347.description: Abbas Ali (Abhishek Bachchan) lives in Karol Bagh, New Delhi with his sister Sania (Asin Thottumkal). They are legally fighting for their ancestral property but the odds turn against them and they lose.

page347.title: Cocktail
page347.description: A love triangle between a guy and two girls, who are best friends but the complete opposite of one another.

page347.title: Mere Dost Picture Abhi Baki Hai
page347.description: Amar Joshi (Sunil Shetty) sells his business in hope to become a film director. After meeting immoral producers and financers, he finds out that his journey won't be so easy.

page347.title: Kyaa Super Kool Hain Hum
page347.description: Adi and Sid want to make big but always run out of luck and series of confusion start taking place when they reach Goa. A Bollywood adult comedy!!

page347.title: Jism 2
page347.description: Izna, a porn star, is tasked by an Indian Intelligence Agency to seduce her ex-boyfriend Kabir, a dreaded assassin, in order to steal vital information relating to his sleeper cell contacts.

page347.title: Bezubaan
page347.description: A young woman must try to keep a one-night stand that she had in college a secret from her husband who happens to be one of his best friends, and thowart a persistant blackmailer intent on collecting money from her to keep quite about it.

page348.title: Gangaajal
page348.description: An IPS officer motivates and leads a dysfunctional, corrupt police force of Tezpur to fight against the corrupt politician.The movie as a sidetrack also mentions the 1980 blinding incident at Bhagalpur.

page348.title: Faasle
page348.description: A story about the blind sense of duty inculcated by the older generation and the self-confidence and arrogance of the youth, it is a story of everyone doing what they believe to be right, all in the name of Love.

page348.title: Dil-E-Nadaan
page348.description: A man and his adopted brother love the same woman; the woman loves the orphan and is set to marry him. But just before his marriage, he gets a colleague pregnant owing to a chance encounter, complicating matters for everyone.

page348.title: Dhol
page348.description: Four lazy friends try to woo a rich girl, in order to live a wealthy lifestyle. Their plan, however goes horribly wrong after they get embroiled with a notorious criminal.A remake of 1990 Malayalam film In Harihar Nagar!!

page348.title: Dhamaal
page348.description: Four slackers race to find a mobster's buried treasure while being pursued by a determined police inspector.

page348.title: Deewane
page348.description: A woman (Urmila Matondkar) doesn't realize that the dedicated cop (Ajay Devgan) she loves is in a coma and a small-time crook who resembles him has been sent home in his place.

page349.title: Dalaal
page349.description: Dalaal is the story of the illiterate Bhola Nath, who escorts young women to meet with their brothers. One day, during the course of his duties, he meets a beautiful woman named Roopali, who makes him understand the true nature of his job: that of a pimp.

page349.title: Chup Chup Ke
page349.description: A debt-ridden young man attempts suicide, but is rescued only to find that his luck is finally turning.

page349.title: Bundal Baaz
page349.description: A poor Rajaram pretends to be wealthy in order to get married to his sweetheart, much to the displeasure of her father. Everything changes when Rajaram finds a bottle containing a 20000 year old genie that will help him for one year.

page349.title: Bol Radha Bol
page349.description: Kishan's life is turned upside down when he returns home one day only to find that his house has been taken over by an imposter that looks identical to him.

page349.title: Bodyguard
page349.description: Lovely Singh gets an assignment of guarding Divya. She finds him to be a major obstacle in leading a regular campus life. To throw him off-track and get him out of the way, she comes up with a plan of trapping him in a fake love affair.

page349.title: Beta
page349.description: The son of a wealthy widower, Raju becomes extremely devoted to his stepmother after his father remarries. When Raju falls for the beautiful Saraswati, unusual circumstances lead to quick courtship and a wedding for the smitten couple.

page350.title: Ajnabee
page350.description: A couple move into a new neighborhood and make new friends. The neighbor's wife is soon murdered.

page350.title: Aan Milo Sajna
page350.description: A palatial mansion is home to the ailing widow, Savitri and her lazy, wicked son, Anil, who is just waiting for nothing but his inheritance. Soon Anil appears to have reformed and Savitri likes his fiance, but is it all true or is she in danger?

page350.title: Teri Meri Kahaani
page350.description: The true love between a couple in 1910, 1960 and 2012. Their love is so strong that even destiny wants to bring them together.

page350.title: Chhodo Kal Ki Baatein
page350.description: A workaholic wakes up to find himself stuck in a time warp. What follows is a series of bizarre events, until he meets a mystery man who gives him life-changing lessons.

page350.title: Vijaypath
page350.description: Vijaypath is a 1994 Bollywood action drama film starring Ajay Devgan, Tabu and Danny Denzongpa.

page350.title: Teesri Manzil
page350.description: A woman blames a nightclub drummer for the suspicious death of her sister, and seeks revenge. However, the pair work together to solve the mystery and become romantically involved, after he introduces himself under another name.

page351.title: Sitamgar
page351.description: Sitamgar is a 1985 Bollywood film starring Dharmendra, Rishi Kapoor, Parveen Babi, Poonam Dhillon.

page351.title: Shikar
page351.description: Shikar is a 1968 Hindi movie produced and directed by Atma Ram. The film is a murder mystery that became a box office hit and its songs were also big hit.

page351.title: Sheesha
page351.description: Businesswoman Sia Malhotra lives a wealthy lifestyle in Bangkok, along with her twin, Ria, who is deaf and dumb due to a neurological disorder. She meets with Raj Oberoi, and both fall in love. An Adult Entertainer!!

page351.title: Seeta Aur Geeta
page351.description: A comedy/drama about identical twins who are separated at birth and grow up with different temperaments. Geeta is rambunctious and sometimes violent. The twins end up swapping places which cause surprise and confusion.

page351.title: Pehchan
page351.description: Pehchan is a 1970 Filmfare Award winning Bollywood romance film produced & directed by Sohanlal Kanwar, & the story is by Sachin Bhowmick. The film stars Manoj Kumar, Babita, and Balraj Sahni. Music is by Shankar Jaikishan.

page351.title: Nishabd
page351.description: A man, who has been married for 27 years, falls in love with his 18-year-old daughter's friend.

page352.title: Naseeb Apna Apna
page352.description: A record executive is forced into an arranged marriage, then falls in love with and marries his colleague.

page352.title: Naina
page352.description: An orphaned girl, blinded in the accident that killed her parents, begins seeing strange things when her vision is restored by surgery years later.

page352.title: Mandi
page352.description: A local official's son falls in love with a prostitute (Smita Patil), unaware that she is actually his half-sister.

page352.title: Loafer
page352.description: A known troublemaker (Anil Kapoor) is arrested for murder, but no one steps forward to defend him. Only a miracle can save him from the gallows.

page352.title: Lal Patthar
page352.description: Lal Patthar is a 1971 Hindi film, produced by F. C. Mehra, and directed by Sushil Majumdar. The film is a remake of the Bengali film, Lal Pathar, which was released in 1964.

page352.title: Lakeer - Forbidden Lines
