page352.description: Karan and Bindiya are childhood friends who live with Karan's brother; Karan discovers that his feelings for Bindiya are stronger than friendship.

page353.title: Garam Masala
page353.description: A rib tickling tale of two flirts who constantly flirts with women despite one of them having engaged. Chaos ensues when the fiancee finds that her to-be bride is cheating on her.

page353.title: Eklavya: The Royal Guard
page353.description: As the kingdom of Devigarh comes apart at the seams, an aging bodyguard attempts to protect the Royal Family, as well as keep its darkest secrets from ever coming to light.

page353.title: Ek Se Mera Kya Hoga
page353.description: Ek Se Mera Kya Hoga 2006 is about a guy who stalks women lure them into his trap marry them as soon as the wedding night ends he dumps them.To catch this man his victim girls create a plan to trap him. An Adult Entertainer!!

page353.title: Dil Ka Kya Kasoor
page353.description: Beautiful and wealthy, Shalini Saxena enjoys the good life residing with her brother, Rajesh. While in college, Shalini begins to write poetry under the pen name of Seema, and her work gains the admiration of Arun Kumar, a handsome young singer.

page353.title: Baazi
page353.description: The chief minister assigns a case to a police inspector to investigate an extravagant international scandal. It turns out that the fraud was committed by the minister's assistant, who frames the police officer for a murder.

page353.title: Baadshah
page353.description: After a man hires a private detective (Shahrukh Khan) to persuade his rebellious daughter (Twinkle Khanna) to marry a man she didn't choose, she falls for the detective.

page354.title: Yugpurush
page354.description: After Anirudh lost his parents in a heavy rain-storm, he loses his senses and withdrew into himself in a catatonic state, and was hospitalized in a mental asylum.After 25 years, Anirudh recovers and is released with a certificate to prove that he is normal.

page354.title: Toonpur Ka Super Hero
page354.description: Aditya (Ajay Devgn) may be a superhero on screen, but for his kids, he is just an ordinary man; a fake hero. He gets his chance to build up his image when he is abducted by a bunch of cartoons and frisked away to Toonpur.

page354.title: The Burning Train
page354.description: A story that begins in the hearts of childhood friends and lasts to adult years where humiliation and rejection can lead to revenge. This plot revolves around a train, the Super Express, that catches fire and might bring death to many on it's first journey.

page354.title: Swarg
page354.description: When Sahibji's family usurp his business and mansion, leaving him penniless, it is up to the poor house servant to fix the matter.

page354.title: Super K : The Movie
page354.description: Dreamzone is a special world in the Galaxy, ruled by the kindhearted King Maximus. Unknown to him, his brother Badmess is plotting to overthrow him.

page354.title: Shikhar
page354.description: An influential businessman traps an innocent young man into his web of greed, to which he cannot differentiate the right or wrong. He is forced to think on his choices after he is double-crossed by his mentor.

page355.title: Sharmilee
page355.description: Captain Ajit Kapoor stops off at a party and meets a fun-loving, Westernized girl he won't soon forget. When his guardian asks him to get married and then takes him to meet a girl, Ajit is thrilled because he thinks it's his dream girl. It's her twin...

page355.title: Salaam Bombay
page355.description: The story of Krishna, Manju, Chillum and the other children on the streets of Bombay. Sometimes they can get a temporary job selling tea, but mostly they have to beg for money and keep out of the way of the police.

page355.title: Sadma
page355.description: One night, Sadma is in a car accident, which leaves her with amnesia. She runs away from the hospital but ends up in a brothel, where she meets a friendly schoolteacher.

page355.title: Saajan
page355.description: A poet (Sanjay Dutt) and his best friend (Salman Khan) fall in love with the same woman (Madhuri Dixit)

page355.title: Professor
page355.description: Sita devi is a very strict aunt for a number of young ladies, and does not allow them to fraternize with males. Along comes Pritam disguised as an elderly Professor Khanna to break every possible rule of the aunt.

page355.title: Prince 1969
page355.description: An irresponsible, womanizing prince gives up his worldly possessions to learn the meaning of life.

page356.title: Om Jai Jagadish
page356.description: A woman has three sons: Om has deep-rooted values; Jai is an ambitious car designer; and Jagadish is a carefree youngster.

page356.title: Khudgarz
page356.description: Amar and Bihari are more brothers than friends.  Amar's father strongly disapproves his son's friendship, and he succeeds in destroying it.Bihari's sister must try to repair the tattered bond between her "brothers".

page356.title: Khandan
page356.description: An ancestral property is distributed between two brothers, then a couple of years later, bitterness divides their families. An outsider in the younger brother's family tries to kill the others, which is resisted in time, and they reunite.

page356.title: Jo Jeeta Wohi Sikandar
page356.description: A rich brat and a poor chap try to woo a girl, with their rivalry culminating in the most prestigious college event - the marathon cycle race.

page356.title: Jeet
page356.description: The story of Karan, a hit man who kills for the mobster Gajraj. On one job, Karan falls madly in love with Kajal, the beautiful daughter of an associate.

page356.title: Jallian Wala Bagh
page356.description: The life of Udham Singh leading up to the assassination of Michael O'Dwyer in retaliation for the Jallianwala Bagh massacre.

page357.title: Jal Mahal
page357.description: Ravi overhears a beautiful woman, Namrita, singing a sad song. He falls in love and tries to pull her away from the abyss of suicide. As time goes by, he proposes and introduces her to his family, only to find out that she is already married to Rajesh.

page357.title: Ishq Hai Tumse
page357.description: Romantic complications arise between a Hindu and a Muslim family after a wedding and a kidney donation.

page357.title: Insaaf Main Karoonga
page357.description: Ravi makes a second attempt at killing the culprit who drove his wife to suicide. But, he is under army officer's watch in hospital.

page357.title: Hungama
page357.description: A singer, a young woman (Rimi Sen) and a bank employee lie to get ahead in life, leading to cases of mistaken identities.

page357.title: Humshakal
page357.description: Commissioner Kapoor makes Dadu Kaliya take the place of his lookalike inspector Vinod who was killed by Devi Dutt but how long will he hide the secret of Vinod's death from his family.

page357.title: Hera Pheri (2000)
page357.description: Three unemployed men find the answer to all their money problems when they recieve a call from a kidnapper. However, things do not go as planned.

page358.title: Hare Rama Hare Krishna
page358.description:
The story of the destruction of the Jaiswal family and how Westernization touched both parents, their son and their daughter. Zeenat Aman, who played a westernized hippie, 
won the Filmfare Best Supporting Actress Award.

page358.title: Guddi
page358.description: Guddi is a schoolgirl in love with the actor Dharmendra who she believes is a superman and will never do harm. Her family is not concerned about her crush until she goes to Bombay and they discover she believes that movies reflect real life! What to do?

page358.title: Geraftaar
page358.description: Long-lost brothers meet in prison and help each other get revenge against a gang.A 1985 Bollywood action drama film directed by Prayag Raaj.

page358.title: Dharam Karam
page358.description: A career criminal tries to protect his son from the consequences of his crimes.

page358.title: Chand Ke Paar Chalo
page358.description: The main protagonist is Chander, a tourist photographer living with his parents, and best friend Johnny. While on his way to work, he meets a stage dancer named Nirmala and is seduced by her beauty.

page358.title: Cash
page358.description: Three unique diamonds. Two teams of thieves. One big heist that spins out into a battle for the ultimate eternal prize: Cash.

page359.title: Baton Baton Mein
page359.description: Mumbai is the setting, but also an important character, and, true to form, Chatterjee has also portrayed the lives of middle class working Indians. A girl and a boy of marriageable age also have to deal with their own very different mothers.

page359.title: Bandhe Haath
page359.description: The story evolves into a society eye opener, of the transformation of a human being from the path of crime, to goodness, his re-acceptance in ideological cast, and is a Hindi cinema classic worth watching.

page359.title: Bade Dil Wala
page359.description: Amrit's generosity and kindness initially lands him in the bad books of a dancer; then in prison; and then as false son-in-law of a very wealthy man.

page359.title: Astitva
page359.description: A philanderer (Sachin Khedekar) learns his wife (Tabu) had an affair with her music teacher (Mohnish Bahl) 25 years earlier, resulting in pregnancy.

page359.title: Around The World
page359.description: A man accompanies his uncle to Tokyo but finds himself in a dilemma when he must travel to Europe immediately, with only $8 at his disposal.

page359.title: Aankhon Aankhon Mein
page359.description: Unfairly maligned by his uncle, half-brother and father, Rakesh moves to a remote region of Northern India, where he works on construction of a dam and falls in love with one of the local women.

page360.title: Aakrosh
page360.description: The Central Bureau of Investigation deputes an Officer to investigate the disappearance of three medical students.

page360.title: Aaja Nachle
page360.description: Dia's dance teacher is dying. She returns to the town where she learnt to live and dance and most importantly to save the endangered Ajanta theatre.

page360.title: Ferrari Ki Sawaari
page360.description: How the pursuit of an Indian cricket legend's Ferrari makes a young boy's dreams of playing cricket at Lords a reality.

page360.title: 3 Bachelors
page360.description: This is a film about two young bachelors and a young-at-heart bachelor. It's a humorous take on their respective love stories.A story full of comedy, romance and confusion!!

page360.title: Shanghai
page360.description: Prime leader of a campaign against a big government project is killed in what appears to be a road accident. An IAS officer is ordered to probe the incident and the veils of falsehood begin to drop.

page360.title: Taur Mitran Di
page360.description: Taur Mittran Di is a campus-based story of 2 boys set in Guru Nanak Dev University, Amritsar. Both being touted as "Badmash" of the university with the strong rivalry between them.

page361.title: Dangerous Ishhq
page361.description: Three doppelgangers(one girl+ two boys).Two of them loves each other and get together from many lives.And the third one(who can't be killed easily)also wants the girl and he tries to separate them through many lives.

page361.title: Housefull 2
page361.description: A comedy of errors wherein four men helps each other to fool their prospective father-in-laws creating a cascade of confusion and mayhem.

page361.title: Ishaqzaade
page361.description: Rising from the ashes of hooliganism and small town clan wars, comes the love story of a passion ignited by hatred. Of two people. Born to hate. Destined to love. One kingdom. One throne

page361.title: Tezz
page361.description: Tezz is one man`s fight to get back what was taken away from him unjustly while the other man will do whatever it takes to stop him from succeeding in his mission.

page361.title: Valentine's Night
page361.description: The movie chronicles the life of four couples breaking up on Valentine`s Day in New Delhi. The broken hearts meet on social networking sites and decide to leave their pain of separation behind. They move out to enjoy the Valentine`s Night.

page361.title: Chaar Din Ki Chandni
page361.description: Chaar Din Ki Chandni is a comedy with the essence of romance, set against the backdrop of Rajasthan at a four-day wedding. The film revolves around a Rajput family and a family from Punjab, who are caught in a situation that creates a comedy of errors.

page362.title: Vicky Donor
page362.description: A man is brought in by an infertility doctor to supply him with his sperm, where he becomes the biggest sperm donor for his clinic.

page362.title: London, Paris, New York
page362.description: Nikhil and Lalitha are two completely different individuals who are drawn to each other in spite of their differences -- or perhaps because of it. Follow their journey as they meet in London, Paris and New York for a night in each city.

page362.title: Sholay
page362.description: After his family is murdered by a notorious and ruthless bandit, a former police officer enlists the services of two outlaws to capture the bandit.

page362.title: Sachche Ka Bol Bala
page362.description: Karan Kaul is the Editor of a daily newspaper. He is respected by his fans and critics alike. He loves Greta. Then Karan himself becomes a suspect, and faces loss of credibility, when he is accused of killing Greta.

page362.title: Phoonk 2
page362.description: While on vacation, children and their father are terrorized by their mother and wife respectively. A sequel to Phoonk Hindi Movie.

page362.title: Khal-Naaikaa
page362.description: After her husband kills himself, an embittered pregnant widow loses her child, and embarks on a mission of vengeance against a woman and her family.

page363.title: Gola Barood
page363.description: Gola Barood is a 1989 Hindi-language Indian action film directed by David Dhawan, starring Shatrughan Sinha and Chunky Pandey in lead roles.

page363.title: Gandhi, My Father
page363.description: Gandhi My Father paints the picture of Gandhi's intricate, complex and strained relationship with his son, Harilal Gandhi. From the onset, the two had dreams in opposite directions.

page363.title: Awarapan
page363.description: A hit man falls in love with a devout Muslim girl, and she teaches him to have compassion for others.

page363.title: Ankush
page363.description: Young men who spend their days hanging out on the streets spend their time fighting members of rival street gangs.

page363.title: An Evening In Paris
page363.description: A wealthy woman (Sharmila Tagore) meets a charming but not completely truthful beau (Shammi Kapoor) in France.

page363.title: Aghaat
page363.description: The benevolent head of a long-established union is threatened by militant rivals in an Indian factory.

page364.title: Jannat 2
page364.description: Jannat 2 is a tumultuous rollercoaster journey of Sonu Dilli (Emraan Hashmi) and an angst ridden cop (Randeep Hooda) set against the murky underbelly of the gun trade.

page364.title: Mr. Bhatti On Chutti
page364.description: Mr Bhatti is a delusional character who wins a trip to the Lake District out of the blue, he comes over, with a group of Indian tourists visiting the Lake District. Bhatti is under the impression that he has been called over by George W.Bush.

page364.title: Veerana
page364.description: A beautiful young girl, unfortunately possessed from her childhood by a vengeful spirit, wanders around lonely places to seduce and kill people and thus, gradually becoming lost into a dark world of revenge and lust.

page364.title: Teesri Aankh
page364.description: Childless Malti is married to Kailash Nath, who one day brings home a newborn baby boy and asks her to take care of him. Malti names the boy Ashok, and brings him up as her own.

page364.title: Tarazu
page364.description: A petty thief enamored of Inspector Ram Yadav, an honest man living with his family, moves into Ram's house disguised as a maid.

page364.title: Shiva
page364.description: Shiva is a 1990 Indian action film based on student politics in a Mafia backdrop written and directed by Ram Gopal Varma.

page365.title: Rakht Charitra
page365.description: Rakta Charitra is a biographical tale of Paritala Ravi from Andhra Pradesh, a prime accused in a number of murder cases.A killer bandit decides to become a politician in order to avenge deaths in his family.

page365.title: Prince
page365.description: A diamond thief loses his memory and is unable to locate a antique coin that he had stolen earlier.

page365.title: Matrubhoomi
page365.description: A village is left without women due to their practice of female infanticide. When Ramsharan finally finds a young woman to marry his son, his entire village lusts after the only available woman.

page365.title: Kuch To Gadbad Hai
page365.description: Justice Balwant Khanna lives a comfortable lifestyle with his wife, Devika, and two sons, Sanjay and Jai. He has placed a lot of faith in his sons hoping that they will marry girls of equal status.

page365.title: Khoon Aur Pani
page365.description: When a poor man named Singh decides to divert some water to his stricken fields, his father is murdered; Singh sets out to avenge his father's death.

page365.title: Jeeva
page365.description: Abducted by Dacoits at a very young age, Jeevan joins them and becomes a legend of his own by creating terror and fear in the region.

page366.title: Jail
page366.description: Convicted of a crime he didn't commit, a man (Neil Nitin Mukesh) must learn to survive inside a brutal Indian prison.

page366.title: Ek Hi Raasta
page366.description: Chotu, a bounty hunter who gets criminals to the police in exchange for money, reunites with his parents whom he never got to meet since he was kidnapped.

page366.title: Yuva
page366.description: Michael, Arjun and Lallan, three men from three different stratas of society, cross paths one morning in Calcutta and change one another's lives forever.

page366.title: Virasat
page366.description: A young man gives up his dream of opening a fast-food franchise for the nobler cause of bringing peace to his village.

page366.title: Parinda
page366.description: Brothers Kishen and Karan live in Bombay, where Karan falls in love with Paro, a pal's beautiful sister. But Karan then leaves India to attend school in America. Kishen, meanwhile, enters into a life of crime, falling under the sway of Anna, a drug dealer.

page366.title: Phool Aur Kaante
page366.description: Nageshwar is a criminal don and has an only son, Ajay who is quite apprehensive about his dad's criminal empire and wants to shape his own destiny - one that is of peace and love.

page367.title: Khiladi
page367.description: Two friends wage bets for money and fun. There comes a time where they race to win the biggest bet, for they know that their lives depend on it.

page367.title: Kabzaa
page367.description: A criminal (Paresh Rawal) endangers the lives of a landowner and two brothers (Raj Babbar, Sanjay Dutt).

page367.title: Hello Brother
page367.description: A ghost (Salman Khan) seeking revenge for his death haunts the man (Arbaaz Khan) who received his heart in a transplant.

page367.title: Dharmatma
page367.description: Dharmatama is a 1975 Hindi thriller movie and the first Bollywood film to be shot in Afghanistan. It was produced and directed by Feroz Khan. The movie is the first attempt in India to localise The Godfather.

page367.title: Asoka
page367.description: In this biopic set before his rise to power, young Prince Asoka (Shahrukh Khan) works to perfect his skills in battle and also deals with family conflict.

page367.title: Ardh Satya
page367.description: Frustrated by corruption in his precinct, a policeman (Om Puri) flies into a rage and gets suspended.Ardh Satya won many awards and went on to become a landmark film in Indian film history.

page368.title: Hate Story
page368.description: After a powerful businessman has her baby forcefully aborted, Kaavya Krishna uses her body as a sexual weapon to destroy his empire, brick by brick.

page368.title: Yateem
page368.description: Story revolves around a police officer who kills a bandit and adopts his orphan son. The boy becomes a police officer and falls in love with the man's daughter Gauri played by Farha.

page368.title: Zindagani
page368.description: Anand is looking to arrest the woman who killed his father, unaware that she's his own mother.

page368.title: Zahreelay
page368.description: A shopkeeper stands up to thugs who are trying to squeeze protection money out of him.

page368.title: Yugandhar
page368.description: Yugandhar was the story of a simpleton who became a legend. Mithun played a Robinhood type character and Kabir Bedi, the Police officer chasing Mithun.

page368.title: Waqt Ki Awaz
page368.description: The daughter of a wealthy businessman refuses to obey her father's instructions to get married to the son of his business partner.

page369.title: Victoria No.203
page369.description: When Durgadas steals some precious diamonds, one henchman turns traitor and decamps with the booty. The man is killed and diamonds missing. A Victoria driver is wrongly sentenced to lifer since he was the last man to be seen with the dead man.

page369.title: Tom, Dick, And Harry
page369.description: Three disabled friends - deaf Tom, blind Dick and dumb Harry - get caught up in a whirlwind adventure involving two beautiful girls, a kidnapping and a ton of cash.

page369.title: The Don
page369.description: A mysterious man (Mithun Chakraborty) protects a college student from the wrath of a gangster (Raza Murad).

page369.title: Sun Sajna
page369.description: A girl from a mountain town falls for a singer in this tale of love and betrayal.A 1982 Hindi film directed by Chander Bahl starring Mithun Chakraborty, Ranjeeta Kaur, Iftekhar, Ram Mohan and Jagdeep.

page369.title: Shreeman Funtoosh
page369.description: An impoverished male, in love with a woman who is about to get married, has a lab-accident and evolves into a destructive iron-man.

page369.title: Sau Din Saas Ke
page369.description: The story of how a tyrannical mother-in-law mends ways and improves her relationships with her sons and daughters-in-law.

page370.title: Sanam
page370.description: Gaurav Anand grows up in his brother's shadow and joins the army to prove to his father that he is just as worthy.

page370.title: Sachaa Jhutha
page370.description: Bhola goes to Bombay to earn money to help his crippled twin sister, Belu. While there we discover a wealthy business man, Ranjit, moonlights as a criminal and is an exact look-alike for Bhola. Ranjit and his mistress, Rita, have plans to use Bhola.

page370.title: Pyasi Sham
page370.description: Raja leads a happy life with his sister. All of a sudden, he takes to alcohol and refuses to marry his lover. Is he hiding a dark secret?

page370.title: Pati Patni Aur Woh
page370.description: The Husband, Wife & Mistress. This comedy begins by indicating parallels between the creation story: Ranjeet is Adam, Sharda is Eve and Nirmala is the apple! Ranjeet & Sharda are happily married for several years, then lies infect their marriage.

page370.title: Palay Khan
page370.description: The British government have taken over there rule in a deserted region in India. But some of the people there strive for freedom; one of those brave freedom fighter is Palay Khan, who owes his intelligence to the entire region.

page370.title: Nishant
page370.description: A schoolteacher is powerless to prevent his wife's abduction at the hands of tyrannical landowners.

page371.title: Madhosh
page371.description: A wealthy man's daughter falls in love with a poor boy but their relationship is disapproved of by her father. When an eligible suitor is selected by her father, the girl decides to manipulate him.

page371.title: London Dreams
page371.description: The story revolves around two childhood friends Arjun and Munnu who find a way to get from a small village in India to Wembley as Rock stars, having overcome their personalities.

page371.title: Khakee
page371.description: A team of police force escorts an alleged terrorist from Chandangarh to Mumbai. However their trip turns into a deadly survival when an ex-cop tries to stop them to reach Mumbai.

page371.title: Karma
page371.description: After Michael, a terrorist being held in a state prison, is broken out by his collaborators, he vows revenge on Vishwa, the jailer who guarded him inside.Michael succeeds in killing Vishwa's grandchildren and takes matters into his own hands.

page371.title: Kajraare
page371.description: A romantic thriller depicting a lawyer played by Himmesh Reshammiya who falls in love with the a girl played by Monalizza in Morroco who disappears under inexplicable circumstances.

page371.title: Dhadkan
page371.description: Anjali is madly in love with Dev, but her family disapproves of the pairing since Dev does not come from the appropriate financial and social background.Anjali's family has arranged for her to marry Ram, who is rich.

page372.title: Company
page372.description: A gangster (Ajay Devgan) develops a strong bond with a new recruit (Vivek Oberoi), but a battle erupts when the two become enemies.

page372.title: Avishkaar
page372.description: A couple in love get married, they have a baby and their life seems perfect until the husband starts working for an advertising agency. His involvement with the models and working hours affects his home life.

page372.title: Apartment
page372.description: Tanushree Dutta needs a paying guest in her new apartment after she fights with boyfriend, Rohit Roy and throws him out.A jilted woman feels threatened after renting a room to a female.

page372.title: A Flat
page372.description: A spate of unexpected events jolted Rahul as soon as he landed from U.S. to pacify his lost love Preeti.Someone else's past can change the course of your life.

page372.title: Be Careful
page372.description: In a bid to escape their domineering wives, two womanizing slackers get saddled with a corpse amongst other challenges in a foreign country.

page372.title: Toh Baat Pakki
page372.description: A pushy busybody invites a young man to be her tenant, in hopes of arranging a marriage for her younger sister; but then has to get rid of him when she believes she has found an even better match.

page373.title: Agnee
page373.description: A man is unhappy that his parents have willed their estate and wealth to his sister and her husband, so he devises a plot which will enable him to get the wealth.

page373.title: Aashiq Awara
page373.description: Kedarnath is a wealthy man with many enemies. One day, a taxi-driver, Dilip Singh, saves his life, but is killed instead. Kedarnath is grateful and is willing to look after Dilip Singh's widow and son. But his enemies find out about this.

page373.title: Ekk Deewana Tha
page373.description: An aspiring filmmaker from Mumbai falls in love with a woman from a strict orthodox Christian family.The film is a remake of Gautham Menon's own Tamil film Vinnaithaandi Varuvaayaa (2010).

page373.title: Jaan E Man
page373.description: Geeky NASA astronaut Agastya (Akshay Kumar) discovers that his college crush, Piya (Preity Zinta), is about to get divorced and decides to make another play for her.

page373.title: Dhund
page373.description: A traveler decides to assist a woman involved in a murder.

page373.title: Chhoti Si Baat
page373.description: "A Small Matter" is considered one of the best Hindi comedy films of the 1970's. A romantic comedy about Arun who falls in love, at first sight, with Prabha, but is too shy & lacks the confidence to let her know. Can he win the girl?

page374.title: Bumm Bumm Bole
page374.description: Pinu loses his sister Rimzim's shoes so they both decide to share a pair of shoes until their father has saved enough money to buy a new pair.

page374.title: Break Ke Baad
page374.description: Childhood friends Abhay and Aaliya experience plenty of obstacles in their paths as they find their way in the world and back to each other.

page374.title: Bombay To Goa
page374.description: When Mala's parents are determined to get her married after seeing her picture in a magazine, she runs away from home taking a lot of money. She sees a friend killed over the money she gave and is now on the run for her life.

page374.title: Badhaai Ho Badhaai
page374.description: A remake of 1996 Tamil movie Poove Unakkaga and the second half of the film was inspired by the Tom Shadyac's, The Nutty Professor.

page374.title: Agent Vinod
page374.description: A series of seemingly unconnected events across the world leads to Agent Vinod undertaking a globe-trotting mission to discover why his colleague was murdered.

page374.title: ? : Question Mark
page374.description: A group of friends went to shoot their film project, but never returned. A few days later, their camera was found.

page375.title: Naqab
page375.description: Imran, a freelance photographer, begins to question his sanity when he repeatedly sees a mysterious singing woman whom no one else can see.

page375.title: Karz
page375.description: A singer discovers that he was murdered by his own wife in a previous lifetime.A 1980 Indian thriller film directed by Subhash Ghai.

page375.title: Mard
page375.description: The son (Amitabh Bachchan) of a freedom fighter (Dara Singh) grows up to fight imperialistic rule.

page375.title: The Dirty Picture
page375.description: The story of a make-up girl who became an extra in movies and gradually the most wanted heroine of the early 80s. It is the story of Silk Smitha, a sex symbol from the South film industry.

page375.title: Teen Patti
page375.description: Set in India and England and starring two of the greatest living acting legends of our times- Amitabh Bachchan and Ben Kingsley - Teen Patti is an emotionally riveting and razor sharp thriller about greed, deception and giant feats of imagination.

page375.title: Robot
page375.description: An android constructed by a scientist falls in love with the bride-to-be of his creator.The robot eventually falls in love with Sharmili, a character played by Aishwarya Rai. The robot starts writing romantic poems and behaves like a human being.

page376.title: Rehnaa Hai Terre Dil Mein
page376.description: Madly in love with an engaged woman (Diya Mirza), a man (Madhavan) impersonates her fiance, whom she has not yet seen.

page376.title: Red Alert: The War Within
page376.description: `Red Alert: the War Within` is based on the true story of Narasimha (Suniel Shetty), a poor farm laborer who desperately needs money to fund the education of his children.An impoverished cook is forced to join a band of Naxalites.

page376.title: Raavan
page376.description: A bandit leader kidnaps the wife of the policeman who killed his sister, but later falls in love with her.

page376.title: Paathshaala
page376.description: A new English school-teacher also teaches music but ends up leading both teachers and students to revolt against the school management.

page376.title: Pakeezah
page376.description: Pakeezah - Pure is an Indian cult classic.The story is about a nautch-girl at the turn of the century in Muslim Lucknow who was forbidden to fall in love. Meena Kumari plays the golden-hearted nautch-girl, but it was her last performance.

page376.title: Neal 'n' Nikki
page376.description: An engaged man (Uday Chopra) meets a spunky woman (Tanishaa Mukerji) while vacationing in Canada to enjoy his last days as a bachelor.

page377.title: Milenge Milenge
page377.description: Hoping that destiny will reunite them, a couple, on the verge of getting married, attempts to locate each other.

page377.title: Khichdi: The Movie
page377.description: In order to immortalize his love, a groom decides to create conflict between his and his to-be bride's families.

page377.title: Hum Dil De Chuke Sanam
page377.description: Nandini has to choose between Sameer, the man who taught her to fall in love; and Vanraj, the man from whom she learnt how to abide and fulfill promises of love.

page377.title: Guru (hindi)
page377.description: A villager, Gurukant Desai, arrives in Bombay 1958, and rises from its streets to become the GURU, the biggest tycoon in Indian history.

page377.title: Ghost
page377.description: Ghost is a horror flick with an element of romance in it. It is set in a hospital with Sayali Bhagat playing a doctor and Shiney Ahuja playing a debonair detective. The movie has been directed by Puja Jatinder Bedi.

page377.title: Gambler
page377.description: A police inspector has a knack for apprehending criminals, but his main inclination is to stick to a desk job.

page378.title: Dus Kahaniyaan
page378.description: Dus Kahaniyaan is a story of expansive highways and modern romance, of kindly strangers, of lives lived in the realms of power, and lives freed from the gloom of oppression.

page378.title: Divya Shakti
page378.description: A reporter is fed up with gangsters running the streets of Bombay, and when he tries to improve the situation, his life turns upside down.

page378.title: Dil Toh Baccha Hai Ji
page378.description: Three man staying under same roof are in search of true love. They meet their ladies but will these man be able to convince them to be their soul mates?

page378.title: Deedar-e-Yaar
page378.description: Two close and devout Muslim youth, Javed and Akhtar, are childhood pals. They both unknowingly fall in love with the same woman, Firdaus.

page378.title: Betaab
page378.description: A young man (Sunny Deol) and woman (Amrita Singh) fall in love, but face obstacles from their families.

page378.title: Barsaat
page378.description: Pran and Gopal travel in a convertible in the Indian countryside when the car breaks down; life changes when they visit a nearby village for help.

page379.title: Action Replay
page379.description: A young man tries to revive his parents' wilting marriage in a unique manner - travel to the 1970s when their romance was budding and make it bloom. This is more complex than he expects.

page379.title: Kahaani
page379.description: A pregnant woman's search for her missing husband takes her from London to Kolkata, but everyone she questions denies having ever met him.

page379.title: Gali Gali Chor Hai
page379.description: A common man is financially taken advantage of by corrupt government officials in this political satire.

page379.title: Chaalis Chauraasi
page379.description: Four friends, who have accidentally committed crimes, decide to loot Rs. 20 crore, posing as cops. But on the way, they encounter a real police inspector, who orders them to do an encounter.

page379.title: Vardi
page379.description: A constable gets killed during the arrest of a criminal, leaving behind his only son. A police officer raises this child, while believing that his own son was killed by the criminal.

page379.title: Tanu Weds Manu
page379.description: Manu comes to India to find a bride for himself and falls for Tanu at first sight but Tanu, a free spirited girl has no plans of marrying him.

page380.title: Sadda Adda
page380.description: This film is the story of these six boys with completely different backgrounds and personalities.Their apartment `Sadda Adda` is nothing short of a trashcan.The house which was only a make-shift accommodation helps them work towards their dreams.

page380.title: Phas Gaye Re Obama
page380.description: Om Shastri, a recession victim comes to India to sell his ancestors property to clear is debt. On reaching he comes to know that selling the property will make his family homeless in India. Later he is kidnapped by goons thinking a rich NRI.

page380.title: My Name Is Khan
page380.description: An Indian Muslim man with Asperger's syndrome takes a challenge to speak to the President seriously and embarks on a cross-country journey.

page380.title: Mere Brother Ki Dulhan
page380.description: A young man tries to arrange a marriage for his brother, but finds himself falling in love with the chosen fiancée.

page380.title: Mausam
page380.description: Mausam, is a love story in different seasons starting with an adolescent attraction between a Punjabi boy Harry(Shahid Kapoor), and a Kashmiri girl Aayat(Sonam Kapoor) progressing into young love in season two.A Timeless Love Story.....

page380.title: Lafangey Parindey
page380.description: An intriguing journey of a blindfolded street fighter and a blind dancer who set out to achieve the impossible.

page381.title: Ladies Vs Ricky Bahl
page381.description: A smooth and charming conman, Ricky Bahl, cons girls for a living but finally meets his match is this fun-filled "ROM-CON."

page381.title: Double Dhamaal
page381.description: The four good-for- nothing jokers from Dhamaal are back again! Four slackers decide to avenge their humiliation at the hands of a con-man.

page381.title: Chalo Dilli
page381.description: Enroute to her destination via plane, a busy executive gets stranded with a middle-classed fast-talking male.

page381.title: Bbuddah... Hoga Terra Baap
page381.description: Amitabh Bachchan plays a retired hitman settled in Paris, who comes back to India to do one last job. The film is a fast-paced action thriller!!

page381.title: Band Baaja Baaraat
page381.description: Shruti and Bittoo become partners in their very own "Wedding planning ka bijness" in Delhi and in the process discover friendship, love and one another.

page381.title: Ek Main Aur Ekk Tu
page381.description: A few drinks too many leads an uptight architect and quick-witted hairstylist to marry in Las Vegas. Can a mistake lead to friendship and love?

page382.title: Don 2
page382.description: An international gangster turns himself in, then dramatically escapes - only to face treachery and betrayal. It is the second installment of the Don franchise, directed by Farhan Akhtar. (This presentation comes with additional scenes.)

page382.title: Antardwand
page382.description: A young man is kidnapped by a local strongman with the intention of forcing him to marry his daughter to secure a family alliance.

page382.title: Zindagi Na Milegi Dobara
page382.description: Three friends decide to turn their fantasy vacation into reality after one of their number becomes engaged.

page382.title: Sankat City
page382.description: The film follows the underbelly of a teeming metropolis, featuring an assortment of zany men and women shadowboxing with the vagaries of chance and fate.

page382.title: Players
page382.description: Two thieves, a magician, a computer hacker, a wannabe actor and a explosives expert plan a robbery to fulfill the dream of Victor Braganza. Will they be successful or will destiny have something different for them?

page382.title: Lanka
page382.description: A woman recounts her story of being confined to live as an unwed wife of an influential gangster.

page383.title: Iqbal
page383.description: Iqbal, the deaf and mute son of a farmer, has a passion for the game of cricket and seeks the tutelage of a washed-up, alcoholic ex-player.

page383.title: Golmaal: Fun Unlimited
page383.description: Four runaway crooks take shelter in a bungalow which is owned by a blind couple.Golmaal: Fun Unlimited is a Hindi comedy movie, based on Gujarati play Aflatoon.

page383.title: Bheja Fry
page383.description: Ranjeet Thadani lives a wealthy lifestyle in Mumbai with his wife, Sheetal. Little does he know his whole life is about to be turned upside down when he meets an Income-Tax Inspector. Based on the French movie Le Dîner de Cons.

page383.title: Agneepath
page383.description: A young boy's father is lynched before his eyes; fifteen years later he returns home for revenge.Agneepath is a remake of the Hindi film of the same name starring Amitabh Bachchan which fetched him a national award.

page383.title: Yuvvraaj
page383.description: Two estranged brothers (Salman Khan, Zayed Khan) must learn to work together to claim their rightful share of an inheritance left solely to their eldest sibling (Anil Kapoor).

page383.title: Veer
page383.description: A Pindari prince (Salman Khan) goes to England to study military tactics so that he can avenge his people, but while there, he falls in love.An Epic Love Story Of A Warrior!!

page384.title: Right Yaaa Wrong
page384.description: What happens when a cop, Vinay Pathak, the closest friend and colleague of Ajay Singh, an honest cop in the police force starts investigating a case of the murder of Ajay Singh`s wife and his prime suspect is no one else but Ajay Singh himself.

page384.title: Kambakkht Ishq
page384.description: A romantic comedy about an Indian stuntman who takes Hollywood by storm but cannot find true love.

page384.title: I Am Kalam
page384.description: An impoverished boy forms an unlikely and unstable friendship with the lonely son of a nobleman.

page384.title: Yeh Dooriyan
page384.description: Simmi is a 35 year-old choreographer is a divorcee and hence lives with her two kids. Her friends Bobby and Nikki work with her. After few years of divorce, her friends and parents force her to re-marry. One fine day, she meets a handsome model Raj.

page384.title: Tere Mere Phere
page384.description: An irate groom-to-be abducts a recently married bickering couple and asks them to take him to his wedding.

page384.title: Rockstar
page384.description: Janardhan Jakhar chases his dreams of becoming a big Rock star, during which he falls in love with Heer.

page385.title: Rivaaz
page385.description: A man falls in love with a village belle who is destined for traditional prostitution.

page385.title: Rascals
page385.description: Rascals is a comedy about two conmen(Sanjay Dutt & Ajay Devgan) competing with each other and trying to out-scheme each other in amusing yet surprising setups till they fall in love with the same girl( Kangana Ranaut).

page385.title: Ra One
page385.description: A video game developer's world spirals out of control when his shape-shifting indestructible virtual creation becomes all too real.

page385.title: Pyaar Ka Punchnama
page385.description: After falling in love, three room-mates experience changes in their lives.

page385.title: 1942: A Love Story
page385.description: A young Indian couple, both from wealthy backgrounds, find themselves caught up in the 1940's Indian revolutionary movement against their families whom are under the thumb a sadistic British general.

page385.title: Mujhse Fraaandship Karoge
page385.description: When you can't make it on your own, the best thing to do is to fake it. But, the question remains, how long can you fake true love?

page386.title: Mod
page386.description: A woman falls for a male she believes is her class-mate until she finds out that he is an unknown and unstable inmate from a mental institute.

page386.title: Loot
page386.description: Four burglars end up stealing a vehicle from robbers as well as unknowingly breaking in the house of a notorious gangster.

page386.title: Hum Tum Shabana
page386.description: Hum Tum Shabana is a comedy flick that revolves around three main characters Tusshar Kapoor, Shreyas Talpadeand Minissha Lamba wherein, the male leads compete with each other to gain Shabana`s attention.

page386.title: Force
page386.description: A vengeful drug dealer/gangster targets and terrorizes an entire police unit and their families.

page386.title: Dum Maaro Dum
page386.description: Dum Maro Dum is an edgy, coming of age, cop caper, a full-fledged film set in Goa.A corrupt police officer has entrusted the task of apprehending drug dealers.

page386.title: Desi Boyz
page386.description: Two friends lose their jobs, then part bitterly after they get exposed as male escorts.It's the year of economic recession and the whole world has been struck by the financial meltdown except 2 friends who don`t feel any discomfort in their lives.

page387.title: Damadamm!
page387.description: Damadamm! is about Sameer (Himesh Reshammiya) who has finally got his long-awaited freedom when his stubby-girlfriend Shikha (Purbi Joshi) leaves for a family wedding.

page387.title: Bubble Gum
page387.description: A teenager faces interfering parents, a sibling, and a rival for the girl he loves.

page387.title: Bin Bulaye Baraati
page387.description: Petty robbers on the run from gangsters and police end up in a town where they are mistaken for police officers.

page387.title: Bhindi Baazaar Inc.
page387.description: The film revolves around gangs of Mumbai who have embraced pickpocketing as an art and a means of earning a livelihood.Power struggles ensue in a gang after the sudden of their leader.An Adult entertainer!!

page387.title: Aazaan
page387.description: A Secret Agent must race against time to stop terrorists about to unleash an unknown strain of the Ebola Virus.

page387.title: Always Kabhi Kabhi
page387.description: A story centered on four students coming of age during a year at their school, St. Marks.It focuses on four teenagers embarking on a dramatic journey during their incident-packed final year at school.

page388.title: Aarakshan
page388.description: A decision by India's supreme court tests a man's friendships and loyalty.Centered on one of the most controversial issues of recent years in India, with the Supreme Courts order on reservations.

page388.title: Wanted
page388.description: Radhe is a ruthless gangster who will kill anyone for money. He is attracted towards Jhanvi, a middle-class girl, who does not approve of his work and wants him to change.

page388.title: Refugee
page388.description: It is the story of an unnamed Indian Muslim, who helps illegal refugees from India and Pakistan cross the border through the Great Rann of Kutch. Inspired by the short story "Love Across the Salt Desert" by Keki N. Daruwalla.

page388.title: Raaz
page388.description: Sanjana and Aditya decide to give their marriage one last chance. They plan a holiday in Ooty, but they don't know that a strange figure is waiting for them to come.

page388.title: Paath Shaala
page388.description: A new English school-teacher also teaches music but ends up leading both teachers and students to revolt against the school management.

page388.title: Paa
page388.description: A father tries to help his son cope with a rare condition that causes the young boy to age beyond his years.

page389.title: Maa Tujhhe Salaam
page389.description: Soldiers are caught between the on-going conflict over a region between two neighboring countries.

page389.title: Kites
page389.description: A wounded man searches for his sweetheart in the Mexican desert while on the run from the police, bounty hunters, and others.

page389.title: Khaata Meetha
page389.description: A seemingly corrupt petty contractor faces challenges from the local municipality, his family, his employees, as well as a former girlfriend and her family.

page389.title: Kaal
page389.description: A tiger expert, his wife, two tourists and a village chief engage in a battle for survival against supernatural beasts within Jim Corbett National Wildlife Park.

page389.title: Jannat
page389.description: The story revolves around a man who is caught in a quagmire of crime and consumerism as he struggles to find heaven on earth.

page389.title: Jab We Met
page389.description: A depressed wealthy businessman finds his life changing after he meets a spunky and care-free young woman.

page390.title: Game
page390.description: A rich man invites four strangers to his private island to blame three of them for his daughter's death. The next morning, the wealthy man is found murdered.

page390.title: Gadar: Ek Prem Katha
page390.description: Set in 1947, Gadar - Ek Prem Katha is a love saga during the troubled partition times. Tara Singh is a truck driver who comes across Sakina during one of his journeys. Love blossoms and grows silently.Then comes partitions and issues....

page390.title: Dil Bole Hadippa!
page390.description: In a village where girls don't play cricket, Veera puts on a turban and beard and becomes Veer to fulfill her dreams and meets Rohan. And fun begins.

page390.title: Chori Chori Chupke Chupke
page390.description: A prostitute agrees to get impregnated and then give the baby to a couple (Raj and Priya) in exchange for a million rupees. Everything changes when she develops feelings for the baby and Raj.

page390.title: Bhoothnath
page390.description: Banku, his mother, Anjali Sharma and father move in to their new house -- the Nath villa, unaware of the fact that the house is inhabited by a ghost.

page390.title: Main Hoon Na
page390.description: An army major goes undercover as a college student. His mission is both professional and personal: to protect his general's daughter from a radical militant, and to find his estranged half-brother.

page391.title: Hum Tumhare Hain Sanam
page391.description: Gopal loves his wife dearly but feels that she is giving undue attention to her friend Suraj. He grows very suspicious, resulting in his throwing Radha out of the house when his jealousy completely overwhelms him.

page391.title: Kabhi Alvida Naa Kehna
page391.description: Dev, a famous footballer, becomes injured and gets dependent on Riya. Brooding on his ill-fate, he gets suspicous of an affair going on between Riya and another man. Is the affair a reality, and if it is, will Dev openly accuse Riya?

page391.title: Dulha Mil Gaya
page391.description: Four people (Shah Rukh Khan, Fardeen Khan, Sushmita Sen) express different outlooks on love and relationships.The movie shows us what happens when these varied characters meet and their love stories get entwined.

page391.title: Pukar
page391.description: A decorated officer (Anil Kapoor), blind to the affections of a childhood friend (Madhuri Dixit), falls in love with another.

page391.title: Dilwale Dulhania Le Jayenge
page391.description: When Raj meets Simran in Europe, it isn't love at first sight but when Simran moves to India for an arranged marriage, love makes its presence felt.

page391.title: Kyon Ki
page391.description: A doctor (Kareena Kapoor) falls for a patient (Salman Khan) at a mental asylum, but her father (Om Puri) opposes the relationship.

page392.title: Waqt: The Race Against Time
page392.description: A wealthy man (Amitabh Bachchan) kicks his spoiled son (Akshay Kumar) out of the house after he secretly marries the daughter (Priyanka Chopra) of an old enemy.

page392.title: Kuch Naa Kaho
page392.description: Kuch Naa Kaho is the story of Raj, a young man who just wants to live his own life, and Namrata, the stunning woman whose job it becomes to find Raj a suitable wife.

page392.title: Namastey London
page392.description: A man takes his thoroughly-British daughter to his home country, India. There, he arranges her marriage to someone she considers a fool. The daughter attempts to outwit them, but the groom quietly and patiently hatches his own plan.

page392.title: Kuch Kuch Hota Hai
page392.description: During their college years, Anjali was in love with her best-friend Rahul, but he had eyes only for Tina. Years later, Rahul and the now-deceased Tina's eight-year-old daughter attempts to reunite her father and Anjali.

page392.title: Veer Zaara
page392.description: The story of the love between Veer Pratap Singh, an Indian, and Zaara Hayaat Khan, a Pakistani...a love so great it knows no boundaries...

page392.title: Taare Zameen Par
page392.description: An eight-year-old boy is thought to be a lazy trouble-maker, until the new art teacher has the patience and compassion to discover the real problem behind his struggles in school.

page393.title: Sarkar
page393.description: Subhash Nagre, well known as Sarkar by his followers, has his own way to bring justice in the law system. Rasheed tries to strike a deal with Sarkar. He promptly refuses on moral grounds and also forbids him from doing it himself.

page393.title: Runway
page393.description: With a hand on the trigger and an eye on the casino owner Victor, Allan (Amarjeet) goes to Mauritius. Back home in Daman is the reason he has turned into a contract killer -Melvyna (Deepal Shaw), a victim of drug abuse.

page393.title: Raakh
page393.description: Raakh is an Underworld tale of revenge and blood. The Romance plays an important part in this movie and ultimately shows good wins over evil.

page393.title: No Entry
page393.description: A remake of the Tamil super hit Charlie Chaplin.Kishen has a suspicious-minded wife, Kaajal, who thinks he is always having an affair with another woman, even though he is extremely faithful to her and wouldn't dream of betraying her in any way.

page393.title: Ghulam
page393.description: A boxer (Aamir Khan) with a criminal brother falls in love with a young woman (Rani Mukherjee) who rides with a motorcycle gang.

page393.title: Dil Chahta Hai
page393.description: Three inseparable childhood friends are just out of college. Nothing comes between them - until they each fall in love, and their wildly different approaches to relationships creates tension.

page394.title: Angel
page394.description: After serving time in jail for running over a man, an ex-convict is then arrested for sexually molesting the man's physically-challenged daughter.

page394.title: Bhool Bhulaiyaa
page394.description: When U.S.-based Siddharth visits his Indian home town with his new wife, he insists they stay at the ancestral home, laughing off family members' warnings of ghostly goings-on in the mansion. But events soon make him reconsider his beliefs.

page394.title: Heyy Babyy
page394.description: Aarush, Ali and Tanmay wake up to find a baby left outside their door.A remake of the 1990 Malayalam movie Thoovalsparsham which itself is an adaptation of 1987 American film Three Men and a Baby.

page394.title: Munna Bhai M.B.B.S.
page394.description: A gangster sets out to fulfill his father's dream of becoming a doctor.The story involves protagonist Munna Bhai (Sanjay Dutt), a goon, going to medical school. He is helped by his sidekick, Circuit (Arshad Warsi).

page394.title: Ready
page394.description: Set in Thailand and India, a case of mistaken identity leads to love; and a man and his family concoct a grand scheme to win over the hearts of a woman and her greedy conniving uncles.

page394.title: Love Aaj Kal
page394.description: An old-fashioned romantic tells his personal love story to a modern man who has just broken up with his girlfriend. Has love really ever changed?

page395.title: Lakshya
page395.description: A journalist (Preity Zinta) and her television crew follow her former boyfriend (Hrithik Roshan) and his squad of soldiers as they fight invaders.

page395.title: Dil To Pagal Hai
page395.description: Promised to another via arranged marriage, a dancer (Madhuri Dixit) falls in love with her director (Shahrukh Khan).

page395.title: Deewangee
page395.description: A singer (Urmila Matondkar) asks a lawyer (Akshaye Khanna) to defend her childhood friend (Ajay Devgan) who is accused of murdering her manager.

page395.title: Awara Paagal Deewane
page395.description: Following the death of an underworld crime boss, the dead man's son, Vikrant (Rahul Dev), and son-in-law, Gulab (Akshay Kumar), begin a fierce rivalry stemming from the old man's will.

page395.title: All The Best: Fun Begins
page395.description: The unexpected arrival of his elder NRI brother and assorted characters complicates the life of a Goan male.

page395.title: Partner
page395.description: A 'Love Guru' assists other males, woos a widowed single mother, but becomes embroiled in controversies.

page396.title: Singham
page396.description: A truly honest police officer is transferred to a town controlled by a gangster he has humiliated. The gangster believes he can use good power to bring down this officer who made him look foolish and weak.

page396.title: Salaam Namaste
page396.description: A quirky take on life and relationships as it looks at a fairy tale with a bit of a squint and an endearing look at what being in love really means.

page396.title: Murder 2
page396.description: Arjun`s family faces poverty which makes it difficult for them to survive because of which money becomes the only priority in life. Arjun meets Sameer, a Goan gangster who has been suffering a huge loss as his call girls have went missing one by one.

page396.title: Koi... Mil Gaya
page396.description: A developmentally disabled young man tries to continue the work his father did in communicating with extra-terrestrials from outer space, which leads to something miraculous and wonderful.

page396.title: Dil Vil Pyar Vyar
page396.description: Three friends, who have known each other for a long time, decide to enter a singing and musical competition. The events that lead to this competition, and their personal lives, including their romantic ties, is the theme of this movie.

page396.title: De Dana Dan
page396.description: Singapore-based Nitin Bankar's education was paid for by his employer, Kuljeet Kaur, and he, after the passing of his father, works as an unpaid maid-chauffeur for her until such time he pays off whatever she had spent.

page397.title: Darr
page397.description: Darr is a girl's (Kiran) story caught between one man's (Sunil) love and another man's (Rahul) obsession.

page397.title: Blue
page397.description: The story follows three men on an underwater treasure hunt. In the Bahamas, Aarav runs a successful fishing company under the title of Blue. He works with Sagar who works as a diver for Aarav's fishing company.

page397.title: Ajab Prem Ki Ghazab Kahani
page397.description: The wacky adventures of a young man who is willing to sacrifice his own love to insure the happiness of others, and get the girl-of-his-dreams married to the boy-of-her-dreams.

page397.title: Baghban
page397.description: An elderly couple wish their children to care for them in their old age. But their children see and treat them as a burden, and they must struggle to regain their worth and dignity to themselves and others.

page397.title: Sarkar Raj
page397.description: UK based Anita Rajan, CEO of an international electrical power firm, approaches Subhash and Shankar Nagre for opening a power plant. After initial reluctance, the Nagres support the project, until it gradually becomes a political minefield.

page397.title: Sarfarosh
page397.description: After his brother is killed and father severly injured by terrorists, a young med student quits his studies to join the Indian Police Service to wipe out the terrorists.

page398.title: Mela
page398.description: When a village belle's brother is killed by a bandit, she vows revenge and enlists the help of two truckers-cum-theatre artists in her mission.

page398.title: Rab Ne Bana Di Jodi
page398.description: A breathtaking, goose flesh igniting, awe inspiring love journey of an ordinary man Suri and his 'total opposite' love Taani.

page398.title: Lagaan
page398.description: The people of a small village in Victorian India stake their future on a game of cricket against their ruthless British rulers.

page398.title: Ghajinii
page398.description: A short-term memory loss patient sets out on his journey to avenge the death of his beloved girl.

page398.title: Fanaa
page398.description: A sweet blind girl Zooni meets a flirty Rehan. She ignores her friends' warnings. It's her time to discover life. Is she making the right love choice?

page398.title: Dil Se
page398.description: The clash between love and ideology is portrayed in this love story between a radio executive and a beautiful revolutionary

page399.title: Dabangg
page399.description: Dabangg means fearless.A corrupt police officer faces challenges from his family, gangsters, and politicians.Robinhood Pandey...Cop...Lover...Rebel

page399.title: Bunty Aur Babli
page399.description: A small town pair become the legendary Bunty and Babli as caper after caper they turn the world on its head. Till they meet a very upset cop.

page399.title: 13 B
page399.description: A man experiences a supernatural occurrence at his newly purchased apartment; a soap opera being telecast exclusively on his TV, which shows the future of his family. The film was simultaneously filmed and released in Tamil as Yavarum Nalam.

page399.title: Jaane Tu... Ya Jaane Na
page399.description: Two best friends being convinced that they are not in love search for each other's love. A  coming of age romantic drama film!!

page399.title: Tees Maar Khan
page399.description: Posing as a movie producer, a conman attempts to trick an entire village into helping him rob a treasure-laden train.

page399.title: Saathiya
page399.description: The tale of a young couple in love who elope and marry, but soon find that that marriage is not the bed of roses it is made out to be.

page400.title: Patiala House
page400.description: A second-generation Sikh in London gives up his dream to save his father`s reputation until he meets a girl who gives him the strength to stand up for what he believes. This cross-generation drama is about second chances.

page400.title: Once Upon A Time In Mumbaai
page400.description: A smuggler rises to power in 1970s Mumbai, a younger gangster seeks to overthrow him, and a police officer is caught in the middle.

page400.title: Om Shanti Om
page400.description: In the 1970s, Om, an aspiring actor, is murdered, but is immediately reincarnated into the present day. He attempts to discover the mystery of his demise and find Shanti, the love of his previous life.

page400.title: Murder
page400.description: Tragedy looms when an unhappily married woman (Mallika Sherawat) renews a steamy affair with a former lover (Emran Hashmi) from college. An Erotic Thriller!!

page400.title: Devdas
page400.description: After his wealthy family prohibits him from marrying the woman he is in love with, Devdas Mukherjee's life spirals further and further out of control as he takes up alcohol and a life of vice to numb the pain.

page400.title: Delhi Heights
page400.description: The story revolves around thirteen people living in Delhii Heights-an apartment in New Delhi, India.

page401.title: Chalte Chalte
page401.description: A truck driver (Shahrukh Khan) falls in love with a sophisticated woman (Rani Mukherji), to the dismay of her wealthy father.

page401.title: Chak De! India
page401.description: Kabir Khan is the coach of the Indian Women's National Hockey Team and his dream is to make his all girls team emerge victorious against all odds.

page401.title: Billu Barber
page401.description: When a famous Bollywood actor visits a small village for a film's shoot, a lowly hairdressers claim that they were once childhood friends soon makes him the centre of attention.

page401.title: Baazigar
page401.description: A young man with a vendetta against a business tycoon seduces and kills his eldest daughter and then proceeds to his younger daughter but she begins to suspect her new lover's ulterior motive.

page401.title: Anjaana Anjaani
page401.description: After numerous attempts at suicide fail, a couple decides to live it up, and then kill themselves on New Year's Day.This is the story of two strangers on an odyssey of discovery - down a path that is ridden with the exquisite pain and joy of falling in love.

page401.title: Aitraaz
page401.description: A man's (Akshay Kumar) honor and more are at stake when he finds himself in a courtroom, accused of a heinous crime.

page402.title: Aankhen
page402.description: The film tells the story of Vijay Singh Rajput (Bachchan) a hard-working but temperamental man, who has spent all his life working for one bank and even achieving them International recognition.

page402.title: 3 Idiots
page402.description: Two friends are searching for their long lost companion. They revisit their college days and recall the memories of their friend who inspired them to think differently, even as the rest of the world called them "idiots".

page402.title: Singh Is King
page402.description: A comic caper about Happy Singh, a Punjabi villager who goes through a series of misadventures and eventually becomes the Kinng of the Australian underworld.

page402.title: Pyaar Impossible!
page402.description: A romantic comedy in which a geek and the most sought-after college beauty are paired together by a twist of fate. And under all odds, an impossible love story begins.

page402.title: New York
page402.description: NEW YORK is a contemporary story of friendship set against the larger than life backdrop of a city often described as the center of the world. Their lives are changed by 9/11 and its aftermath.

page402.title: Mohabbatein
page402.description: Two stubborn men with opposing beliefs battle each other - three love stories are at stake

page403.title: Kal Ho Naa Ho
page403.description: Naina, an introverted, perpetually depressed girl's life changes when she meets Aman. But Aman has a secret of his own which changes their lives forever. Embroiled in all this is Rohit, Naina's best friend who conceals his love for her.

page403.title: Kabhi Khushi Kabhie Gham
page403.description: Also, Know as K3G, the film tells the story of an Indian family, which faces troubles and misunderstandings over their adopted son's marriage to a girl belonging to a lower socio-economic group than them.

page403.title: Hum Tum
page403.description: Hum Tum is a refreshing look at the eternal battle of the sexes as it follows the lives of Karan and Rhea.

page403.title: Housefull
page403.description: Believing himself to be jinxed, a man attempts to find true love but instead gets caught in a web of lies.It is the first installment of the Housefull film series.

page403.title: Golmaal Returns
page403.description: Obsessed with day-time TV soaps, Ekta Santoshi starts suspecting her husband, Gopal, of having an affair with an unknown woman. Not satisfied with his explanations, she decides to investigate, setting off a chain of hilarious events

page403.title: Golmaal 3
page403.description: In Goa, Pritam meets his love Geeta after many years. They decide to get married but the feud between their respective children creates tension in their marriage.
